/ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/amazon-bought-whole-foods-year-ago-heres-changed-191428325.html |title=Amazon bought Whole Foods a year ago. Here's what has changed | publisher=[[Yahoo! Finance]]}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Amazon.com, Inc.'''<ref>{{cite web |title=Amazon.com, Inc. - Form-10K |url=http://secfilings.nasdaq.com/filingFrameset.asp?FilingID=13184158&RcvdDate=2/1/2019&CoName=AMAZON%20COM%20INC&FormType=10-K&View=html |publisher=[[NASDAQ]] |accessdate=March 17, 2019 |date=December 31, 2018}}</ref> ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|\u00e6|m|\u0259|z|\u0252|n}}), is an American multinational technology company based in [[Seattle]], with 750,000 employees.<ref>{{cite news |last=Greene |first=Jay |date=January 27, 2020 |title=Amazon employees launch mass defiance of company communications policy in support of colleagues |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2020/01/26/amazon-employees-plan-mass-defiance-company-communications-policy-support-colleagues/ |work=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref> It focuses on [[e-commerce]], [[cloud computing]], [[digital streaming]], and [[artificial intelligence]]. It is considered one of the [[Big Four tech companies]], along with [[Google]], [[Apple Inc.|Apple]], and [[Microsoft]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://theconversation.com/big-tech-isnt-one-big-monopoly-its-5-companies-all-in-different-businesses-92791|title='Big Tech' isn't one big monopoly \u2013 it's 5 companies all in different businesses|last=Lotz|first=Amanda|website=The Conversation|language=en|access-date=2019-05-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2017-10-31/the-big-four-of-technology|title=The Big Four of Technology|date=2017-10-31|access-date=2019-05-16|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.barrons.com/articles/ranking-the-big-four-internet-stocks-google-is-no-1-apple-comes-in-last-1503412102|title=Ranking The Big Four Tech Stocks: Google Is No. 1, Apple Comes In Last|last=Rivas|first=Teresa|website=www.barrons.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-16}}</ref> It has been referred to as \"one of the most influential economic and cultural forces in the world.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/frontline/film/amazon-empire/ | title=Amazon Empire: The Rise and Reign of Jeff Bezos}}</ref>\n\nAmazon is known for its disruption of well-established industries through technological innovation and mass scale.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/312481|title=Why Amazon and Jeff Bezos Are So Successful at Disruption|last=Furth|first=John F.|date=2018-05-18|website=Entrepreneur|language=en|access-date=2019-05-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/299129|title=Amazon's Lesson About Disruption: Rattle Any Market You Can|last=Bylund|first=Per|date=2017-08-29|website=Entrepreneur|language=en|access-date=2019-05-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/danielnewman/2018/10/24/alibaba-vs-amazon-the-battle-of-disruptive-innovation-beyond-traditional-e-commerce/|title=Alibaba vs. Amazon: The Battle Of Disruptive Innovation Beyond Traditional E-Commerce|last=Newman|first=Daniel|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-05-16}}</ref> It is the world's largest [[online marketplace]], [[AI assistant]] provider, and [[cloud computing]] platform<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.srgresearch.com/articles/microsoft-cloud-revenues-leap-amazon-still-way-out-front |title=Microsoft Cloud Revenues Leap; Amazon is Still Way Out in Front|publisher=Synergy Research Group|location=Reno, Nevada|work=srgresearch.com}}</ref> as measured by [[revenue]] and [[market capitalization]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Jopson |first=Barney |url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/61828252-ac1d-11e0-b85c-00144feabdc0.html |title=Amazon urges California referendum on online tax |work=Financial Times |date=July 12, 2011 |accessdate=August 4, 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714230245/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/61828252-ac1d-11e0-b85c-00144feabdc0.html |archivedate=July 14, 2011 |url-status=live |df=}}</ref> Amazon is the [[largest Internet company by revenue]] in the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fortune.com/global500/list/|title=Fortune Global 500 List 2018: See Who Made It|website=Fortune|access-date=January 8, 2019}}</ref> It is the second [[List of largest employers in the United States|largest private employer in the United States]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2016/09/23/amazon-climbs-into-list-of-top-five-largest-us-stocks-by-market-cap.html|title=Amazon climbs into list of top five largest US stocks by market cap|last=Cheng|first=Evelyn|date=September 23, 2016|website=CNBC|access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref> and one of the [[world's most valuable companies]].\n\nAmazon was founded by [[Jeff Bezos]] in [[Bellevue, Washington]], in July 1994. The company initially started as an online marketplace for books but later expanded to sell electronics, software, video games, apparel, furniture, food, toys, and jewelry<!--jewelry is U.S. spelling-->. In 2015, Amazon surpassed [[Walmart]] as the most valuable retailer in the United States by [[market capitalization]].<ref name=\":3\" /> In 2017, Amazon acquired [[Whole Foods Market]] for {{USD}}13.4 billion, which vastly increased Amazon's presence as a brick-and-mortar retailer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/16/business/dealbook/amazon-whole-foods.html|title=Amazon to Buy Whole Foods for $13.4 Billion|last=Wingfield|first=Nick|date=June 16, 2017|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 20, 2019|last2=de la Merced|first2=Michael J.|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In 2018, Bezos announced that its two-day delivery service, [[Amazon Prime]], had surpassed 100 million subscribers worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/04/18/amazon-ceo-jeff-bezos-2018-shareholder-letter.html|title=Jeff Bezos reveals Amazon has 100 million Prime members in letter to shareholders|last=|first=|date=April 18, 2018|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=January 2, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://phx.corporate-ir.net/phoenix.zhtml?c=97664&p=irol-reportsannual|title=Amazon - Investor Relations - Annual Reports, Proxies and Shareholder Letters|website=phx.corporate-ir.net|access-date=September 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAmazon distributes downloads and streaming of [[Amazon Video|video]], music, and [[Audible.com|audiobooks]] through its [[Prime Video]], [[Amazon Music]], and [[Audible (store)|Audible]] subsidiaries. Amazon also has a publishing arm, [[Amazon Publishing]], a film and television studio, [[Amazon Studios]], and a cloud computing subsidiary, [[AWS|Amazon Web Services]]. It produces [[consumer electronics]] including [[Amazon Kindle|Kindle]] [[e-reader]]s, [[Kindle Fire|Fire]] [[tablet computer|tablets]], [[Fire TV]], and [[Amazon Echo|Echo]] devices. In addition, Amazon acquisitions include [[Ring Inc.|Ring]], [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]], Whole Foods Market, and [[IMDb]]. Among various controversies, the company has been [[Criticism of Amazon|criticized]] for technological surveillance overreach,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2019/04/30/amazons-facial-recognition-technology-is-supercharging-local-police/|title=Amazon's facial-recognition AI is supercharging police in Oregon.|last=Harwell|first=Drew|date=April 30, 2019|work=The Washington Post|access-date=June 30, 2019}}</ref> a hyper-competitive and demanding work culture,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kantor |first1=Jodi |last2=Streitfeld |first2=David |title=Inside Amazon: Wrestling Big Ideas in a Bruising Workplace |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/16/technology/inside-amazon-wrestling-big-ideas-in-a-bruising-workplace.html |website=[[New York Times]] |accessdate=15 February 2020}}</ref> [[tax avoidance]],<ref name=\"fortune\" /> and [[anti-competitive practices|anti-competitive practices.]]<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite journal|last=Khan|first=Lina|date=January 2017|title=Amazon's Antitrust Paradox|url=https://www.yalelawjournal.org/note/amazons-antitrust-paradox|journal=Yale Law Journal|volume=126|issue=3|pages=564\u2013907|via=}}</ref><ref name=\"baum\" />\n\n== History ==\n{{Further|History of Amazon}}\n[[File:Amazon Hyderabad campus.jpg|thumb|The company's largest campus outside of the US was inaugurated in [[Hyderabad]], [[India]] in September 2019.]]\n\n[[Jeff Bezos]] founded Amazon in July 1994. He chose [[Seattle]] because of technical talent as [[Microsoft]] is located there.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f3NBQcAqyu4&t=223 The David Rubenstein Show: Jeff Bezos], Bloomberg Markets and Finance, 2018-09-19</ref> In May 1997, the organization went [[public company|public]]. The company began selling music and videos in 1998, at which time it began operations internationally by acquiring online sellers of books in [[United Kingdom]] and [[Germany]]. The following year, the organization also sold video games, consumer electronics, home-improvement items, software, games, and toys in addition to other items.\n\nIn 2002, the corporation started [[Amazon Web Services]] (AWS), which provided data on Web site popularity, Internet traffic patterns and other statistics for marketers and developers. In 2006, the organization grew its AWS portfolio when [[Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud|Elastic Compute Cloud]] (EC2), which rents computer processing power as well as [[Simple Storage Service]] (S3), that rents data storage via the Internet, were made available. That same year, the company started'' Fulfillment by Amazon ''which managed the inventory of individuals and small companies selling their belongings through the company internet site. In 2012, Amazon bought [[Amazon Robotics|Kiva Systems]] to automate its inventory-management business, purchasing [[Whole Foods Market]] supermarket chain five years later in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/topic/Amazoncom|title=Amazon.com - History & Facts|website=Encyclopedia Britannica|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Board of directors ==\n[[File:Jeff Bezos 2016.jpg|thumb|upright|Amazon founder [[Jeff Bezos]] in 2016]]\n\n{{As of|2019|November|df=}}, the board of directors is:<ref>{{cite web |title=Officers & Directors |url=https://ir.aboutamazon.com/board-of-directors|website=Amazon |accessdate=March 29, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Jeff Bezos]], President, CEO, and Chairman\n* [[Rosalind Brewer]], Group President, and COO, [[Starbucks]]\n* [[Jamie Gorelick]], partner, [[Wilmer Cutler Pickering Hale and Dorr|Wilmer Cutler Pickering Hale, and Dorr]]\n* [[Daniel P. Huttenlocher]], Dean of the Schwarzman College of Computing at the [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]]\n* [[Judy McGrath]], former CEO, [[MTV Networks]]\n* [[Indra Nooyi]], former CEO, [[PepsiCo]]\n* [[Jon Rubinstein]], former Chairman, and CEO, [[Palm, Inc.]]\n* [[Thomas O. Ryder]], former Chairman, and CEO, [[Reader's Digest Association]]\n* [[Patty Stonesifer]], President, and CEO, [[Martha's Table]]\n* [[Wendell P. Weeks]], Chairman, President, and CEO, [[Corning Inc.]]\n\n== Merchant partnerships ==\nIn 2000, U.S. toy retailer [[Toys \"R\" Us]] entered into a 10-year agreement with Amazon, valued at $50 million per year plus a cut of sales, under which Toys \"R\" Us would be the exclusive supplier of toys and baby products on the service, and the chain's website would redirect to Amazon's Toys & Games category. In 2004, Toys \"R\" Us sued Amazon, claiming that because of a perceived lack of variety in Toys \"R\" Us stock, Amazon had knowingly allowed third-party sellers to offer items on the service in categories that Toys \"R\" Us had been granted exclusivity. In 2006, a court ruled in favor of Toys \"R\" Us, giving it the right to unwind its agreement with Amazon and establish its own independent e-commerce website. The company was later awarded $51 million in damages.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/1080389/a-dot-com-era-deal-with-amazon-marked-the-beginning-of-the-end-for-toys-r-us/|title=Toys R Us bankruptcy: A dot-com-era deal with Amazon marked the beginning of the end |website=Quartz|language=en|access-date=November 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/business/4769896.stm|title=Toys R Us wins Amazon lawsuit|work=[[BBC News]]|date=March 3, 2006|accessdate=December 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/tech/news/2009-06-12-amazon-toys_N.htm|title=Amazon to pay Toys R Us $51M to settle suit|last=Metz|first=Rachel|date=June 12, 2009|work=[[USA Today]]|accessdate=December 1, 2012|agency=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, Amazon entered into a similar agreement with [[Borders Group]], under which Amazon would comanage Borders.com as a co-branded service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://money.cnn.com/2001/04/11/companies/amazon/index.htm|title=Amazon/Borders form online partnership|website=CNN Money|date=April 11, 2001|access-date=November 11, 2018}}</ref> Borders pulled out of the arrangement in 2007, with plans to also launch its own online store.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sfgate.com/business/article/How-Amazon-factor-killed-retailers-like-6378619.php|title=How 'Amazon factor' killed retailers like Borders, Circuit City|date=July 13, 2015|work=SFGate|access-date=November 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn October 18, 2011, Amazon.com announced a partnership with [[DC Comics]] for the exclusive digital rights to many popular comics, including ''[[Superman]]'', ''[[Batman]]'', ''[[Green Lantern]]'', ''[[The Sandman (Vertigo)|The Sandman]],'' and ''[[Watchmen]]''. The partnership has caused well-known bookstores like Barnes & Noble to remove these titles from their shelves.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/10/19/technology/bookstores-drop-comics-after-amazon-deal-with-dc.html|title=Bookstores Drop Comics After Amazon Deal With DC|last=Streitfeld|first=David|date=October 18, 2011|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 20, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2013, Amazon announced a partnership with the [[United States Postal Service]] to begin delivering orders on Sundays. The service, included in Amazon's standard shipping rates, initiated in metropolitan areas of [[Los Angeles]] and [[New York, New York|New York]] because of the high-volume and inability to deliver in a timely way, with plans to expand into [[Dallas, Texas|Dallas]], [[Houston]], [[New Orleans]] and [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]] by 2014.<ref>{{cite news |last=Barr |first=Alistair |title=Amazon starts Sunday delivery with US Postal Service |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2013/11/11/amazon-sunday-delivery-usps/3479055/ |work=USA Today |accessdate=November 25, 2013 |date=November 11, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2017, [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]] confirmed a \"pilot\" partnership with Amazon to sell goods directly on the platform.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2017/06/30/nike-amazon-confirmed/ |title=Nike confirms 'pilot' partnership with Amazon |website=Engadget|access-date=July 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/06/29/technology/business/nike-amazon-shoes/index.html |title=Nike confirms Amazon partnership |last=Wattles |first=Jackie |date=June 29, 2017 |website=CNNMoney|access-date=July 3, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://fortune.com/2017/06/30/nike-amazon-instagram/ |title=Nike confirms it will sell directly on Amazon and Instagram |last=Wahba |first=Phil |website=Fortune|access-date=July 3, 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{as of|2017|October|11|df=US}}, [[AmazonFresh]] sold a range of [[Booths Supermarkets|Booths]] branded products for home delivery in selected areas.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2017/10/11/booths-teams-amazon-sell-south-first-time/ |title=Booths teams up with Amazon to sell down South for the first time |date=October 11, 2017 |newspaper=Telegraph |accessdate=October 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, Amazon ventured with one of its sellers JV Appario Retail owned by Patni Group which has recorded a total income of US$&thinsp;104.44&thinsp;million ([[Indian rupee|\u20b9]]&thinsp;759&thinsp;[[crore]]) in financial year 2017\u201318.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inc42.com/buzz/amazons-jv-appario-retail-clocks-in-104-4-mn-for-fy18/|title=Amazon's JV Appario Retail Clocks In $104.4 Mn For FY18|last=Bhumika|first=Khatri|date=September 27, 2018|website=Inc42 Media}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2018, Amazon reached an agreement with [[Apple Inc.]] to sell selected products through the service, via the company and selected Apple Authorized Resellers. As a result of this partnership, only Apple Authorized Resellers may sell Apple products on Amazon effective January 4, 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/11/9/18079340/amazon-apple-iphone-ipad-watch-beats-deal-selling-products-online|title=Amazon strikes deal with Apple to sell new iPhones and iPads|work=The Verge|access-date=November 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/apple-pumps-up-its-amazon-listings-with-iphones-ipads-and-more/|title=Apple pumps up its Amazon listings with iPhones, iPads and more|date=November 10, 2018|work=CNET|access-date=November 11, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Products and services ==\n{{Main|List of Amazon products and services}}\nAmazon.com's product lines available at its website include several media ([[book]]s, DVDs, music CDs, [[VHS|videotapes]] and software), apparel, baby products, [[consumer electronics]], [[Cosmetics|beauty products]], gourmet food, groceries, health and personal-care items, industrial & scientific supplies, kitchen items, [[jewelry]], watches, lawn and garden items, musical instruments, [[Sports equipment|sporting goods]], tools, automotive items and toys & games.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}} In August 2019, Amazon applied to have a liquor store in San Francisco, CA as a means to ship beer and alcohol within the city.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/amazon-liquor-license-storefront-san-francisco-2019-8|title=Amazon is looking to open a brick-and-mortar liquor store in San Francisco|last=Leskin|first=Paige|website=Business Insider|access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref> Amazon has separate retail websites for some countries and also offers international shipping of some of its products to certain other countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/1562/0001193125-13-028520.pdf |title=Amazon.com, Form 10-K, Annual Report, Filing Date Jan 30, 2013 |publisher=SEC database |accessdate=February 26, 2013}}</ref>\n\nAmazon.com has a number of products and services available, including:\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[AmazonFresh]]\n* [[Amazon Prime]]\n* [[Amazon Web Services]]\n* [[Amazon Alexa|Alexa]]\n* [[Amazon Appstore|Appstore]]\n* [[Amazon Drive]]\n* [[Amazon Echo|Echo]]\n* [[Amazon Kindle|Kindle]]\n* [[Kindle Fire|Fire tablets]]\n* [[Amazon Fire TV|Fire TV]]\n* [[Amazon Video|Video]]\n* [[Kindle Store]]\n* [[Amazon Music|Music]]\n* [[Amazon Music Unlimited|Music Unlimited]]\n* [[Amazon Digital Game Store]]\n* [[Amazon Studios]]\n* [[AmazonWireless]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Subsidiaries ==\n{{See also|List of Amazon locations}}\n\nAmazon owns over 40 subsidiaries, including [[Zappos]], [[Shopbop]], Diapers.com, Kiva Systems (now [[Amazon Robotics]]), [[Audible (store)|Audible]], [[Goodreads]], Teachstreet, [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] and [[IMDb]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amazon.jobs/team-category/subsidiaries|title=Amazon Jobs \u2013 Work for a Subsidiary|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140801055637/http://www.amazon.jobs/team-category/subsidiaries|archivedate=August 1, 2014|url-status=dead|accessdate=October 27, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===A9.com===\n[[A9.com]], a company focused on researching and building innovative [[technology]], has been a subsidiary since 2003.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blogs.pcworld.com/techlog/archives/002876.html|title=Amazon's A9 Search as We Knew It: Dead!|last=McCracken|first=Harry|date=September 29, 2006|website=[[PC World]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716052029/http://blogs.pcworld.com/techlog/archives/002876.html|archive-date=July 16, 2011|url-status=dead|access-date=September 6, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Amazon Maritime===\nAmazon Maritime, Inc. holds a [[Federal Maritime Commission]] license to operate as a [[NVOCC|non-vessel-owning common carrier]] (NVOCC), which enables the company to manage its own shipments from China into the United States.<ref>Steele, B., [https://www.engadget.com/2017/01/26/amazon-shipping-ocean-freight/ Amazon is now managing its own ocean freight], [[engadget.com]], January 27, 2017, accessed January 29, 2017</ref>\n\n===Annapurna Labs===\nIn January 2015, [[Amazon Web Services]] acquired [[Annapurna Labs]], an Israel-based microelectronics company reputedly for US$350\u2013370M.<ref name=\"reut_Amaz\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/01/22/us-annapurna-m-a-amazon-com-idUSKBN0KV0SG20150122|title=Amazon to buy Israeli start-up Annapurna Labs|author=|date=|work=Reuters|language=|accessdate=2015-01-24|quote=}}</ref><ref name=\"extr_Amaz\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.extremetech.com/computing/198140-amazon-buys-secretive-chip-maker-annapurna-labs-for-350-million|title=Amazon buys secretive chip maker Annapurna Labs for $350 million|author=|date=|work=ExtremeTech|accessdate=2015-01-24|quote=}}</ref>\n\n===Audible.com===\n[[Audible.com]] is a seller and producer of spoken audio entertainment, information and educational programming on the Internet. Audible sells digital [[audiobooks]], radio and TV programs and audio versions of magazines and newspapers. Through its production arm, Audible Studios, Audible has also become the world's largest producer of downloadable audiobooks. On January 31, 2008, Amazon announced it would buy Audible for about $300 million. The deal closed in March 2008 and Audible became a subsidiary of Amazon.<ref>{{cite news |work=PC World |author=Sayer, Peter |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/01/31/AR2008013101662.html |title=Amazon buys Audible for US$300 million |date=January 31, 2008}}</ref>\n\n===Beijing Century Joyo Courier Services===\nBeijing Century Joyo Courier Services is a subsidiary of Amazon and it applied for a [[Freight forwarder|freight forwarding]] license with the [[Federal Maritime Commission|US Maritime Commission]]. Amazon is also building out its logistics in [[Trucking industry in the United States|trucking]] and [[air freight]] to potentially compete with [[United Parcel Service|UPS]] and [[FedEx]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/01/29/is-logistics-about-to-get-amazoned/ |title=Is Logistics About To Get Amazon'ed? |date=January 29, 2016 |publisher=AOL |work=TechCrunch}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://fortune.com/2016/01/14/amazon-china-earns-its-ocean-shipping-license/ |title=Amazon China Has Its Ocean Shipping License \u2013 Fortune |author=David Z. Morris |date=January 14, 2016 |work=Fortune}}</ref>\n\n===Brilliance Audio===\nBrilliance Audio is an audiobook publisher founded in 1984 by Michael Snodgrass in [[Grand Haven, Michigan]].<ref name=\"brilliance\">{{cite web |url=http://www.brillianceaudio.com/company_overview |title=Company Overview |publisher=Brilliance Audio |author= |date= |accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref> The company produced its first 8 audio titles in 1985.<ref name=\"brilliance\" /> The company was purchased by Amazon in 2007 for an undisclosed amount.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.taume.com/World-Business/Business-Finance/Amazon_com-Acquires-Brilliance-Audio-1358 |title=amazon.com Acquires Brilliance Audio |work=Taume News |date=May 27, 2007 |accessdate=May 28, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070704192411/http://news.taume.com/World-Business/Business-Finance/Amazon_com-Acquires-Brilliance-Audio-1358 |archivedate=July 4, 2007 |url-status=dead |df=}}</ref><ref name=\"gigaom\">{{cite web |url=http://gigaom.com/2007/05/23/419-amazon-acquires-audiobook-indie-brilliance-audio/ |title=Amazon Acquires Audiobook Indie Brilliance Audio |work=Gigaom |author=Staci D. Kramer |date=May 23, 2007 |accessdate=February 14, 2014}}</ref> At the time of the acquisition, Brilliance was producing 12\u201315 new titles a month.<ref name=\"gigaom\" /> It operates as an independent company within Amazon.\n\nIn 1984, Brilliance Audio invented a technique for recording twice as much on the same cassette.<ref name=\"blake\">{{cite book |title=Information Literacies for the Twenty-First Century |chapter=Something New Has Been Added: Aural Literacy and Libraries |publisher=G. K. Hall & Co. |author=Virgil L. P. Blake |year=1990 |pages=203\u2013218}}</ref> The technique involved recording on each of the two channels of each stereo track.<ref name=\"blake\" /> It has been credited with revolutionizing the burgeoning audiobook market in the mid-1980s since it made unabridged books affordable.<ref name=\"blake\" />\n\n===ComiXology===\n[[ComiXology]] is a [[Cloud computing|cloud]]-based digital comics platform with over 200 million comic downloads {{as of|2013|September|lc=y}}. It offers a selection of more than 40,000 comic books and graphic novels across Android, iOS, Fire OS and Windows 8 devices and over a web browser. Amazon bought the company in April 2014.<ref>{{cite news |title=Amazon Buys ComiXology, Takes Over Digital Leadership |work=Bloomberg BusinessWeek |url=http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-04-11/amazon-buys-comixology-takes-over-digital-leadership-of-comic-book-world |author=Stone, Brad |date=April 11, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===CreateSpace===\nCreateSpace, which offers self-publishing services for independent content creators, publishers, film studios, and music labels, became a subsidiary in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.createspace.com/|title=Independent Publishing with CreateSpace|website=CreateSpace: An Amazon Company|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131126161130/https://www.createspace.com/|archivedate=November 26, 2013|url-status=dead|accessdate=January 22, 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.createspace.com/AboutUs.jsp|title=About CreateSpace : History|website=CreateSpace: An Amazon Company|accessdate=January 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Eero===\nEero is a company that manufactures mesh-capable routers. The company was founded in 2015 and is based in San Francisco. Amazon announced it would buy Eero in 2019.\n\n===Goodreads===\n[[Goodreads]] is a \"[[social cataloging]]\" website founded in December 2006 and launched in January 2007 by Otis Chandler, a software engineer, and entrepreneur, and Elizabeth Chandler. The website allows individuals to freely search Goodreads' extensive user-populated database of books, annotations, and reviews. Users can sign up and register books to generate library catalogs and reading lists. They can also create their own groups of book suggestions and discussions. In December 2007, the site had over 650,000 members and over 10 million books had been added. Amazon bought the company in March 2013.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/03/29/business/media/amazon-to-buy-goodreads.html|title=Amazon to Buy Social Site Dedicated to Sharing Books|last=Kaufman|first=Leslie|date=March 28, 2013|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 20, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n===Health Navigator===\nIn October 2019, Amazon finalized the acquisition of Health Navigator, a startup developing [[Application programming interface|APIs]] for online health services. The startup will form part of Amazon Care, which is the company's employee healthcare service. This follows the 2018 purchase of [[PillPack]] for under $1 billion, which has also been included into Amazon Care.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Shu |first1=Catherine |title=Amazon acquires Health Navigator for Amazon Care, its pilot employee healthcare program |url=https://techcrunch.com/2019/10/23/amazon-acquires-health-navigator-for-amazon-care-its-pilot-employee-healthcare-program/ |website=Tech Crunch |accessdate=31 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Junglee===\nJunglee is a former online shopping service provided by Amazon that enabled customers to search for products from online and offline retailers in India. Junglee started off as a virtual database that was used to extract information off the internet and deliver it to enterprise applications. As it progressed, Junglee started to use its database technology to create a single window marketplace on the internet by making every item from every supplier available for purchase. Web shoppers could locate, compare and transact millions of products from across the Internet shopping mall through one window.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://expressindia.indianexpress.com/ie/daily/19980814/22650774.html |title=Junglee boys strike gold on the net |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217162934/http://expressindia.indianexpress.com/ie/daily/19980814/22650774.html |archivedate=December 17, 2013 |df=}}</ref>\n\nAmazon acquired Junglee in 1998, and the website Junglee.com was launched in India in February 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=http://in.reuters.com/article/2012/02/02/amazon-india-launch-idINDEE81108G20120202 |title=Amazon Launches Online Shopping Service In India |publisher=reuters.com |date=February 2, 2012}}</ref> as a comparison-shopping website. It curated and enabled searching for a diverse variety of products such as clothing, electronics, toys, jewelry and video games, among others, across thousands of online and offline sellers. Millions of products are browse-able, whereby the client selects a price, and then they are directed to a seller. In November 2017, Amazon closed down Junglee.com and the former domain currently redirects to Amazon India.<ref>{{cite web |title=Amazon brings the curtains down on Junglee.com, finally |url=https://www.vccircle.com/amazon-brings-the-curtains-down-on-junglee-com-finally/ |website=vccircle.com |accessdate=February 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Kuiper Systems{{anchor|Project Kuiper}}===\nAmazon announced in April 2019 that they would fund and deploy a large [[broadband]] [[satellite internet constellation]] called \"'''Project Kuiper'''\".<ref name=cnbc20190404>{{cite news |last=Sheetz|first=Michael |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/04/04/amazon-project-kuiper-broadband-internet-small-satellite-network.html |title=Amazon wants to launch thousands of satellites so it can offer broadband internet from space |work=[[CNBC]] |date=4 April 2019 |accessdate=4 April 2019 }}</ref><ref name=sn20190404>{{cite news |last=Henry|first=Caleb |url=https://spacenews.com/amazon-planning-3236-satellite-constellation-for-internet-connectivity/ |title=Amazon planning 3,236-satellite constellation for internet connectivity |work=[[SpaceNews]] |date=4 April 2019 |accessdate=5 April 2019 }}</ref> It is expected to take up to a decade to fully deploy all 3,236 satellites planned for the full constellation in order to provide internet to \"tens of millions of people who lack basic access to broadband internet.\"<ref name=cnbc20190404/> Amazon has not announced if they intend to sell [[broadband]] service directly to consumers, but they will \"offer broadband service through partnerships with other companies.\"<ref name=ars20190708/>\n\nThe satellites will use an orbit with a height between {{cvt|590 and 630|km}}.<ref name=bb20090705>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-07-05/amazon-asks-to-join-broadband-space-race-with-elon-musk-s-spacex|title=Chasing SpaceX, Amazon Seeks to Launch 3,236 Internet Satellites|date=July 5, 2019}}</ref> Kuiper will work in concert with Amazon's previously announced large network of 12 satellite ground station facilities (the \"'''AWS Ground Station unit'''\") announced in November 2018.<ref name=cnbc20181127>{{cite news |last=Sheetz|first=Michael |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/11/27/amazon-launches-aws-ground-station-satellite-data-collection-service.html |title=Amazon cloud business reaches into space with satellite connection service |work=[[CNBC]] |date=27 November 2018 |accessdate=4 April 2019 }}</ref> Amazon filed communications license documents with the U.S. [[regulatory authority|regulatory authorities]] the [[FCC]] in July 2019, which included information that the wholly owned Amazon subsidiary that intended to deploy the satellite constellation was Kuiper Systems LLC, based in Seattle, Washington.<ref name=fcc20190704/>  The Kuiper System will consist of 3,236 satellites operating in 98 [[Orbital plane (astronomy)|orbital planes]] in three [[Orbital shell (spaceflight)|orbital shells]], one each at {{convert|590|km|sp=us}}, {{cvt|610|km}}, and {{cvt|630|km}} [[orbital altitude]].<ref name=sn20190708>[https://spacenews.com/amazon-lays-out-constellation-service-goals-deployment-and-deorbit-plans-to-fcc/ Amazon lays out constellation service goals, deployment and deorbit plans to FCC], Caleb Henry, [[SpaceNews]], 8 July 2019, accessed 9 September 2019.</ref>  The Kuiper System includes high-performance satellites, terrestrial [[Gateway (telecommunications)|gateways]], internetworking technologies, and a range of customer terminals.\"<ref name=fcc20190704>{{cite web |url=https://licensing.fcc.gov/myibfs/download.do?attachment_key=1773656 |title=APPLICATION FOR AUTHORITY TO LAUNCH AND OPERATE A NON-GEOSTATIONARY SATELLITE ORBIT SYSTEM IN KA-BAND FREQUENCIES |work=licensing.fcc.gov |publisher=[[Federal Communications Commission]] |date=4 July 2019 |accessdate=6 July 2019 }}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, information became public that Amazon is asking the FCC to waive requirements that [[SpaceX]] and [[OneWeb]] had to follow in order to get their large satellite internet constellations licensed.<ref name=vice201912>{{cite news |url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/5dmzyx/spacex-is-lobbying-against-amazons-internet-beaming-satellites |title=SpaceX Is Lobbying Against Amazon's Internet-Beaming Satellites |work=Vice |date= |access-date=23 December 2019 |quote=Amazon is trying to get a waiver to FCC rules that companies like SpaceX and OneWeb had to follow. }}</ref>  The FCC has not yet ruled on the request.\n\nThe president of Kuiper Systems is Rajeev Badyal, a former vice president of [[SpaceX]]'s [[SpaceX Starlink|Starlink]] satellite internet constellation.<ref name=ars20190708>\n{{cite news |last=Brodkin|first=Jon |url=https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2019/07/amazon-follows-spacex-into-satellite-broadband-asks-fcc-to-ok-launch-plan/ |title=Amazon plans nationwide broadband\u2014with both home and mobile service |work=ars Technica |date=8 July 2019 |accessdate=9 July 2019 |quote=''Kuiper is wholly owned by Amazon, and its president is Rajeev Badyal, a former SpaceX vice president who was reportedly fired because SpaceX CEO Elon Musk was unsatisfied with his company's satellite-broadband progress.'' }}</ref> During 2020 the Kuiper team will move to a larger R&D facility in [[Redmond, Washington]].<ref name=sn-20191218>{{cite news |url=https://spacenews.com/amazon-moving-project-kuiper-team-to-new-rd-headquarters/ |title=Amazon moving Project Kuiper team to new R&D headquarters |last=Henry |first=Caleb |publisher=SpaceNews |date=18 December 2019 |access-date=20 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Lab126===\n{{main|Amazon Lab126}}\nLab126, developers of integrated consumer electronics such as the [[Amazon Kindle|Kindle]], became a subsidiary in 2004.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mercurynews.com/2012/09/19/amazon-research-unit-lab-126-agrees-to-big-lease-that-could-bring-sunnyvale-2600-new-workers/|title=Amazon research unit Lab 126 agrees to big lease that could bring Sunnyvale 2,600 new workers|last=Avalos|first=George|date=September 19, 2012|work=The Mercury News|access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Ring===\n{{main|Ring Inc.}}\nRing is a home automation company founded by Jamie Siminoff in 2013. It is primarily known for its WiFi powered [[smart doorbell]]s, but manufactures other devices such as security cameras. Amazon bought Ring for $1 billion USD in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/02/27/amazon-buys-ring-a-former-shark-tank-reject.html|title=Amazon buys Ring, a former 'Shark Tank' reject|last=Montag|first=Ali|date=February 27, 2018|website=CNBC|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Shelfari===\n[[Shelfari]] was a [[social cataloging]] website for books. Shelfari users built virtual bookshelves of the titles which they owned or had read and they could rate, review, [[tag (metadata)|tag]] and discuss their books. Users could also create groups that other members could join, create discussions and talk about books, or other topics. Recommendations could be sent to friends on the site for what books to read. Amazon bought the company in August 2008.<ref name=\":0\" /> Shelfari continued to function as an independent book social network within the Amazon until January 2016, when Amazon announced that it would be merging Shelfari with Goodreads and closing down Shelfari.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thereadersroom.org/2016/01/12/amazon-kills-shelfari/|title=Amazon Kills Shelfari|date=January 13, 2016|website=The Reader's Room|language=en|access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://thebookmarketingnetwork.com/profiles/blogs/shelfari-is-closing-but-you-can-merge-your-account-with-goodreads |title=Shelfari Is Closing! BUT, You Can Merge Your Account with Goodreads! |author=Holiday, J.D. |date=January 13, 2016 |website=The Book Marketing Network}}</ref>\n\n===Souq===\n{{main|Souq.com}}\n\n[[Souq.com]] is the largest [[Ecommerce platform|E-Commerce platform]] in the Middle East based in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. On March 28, 2017, Amazon confirmed it would be acquiring Souq.com for $580 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1018724/000101872417000051/amzn-20170331x10q.htm|title= Amazon 10-Q filing}}</ref> Souq.com is now a subsidiary of Amazon, and acts as Amazon's arm into the Middle East region.\n\n===Twitch===\n[[File:E3 \u2013 2014 (23113432796).jpg|thumb|[[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] at the [[Electronic Entertainment Expo]]]]\n\n[[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] is a [[live streaming]] platform for video, primarily oriented towards video gaming content. The service was first established as a spin-off of a general-interest streaming service known as [[Justin.tv]]. Its prominence was eclipsed by that of Twitch, and Justin.tv was eventually shut down by its parent company in August 2014 in order to focus exclusively on Twitch.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/twitch-pulls-the-plug-on-video-streaming-site-justin-tv/ |title=Twitch pulls the plug on video-streaming site Justin.tv |work=CNET|access-date=August 8, 2017 |language=en}}</ref> Later that month, Twitch was acquired by Amazon for $970 million.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2014/8/25/6066295/amazon-reportedly-buying-twitch-for-over-1-billion |title=Amazon, not Google, is buying Twitch for $970 million |last=Welch |first=Chris |date=August 25, 2014 |website=The Verge|access-date=August 8, 2017}}</ref> Through Twitch, Amazon also owns [[Curse, Inc.]], an operator of video gaming communities and a provider of [[VoIP]] services for gaming.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2016/8/16/12507616/twitch-buys-curse |title=Twitch to acquire Curse |last=Hall |first=Charlie |date=August 16, 2016 |website=Polygon|access-date=August 8, 2017}}</ref> Since the acquisition, Twitch began to sell games directly through the platform,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/2/27/14748896/twitch-sell-games-streamers-cut |title=Twitch will start selling games and giving its streamers a cut |last=McCormick |first=Rich |date=February 27, 2017 |website=The Verge|access-date=August 8, 2017}}</ref> and began offering special features for Amazon Prime subscribers.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2016/9/30/13125824/twitch-prime-amazon-ad-free-game-discounts |title=Twitch will be ad-free for all Amazon Prime subscribers |last=Statt |first=Nick |date=September 30, 2016 |website=The Verge|access-date=August 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe site's rapid growth had been boosted primarily by the prominence of major [[esports]] competitions on the service, leading [[GameSpot]] senior esports editor Rod Breslau to have described the service as \"the [[ESPN]] of esports\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2013/9/30/4719766/twitch-raises-20-million-esports-market-booming |title=Field of streams: how Twitch made video games a spectator sport |last=Popper |first=Ben |date=September 30, 2013 |website=The Verge|access-date=August 8, 2017}}</ref> {{as of|2015}}, the service had over 1.5 million broadcasters and 100 million monthly viewers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2015/01/29/twitchs-viewers-reach-100-million-a-month/|title=Twitch's Viewers Reach 100 Million a Month|last=Needleman|first=Sarah E.|date=January 29, 2015|website=WSJ|language=en-US|access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Whole Foods Market===\n[[File:Whole Foods Market Cranbrook Village Ann Arbor Michigan.JPG|thumb|[[Whole Foods Market]] store in [[Ann Arbor, Michigan]]]]\n\n[[Whole Foods Market]] is an American [[supermarket]] [[chain store|chain]] exclusively featuring foods without artificial preservatives, colors, flavors, sweeteners, and hydrogenated fats.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wholefoodsmarket.com/quality-standards |title=Quality Standards |publisher=Whole Foods Market |date=<!--undated--> |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->}}</ref>\n\nOn August 23, 2017, it was reported that the [[Federal Trade Commission]] approved the merger between Amazon.com and Whole Foods Market.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2017/08/23/ftc-allows-amazon-whole-foods-deal-to-proceed.html|title=FTC allows Amazon, Whole Foods deal to proceed |last=LaVito |first=Angelica |work=CNBC |date=August 23, 2017 |accessdate=October 31, 2018}}</ref> The following day it was announced that the deal would be closed on August 28, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |title=Amazon and Whole Foods Market Announce Acquisition to Close This Monday, Will Work Together to Make High-Quality, Natural and Organic Food Affordable for Everyone |url=http://phx.corporate-ir.net/phoenix.zhtml?c=176060&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=2295514 |website=Amazon.com |publisher=BUSINESS WIRE |accessdate=August 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Supply chain==\nAmazon first launched its distribution network in 1997 with two fulfillment centers in [[Seattle]] and [[New Castle, Delaware]]. Amazon has several types of distribution facilities consisting of crossdock centers, fulfillment centers, sortation centers, delivery stations, Prime now hubs, and Prime air hubs. There are 75 fulfillment centers and 25 sortation centers with over 125,000 employees.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Routley |first1=Nick |title=Amazon's Massive Distribution Network in One Giant Visualization |url=https://www.visualcapitalist.com/footprint-all-amazons-warehouses/ |accessdate=7 July 2019|date=September 8, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=9 facts about Amazon's unprecedented warehouse empire |url=https://www.curbed.com/2017/11/21/16686150/black-friday-2018-amazon-warehouse-fulfillment |accessdate=7 July 2019|date=November 21, 2017 }}</ref> Employees are responsible for five basic tasks: unpacking and inspecting incoming goods; placing goods in storage and recording their location; picking goods from their computer recorded locations to make up an individual shipment; sorting and packing orders; and shipping. A computer that records the location of goods and maps out routes for pickers plays a key role: employees carry hand-held computers which communicate with the central computer and monitor their rate of progress. Some warehouses are partially automated with systems built by [[Amazon Robotics]].\n\n<gallery mode=\"packed\">\nFile:Lauwin-Planque - Lauwin-Park (02).JPG|Amazon.fr fulfillment center LIL1 in [[Lauwin-Planque]], [[France]]\nFile:Amazon Espa\u00f1a por dentro (San Fernando de Henares).JPG|Amazon.es fulfillment center in [[San Fernando de Henares]], [[Spain]]\nFile:Amazon warehouse Glenrothes.jpg|Amazon.co.uk fulfillment center in [[Glenrothes]], [[Scotland]]\nFile:Amazon.de 1204 - panoramio.jpg|Amazon.de fulfillment center in [[Germany]]\nFile:AmazonIchikawaFC (78316917).jpg|Amazon.co.jp fulfillment center in [[Ichikawa, Chiba|Ichikawa]], [[Japan]]\nFile:Amazon fulfillment center, Macon.jpg|Amazon fulfillment center in [[Macon, Georgia]], United States\n</gallery>\n\n== Website ==\n{{Infobox website\n| name            = Amazon.com\n| logo            = Amazon.com-Logo.svg\n| logo_size       = 200px\n| screenshot      = amazon.com screenshot.jpeg\n| collapsible     = yes\n| collapsetext    = Screenshot\n| caption         = amazon.com homepage\n| url             = {{URL|Amazon.com}} (original U.S. site)\n| commercial      = Yes\n| type            = [[E-commerce]]\n| registration    = Optional\n| language        = {{hlist|Arabic|English|French|German|Spanish|Italian|Chinese|Japanese|Portuguese|Dutch|Turkish}}\n| programming_language= [[C++]] and [[Java (programming language)|Java]]\n| owner           = Amazon.com\n| launch_date     = 1995\n| alexa           = {{Steady}} [http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/amazon.com 12] {{small|{{nowrap|(Global, {{as of|2019|12|21|alt=December 2019}})}}}}\n| current_status = Online\n| footnotes = <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/Amazon.com |title=Amazon.com Site Info |publisher=[[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate=July 4, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lextrait.com/Vincent/implementations.html |title=The Programming Languages Beacon, v10.0 |first=Vincent |last=Lextrait |date=January 2010 |accessdate=March 14, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120530/http://www.lextrait.com/Vincent/implementations.html |archivedate=May 30, 2012 |df=}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe domain ''amazon.com'' attracted at least 615 million visitors annually by 2008.<ref>[http://siteanalytics.compete.com/amazon.com/ SnapShot of amazon.com, amazonellers.com, walmart.com]. Retrieved April 12, 2008.</ref> Amazon attracts over 130 million customers to its US website per month by the start of 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://siteanalytics.compete.com/amazon.com |title=SnapShot of amazon.com \u2013 Compete |publisher=Siteanalytics.compete.com |accessdate=March 24, 2016}}</ref> The company has also invested heavily on a massive amount of server capacity for its website, especially to handle the excessive traffic during the December [[Christmas holiday season]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Why attackers can't take down Amazon.com |url=http://money.cnn.com/2010/12/09/technology/amazon_wikileaks_attack |publisher=CNN |date=December 9, 2010 |accessdate=December 14, 2010 |quote=Amazon has famously massive server capacity in order to handle the December e-commerce rush. That short holiday shopping window is so critical and so intense, that even a few minutes of downtime could cost Amazon millions. |first=Julianne |last=Pepitone}}</ref>\n\nResults generated by Amazon's search engine are partly determined by promotional fees.<ref name=\"New Yorker\">{{cite web |last=Packer |first=George |authorlink=George Packer |date=February 17, 2014 |title=Cheap Words |url=https://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2014/02/17/140217fa_fact_packer?currentPage=all |work=[[The New Yorker|newyorker.com]] |accessdate=March 22, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAmazon's [[Internationalization and localization|localized]] storefronts, which differ in selection and prices, are differentiated by [[top-level domain]] and [[country code]]:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:right\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Region !! scope=\"col\" | Country !! scope=\"col\" | [[Domain name]]\n!Since\n|-\n! rowspan=\"4\" {{rh2|align=right}} class=\"rh heading table-rh\" | Americas\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Brazil}} || amazon.com[[.br]]\n|December 2012\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Canada}} || amazon[[.ca]]\n|June 2002\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Mexico}} || amazon.com[[.mx]]\n|August 2013\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|United States}} || amazon[[.com]]\n|July 1995\n|-\n! rowspan=\"6\" {{rh2|align=right}} class=\"rh heading table-rh\" | Asia\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|China}} || amazon[[.cn]]\n|September 2004\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|India}} || amazon[[.in]]\n|June 2013\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Japan}} || amazon.co[[.jp]]\n|November 2000\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Singapore}} || amazon[[.sg]]\n|July 2017\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Turkey}} || amazon.com[[.tr]]\n|September 2018\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|United Arab Emirates}} || amazon[[.ae]]\n|May 2019\n|-\n! rowspan=\"6\" {{rh2|align=right}} class=\"rh heading table-rh\" | Europe\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|France}} || amazon[[.fr]]\n|August 2000\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Germany}} || amazon[[.de]]\n|October 1998\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Italy}} || amazon[[.it]]\n|November 2010\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Netherlands}} || amazon[[.nl]]\n|November 2014\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Spain}} || amazon[[.es]]\n|September 2011\n|-\n| {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|United Kingdom}} || amazon.co[[.uk]]\n|October 1998\n|-\n| {{rh2|align=right}} class=\"rh heading table-rh\" | Oceania || {{rh|align=left}} class=\"table-rh\" | {{small|Australia}} || amazon.com[[.au]]\n|November 2017\n|}\n\n=== Reviews ===\n{{See also|Criticism of Amazon#Amazon reviews}}\nAmazon allows users to submit reviews to the web page of each product. Reviewers must rate the product on a [[rating scale]] from one to five stars. Amazon provides a badging option for reviewers which indicate the real name of the reviewer (based on confirmation of a credit card account) or which indicate that the reviewer is one of the top reviewers by popularity. Customers may comment or vote on the reviews, indicating whether they found a review helpful to them. If a review is given enough \"helpful\" hits, it appears on the front page of the product. In 2010, Amazon was reported as being the largest single source of Internet consumer reviews.<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20100503005110/en/2010-Social-Shopping-Study-Reveals-Consumers%E2%80%99-Online |title=2010 Social Shopping Study Reveals Changes in Consumers' Online Shopping Habits and Usage of Customer Reviews |work=the e-tailing group, PowerReviews |publisher=[[Business Wire]] |date=May 3, 2010 |accessdate=January 31, 2013}}</ref>\n\nWhen publishers asked Bezos why Amazon would publish negative reviews, he defended the practice by claiming that Amazon.com was \"taking a different approach ... we want to make every book available\u2014the good, the bad and the ugly ... to let truth loose\".<ref>{{cite book |title=Amazon.com |author=Spector, Robert |year=2002 |page=132}}</ref>\n\nThere have been cases of positive reviews being written and posted by [[public relations]] companies on behalf of their clients<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cincinnatibeacon.com/index.php?/contents/comments/amazon.com_rave_book_reviews_too_good_to_be_true |title=BEACON SPOTLIGHT: Amazon.com rave book reviews \u2013 too good to be true? |work=The Cincinnati Beacon |date=May 25, 2010 |accessdate=January 31, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502004404/http://www.cincinnatibeacon.com/index.php?%2Fcontents%2Fcomments%2Famazon.com_rave_book_reviews_too_good_to_be_true |archivedate=May 2, 2014 }}</ref> and instances of writers using pseudonyms to leave negative reviews of their rivals' works.\n\n=== Content search ===\n\"Search Inside the Book\" is a feature which allows customers to search for keywords in the full text of many books in the catalog.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com |title=Amazon's online reader ''Search Inside'' reference |date=September 9, 2009 |accessdate=August 29, 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100828044958/http://www.amazon.com/ |archivedate=August 28, 2010 |url-status=live |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com |title=''Search Inside'' reference |date=September 9, 2009 |accessdate=August 29, 2010}}</ref> The feature started with 120,000 titles (or 33 million pages of text) on October 23, 2003.<ref>{{cite web |first=Eric |last=Ward |url=http://www.urlwire.com/news/102203.html |title=Amazon.com Launches \"Search Inside the Book\" Feature |publisher=Urlwire.com |date=October 23, 2003 |accessdate=August 29, 2010}}</ref> There are about 300,000 books in the program. Amazon has cooperated with around 130 [[publisher]]s to allow users to perform these searches.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}}\n\nTo avoid copyright violations, Amazon does not return the computer-readable text of the book. Instead, it returns a picture of the matching page, instructs the web browser to disable printing and puts limits on the number of pages in a book a single user can access. Additionally, customers can purchase online access to some of the same books via the \"Amazon Upgrade\" program.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}}\n\n=== Third-party sellers ===\nAmazon derives many of its sales (around 40% in 2008) from third-party sellers who sell products on Amazon.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.stanford.edu/class/ee204/Publications/Amazon-EE353-2008-1.pdf |title=AMAZON ENTERS THE CLOUD COMPUTING BUSINESS |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> Associates receive a commission for referring customers to Amazon by placing links to Amazon on their websites if the referral results in a sale. Worldwide, Amazon has \"over 900,000 members\" in its affiliate programs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://affiliate-program.amazon.co.uk/gp/associates/join |title=Amazon.co.uk Associates: The web's most popular and successful Affiliate Program |publisher=Affiliate-program.amazon.co.uk |date=July 9, 2010 |accessdate=August 29, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080826210540/http://affiliate-program.amazon.co.uk/gp/associates/join |archivedate=August 26, 2008 }}</ref> In the middle of 2014, the Amazon Affiliate Program is used by 1.2% of all websites and it is the second most popular advertising network after Google Ads.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://w3techs.com/technologies/overview/advertising/all |title=Usage of advertising networks for websites |publisher=W3Techs.com |date=July 22, 2014 |accessdate=July 22, 2014}}</ref> It is frequently used by websites and non-profits to provide a way for supporters to earn them a commission.<ref>{{cite web |title=14 Easy Fundraising Ideas for Non-Profits |url=http://www.blisstree.com/2009/04/12/sex-relationships/14-easy-fundraising-ideas-for-non-profits/ |website=blisstree.com |accessdate=November 24, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222120701/http://www.blisstree.com/2009/04/12/sex-relationships/14-easy-fundraising-ideas-for-non-profits/ |archive-date=December 22, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Amazon reported over 1.3 million sellers sold products through Amazon's websites in 2007. Unlike [[eBay.com|eBay]], Amazon sellers do not have to maintain separate payment accounts; all payments are handled by Amazon.{{citation needed|date=May 2017}}\n\nAssociates can access the Amazon catalog directly on their websites by using the [[Amazon Web Services]] (AWS) [[XML]] service. A new affiliate product, aStore, allows Associates to embed a subset of Amazon products within another website, or linked to another website. In June 2010, Amazon Seller Product Suggestions was launched (rumored to be internally called \"Project Genesis\") to provide more transparency to sellers by recommending specific products to third-party sellers to sell on Amazon. Products suggested are based on customers' browsing history.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.amazonservices.com/content/product_alerts.htm?ld=AOguerillaPGJG |title=Amazon Seller Product Suggestions |publisher=Amazonservices.com |accessdate=August 29, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101205225641/http://www.amazonservices.com/content/product_alerts.htm?ld=AOguerillaPGJG |archive-date=December 5, 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2019, Amazon launched a bigger local online store in [[Singapore]] to expand its product selection in the face of intensifying competition with competitors in the region.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-amazon-singapore-idUSKBN1WN05N|title=Amazon launches bigger local online store in Singapore|date=2019-10-08|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-10-08|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019 the 3rd U.S. City Court of Appeals in Philadelphia ruled that Amazon can be held accountable for faulty third-party sales.<ref>https://www2.ca3.uscourts.gov/opinarch/181041p.pdf</ref> The decision ran counter to a past lower court ruling that had favored Amazon. Heather Oberdorf had sued the company in 2016 over a dog leash that snapped, causing permanent loss of vision in one eye. If upheld, the decision would expose Amazon and similar platform businesses to strict liability lawsuits for defective products, which represents a major change in the law.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.natlawreview.com/article/supply-chain-decision-online-marketplaces-risk-due-to-federal-court-ruling-oberdorf|title=Supply Chain Decision: Online Marketplaces At Risk Due To Federal Court Ruling in Oberdorf v. Amazon.com Inc.|last=|first=|date=22 July 2019|website=The National Law Review|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=31 January 2020}}</ref> The panel sent the case back to the lower court, to decide whether the leash was actually defective.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-amazon-com-liability/amazon-can-be-held-liable-for-third-party-seller-products-u-s-appeals-court-idUSKCN1TY2HM|title=Amazon can be held liable for third-party seller products: U.S. appeals court|last=|first=|date=3 July 2019|website=Reuters|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=31 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Amazon sales rank ==\nThe Amazon sales rank (ASR) provides an indication of the popularity of a product sold on any Amazon locale. It is a relative indicator of popularity that is updated hourly. Effectively, it is a \"best sellers list\" for the millions of products stocked by Amazon.<ref name=\"amazon\">{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=14101911 |title=Amazon FAQ |accessdate=September 5, 2011}}</ref> While the ASR has no direct effect on the sales of a product, it is used by Amazon to determine which products to include in its bestsellers lists.<ref name=\"amazon\" /> Products that appear in these lists enjoy additional exposure on the Amazon website and this may lead to an increase in sales. In particular, products that experience large jumps (up or down) in their sales ranks may be included within Amazon's lists of \"movers and shakers\"; such a listing provides additional exposure that might lead to an increase in sales.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/movers-and-shakers |title=Amazon.com Movers and shakers |accessdate=September 5, 2011}}</ref> For competitive reasons, Amazon does not release actual sales figures to the public. However, Amazon has now begun to release [[point of sale]] data via the [[Nielsen BookScan]] service to verified authors.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://authorcentral.amazon.com/gp/help?topicID=200580390 |title=Amazon.com Author Central |accessdate=September 5, 2011}}</ref> While the ASR has been the source of much speculation by publishers, manufacturers, and marketers, Amazon itself does not release the details of its sales rank calculation algorithm. Some companies have analyzed Amazon sales data to generate sales estimates based on the ASR,<ref>{{cite web |title=Amazon Sales Estimator |publisher=Jungle Scout |url=http://www.junglescout.com/estimator/ |date=May 15, 2017}}</ref> though Amazon states:\n\n{{quote|text=Please keep in mind that our sales rank figures are simply meant to be a guide of general interest for the customer and not definitive sales information for publishers\u2014we assume you have this information regularly from your distribution sources|sign=Amazon.com Help<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=14101911 |title=Frequently Asked Questions about Amazon.com |accessdate=September 6, 2012}}</ref>}}\n\n== Multi-level sales strategy ==\nAmazon employs a multi-level e-commerce strategy. Amazon started by focusing on business-to-consumer relationships between itself and its customers and business-to-business relationships between itself and its suppliers and then moved to facilitate customer-to-customer with the Amazon marketplace which acts as an intermediary to facilitate transactions. The company lets anyone sell nearly anything using its platform. In addition to an affiliate program that lets anyone post Amazon links and earn a commission on click-through sales, there is now a program which lets those affiliates build entire websites based on Amazon's platform.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://money.howstuffworks.com/amazon2.htm |title=How Amazon Works |accessdate=December 15, 2011|date=January 25, 2006 }}</ref>\n\nSome other large e-commerce sellers use Amazon to sell their products in addition to selling them through their own websites. The sales are processed through Amazon.com and end up at individual sellers for processing and order fulfillment and Amazon leases space for these retailers. Small sellers of used and new goods go to Amazon Marketplace to offer goods at a fixed price.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=743056 |title=Help |accessdate=December 16, 2011}}</ref>\n\nAmazon also employs the use of [[drop shipping|drop shippers]] or meta sellers. These are members or entities that advertise goods on Amazon who order these goods direct from other competing websites but usually from other Amazon members. These meta sellers may have millions of products listed, have large transaction numbers and are grouped alongside other less prolific members giving them credibility as just someone who has been in business for a long time. Markup is anywhere from 50% to 100% and sometimes more, these sellers maintain that items are in stock when the opposite is true. As Amazon increases their dominance in the marketplace these drop shippers have become more and more commonplace in recent years.{{citation needed|date=July 2014}}\n\nIn November 2015, Amazon opened a physical Amazon Books store in [[University Village, Seattle|University Village]] in Seattle. The store is 5,500 square feet and prices for all products match those on its website.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/amazon-plans-hundreds-of-brick-and-mortar-bookstores-mall-ceo-says-1454449475|title=Amazon Plans Hundreds of Brick-and-Mortar Bookstores, Mall CEO Says|last=Bensinger|first=Greg|date=February 2, 2016|work=Wall Street Journal|access-date=February 20, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0099-9660}}</ref> Amazon will open its tenth physical book store in 2017;<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.recode.net/2017/3/8/14850324/amazon-books-store-bellevue-mall-expansion |title=Amazon just confirmed its 10th book store, signaling this is way more than an experiment |first=Jason Del |last=Rey |date=March 8, 2017 |website=Recode}}</ref> media speculation suggests Amazon plans to eventually roll out 300 to 400 bookstores around the country.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nAmazon plans to open brick and mortar bookstores in Germany.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.faz.net/1.5347928 |title=Einzelhandel: Amazon plant Offline-Filialen in Deutschland |author= |date= |publisher= |accessdate=June 4, 2018 |newspaper=Faz.net}}</ref>\n\n== Finances ==\nAmazon.com is primarily a retail site with a sales revenue model; Amazon takes a small percentage of the sale price of each item that is sold through its website while also allowing companies to advertise their products by paying to be listed as featured products.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://marketingteacher.com/swot/amazon-swot.html |title=SWOT Analysis Amazon |accessdate=December 17, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111203164606/http://www.marketingteacher.com/swot/amazon-swot.html |archivedate=December 3, 2011 }}</ref> {{as of|2018}}, Amazon.com is ranked 8th on the [[Fortune 500]] rankings of the largest United States corporations by total revenue.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fortune.com/fortune500/list/|title=Fortune 500 Companies 2018: Who Made the List|website=Fortune|language=en-US|access-date=November 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\nFor the fiscal year 2018, Amazon reported earnings of US$10.07 billion, with an annual revenue of US$232.887 billion, an increase of 30.9% over the previous fiscal cycle. Since 2007 sales increased from 14.835 billion to 232.887 billion, thanks to continued business expansion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.statista.com/statistics/266282/annual-net-revenue-of-amazoncom/|title=Amazon: annual revenue 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=Statista|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=November 7, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAmazon's market capitalization went over US$1 trillion again in early February 2020 after the announcement of the fourth quarter 2019 results.<ref name=\"4Q 2020\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/30/technology/amazon-earningts.html/|title=Amazon Powers Ahead With Robust Profit|date=January 30, 2020|last=Streitfeld|first=David|work=[[The New York Times]]|language=en-US|access-date=February 2, 2020}}</ref> Amazon's total employees now number 798,000. <ref name=\"4Q 2020\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable float-left\" style=\"text-align: right;\"\n!Year\n!Revenue<br />in mil. USD$\n!Net income<br />in mil. USD$\n!Total Assets<br />in mil. USD$\n!Employees\n|-\n|2007<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.aboutamazon.com/static-files/56afc458-02b3-4938-9918-85d610d6f146|title=2007 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=|website=Ir.aboutamazon.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|14,835\n|476\n|6,485\n|17,000\n|-\n|2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.aboutamazon.com/static-files/e1846da7-9425-42d9-add7-84218d7ee5e7|title=2008 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=|website=Ir.aboutamazon.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|19,166\n|645\n|8,314\n|20,700\n|-\n|2009<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.aboutamazon.com/static-files/f793debb-dc0a-4edf-a56d-9ff739d53b41|title=2009 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=|website=Ir.aboutamazon.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|24,509\n|902\n|13,813\n|24,300\n|-\n|2010<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.aboutamazon.com/static-files/6f3c99ed-5094-4fed-a9ad-e18cdbf37478|title=2010 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=|website=Ir.aboutamazon.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|34,204\n|1,152\n|18,797\n|33,700\n|-\n|2011<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.aboutamazon.com/static-files/02a49fbe-6860-4ed7-ade4-905bcf16a5e1|title=2011 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=|website=Ir.aboutamazon.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|48,077\n|631\n|25,278\n|56,200\n|-\n|2012<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.aboutamazon.com/static-files/28bfea7a-7b18-4ab0-ba03-581c6ccaa3a4|title=2012 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=|website=Ir.aboutamazon.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|61,093\n|\u221239\n|32,555\n|88,400\n|-\n|2013<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.aboutamazon.com/static-files/1be0475a-fcab-4826-9258-17f11c208487|title=2013 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=|website=Ir.aboutamazon.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|74,452\n|274\n|40,159\n|117,300\n|-\n|2014<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/jan/29/amazon-reports-89b-in-sales-2014|title=Amazon reports $89bn in sales last year as shares jump 11% after hours|last=Neate|first=Rupert|date=January 29, 2015|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|language=en|access-date=November 7, 2018}}</ref>\n|88,988\n|\u2212241\n|54,505\n|154,100\n|-\n|2015<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/biz/news/amazon-clocks-107-billion-in-revenue-in-2015-1201691106/|title=Amazon Clocks $107 Billion In Revenue In 2015|last=Roettgers|first=Janko|date=January 28, 2016|website=Variety.com|access-date=November 7, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|107,006\n|596\n|64,747\n|230,800\n|-\n|2016<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.seattletimes.com/business/amazon/amazon-revenues-hit-by-stronger-dollar-miss-wall-street-expectations/|title=Amazon sales hit $136B in 2016; dollar hurts overseas business|date=February 2, 2017|work=The Seattle Times|access-date=November 7, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|135,987\n|2,371\n|83,402\n|341,400\n|-\n|2017<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-42911123|title=Amazon 2017 sales jump by nearly a third|date=February 1, 2018|work=BBC News|access-date=November 7, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n|177,866\n|3,033\n|131,310\n|566,000\n|-\n|2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.annualreports.com/HostedData/AnnualReports/PDF/NASDAQ_AMZN_2018.pdf|title=2018 Annual Report|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|232,887\n|10,073\n|162,648\n|647,500\n|}\n\n== Controversies ==\n{{Main|Criticism of Amazon}}\n\nSince its founding, the company has attracted criticism and controversy for its actions, including: supplying law enforcement with facial recognition surveillance tools;<ref name=\"washingtonpost.com\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-switch/wp/2018/05/22/amazon-is-selling-facial-recognition-to-law-enforcement-for-a-fistful-of-dollars/|title=Amazon is selling facial recognition to law enforcement \u2014 for a fistful of dollars|date=May 22, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> forming cloud computing partnerships with the [[CIA]];<ref name=\"vanity-fair\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2018/08/has-bezos-become-more-powerful-in-dc-than-trump|title=\"Everybody immediately knew that it was for Amazon\": Has Bezos become more powerful in DC than Trump?|first=May|last=Jeong|magazine=Vanity Fair|date=August 13, 2018|accessdate=September 14, 2018}}</ref> leading customers away from bookshops;<ref>{{cite news |title=Amazon Lure's Shoppers Away from Stores |first=Nick |last=Leiber |url=http://www.businessweek.com/smallbiz/running_small_business/archives/2011/12/amazon_turns_shops_into_showrooms_with_new_app.html |newspaper=Bloomberg BusinessWeek |date=December 7, 2011 |accessdate=December 7, 2011}}</ref> adversely impacting the environment;<ref name=Cavaillez /> placing a low priority on warehouse conditions for workers; actively opposing unionization efforts;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Matsakis |first1=Louise |title=Why Amazon Really Raised Its Minimum Wage to $15 |url=https://www.wired.com/story/why-amazon-really-raised-minimum-wage/ |work=[[Wired (magazine)|Wired]] |date=2 October 2018}}</ref> remotely deleting content purchased by Amazon Kindle users; taking public subsidies; seeking to patent its [[1-Click]] technology; engaging in anti-competitive actions and [[price discrimination]];<ref name=\":6\" /><ref name=\"baum\">{{cite news |last1=Baum |first1=Andrew |title=Amazon Wins Ruling on Results for Searches on Brands It Doesn't Sell |url=http://www.natlawreview.com/article/amazon-wins-ruling-results-searches-brands-it-doesn-t-sell |accessdate=December 21, 2015 |work=The National Law Review |publisher=Foley & Lardner |date=October 23, 2015}}</ref> and reclassifying [[LGBT]] books as adult content.<ref>{{cite web |last=Slatterly |first=Brennon |title=Amazon 'Glitch' Yanks Sales Rank of Hundreds of LGBT Books |url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/162996/amazon_glitch_yanks_sales_rank_of_hundreds_of_lgbt_books.html |work=PC World |accessdate=July 28, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Armstrong |first=Paul |title=Amazon: 'Glitch' caused gay censorship error |url=http://articles.cnn.com/2009-04-14/tech/amazon.gay.lesbian.ranking_1_online-retailer-amazon-amazon-spokeswoman-patty-smith-glitch |publisher=CNN |accessdate=July 28, 2012 |date=November 28, 2000 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116020212/http://articles.cnn.com/2009-04-14/tech/amazon.gay.lesbian.ranking_1_online-retailer-amazon-amazon-spokeswoman-patty-smith-glitch |archivedate=January 16, 2013 }}</ref> Criticism has also concerned various decisions over whether to censor or publish content such as the [[WikiLeaks]] website, works containing [[Defamation|libel]] and material facilitating [[Dog fighting|dogfight]], [[cockfight]], or [[pedophilia|pedophile]] activities. In December 2011, Amazon faced a backlash from small businesses for running a one-day deal to promote its new Price Check app. Shoppers who used the app to check prices in a brick-and-mortar store were offered a 5% discount to purchase the same item from Amazon.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2011/12/20/groupon-launches-anti-amazon-promotion-of-sorts/|title=Groupon Launches Anti-Amazon Promotion of Sorts|last=Raice|first=Shayndi|date=December 20, 2011|website=WSJ|language=en-US|access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref> Companies like [[Groupon]], [[eBay]] and Taap.it countered Amazon's promotion by offering $10 off from their products.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.internetretailer.com/commentary/2011/12/22/while-some-still-cry-others-fight-back |title=Focus on Mobile Commerce \u2013 While some still cry, others fight back |work=Internet Retailer |accessdate=February 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mobilecommercedaily.com/2011/12/20/what-can-retailers-learn-from-amazon-groupon-and-ebay |title=What can retailers learn from Amazon, Groupon and eBay? \u2013 Mobile Commerce Daily \u2013 Multichannel retail support |work=Mobile Commerce Daily |date=December 20, 2011 |accessdate=February 1, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120207203932/http://www.mobilecommercedaily.com/2011/12/20/what-can-retailers-learn-from-amazon-groupon-and-ebay |archivedate=February 7, 2012 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The company has also faced accusations of putting undue pressure on suppliers to maintain and extend its profitability. One effort to squeeze the most vulnerable book publishers was known within the company as the Gazelle Project, after Bezos suggested, according to [[Brad Stone (journalist)|Brad Stone]], \"that Amazon should approach these small publishers the way a cheetah would pursue a sickly gazelle.\"<ref name=\"New Yorker\" /> In July 2014, the [[Federal Trade Commission]] launched a lawsuit against the company alleging it was promoting in-app purchases to children, which were being transacted without parental consent.<ref>{{cite web |title=Complaint, Federal Trade Commission v. Amazon.com, Inc. |url=https://www.pacermonitor.com/view/FGNCSIQ/Federal_Trade_Commission_v_Amazoncom_Inc__wawdce-14-01038__0001.0.pdf |website=PacerMonitor |publisher=PacerMonitor |accessdate=June 16, 2016}}</ref> In 2019, Amazon banned selling [[Skin whitening|skin-lightening]] and [[Racism|racist]] products that might effect the consumer health.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/amazon-skin-lightening-products-with-high-mercury-levels/|title=Amazon pulls \"racist\" skin-lightening products|website=www.cbsnews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-24}}</ref>\n\n===Environmental impact===\nIn 2018, Amazon emitted 44.4 million metric tons of [[carbon dioxide|{{CO2}}]].<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=New York Times|date=February 17, 2020|title=Jeff Bezos commits $10 billion to address climate change|author=Karen Weise|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/17/technology/jeff-bezos-climate-change-earth-fund.html}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2019, Amazon workers organized a walk-out as part of the [[Global Climate Strike of September 2019|Global Climate Strike]].<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/09/20/tech/amazon-climate-strike-global-tech/index.html|title=Amazon workers walk out to protest climate change inaction|last=Business|first=Ahiza Garcia, CNN|website=CNN|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/recode/2019/9/20/20874497/amazon-climate-change-walkout-google-microsoft-strike-tech-activism|title=Here's why the Amazon climate walkout is a big deal|last=Ghaffary|first=Shirin|date=2019-09-20|website=Vox|language=en|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref> An internal group called Amazon Employees for Climate Justice said over 1,800 employees in 25 cities and 14 countries committed to participating in the action to protest Amazon's environmental impact and inaction to [[Global warming|climate change]].<ref name=\":4\" /> This group of workers petitioned Jeff Bezos and Amazon with three specific demands: to stop donating to politicians and [[Lobbying|lobbyists]] that [[Climate change denial|deny climate change]], to stop working with [[fossil fuel]] companies to accelerate oil and gas extraction, and to achieve zero [[carbon emissions]] by 2030.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/@amazonemployeesclimatejustice/amazon-employees-are-joining-the-global-climate-walkout-9-20-9bfa4cbb1ce3|title=Amazon employees are joining the Global Climate Walkout, 9/20|last=Amazon Employees for Climate Justice|date=2019-09-09|website=Medium|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/amazon-walkout-climate-change/|title=Amazon Employees Will Walk Out Over Climate Change Inaction|last=Matsakis|first=Louise|date=September 9, 2019|work=Wired|access-date=2020-02-06|url-status=live|language=en|issn=1059-1028}}</ref><ref name=\":5\" />\n\nAmazon has introduced the Shipment Zero program, however Shipment Zero has only committed to reducing 50% of its shipments to net zero by 2030. Also, even that 50% does not necessarily mean a decrease in emissions compared to current levels given Amazon's rate of growth in orders.<ref>[https://medium.com/@amazonemployeesclimatejustice/amazon-employees-are-joining-the-global-climate-walkout-9-20-9bfa4cbb1ce3 Amazon employees are joining the Global Climate Walkout, 9/20]</ref>\n\nThat said, Amazon's CEO has also signed the Climate Pledge, in which Amazon would meet the Paris climate agreement goals 10 year ahead of schedule, and would be carbon-neutral by 2040. Besides this pledge, it also ordered 100 000 electric delivery trucks from [[Rivian]].<ref name=autogenerated1>[https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/17/technology/jeff-bezos-climate-change-earth-fund.html Jeff Bezos commits $10 billion to address climate change]</ref>\n\nAmazon funds both climate denial groups including the [[Competitive Enterprise Institute]] and politicians denying climate change including [[Jim Inhofe]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Root|first=Tik|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/10/climate/nyt-climate-newsletter-cei.html|title=Following the Money That Undermines Climate Science|date=2019-07-10|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-02-07|last2=Friedman|first2=Lisa|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|last3=Tabuchi|first3=Hiroko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://popular.info/p/these-corporations-are-quietly-bankrolling|title=These corporations are quietly bankrolling Congress' top climate denier|last=Legum|first=Judd|website=popular.info|access-date=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2018, a community action group opposed the construction permit delivered to [[Goodman Group]] for the construction of a {{convert|160000|m2|sqft}} logisitics platform Amazon will operate at [[Lyon\u2013Saint-Exup\u00e9ry Airport]]. In February 2019, [[:fr:\u00c9tienne T\u00eate|\u00c9tienne T\u00eate]] filed a request on behalf of a second regional community action group asking the administrative court to decide whether the platform served a sufficiently important public interest to justify its environmental impact. Construction has been suspended while these matters are decided.<ref name=Cavaillez>{{cite news|newspaper=[[Le Progr\u00e8s]]|url=https://www.leprogres.fr/rhone-69-edition-lyon-metropole/2019/03/05/plateforme-logistique-amazon-bras-de-fer-dans-l-est-lyonnais|title=Plateforme logistique Amazon : bras de fer dans l'Est lyonnais|author=Jean-Philippe Cavaillez|date=March 5, 2019|page=10|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nAmazon considered making an option for Prime customers to have packages delivered at the most efficient and environmentally-friendly time (allowing the company to combine shipments with the same destination) but decided against it out of fear customers might reduce purchases.<ref name=\"day\">{{cite news |author=Matt Day |date=7 March 2020 |title=Amazon nixed \u2018green\u2019 shipping proposal to avoid alienating shoppers |url=https://www.seattletimes.com/business/amazon-nixed-green-shipping-proposal-to-avoid-alienating-shoppers/ |agency=Bloomberg}}</ref> Since 2019, the company has instead offered customer an \"Amazon Day\" option, where all orders are delivered on the same day, emphasizing customer convenience, and it occasionally offers Prime customers credits in return for selecting slower and less expensive shipping options.<ref name=\"day\" />\n\n=== Selling counterfeit items ===\nOn October 16, 2016, [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] filed a trademark infringement case against Mobile Star LLC for selling counterfeit Apple products to Amazon. In the suit, Apple provided evidence that Amazon was selling these counterfeit Apple products and advertising them as genuine. Through purchasing, Apple found that it was able to identify counterfeit products with a success rate of 90%. Amazon was sourcing and selling items without properly determining if they are genuine. Mobile Star LLC settled with Apple for an undisclosed amount on April 27, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.patentlyapple.com/patently-apple/2016/10/apple-sues-mobile-star-for-selling-counterfeit-power-adapters-and-charging-cables-through-amazon.html |title=Apple Sues Mobile Star for Selling Counterfeit Power Adapters and Charging Cables through Amazon |website=Patently Apple}}</ref>\n\n=== Sales and use taxes ===\n{{Main|Amazon tax}}\nAmazon's state sales tax collection policy has changed over the years since it did not collect any sales taxes in its early years. In the U.S., [[Sales taxes in the United States|state and local sales taxes]] are levied by state and local governments, not at the federal level. In most countries where Amazon operates, a sales tax or [[value added tax]] is uniform throughout the country, and Amazon is obliged to collect it from all customers. Proponents of forcing Amazon.com to collect sales tax\u2014at least in states where it maintains a physical presence\u2014argue the corporation wields an anticompetitive advantage over storefront businesses forced to collect sales tax.<ref name=\"Bloomberg/BusinessWeek\">{{cite web |url=http://www.businessweek.com/smallbiz/content/apr2011/sb20110428_074924.htm |title=To Help Main Street, Close the Internet Sales Tax Loophole |last=Milchen |first=Jeff |date=April 28, 2011 |accessdate=November 17, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160315102652/http://www.businessweek.com/smallbiz/content/apr2011/sb20110428_074924.htm |archivedate=March 15, 2016}}</ref>\n\nMany U.S. states in the 21st century have passed [[online shopping]] sales tax laws designed to compel Amazon.com and other [[e-commerce]] retailers to collect state and local sales taxes from its customers. Amazon.com originally collected sales tax only from five states {{as of|2011|lc=y}}, but {{as of|2017|April|lc=y}}, Amazon collects sales taxes from customers in all 45 states that have a state sales tax and in [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/3/24/15055662/amazon-us-sales-tax-collection-all-states |title=Amazon will start collecting sales tax nationwide starting April 1st |website=The Verge |accessdate=April 6, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Income taxes ===\nAmazon paid no [[Income tax in the United States|federal income taxes]] in the U.S. in 2017 and 2018, and actually received tax refunds worth millions of dollars, despite recording several billion dollars in profits each year.<ref name=\"fortune\">{{Cite web|url=http://fortune.com/2019/02/14/amazon-doesnt-pay-federal-taxes-2019/|title=Amazon Will Pay a Whopping $0 in Federal Taxes on $11.2 Billion Profits|last=Stampler|first=Laura|date=February 14, 2019|website=Fortune|language=en|access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref> [[CNN]] reported that Amazon's tax bill was zero because they took advantage of provisions in years when they were losing money that allowed them to [[Net operating loss#Loss carry back and carry forward mechanisms|offset future taxes on profits]], as well as various other tax credits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/02/15/tech/amazon-federal-income-tax/index.html|title=Despite record profits, Amazon didn't pay any federal income tax in 2017 or 2018. Here's why|last=Isidore|first=Chris|date=February 15, 2019|website=CNN|access-date=February 20, 2019}}</ref> Amazon was criticized by political figures for not paying federal income taxes.<ref>[https://www.marketwatch.com/story/amazon-riled-up-the-left-for-not-paying-federal-taxes-and-its-in-a-position-to-offset-future-profits-too-2019-02-15 Amazon riled up the left for not paying federal taxes \u2014 and it's in a position to offset future profits, too] (MarketWatch)</ref>\n\n=== Comments by Donald Trump and Bernie Sanders ===\nIn early 2018, President [[Donald Trump]] repeatedly criticized Amazon's use of the [[United States Postal Service]] and its prices for the delivery of packages, stating, \"I am right about Amazon costing the United States Post Office massive amounts of money for being their Delivery Boy,\" Trump tweeted. \"Amazon should pay these costs (plus) and not have them bourne [sic] by the American Taxpayer.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/04/03/amazon-shares-turn-negative-after-trump-bashes-company-for-a-fourth-time-in-a-week.html |title=Amazon shares turn negative after Trump bashes company for a fourth time in a week |last=Franck |first=Thomas |date=April 3, 2018 |work=CNBC|access-date=April 3, 2018}}</ref> Amazon's shares fell by 6 percent as a result of Trump's comments. [[Shepard Smith]] of [[Fox News]] disputed Trump's claims and pointed to evidence that the USPS was offering below-market prices to all customers with no advantage to Amazon. However, analyst Tom Forte pointed to the fact that Amazon's payments to the USPS are not made public and that their contract has a reputation for being \"a sweetheart deal\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-amazon-com-trump/amazon-shares-fall-6-percent-as-trump-renews-attack-idUSKCN1H9185 |title=Amazon shares fall 6 percent as Trump renews attack |last=Editorial |first=Reuters |work=U.S.|access-date=April 3, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://thehill.com/homenews/media/381542-foxs-shep-smith-fact-checks-trumps-amazon-claims-none-of-that-was-true |title=Fox's Shep Smith fact-checks Trump's Amazon claims: 'None of that was true' |last=Manchester |first=Julia |work=The Hill|access-date=April 3, 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nThroughout the summer of 2018, Vermont Senator [[Bernie Sanders]] criticized Amazon's wages and working conditions in a series of [[YouTube]] videos and media appearances. He also pointed to the fact that Amazon had paid no federal income tax in the previous year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.inlander.com/spokane/workers-describe-pressures-at-amazon-warehouses-as-sen-bernie-sanders-gears-up-to-make-the-corporation-pay/Content?oid=12226281|title=Workers describe pressures at Amazon warehouses as Bernie Sanders gears up to make the corporation pay|first=Samantha|last=Wohlfeil|publisher=Inlander|date=September 6, 2018|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> Sanders solicited stories from Amazon warehouse workers who felt exploited by the company.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/truth-about-amazon-food-stamps-tax-breaks/|title=Bernie Sanders and the Truth About Amazon, Food Stamps, and Tax Breaks|last=Matsakis|first=Louise|date=September 6, 2018|work=Wired|access-date=February 20, 2019|issn=1059-1028}}</ref> One such story, by [[James Bloodworth (journalist)|James Bloodworth]], described the environment as akin to \"a low-security prison\" and stated that the company's culture used an Orwellian [[newspeak]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2018/sep/17/amazon-warehouse-bernie-sanders|title=I worked in an Amazon warehouse. Bernie Sanders is right to target them|first=James|last=Bloodworth|newspaper=The Guardian|date=September 17, 2018|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> These reports cited a finding by New Food Economy that one third of fulfilment center workers in Arizona were on the [[Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program]] (SNAP).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/9/5/17819450/bernie-sanders-stop-bezos-amazon-worker-pay-corporate-welfare-tax-bill|title=Bernie Sanders introduces \"Stop BEZOS\" bill to tax Amazon for underpaying workers|first=Adi|last=Robertson|website=The Verge|date=September 5, 2018|accessdate=September 14, 2018}}</ref> Responses by Amazon included incentives for employees to tweet positive stories and a statement which called the salary figures used by Sanders \"inaccurate and misleading\". The statement also charged that it was inappropriate for him to refer to SNAP as \"food stamps\".<ref name=\":2\" /> On September 5, 2018, Sanders along with [[Ro Khanna]] introduced the Stop Bad Employers by Zeroing Out Subsidies (Stop [[Jeff Bezos|BEZOS]]) Act aimed at Amazon and other alleged beneficiaries of [[corporate welfare]] such as [[Walmart]], [[McDonald's]] and [[Uber]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/bernie-sanders-amazon-walmart-with-100-tax/|title=Bernie Sanders targets Amazon, Walmart with 100% tax|first=Kate|last=Gibson|publisher=CBS|date=September 5, 2018|accessdate=September 14, 2018}}</ref> Among the bill's supporters were [[Tucker Carlson]] of [[Fox News]] and [[Matt Taibbi]] who criticized himself and other journalists for not covering Amazon's contribution to wealth inequality earlier.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/tucker-carlson-bernie-sanders-food-stamps_us_5b895651e4b0511db3d7aa34|title=Why Bernie Sanders and Tucker Carlson agree on food stamps|first=Arthur|last=Delaney|work=The Huffington Post|date=August 31, 2018|accessdate=September 14, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/politics-news/bernie-sanders-amazon-bezos-725282/|title=Bernie Sanders' Anti-Amazon Bill is an Indictment of the Media, Too|first=Matt|last=Taibbi|magazine=Rolling Stone|date=September 18, 2018|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn October 2, Amazon announced that its minimum wage for all American employees would be raised to $15 per hour. Sanders congratulated the company for making this decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/10/2/17927478/amazon-minimum-wage-15-dollars-increase-bernie-sanders|title=Amazon raises minimum wage to $15 for all 350,000 US workers following criticism|first=Jon|last=Porter|website=The Verge|date=October 2, 2018|accessdate=October 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Working conditions ===\nFormer employees, current employees, the media, and politicians have criticized Amazon for poor working conditions at the company.<ref name=\"linkedin\">[https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/amazonians-response-inside-amazon-wrestling-big-ideas-nick-ciubotariu An Amazonian's response to \"Inside Amazon: Wrestling Big Ideas in a Bruising Workplace\"] August 16, 2015</ref><ref>[http://www.recruiter.co.uk/news/2013/08/amazon-under-fire-for-staffing-practices-in-randstad-contract/ Amazon under fire for staffing practices in Randstad contract|Business intelligence for recruitment and resourcing professionals] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130804221109/http://www.recruiter.co.uk/news/2013/08/amazon-under-fire-for-staffing-practices-in-randstad-contract/ |date=August 4, 2013}}. Recruiter.co.uk (August 2, 2013). Retrieved on August 16, 2013.</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/brutal-conditions-in-amazons-warehouses-2013-8 |title=Brutal Conditions In Amazon's Warehouse's Threaten To Ruin The Company's Image |first=Jim |last=Edwards |date=August 5, 2013 |work=[[Business Insider]] |accessdate=February 24, 2014}}</ref> In 2011, it was publicized that workers had to carry out tasks in {{convert|100|\u00b0F|\u00b0C}} heat  at the [[Breinigsville, Pennsylvania]] warehouse. As a result of these inhumane conditions, employees became extremely uncomfortable and suffered from dehydration and [[Collapse (medical)|collapse]]. Loading-bay doors were not opened to allow in fresh air because of concerns over theft.<ref name=\"AllentownMorningCall1\">{{cite news |last1=Soper |first1=Spencer |title=Inside Amazon's Warehouse |url=http://www.mcall.com/news/local/amazon/mc-allentown-amazon-complaints-20110917-story.html |accessdate=March 15, 2018 |work=[[The Morning Call]] |date=September 18, 2011}}</ref> Amazon's initial response was to pay for an ambulance to sit outside on call to cart away overheated employees.<ref name=\"AllentownMorningCall1\" /> The company eventually installed air conditioning at the warehouse.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Soper |first1=Spencer |last2=Kraus |first2=Scott |title=Amazon gets heat over warehouse |url=http://www.mcall.com/news/local/amazon/mc-allentown-amazon-folo-20110917-story.html |accessdate=March 15, 2018 |work=[[The Morning Call|Morning Call]] |date=September 25, 2011}}</ref>\n\nSome workers, \"pickers\", who travel the building with a trolley and a handheld scanner \"picking\" customer orders can walk up to 15 miles during their workday and if they fall behind on their targets, they can be reprimanded. The handheld scanners give real-time information to the employee on how quickly or slowly they are working; the scanners also serve to allow Team Leads and Area Managers to track the specific locations of employees and how much \"idle time\" they gain when not working.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/amazon-warehouse-rules-2011-9 |last1=Yarrow |first1=Jay |last2=Kovach |first2=Steve |title=10 Crazy Rules That Could Get You Fired From Amazon Warehouses |accessdate=April 21, 2013 |date=September 20, 2011 |work=Business Insider}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/2/ed6a985c-70bd-11e2-85d0-00144feab49a.html |title=Amazon unpacked |last1=O'Connor |first1=Sarah |accessdate=April 21, 2013 |date=February 8, 2013 |work=Financial Times}}</ref>\n\nIn a German television report broadcast in February 2013, journalists Diana L\u00f6bl and Peter Onneken conducted a covert investigation at the distribution center of Amazon in the town of [[Bad Hersfeld]] in the German state of [[Hessen]]. The report highlights the behavior of some of the security guards, themselves being employed by a third party company, who apparently either had a [[Neo-Nazism|neo-Nazi]] background or deliberately dressed in neo-Nazi apparel and who were intimidating foreign and temporary female workers at its distribution centers. The third party security company involved was delisted by Amazon as a business contact shortly after that report.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tagesschau.de/inland/amazon136.html |title=Kritik an Arbeitsbedingungen bei Amazon |publisher=tagesschau.de |date= |accessdate=February 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.daserste.de/information/reportage-dokumentation/dokus/sendung/hr/13022013-ausgeliefert-leiharbeiter-bei-amazon-100.html |title=Ausgeliefert! Leiharbeiter ... \u2013 Ausgeliefert! Leiharbeiter bei Amazon \u2013 Reportage & Documentation \u2013 ARD &#124; Das Erste |publisher=Daserste.de |date=February 13, 2013 |accessdate=February 20, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130218013257/http://www.daserste.de/information/reportage-dokumentation/dokus/sendung/hr/13022013-ausgeliefert-leiharbeiter-bei-amazon-100.html |archivedate=February 18, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Tony |last=Paterson |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/amazon-used-neonazi-guards-to-keep-immigrant-workforce-under-control-in-germany-8495843.html |title=Amazon 'used neo-Nazi guards to keep immigrant workforce under control' in Germany \u2013 Europe \u2013 World |work=The Independent |date=February 14, 2013 |accessdate=February 20, 2013 |location=London}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Amazon to investigate reports temporary staff in Germany were mistreated |url=http://globalnews.ca/news/392864/amazon-to-investigate-reports-temporary-staff-in-germany-were-mistreated/ |accessdate=July 14, 2015 |first= |last= |website=Globalnews.ca}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2015, it was reported in ''[[The Verge]]'' that Amazon will be removing [[non-compete clause]]s of 18 months in length from its US employment contracts for hourly-paid workers, after criticism that it was acting unreasonably in preventing such employees from finding other work. Even short-term temporary workers have to sign contracts that prohibit them from working at any company where they would \"directly or indirectly\" support any good or service that competes with those they helped support at Amazon, for 18 months after leaving Amazon, even if they are fired or made redundant.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Woodman |first1=Spencer |title=Exclusive: Amazon makes even temporary warehouse workers sign 18-month non-competes |url=https://www.theverge.com/2015/3/26/8280309/amazon-warehouse-jobs-exclusive-noncompete-contracts |accessdate=March 28, 2015 |work=The Verge |date=March 26, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Kasperkevic |first1=Jana |title=Amazon to remove non-compete clause from contracts for hourly workers |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/mar/27/amazon-remove-noncompete-clause-contracts-hourly-workers |accessdate=March 28, 2015 |work=The Guardian |date=March 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\nA 2015 front-page article in ''[[The New York Times]]'' profiled several former Amazon employees<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/16/technology/inside-amazon-wrestling-big-ideas-in-a-bruising-workplace.html|title=Inside Amazon: Wrestling Big Ideas in a Bruising Workplace|last=Kantor|first=Jodi|date=August 15, 2015|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 20, 2019|last2=Streitfeld|first2=David|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> who together described a \"bruising\" workplace culture in which workers with illness or other personal crises were pushed out or unfairly evaluated.<ref name=\":3\" /> Bezos responded by writing a Sunday memo to employees,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.geekwire.com/2015/full-memo-jeff-bezos-responds-to-cutting-nyt-expose-says-tolerance-for-lack-of-empathy-needs-to-be-zero/ |title=Full memo: Jeff Bezos responds to brutal NYT story, says it doesn't represent the Amazon he leads |last=Cook |first=John |date=November 8, 2017 |work=GeekWire|access-date=April 3, 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=|language=en-US}}</ref> in which he disputed the ''Times''{{'}}s account of \"shockingly callous management practices\" that he said would never be tolerated at the company.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/18/technology/amazon-bezos-workplace-management-practices.html|title=Jeff Bezos and Amazon Employees Join Debate Over Its Culture|last=Streitfeld|first=David|date=August 17, 2015|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 20, 2019|last2=Kantor|first2=Jodi|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nIn an effort to boost employee morale, on November 2, 2015, Amazon announced that it would be extending six weeks of paid leave for new mothers and fathers. This change includes birth parents and adoptive parents and can be applied in conjunction with existing maternity leave and medical leave for new mothers.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Amazon increases paid leave for new parents |url=http://www.seattletimes.com/business/technology/amazon-increases-paid-leave-for-new-parents/ |website=The Seattle Times |date=November 2, 2015 |accessdate=November 13, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn mid-2018, investigations by journalists and media outlets such as ''[[The Guardian]]'' reported poor working conditions at Amazon's fulfillment centers.<ref>{{cite news |last=Picchi |first=Aimee |date=April 19, 2018 |title=Inside an Amazon warehouse: \"Treating human beings as robots\"|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/inside-an-amazon-warehouse-treating-human-beings-as-robots/|work=[[CBS MoneyWatch]]|location= |access-date=September 22, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last= Sainato|first=Michael|date=July 30, 2018 |title=Accidents at Amazon: workers left to suffer after warehouse injuries|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2018/jul/30/accidents-at-amazon-workers-left-to-suffer-after-warehouse-injuries|work=The Guardian |location= |access-date=September 22, 2018 }}</ref> Later in 2018, another article exposed poor working conditions for Amazon's delivery drivers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/amazon-delivery-drivers-reveal-claims-of-disturbing-work-conditions-2018-8 |title=Missing wages, grueling shifts, and bottles of urine: The disturbing accounts of Amazon delivery drivers may reveal the true human cost of 'free' shipping |first=Hayley |last=Peterson |date=September 11, 2018 |website= www.businessinsider.com}}</ref>\n\nIn response to criticism that Amazon does not pay its workers a livable wage, Jeff Bezos announced beginning November 1, 2018, all US and UK Amazon employees will earn a $15 an hour minimum wage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/amazon-raise-companys-minimum-wage-15-employees/story?id=58225644|title=Amazon to raise wages for more than 350,000 employees|date=October 2, 2018|website=ABC News|accessdate=January 3, 2019}}</ref> Amazon will also lobby to make $15 an hour the federal [[minimum wage]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2018/oct/02/amazon-raises-minimum-wage-us-uk-employees|title=Amazon raises minimum wage for US and UK employees|first=Richard|last=Partington|date=October 2, 2018|accessdate=January 3, 2019|website=Theguardian.com}}</ref> At the same time, Amazon also eliminated stock awards and bonuses for hourly employees.<ref>{{cite news |last=Soper |first=Spencer |date=October 3, 2018 |title=Amazon Warehouse Workers Lose Bonuses, Stock Awards for Raises|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-10-03/amazon-eliminating-bonuses-stock-awards-to-help-pay-for-raises|website=Bloomberg.com |location= |access-date=October 4, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nOn [[Black Friday (shopping)|Black Friday]] 2018, Amazon warehouse workers in several European countries, including Italy, Germany, Spain and the United Kingdom, went on strike to protest inhumane working conditions and low pay.<ref>{{cite news |last= Hamilton|first=Isobel Asher|date=November 23, 2018 |title='We are not robots': Thousands of Amazon workers across Europe are striking on Black Friday over warehouse working conditions|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/black-friday-amazon-workers-protest-poor-working-conditions-2018-11|work=[[Business Insider]] |location= |access-date=November 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Daily Beast]]'' reported in March 2019 that emergency services responded to 189 calls from 46 Amazon warehouses in 17 states between the years 2013 and 2018, all relating to suicidal employees. The workers attributed their mental breakdowns to employer-imposed social isolation, aggressive surveillance, and the hurried and dangerous working conditions at these fulfillment centers. One former employee told ''The Daily Beast'' \"It's this isolating colony of hell where people having breakdowns is a regular occurrence.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Zahn|first1=Max |last2=Paget|first2=Sharif |date=March 11, 2019 |title='Colony of Hell': 911 Calls From Inside Amazon Warehouses|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/amazon-the-shocking-911-calls-from-inside-its-warehouses|work=[[The Daily Beast]]|location= |access-date=March 13, 2019 }}</ref>\n\nOn July 15, 2019, during the onset of Amazon's \"Prime Day\" sale event, Amazon employees working in the United States and Germany went on strike in protest of unfair wages and poor working conditions.<ref>{{cite news |last= Chen|first=Michelle|date=July 16, 2019|title=Amazon Prime Day deals aren't worth the moral cost of exploiting their workers|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/think/opinion/amazon-prime-day-deals-aren-t-worth-moral-cost-exploiting-ncna1030361|work=[[NBC News]] |location= |access-date=July 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/07/15/business/german-amazon-workers-strike-prime-day-scli-intl/index.html|title=Amazon workers go on strike in Germany as Prime Day begins|last=Business|first=Amy Woodyatt and Barbara Wojazer, CNN|website=CNN|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, during the coronavirus outbreak when the government instructed companies to restrict social contact, Amazon's UK staff was forced to work overtime to meet the demand spiked by the disease. A [[GMB (trade union)]] spokesperson said the company had put \"profit before safety\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Jones|first=Lora|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-51921916|title=Amazon staff told to work overtime as virus hits|date=2020-03-17|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-17|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n=== Conflict of interest with the CIA and DOD ===\nIn 2013, Amazon secured a {{USD|600 million}} contract with the [[CIA]], which poses a potential [[conflict of interest]] involving the Bezos-owned ''[[The Washington Post]]'' and his newspaper's coverage of the CIA.<ref>\"[https://www.huffingtonpost.com/norman-solomon/the-cia-amazon-bezos-and_b_4559317.html The CIA, Amazon, Bezos and the Washington Post : An Exchange with Executive Editor Martin Baron]\". ''The Huffington Post''. January 8, 2014.</ref> Kate Martin, director of the Center for National Security Studies, said, \"It's a serious potential conflict of interest for a major newspaper like ''The Washington Post'' to have a contractual relationship with the government and the most secret part of the government.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/08/18/business/expecting-the-unexpected-from-jeff-bezos.html|title=Expecting the Unexpected From Jeff Bezos|last=Streitfeld|first=David|date=August 17, 2013|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 20, 2019|last2=Haughney|first2=Christine|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> This was later followed by a {{USD|10 billion}} contract with the Department of Defense.<ref name=\"vanity-fair\" />\n\n=== Seattle head tax and houselessness services ===\nIn May 2018, Amazon threatened the [[Seattle City Council]] over an [[Seattle head tax|employee head tax proposal]] that would have funded houselessness services and low-income housing. The tax would have cost Amazon about $800 per employee, or 0.7% of their average salary.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.seattletimes.com/business/amazon/amazon-pauses-plans-for-seattle-office-towers-while-city-council-considers-business-tax/|title=Amazon puts high-profile Seattle plans on ice over proposal to tax large employers|date=May 2, 2018|work=The Seattle Times|access-date=May 3, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> In retaliation, Amazon paused construction on a new building, threatened to limit further investment in the city, and funded a repeal campaign. Although originally passed, the measure was soon repealed after an expensive repeal campaign spearheaded by Amazon.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://seattletimes.com/seattle-news/politics/business-backed-opponents-of-seattle-head-tax-outspent-supporters-2-to-1/|title='Show of force': Business-backed opponents of Seattle head tax outspent supporters 2 to 1|date=July 13, 2018|work=The Seattle Times|access-date=July 17, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n===Nashville Operations Center of Excellence===\nThe incentives given by the [[Metropolitan Council of Nashville and Davidson County]] to Amazon for their new Operations Center of Excellence in [[Nashville Yards]], a site owned by developer [[Southwest Value Partners]], have been controversial, including the decision by the Tennessee Department of Economic and Community Development to keep the full extent of the agreement secret.<ref name=\"tenneseanwantstokeepits\">{{cite news |last1=Reicher |first1=Mike |title=Tennessee wants to keep its incentives offer for Amazon's HQ2 secret for 5 years |url=https://tennessean.com/story/news/2019/01/04/tennessee-amazon-incentives-kept-secret-five-years-public-records-original-pitch/2482548002/ |accessdate=January 6, 2019 |work=The Tennessean |date=January 4, 2019}}</ref> The incentives include \"$102 million in combined grants and tax credits for a scaled-down Amazon office building\" as well as \"a $65 million cash grant for capital expenditures\" in exchange for the creation of 5,000 jobs over seven years.<ref name=\"tenneseanwantstokeepits\"/>\n\nThe Tennessee Coalition for Open Government called for more transparency.<ref name=\"tenneseanwantstokeepits\"/> Another local organization known as the People's Alliance for Transit, Housing, and Employment (PATHE) suggested no public money should be given to Amazon; instead, it should be spent on building more public housing for the working poor and the homeless and investing in more public transportation for Nashvillians.<ref name=\"tntribunewillamazonbe\">{{cite news |last1=White |first1=Peter |title=Will Amazon be Naughty or Nice? |url=https://tntribune.com/community/local/nashville/will-amazon-be-naughty-or-nice/ |accessdate=December 21, 2018 |work=Tennessee Tribune |date=December 13, 2018|quote=PATHE does not want Metro to give Amazon a dime. They want the city to build at least 5,000 more affordable homes to address the \"Amazon effect\" on the local housing market. And they want a new transit referendum that focuses on the needs of working people and better public bus service.}}</ref> Others suggested incentives to big corporations do not improve the local economy.<ref name=\"tennesseandidtennesseetaxpayers\">{{cite news |last1=Mazza |first1=Sandy |title=Did Tennessee taxpayers get a good deal with $102M Amazon payment? |url=https://tennessean.com/story/money/2018/11/19/critics-worry-amazon-incentives-drain-community-services/1989884002/ |accessdate=February 11, 2019 |work=The Tennessean |date=November 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2018, the proposal to give Amazon $15 million in incentives was criticized by the Nashville Firefighters Union and the Nashville chapter of the [[Fraternal Order of Police]],<ref name=\"newschannel5feelleftbehind\">{{cite news |last1=Koehn |first1=Alexandra |title=Metro employees feel 'left behind' after no pay raise |url=https://www.newschannel5.com/news/metro-employees-feel-left-behind-after-no-pay-raise |accessdate=December 12, 2018 |work=News Channel 5 |date=November 29, 2018}}</ref> who called it \"[[corporate welfare]].\"<ref name=\"apnewsnashvillepoliceunion\">{{cite news |title=Nashville police union: Amazon getting 'corporate welfare' |url=https://www.apnews.com/0a82b2c4d5ed4095b9bd4a1544f4615a |accessdate=February 10, 2019 |work=AP News |date=November 30, 2018}}</ref> In February 2019, another $15.2 million in infrastructure was approved by the council, although it was voted down by three council members, including Councilwoman Angie Henderson who dismissed it as \"[[cronyism]]\".<ref name=\"tennesseancouncilapproves\">{{cite news |last1=Garrison |first1=Joey |title=Nashville council approves $15M in infrastructure work for future home of Amazon hub |url=https://tennessean.com/story/news/2019/02/06/nashville-approves-15-m-infrastructure-future-home-amazon-hub/2777894002/ |accessdate=February 10, 2019 |work=The Tennessean |date=February 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Facial recognition technology and law enforcement ===\nWhile Amazon has publicly opposed secret government surveillance, as revealed by Freedom of Information Act requests it has supplied [[facial recognition system|facial recognition]] support to law enforcement in the form of the [[Amazon Rekognition|Rekognition]] technology and consulting services. Initial testing included the city of [[Orlando, Florida]], and [[Washington County, Oregon]]. Amazon offered to connect Washington County with other Amazon government customers interested in Rekognition and a body camera manufacturer. These ventures are opposed by a coalition of civil rights groups with concern that they could lead to an expansion of surveillance and be prone to abuse. Specifically, it could automate the identification and tracking of anyone, particularly in the context of potential police body camera integration.<ref name=\"washingtonpost.com\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/opinion/yes-amazon-is-tracking-people-and-sending-their-data-to-police|title=Yes, Amazon is tracking people|website=Washingtonexaminer.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.aclu.org/blog/privacy-technology/surveillance-technologies/amazon-teams-government-deploy-dangerous-new|title=Amazon Teams Up With Government to Deploy Dangerous New Facial Recognition Technology|website=Aclu.org}}</ref> Because of the backlash, the city of [[Orlando, Florida|Orlando]] publicly stated it will no longer use the technology, but may revisit this decision at a later date.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newsweek.com/orlando-stops-using-amazons-facial-recognition-tech-996057|title=Orlando Stops Using Amazon's Face-Scanning Tech Amid Spying Concerns|website=Newsweek.com|date=June 26, 2018|language=en-USA}}</ref>\n\n=== Access to NHS data ===\nThe UK government awarded Amazon a contract that gives the company free access to healthcare information collected by the UK's National Health Service<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://privacyinternational.org/long-read/3298/alexa-what-hidden-behind-your-contract-nhs|title=Alexa, what is hidden behind your contract with the NHS?|last=|first=|date=6 December 2020|website=Privacy International|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=24 January 2020}}</ref>. This will let people have their medical questions answered by Amazon's Alexa. The material, which excludes patient data, could also allow the company to make, advertise and sell its own products. The contract allows Amazon access to information on symptoms, causes and definitions of conditions, and \"all related copyrightable content and data and other materials\". Amazon can then create \"new products, applications, cloud-based services and/or distributed software\", which the NHS will not benefit from financially. The company can also share the information with third parties. The government said that allowing Alexa devices to offer expert health advice to users will reduce pressure on doctors and pharmacists<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2019/dec/08/nhs-gives-amazon-free-use-of-health-data-under-alexa-advice-deal|title=NHS gives Amazon free use of health data under Alexa advice deal|last=|first=|date=8 December 2019|website=The Guardian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=24 January 2020}}</ref>.\n\n=== Collection of data and surveillance===\nOn February 17, 2020, a Panorama documentary highlighted the amount of data collected by the company and the move into surveillance causing concerns of politicians and regulators in the US and Europe.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/m000fjdz/panorama-amazon-what-they-know-about-us BBC iPlayer - Panorama - Amazon: What They Know About Us<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> <ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/extra/CLQYZENMBI/amazon-data Amazon: How Bezos built his data machine<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n== Response to Covid-19 pandemic ==\n\n=== Additional hiring as a result of pandemic ===\nIn response to the COVID-19 pandemic, Amazon introduced temporary restrictions on the sale of non-essential goods. In March 2020, it hired some 100,000 more staff in the US to help deal with essential items such as food and medical equipment. It also reported that it was so busy that it was unable to bring on board new customers and therefore had to have a waiting list. In April, the firm announced that it was going to hire up to 75,000 workers to help deal with inreased demand.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-52276149|title=Amazon hiring spree as orders surge under lockdown|date=2020-04-14|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-04-14|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n=== Employee protests during Covid-19 ===\n\nDuring the outbreak of the [[Coronavirus pandemic]] (COVID-19) there have been protests by the Amazon workers at warehouses in the US, France, and Italy. The BBC reported that there were confirmed  coronavirus cases in more than 50 locations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-52276149|title=Amazon hiring spree as orders surge under lockdown|date=2020-04-14|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-04-14|language=en-GB}}</ref> The reason for the protests is the company policy to \"run normal shifts\" despite many positive cases of the virus.<ref name=FTMarch19/> According to the [[UNI Global Union]], \"Amazon cannot act like this is business as usual. We are facing a deadly virus that has already taken the lives of thousands of people and paralyzed the world's economy. If distribution centers are not safe for workers right now, they should be closed immediately.\"<ref name=FTMarch19>{{cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/08395e49-0bb1-4f49-a6f5-c6639ce3d719|title= Amazon workers protest over normal shifts despite Covid-19 cases|work=[[Financial Times]]|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref> In Spain, the company has faced legal complaints over its policies.<ref name=BBCMarch31/> Despite workers at 19 warehouses in the US having tested positive for COVID-19, Amazon did not shut down warehouses, only doing so when forced by the government or because of protests. A group of US Senators wrote an open letter to Bezos in March 2020, expressing concerns about worker safety.<ref name=TheVergeMarch31/>\n\nAn Amazon warehouse protest on March 30, 2020 in [[Staten Island]] led to its organizer, Christian Smalls, being fired. Amazon defended the decision by saying that Smalls was supposed to be in self-isolation at the time and leading the protest put its other workers at risk.<ref name=BBCMarch31/> Smalls has called this response \"ridiculous\".<ref name=CommonDreamsMarch31/> The New York state attorney general, [[Letitia James]], is considering legal retaliation to the firing which she called \"immoral and inhumane.\"<ref name=BBCMarch31>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-52096273|title=Amazon workers strike over virus protection|date=2020-03-31|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-31|language=en-GB}}</ref> She also asked the [[National Labor Relations Board]] to investigate Smalls' firing. Smalls himself accuses the company of retaliating against him for organizing a protest.<ref name=CommonDreamsMarch31>{{Cite web|url=https://www.commondreams.org/news/2020/03/31/new-york-ag-denounces-immoral-and-inhumane-firing-amazon-worker-who-led-protest-over|title=New York AG Denounces 'Immoral and Inhumane' Firing of Amazon Worker Who Led Protest Over Lack of Coronavirus Protections|website=Common Dreams|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> At the Staten Island warehouse, one case of COVID-19 has been confirmed by Amazon; workers believe there are more, and say that the company has not cleaned the building, given them suitable protection, or informed them of potential cases.<ref name=TheVergeMarch31>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/30/21199942/amazon-warehouse-coronavirus-covid-new-york-protest-walkout|title=Amazon warehouse workers walk out in rising tide of COVID-19 protests|last=Dzieza|first=Josh|date=2020-03-30|website=The Verge|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> Smalls added specifically that there are many workers there in risk categories, and the protest only demanded that the building be sanitized and the employees continue to be paid during that process.<ref name=CommonDreamsMarch31/> Derrick Palmer, another worker at the Staten Island facility, told ''[[The Verge]]'' that Amazon quickly communicates through text and email when they need the staff to complete mandatory overtime, but have not been using this to tell people when a colleague has contracted the disease, instead waiting days and sending managers to speak to employees in person.<ref name=TheVergeMarch31/> Amazon claim that the Staten Island protest only attracted 15 of the facility's 5,000 workers,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/amazon-workers-in-staten-island-protest-coronavirus-working-conditions/|title=Amazon fires warehouse worker who organized Staten Island protest|last=Rubin|first=Ben Fox|website=CNET|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> while other sources describe much larger crowds.<ref name=TheVergeMarch31/>\n\nOn April 14, 2020, two Amazon employees were fired for \"repeatedly violating internal policies\", after they had circulated a petition about health risks for warehouse workers internally <ref>{{cite web |last1=Paul |first1=Kari |title=Amazon fires two employees who condemned treatment of warehouse workers |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/apr/14/amazon-workers-fired-coronavirus-emily-cunningham-maren-costa |website=the Guardian |accessdate=15 April 2020 |language=en |date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Closure in France ===\n\nThe [[Solidaires Unitaires D\u00e9mocratiques|SUD]] (trade unions) brought a court case against Amazon for unsafe working conditions. This resulted in a French district court ([[Nanterre]]) ruling on April 15, 2020 ordering the company to limit its deliveries to food and essential medical or hygienic products or pay a \u20ac1 million  per day fine.  Amazon said it would appeal, and on the following day shut its six French warehouses until at least April 21, 2020 for evaluation of the situation.<ref>{{cite news|newspaper=Le Figaro|language=fr|date=April 16, 2020|url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-eco/amazon-menace-de-suspendre-l-activite-de-ses-centres-en-france-20200415|title=Amazon ferme ses entrep\u00f4ts pour cinq jours en France|author=Olivia D\u00e9troyat}}</ref>\n\n== Lobbying ==\nAmazon lobbies the United States federal government and state governments on issues such as the enforcement of sales taxes on online sales, transportation safety, privacy and [[Information privacy|data protection]] and intellectual property. According to regulatory filings, Amazon.com focuses its lobbying on the [[United States Congress]], the [[Federal Communications Commission]] and the [[Federal Reserve System|Federal Reserve]]. Amazon.com spent roughly $3.5 million, $5 million and $9.5 million on lobbying, in 2013, 2014 and 2015, respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=Amazon's Lobbying Expenditures |url=https://www.opensecrets.org/lobby/clientsum.php?id=D000023883|website=Opensecrets.org}}</ref>\n\nAmazon.com was a corporate member of the [[American Legislative Exchange Council]] (ALEC) until it dropped membership following protests at its shareholders' meeting on May 24, 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/news/2012/05/24/amazon-shareholders-met-by-protesters.html |first=Emily |last=Parkhurst |title=Amazon shareholders met by protesters, company cuts ties with ALEC|website=Bizjournals.com |date=May 24, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Amazon expanded its lobbying practices as it prepared to lobby the [[Federal Aviation Administration]] to approve its drone delivery program, hiring the [[Akin Gump Strauss Hauer & Feld]] lobbying firm in June.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Romm |first1=Tony |title=In Amazon's shopping cart: D.C. influence |url=http://www.politico.com/story/2014/08/amazon-dc-influence-109776.html |website=Politico.com |publisher=Politico |accessdate=August 7, 2014}}</ref> Amazon and its lobbyists have visited with Federal Aviation Administration officials and aviation committees in Washington, D.C. to explain its plans to deliver packages.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/12/28/technology/faa-drone-laws-start-to-clash-with-stricter-local-rules.html|title=F.A.A. Drone Laws Start to Clash With Stricter Local Rules|last=Kang|first=Cecilia|date=December 27, 2015|work=The New York Times|access-date=February 20, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019 it\u00a0spent $16.8m and had a team of 104 lobbyists, up from $14.4m and 103 lobbyists in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.opensecrets.org/federal-lobbying/clients/summary?cycle=2019&id=D000023883|title=Client Profile: Amazon.com|last=|first=|date=|website=Centre for Responsive Politics|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Internet|Companies}}\n* [[Amazon Breakthrough Novel Award]]\n* [[Amazon Flexible Payments Service]]\n* [[Amazon Marketplace]]\n* [[Amazon Standard Identification Number]] (ASIN)\n* [[Camelcamelcamel]] \u2013 a website that tracks the prices of products sold on Amazon.com\n* [[List of book distributors]]\n* [[Carbon_tax#Internal_price_on_carbon|Internal carbon pricing]]\n* [[Statistically improbable phrases]] \u2013 Amazon.com's phrase extraction technique for indexing books\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |url=http://us.penguingroup.com/nf/Book/BookDisplay/0,,9781591843757,00.html |title=One Click: Jeff Bezos and the Rise of Amazon.com |last=Brandt |first=Richard L. |publisher=Portfolio Penguin |year=2011 |isbn=978-1-59184-375-7 |location=New York |accessdate=}}\n* {{cite book |title=21 Dog Years |last=Daisey |first=Mike |publisher=Free Press |year=2002 |isbn=0-7432-2580-5 |authorlink=Mike Daisey |url=https://archive.org/details/21dogyearsdoingt00dais }}\n* {{cite book |title=Amazon.com for Dummies |last=Friedman |first=Mara |publisher=Wiley Publishing |year=2004 |isbn=0-7645-5840-4 |url=https://archive.org/details/amazoncomfordumm00frie }}\n* {{cite book |title=Amazonia: Five Years at the Epicenter of the Dot.Com Juggernaut |last=Marcus |first=James |publisher=W. W. Norton |year=2004 |isbn=1-56584-870-5 |url=https://archive.org/details/amazonia00marc }}\n* {{cite book |title=Amazon.com \u2013 Get Big Fast: Inside the Revolutionary Business Model That Changed the World |last=Spector |first=Robert |publisher=HarperCollins |year=2000 |isbn=0-06-662041-4 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/amazoncomgetbigf00spec }}\n* {{cite book |title=The Everything Store: Jeff Bezos and the Age of Amazon |last=Stone |first=Brad |publisher=Little Brown and Co |year=2013 |isbn=978-0-316-21926-6 |location=New York |oclc=856249407 |authorlink=Brad Stone (journalist)|title-link=The Everything Store: Jeff Bezos and the Age of Amazon }}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Amazon.com}}\n* {{official website}}\n* {{OpenCorp|Amazon}}\n{{Finance links\n|name=Amazon.com, Inc.\n|symbol=AMZN\n|sec_cik=1018724\n|bloomberg= AMZN:US\n|yahoo = AMZN\n|google = AMZN\n}}\n\n{{Amazon|state=expanded}}\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{NASDAQ-100}}\n{{Seattle Corporations}}\n{{ebooks}}\n{{Music industry}}\n{{Major mobile device companies}}\n{{Major Internet companies}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Amazon (company)| ]]\n[[Category:1994 establishments in Washington (state)]]\n[[Category:3D publishing]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 1994]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) software]]\n[[Category:Arts and crafts retailers]]\n[[Category:Bookstores of the United States]]\n[[Category:Cloud computing providers]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on NASDAQ]]\n[[Category:E-book suppliers]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 1994]]\n[[Category:IOS software]]\n[[Category:Mobile phone manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Multinational companies headquartered in the United States]]\n[[Category:Online music stores of the United States]]\n[[Category:Online retailers of the United States]]\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1994]]\n[[Category:Self-publishing companies]]\n[[Category:Software companies based in Seattle]]\n[[Category:Software companies established in 1994]]\n[[Category:Technology companies established in 1994]]\n[[Category:TvOS software]]\n[[Category:Universal Windows Platform apps]]\n[[Category:Webby Award winners]]\n[[Category:Logistics companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:Software companies of the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Lovemankind83", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_(company)"}
{"title_page": "1755 Lisbon earthquake", "text_new": "{{Use American English|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{short description|Catastrophic earthquake that primarily affected Lisbon, Kingdom of Portugal}}\n{{Earthquake\n| title = 1755 Lisbon earthquake\n| pre-1900 = yes\n| map =1755_Lisbon_Earthquake_Location.png\n| local-date = {{start-date|1 November 1755|1 November 1755}}\n| local-time = 09:40\n| magnitude = 8.5\u20139.0 [[Moment magnitude scale|M<sub>w</sub>]] (est.)\n| depth =\n| countries affected = [[Kingdom of Portugal|Portugal]], [[Enlightenment in Spain|Spain]], and [[Morocco]]. The tsunami affected Southern [[Kingdom of Great Britain|Great Britain]] and [[Kingdom of Ireland|Ireland]]\n| location = {{Coord|36|N|11|W|display=inline, title}} <br /> About 200&nbsp;km (120 mi) west-southwest of [[Cape St. Vincent]]\n| intensity = [[Mercalli intensity scale|XI (''Extreme'')]] <ref name=NGDC/>\n| casualties = 10,000\u2013100,000 deaths\n}}\n\nThe '''1755 Lisbon earthquake''', also known as the '''Great Lisbon earthquake''', occurred in [[Kingdom of Portugal|Portugal]] on the morning of Saturday, 1 November, [[All Saints' Day|Feast of All Saints]], at around 09:40 local time.<ref>[http://www.brown.edu/Departments/Portuguese_Brazilian_Studies/ejph/html/issue4/html/belo_main.html Between History and Periodicity: Printed and Hand-Written News in 18th-Century Portugal]</ref> In combination with subsequent [[fire]]s and a [[tsunami]], the earthquake almost totally destroyed [[Lisbon]] and adjoining areas. [[Seismologist]]s today estimate the Lisbon earthquake had a magnitude in the range 8.5\u20139.0<ref name=\"Gutscher\">{{cite journal|last=Gutscher|first=M.-A.|author2=Baptista M.A. & Miranda J.M.|year=2006|title=The Gibraltar Arc seismogenic zone (part 2): Constraints on a shallow east dipping fault plane source for the 1755 Lisbon earthquake provided by tsunami modeling and seismic intensity|journal=Tectonophysics|volume=426|issue=1\u20132|pages=153\u2013166|doi=10.1016/j.tecto.2006.02.025|bibcode = 2006Tectp.426..153G |last3=Miranda|first3=J.M.}}</ref><ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20091220105221/https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/world/events/1755_11_01.php Historic Earthquakes \u2013 Lisbon, Portugal].\" [[U.S. Geological Survey]], 26 October 2009. {Estimate: 8.7}</ref> on the [[moment magnitude scale]], with its [[epicenter]] in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] about {{Convert|200|km|mi|abbr=on}} west-southwest of [[Cape St. Vincent]]. Chronologically it was the third known large scale earthquake to hit the city (one in 1321 and another in [[1531 Lisbon earthquake|1531]]). Estimates place the death toll in Lisbon alone between 10,000 and 100,000 people,<ref>Pereira (2006), p. 5.</ref> making it one of the [[Lists of earthquakes#Deadliest earthquakes|deadliest earthquakes in history]].\n\nThe earthquake accentuated political tensions in Portugal and profoundly disrupted the country's [[Portuguese empire|colonial ambitions]]. The event was widely discussed and dwelt upon by European [[The Age of Enlightenment|Enlightenment]] [[philosophy|philosophers]], and inspired major developments in [[theodicy]]. As the first earthquake studied scientifically for its effects over a large area, it led to the birth of modern [[seismology]] and [[earthquake engineering]].\n\n==Earthquake and tsunami==\n[[File:1755 Lisbon earthquake.jpg|thumb|left|1755 copper engraving showing [[Lisbon]] in flames and a [[tsunami]] overwhelming the ships in the harbor]]\n\nThe earthquake struck on the morning of 1 November 1755, [[All Saints' Day]]. Contemporary reports state that the earthquake lasted between three and a half and six minutes, causing fissures 5 meters (16 feet) wide in the city center. Survivors rushed to the open space of the docks for safety and watched as the sea receded, revealing a plain of mud littered with lost cargo and shipwrecks. Approximately 40 minutes after the earthquake, a [[tsunami]] engulfed the harbor and downtown area, rushing up the [[Tagus]] river<ref>Viana-Baptista MA, Soares PM. Tsunami propagation along Tagus estuary (Lisbon, Portugal) preliminary results. ''[[Science of Tsunami Hazards]]'' 2006; 24(5):329 [http://www.sthjournal.org/245/baptista.pdf Online PDF]. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011111854/http://www.sthjournal.org/245/baptista.pdf |date=11 October 2008 }} 27 May 2009.</ref> \"so fast that several people riding on horseback&nbsp;... were forced to gallop as fast as possible to the upper grounds for fear of being carried away.\" It was followed by two more waves. Candles lit in homes and churches all around the city for All Saints' Day were knocked over, starting a fire that developed into a [[firestorm]] which burned for hours in the city, asphyxiating people up to 30 meters (100 feet) from the blaze.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2015/11/02/454051690/this-gulf-of-fire-examines-the-lisbon-portugal-earthquake-in-1755|title='This Gulf Of Fire' Examines The Lisbon, Portugal, Earthquake In 1755|publisher=NPR|date=2 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Lissabon-2.jpg|thumb|A depiction of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake as seen from across the Tagus River]]\n\nLisbon was not the only [[Portugal|Portuguese]] city affected by the catastrophe. Throughout the south of the country, in particular the [[Algarve]], destruction was rampant. The tsunami destroyed some coastal fortresses in the Algarve and, in the lower levels, it razed several houses. Almost all the coastal towns and villages of the Algarve were heavily damaged, except [[Faro, Portugal|Faro]], which was protected by the sandy banks of [[Ria Formosa]]. In [[Lagos, Portugal|Lagos]], the waves reached the top of the city walls. Other towns of different Portuguese regions, such as [[Peniche, Portugal|Peniche]], [[Cascais]], and even [[Covilh\u00e3]], which is located near the [[Serra da Estrela]] mountain range in central inland Portugal, were affected. The shock waves of the earthquake destroyed part of Covilh\u00e3's castle walls and its large towers. On the island of [[Madeira]], [[Funchal]] and many smaller settlements suffered significant damage. Almost all of the ports in the [[Azores]] archipelago suffered most of their destruction from the tsunami, with the sea penetrating about 150 m inland. Portuguese towns in northern Africa were also affected by the earthquake, such as [[Ceuta]] and [[El Jadida|Mazagon]], where the tsunami hit hard the coastal fortifications of both towns, in some cases going over it, and flooding the harbor area. In Spain, the tsunamis swept the [[Andalusia]]n Atlantic Coast, nearly destroying the city of [[C\u00e1diz|Cadiz]], killing at least 1/3 of its population.\n\n[[File:Tsunami Forecast Model Animation- Lisbon 1755.webm|thumb|left|2016 animation from [[NOAA]]]]\n[[File:Lisbon 1755 tsunami travel times.jpg|thumb|left|Calculated travel times (in hours) for the tsunami waves of 1 November 1755]]\n\nShocks from the earthquake were felt throughout [[Europe]]<ref>{{citation|jstor=104951|title=An Extraordinary and Surprising Agitation of the Waters, though without Any Perceptible Motion of the Earth, Having Been Observed in Various Parts of This Island, Both Maritime and Inland, on the Same Day, and Chiefly about the Time, That the More Violent Commotions of Both Earth and Waters so Extensively Affected Many Very Distant Parts of the Globe; the Following Accounts, Relating to the Former, Have Been Transmitted to the Society; in Which are Specified the Times and Places when and Where They Happened|journal=  Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London |series=Series I|volume=49|pages=351\u2013398|last1=Robertson|first1=John|last2=Webb|first2=Philip Carteret|last3=Adee|first3=Swithin|last4=Hodgson|first4=John|author5=Cranbrook|last6=Pringle|first6=John|last7=Mills|first7=Henry|last8=Birch|first8=Thomas|last9=Thomlinson|first9=Mr|last10=Philips|first10=Richard|last11=Crusius|first11=Lewis|last12=Blair|first12=John|last13=Parker|first13=Viscount|last14=Huxham|first14=John|last15=Borlase|first15=William|author16=Swanzey|last17=Arderon|first17=William|last18=Barber|first18=Thomas|last19=Harrison|first19=John|last20=Cowper|first20=Spencer|last21=Gardener|first21=Robert|last22=Colquhoun|first22=James|last23=Nicola|first23=L.|last24=Brocklesby|first24=Richard|author25=HEN TOM|last26=Steplin|first26=Joseph|last27=Hondt|first27=De|last28=Allamond|first28=Mons|year=1755|doi=10.1098/rstl.1755.0059|bibcode=1755RSPT...49..351R}}</ref><ref>''[[Memoirs of Jacques Casanova]]'', Book 2, Ch. XXVI; [[Casanova]] himself noted feeling the shocks when he was imprisoned in \"[[The Leads]]\" in Venice and specifically states they were the same ones that destroyed Lisbon</ref> as far as [[Finland]] and [[North Africa]], and according to some sources even in [[Greenland]],<ref>[[Brockhaus' Konversations-Lexikon]]. 14th ed., Leipzig, Berlin and Vienna 1894; Vol. 6, p. 248</ref> and the [[Caribbean]].<ref name=\"Lyell\">[[Charles Lyell|Lyell, Charles]]. ''[[Principles of Geology]]''. 1830. Vol. 1, chapter 25, p. 439 [http://www.esp.org/books/lyell/principles/facsimile/contents/lyell-v1-ch25.pdf Online electronic edition]. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080720151125/http://www.esp.org/books/lyell/principles/facsimile/contents/lyell-v1-ch25.pdf |date=20 July 2008 }} 21 May 2009.</ref> Tsunamis as tall as 20&nbsp;metres (66&nbsp;ft) swept the coast of [[North Africa]], and struck [[Martinique]] and [[Barbados]] across the [[Atlantic Ocean|Atlantic]]. A three-metre (ten-foot) [[tsunami]] hit [[Cornwall]] on the southern [[England|English]] coast. [[Galway]], on the west coast of [[Ireland]], was also hit, resulting in partial destruction of the \"[[Spanish Arch]]\" section of the city wall. In County Clare there was the creation of [[Aughinish, County Clare|Aughinish Island]] when a low lying connection to the mainland was washed away. At [[Kinsale]], several vessels were whirled round in the harbor, and water poured into the marketplace.<ref name=\"Lyell\" />\n\nIn 2015, it was revealed that the tsunami waves may have reached the coast of [[Colonial Brazil|Brazil]], then a colony of Portugal. Letters sent by Brazilian authorities at the time of the earthquake describe damage and destruction caused by gigantic waves.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Losekann|first1=Marcos|authorlink1=Marcos Losekann|title=Documentos mostram que tsunami atingiu costa brasileira s\u00e9culo XVIII|url=http://g1.globo.com/fantastico/noticia/2015/10/documentos-mostram-que-tsunami-atingiu-costa-brasileira-seculo-xviii.html|website=[[Fant\u00e1stico]]|publisher=[[Rede Globo]]|accessdate=27 October 2015|language=Portuguese|date=18 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nAlthough seismologists and geologists have always agreed that the epicenter was in the Atlantic to the West of the [[Iberian Peninsula]], its exact location has been a subject of considerable debate. Early hypotheses had proposed the [[Gorringe Ridge]] until [[earthquake simulation|simulations]] showed that a source closer to the shore of Portugal was required to comply with the observed effects of the tsunami. A 1992 seismic reflection survey of the ocean floor along the [[Azores\u2013Gibraltar Transform Fault]] detected a 50&nbsp;km-long [[thrust fault]] southwest of [[Cape St. Vincent]], with a [[dip-slip]] throw of more than 1&nbsp;km. This structure may have created the primary [[tectonic]] event.<ref>Zitellini N. et al., The tectonic source of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake and tsunami. Anali di Geofisica 1999; 42(1): 49. [http://www.earth-prints.org/bitstream/2122/1344/1/06%20zitellini.pdf Online PDF]. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011033749/http://www.earth-prints.org/bitstream/2122/1344/1/06%20zitellini.pdf |date=11 October 2007 }} 27 May 2009.</ref>\n\n==Casualties and damage==\n[[File:Convento do Carmo ruins in Lisbon.jpg|thumb|The [[ruins]] of the [[Carmo Convent (Lisbon)|Carmo Convent]], which was destroyed in the Lisbon earthquake.]]\n\nEconomic historian \u00c1lvaro Pereira estimated that of Lisbon's population at the time, of approximately 200,000 people, some 30,000\u201340,000 were killed; another 10,000 may have lost their lives in [[Morocco]]. However, a 2009 study of contemporary reports relating to the 1 November event found them vague and difficult to separate from reports of another local series of earthquakes on 18\u201319 November.<ref>Blanc P.-L. (2009) [https://www.nat-hazards-earth-syst-sci.net/9/725/2009/nhess-9-725-2009.pdf Earthquakes and tsunami in November 1755 in Morocco: a different reading of contemporaneous documentary sources]. ''[[Nat. Hazards Earth Syst. Sci.]]'' 2009; 9: 725\u2013738.</ref> Pereira estimated the total death toll in Portugal, Spain and Morocco from the earthquake and the resulting fires and tsunami at 40,000 to 50,000 people.<ref>Pereira (2006), pp. 8\u20139, 33\u20139921.</ref>\n\nEighty-five percent of Lisbon's buildings were destroyed, including famous palaces and libraries, as well as most examples of Portugal's distinctive 16th-century [[Manueline]] architecture. Several buildings that had suffered little earthquake damage were destroyed by the subsequent fire. The new Lisbon opera house (the \"[[\u00d3pera do Tejo]]\"), opened just six months before, burned to the ground. The [[Ribeira Palace|Royal Ribeira Palace]], which stood just beside the [[Tagus]] river in the modern square of ''[[Terreiro do Pa\u00e7o]]'', was destroyed by the earthquake and tsunami. Inside, the 70,000-volume royal library as well as hundreds of works of art, including paintings by [[Titian]], [[Peter Paul Rubens|Rubens]], and [[Antonio da Correggio|Correggio]], were lost. The royal archives disappeared together with detailed historical records of explorations by [[Vasco da Gama]] and other early navigators. The palace of [[Henrique de Meneses, 3rd Marquis of Louri\u00e7al]], which housed an invaluable library of 18,000 books, was also destroyed.<ref name=\"Li&Lin\">{{cite web|url=https://academics.tjhsst.edu/canoe/hum/gw/WesternEU/group7/lisbonearthquake.doc|title=A Comprehensive Report of the Great Lisbon Earthquake|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121222021717/http://academics.tjhsst.edu/canoe/hum/gw/WesternEU/group7/lisbonearthquake.doc|archive-date=22 December 2012|url-status=dead|accessdate=11 March 2018}}</ref> The earthquake damaged several major churches in Lisbon, namely the [[Lisbon Cathedral]], the [[Basilica]]s of S\u00e3o Paulo, Santa Catarina, [[Monastery of S\u00e3o Vicente de Fora|S\u00e3o Vicente de Fora]], and the [[Church of Nossa Senhora da Concei\u00e7\u00e3o Velha|Miseric\u00f3rdia Church]]. The [[Hospital Real de Todos os Santos|Royal Hospital of All Saints]] (the largest public hospital at the time) in the [[Rossio]] square was consumed by fire and hundreds of patients burned to death. The tomb of national hero [[Nuno \u00c1lvares Pereira]] was also lost. Visitors to Lisbon may still walk the ruins of the [[Carmo Convent (Lisbon)|Carmo Convent]], which were preserved to remind Lisboners of the destruction.\nThe men and women cried for help and money burned\n\n==Relief and reconstruction efforts==\n{{Further|Pombaline style}}\n[[File:Lisbon1755hangingdetail.JPG|thumb|left|''Detail from above'': Executions in the aftermath of the Lisbon earthquake.  At least 34 looters were hanged in the chaotic aftermath of the disaster.  As a warning against looting, King [[Joseph I of Portugal]] ordered [[gallows]] to be constructed in several parts of the city.]]\n\nThe royal family escaped unharmed from the catastrophe: King [[Joseph I of Portugal]] and the court had left the city, after attending mass at sunrise, fulfilling the wish of one of the king's daughters to spend the holiday away from Lisbon. After the catastrophe, Joseph I developed a fear of living within walls, and the court was accommodated in a huge complex of tents and pavilions in the hills of [[Ajuda]], then on the outskirts of Lisbon. The king's [[claustrophobia]] never waned, and it was only after Joseph's death that his daughter [[Maria I of Portugal]] began building the royal [[Ajuda Palace]], which still stands on the site of the old tented camp. Like the king, the prime minister [[Sebasti\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 de Carvalho e Melo, 1st Marquis of Pombal|Sebasti\u00e3o de Melo]] (1st Marquis of Pombal) survived the earthquake. When asked what was to be done, Pombal reportedly replied \"Bury the dead and heal the living\",<ref>{{cite book |author=T. D. Kendrick|title= The Lisbon Earthquake |page=75|author-link= T. D. Kendrick }} Kendrick writes that the remark is apocryphal and is attributed to other sources in anti-Pombal literature.</ref> and set about organizing relief and rehabilitation efforts. Firefighters were sent to extinguish the raging flames, and teams of workers and ordinary citizens were ordered to remove the thousands of corpses before disease could spread. Contrary to custom and against the wishes of the Church, many corpses were loaded onto [[barge]]s and [[burial at sea|buried at sea]] beyond the mouth of the Tagus. To prevent disorder in the ruined city, the [[Portuguese Army]] was deployed and [[gallows]] were constructed at high points around the city to deter looters; more than thirty people were publicly executed.<ref>Gunn (2008), p. 77.</ref> The army prevented many able-bodied citizens from fleeing, pressing them into relief and reconstruction work.\n\nThe [[Project for the Royal Palace in Campo de Ourique]] was proposed as the new royal residence in 1760, but the plans were later abandoned due to a lack of priority or interest in a palace being built in the [[Campo de Ourique]] neighborhood of Lisbon.\n\nThe king and the prime minister immediately launched efforts to rebuild the city. On 4 December 1755, little more than a month after the earthquake, Manuel da Maia, chief engineer to the realm, presented his plans for the re-building of Lisbon. Maia presented four options from abandoning Lisbon to building a completely new city. The first plan was to rebuild the old city using re-cycled materials; this was the cheapest option. The second and third plans proposed widening certain streets. The fourth option boldly proposed razing the entire Baixa quarter and \"laying out new streets without restraint\". This last option was chosen by the king and his minister.<ref>Shrady, ''The Last Day'' pp. 152\u2013155.</ref>\n\n[[File:Gaiola pombalina.jpg|thumb|Model of the [[seismology|seismically]] protective wooden structure called \"[[gaiola (construction)|gaiola]] pombalina\" (pombaline cage), developed for the reconstruction of [[Pombaline Lower Town]] ]]\n\nIn less than a year, the city was cleared of debris. Keen to have a new and perfectly ordered city, the king commissioned the construction of big squares, rectilinear, large avenues and widened streets&nbsp;\u2013 the new ''mottos'' of Lisbon.\n\nThe [[Pombaline style|Pombaline]] buildings are among the earliest [[seismology|seismically]] protected constructions in Europe. Small wooden models were built for testing, and earthquakes were simulated by marching troops around them. Lisbon's \"new\" Lower Town, known today as the [[Pombaline Lower Town]] (''Baixa Pombalina''), is one of the city's famed attractions. Sections of other Portuguese cities, such as the [[Vila Real de Santo Ant\u00f3nio Municipality|Vila Real de Santo Ant\u00f3nio]] in [[Algarve]], were also rebuilt along Pombaline principles.\n\nThe [[Casa Pia]], a Portuguese institution founded by Maria I (known as ''A Pia'', \"Maria the Pious\"), and organized by Police Intendant Pina Manique in 1780, was founded following the social disarray of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake.\n\n==Effect on society, economy and philosophy==\n{{refimprove section|date=October 2016}}\nThe earthquake had wide-ranging effects on the lives of the populace and intelligentsia. The earthquake had struck on an important religious holiday and had destroyed almost every important church in the city, causing anxiety and confusion amongst the citizens of a staunch and devout [[Roman Catholic]] country. Theologians and philosophers focused and speculated on the religious cause and message, seeing the earthquake as a manifestation of [[divine judgment]].<ref name=\"Kendrick\">{{cite book | url=https://archive.org/stream/lisbonearthquake010555mbp/lisbonearthquake010555mbp_djvu.txt | title=The Lisbon Earthquake | accessdate=7 May 2014| publisher=J.B. Lippincott Company }}</ref>\n\n=== Economy ===\nA 2009 study estimated that the earthquake cost between 32 and 48 percent of Portugal's GDP.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Pereira|first=Alvaro S.|date=1 June 2009|title=The Opportunity of a Disaster: The Economic Impact of the 1755 Lisbon Earthquake|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-economic-history/article/div-classtitlethe-opportunity-of-a-disaster-the-economic-impact-of-the-1755-lisbon-earthquakediv/1B56CD03A5683C8A9452DE69E871BB54|journal=The Journal of Economic History|volume=69|issue=2|pages=466\u2013499|doi=10.1017/S0022050709000850|issn=1471-6372}}</ref> Also, \"in spite of strict controls, prices and wages remained volatile in the years after the tragedy. The recovery from the earthquake also led to a rise in the wage premium of construction workers. More significantly, the earthquake became an opportunity to reform the economy and to reduce the economic semi-dependency vis-\u00e0-vis Britain.\"<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n=== Philosophy ===\n[[File:O Terramoto de 1755 (1756-92) - Jo\u00e3o Glama (MNAA).png|thumb|300px|''Allegory of the 1755 Earthquake'', by Jo\u00e3o Glama Strob\u00ebrle (who depicted himself standing on a pile of rubble on the lower-right corner). In the upper-left corner is an angel holding a fiery sword, personifying divine judgement.]]\n\nThe earthquake and its aftermath strongly influenced the intelligentsia of the [[Europe]]an [[The Age of Enlightenment|Age of Enlightenment]]. The noted writer-philosopher [[Voltaire]] used the earthquake in ''[[Candide]]'' and in his ''[[Po\u00e8me sur le d\u00e9sastre de Lisbonne]]'' (\"Poem on the Lisbon disaster\"). Voltaire's ''Candide'' attacks the notion that all is for the best in this, \"[[the best of all possible worlds]]\", a world closely supervised by a benevolent deity.  The Lisbon disaster provided a counterexample. As [[Theodor Adorno]] wrote, \"[t]he earthquake of Lisbon sufficed to cure Voltaire of the [[theodicy]] of [[Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz|Leibniz]]\" (''[[Negative Dialectics]]'' 361).  [[Jean-Jacques Rousseau]] was also influenced by the devastation following the earthquake, whose severity he believed was due to too many people living within the close quarters of the city. Rousseau used the earthquake as an argument against cities as part of his desire for a more naturalistic way of life.<ref name=\"Csmonitor.com\">{{cite journal | url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Global-Issues/2010/1028/Japan-tsunami-is-small-compared-to-five-of-world-s-biggest-tsunamis/1755-Lisbon-tsunami | title=Japan tsunami is small compared to five of world's biggest tsunamis | journal=Christian Science Monitor| date=28 October 2010 }}</ref>\n\n[[Immanuel Kant]] published three separate texts on the Lisbon earthquake.<ref>See:\n* Kant, I. (1756a) [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951001073880s;view=1up;seq=448 \"Von den Ursachen der Erdersch\u00fctterungen bei Gelegenheit des Ungl\u00fccks, welches die westliche L\u00e4nder von Europa gegen das Ende des vorigen Jahres betroffen hat\"] [On the causes of the earthquakes on the occasion of the disaster which affected the western countries of Europe towards the end of last year] In:  K\u00f6niglich Preussischen Akademie der Wissenschaften (Royal Prussian Academy of Sciences), ed.s (1902) ''Kant's gesammelte Schriften'' [Kant's collected writings] (in German) Berlin, Germany:  G. Reimer.  vol. 1, pp. 417\u2013427. \n* Kant, I. (1756b) [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951001073880s;view=1up;seq=460 \"Geschichte und Naturbeschreibung der merkw\u00fcrdigsten Vorf\u00e4lle des Erdbebens, welches an dem Ende des 1755sten Jahres einen gro\u00dfen Theil der Erde ersch\u00fcttert hat\"] [History and description of the nature of the most remarkable events of the earthquake which shook a large part of the Earth at the end of the year 1755], ibid. pp. 429\u2013461.\n* Kant, I. (1756c) [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951001073880s;view=1up;seq=494 \"Immanuel Kants fortgesetzte Betrachtung der seit einiger Zeit wahrgenommenen Erdersch\u00fctterungen\"] [Immanuel Kant's continued consideration of the earthquakes that were felt some time ago], ibid. pp. 463\u2013472.\n* Amador, Filomena (2004) \"The causes of 1755 Lisbon earthquake on Kant\" In:  Escribano Benito, J.J.; Espa\u00f1ol Gonz\u00e1lez, L.; Mart\u00ednez Garc\u00eda, M.A., ed.s.  ''Actas VIII Congreso de la Sociedad Espa\u00f1ola de Historia de las Ciencias y de las T\u00e9cnicas'' [Proceedings of the Eighth Congress of the Spanish Society of the History of the Sciences and Technology] (in English) Logro\u00f1o, Spain: Sociedad Espa\u00f1ola de Historia de las Ciencias y de las T\u00e9cnicas (Universidad de la Rioja), vol. 2, pp. 485\u2013495.</ref> As a younger man, fascinated with the earthquake, he collected all the information available in news pamphlets and formulated a theory of the causes of earthquakes. Kant's theory, which involved shifts in huge caverns filled with hot gases, was incorrect, but was one of the first systematic attempts to explain earthquakes in natural rather than supernatural terms. According to [[Walter Benjamin]], Kant's slim early book on the earthquake \"probably represents the beginnings of scientific geography in Germany. And certainly the beginnings of seismology\".\n\n[[Werner Hamacher]] has claimed that the earthquake's consequences extended into the vocabulary of philosophy, making the common metaphor of firm \"grounding\" for philosophers' arguments shaky and uncertain: \"Under the impression exerted by the Lisbon earthquake, which touched the European mind in one [of] its more sensitive epochs, the metaphor of ground and tremor completely lost their apparent innocence; they were no longer merely figures of speech\" (263).  Hamacher claims that the foundational certainty of [[Ren\u00e9 Descartes]]' philosophy began to shake following the Lisbon earthquake.\n\n=== Politics ===\n[[File:Retrato do Marqu\u00eas de Pombal - escola portuguesa, s\u00e9c. XVIII.png|thumb|[[Sebasti\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 de Carvalho e Melo, 1st Marquis of Pombal]]]]\nThe earthquake had a major impact on politics. The prime minister, [[Sebasti\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 de Carvalho e Melo, 1st Marquis of Pombal]], was the favorite of the king, but the [[Portuguese nobility|aristocracy]] despised him as an upstart son of a country squire. The prime minister, in turn, disliked the old nobles, whom he considered corrupt and incapable of practical action. Before 1 November 1755 there was a constant struggle for power and royal favor, but the competent response of the Marquis of Pombal effectively severed the power of the old aristocratic factions. However, silent opposition and resentment of King Joseph I began to rise, which would culminate with the attempted assassination of the king in 1758 and the subsequent elimination of the powerful [[Duke of Aveiro]] and the [[T\u00e1vora affair|T\u00e1vora family]].{{clarify|date=January 2017}}\n\n==Development of seismology==\n{{Main|Parochial Memories of 1758}}\nThe prime minister's response was not limited to the practicalities of reconstruction. He ordered a query sent to all [[parish]]es of the country regarding the earthquake and its effects. Questions included:\n* At what time did the earthquake begin, and how long did the earthquake last?\n* Did you perceive the shock to be greater from one direction than another? Example, from north to south? Did buildings seem to fall more to one side than the other?\n* How many people died and were any of them distinguished?\n* Did the sea rise or fall first, and how many [[Hand (unit)|hands]] did it rise above the normal?\n* If fire broke out, how long did it last and what damage did it cause?<ref>Shrady, ''The Last Day'', pp.145\u2013146</ref>\n\nThe answers to these and other questions are still archived in the [[Torre do Tombo]], the national historical archive. Studying and cross-referencing the priests' accounts, modern scientists were able to reconstruct the event from a scientific perspective. Without the questionnaire designed by the [[Sebasti\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 de Carvalho e Melo, 1st Marquess of Pombal|Marquis of Pombal]], this would have been impossible. Because the marquis was the first to attempt an objective scientific description of the broad causes and consequences of an earthquake, he is regarded as a forerunner of modern seismological scientists.{{by whom|date=October 2019}}\n\n==In popular culture==\nA fictionalized version of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake features as a main plot element of the 2014 [[video game]] ''[[Assassin's Creed Rogue]]'', developed and published by [[Ubisoft]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2014/8/5/5971421/assassins-creed-rogue-trailer-confirmed-ubisoft|title=Assassin's Creed Rogue confirmed by Ubisoft - here's the first trailer|last=McWhertor|first=Michael|date=5 August 2014|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=31 December 2019}}</ref> Notably, a similar earthquake occurs earlier in the story in [[Port-au-Prince]], [[Haiti]], and possibly coincides with a real-world earthquake recorded there in [[List of earthquakes in Haiti|1751]].<ref>{{citation|title=Significant Earthquake Database|url=https://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/nndc/struts/form?t=101650&s=1&d=1|author=NGDC|publisher=[[National Geophysical Data Center]], [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration|NOAA]]|doi=10.7289/V5TD9V7K|year=1972|type=Data Set}}</ref>\n\nThe album [[1755 (album)|1755]] by the Portuguese [[Gothic metal|Gothic Metal]] band [[Moonspell]] is a concept album detailing the story of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake. The album is entirely sung in Portuguese and explores not only the history but also its effects on Portuguese society, culture and spirituality.\n\n==See also==\n* {{Portal-inline|Portugal}}\n* [[1755 Cape Ann earthquake]]\n* [[Azores\u2013Gibraltar Transform Fault]]\n* [[Earthquake Baroque]]\n* [[List of historical earthquakes]]\n* [[List of historical tsunamis]]\n* [[Southwest Iberian Margin]]\n* {{illm|List of earthquakes in Portugal|pt|Lista de sismos em Portugal}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=NGDC>{{citation|title=Significant Earthquake Database|url=https://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/nndc/struts/form?t=101650&s=1&d=1|author=National Geophysical Data Center / World Data Service (NGDC/WDS)|publisher=[[National Geophysical Data Center]], [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration|NOAA]]|doi=10.7289/V5TD9V7K|year=1972|type = Data Set}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n* [[Walter Benjamin|Benjamin, Walter]]. \"The Lisbon Earthquake.\" In ''Selected Writings'' vol. 2. Belknap, 1999. {{ISBN|0-674-94586-7}}.  The often abstruse critic Benjamin gave a series of radio broadcasts for children in the early 1930s; this one, from 1931, discusses the Lisbon earthquake and summarizes some of its impact on European thought.\n* Braun, Theodore E. D., and John B. Radner, eds. ''The Lisbon Earthquake of 1755: Representations and Reactions'' (''SVEC'' 2005:02).  Oxford: Voltaire Foundation, 2005.  {{ISBN|0-7294-0857-4}}.  Recent scholarly essays on the earthquake and its representations in art, with a focus on Voltaire.  (In English and French.)\n* Brooks, Charles B. ''Disaster at Lisbon: The Great Earthquake of 1755''. Long Beach: Shangton Longley Press, 1994.  (No apparent ISBN.) A narrative history.\n* Chase, J. \"The Great Earthquake at Lisbon (1755)\". Colliers Magazine, 1920.\n* Dynes, Russell Rowe. \"The dialogue between Voltaire and Rousseau on the Lisbon earthquake: The emergence of a social science view.\" University of Delaware, Disaster Research Center, 1999.\n* Fonseca, J. D. ''1755, O Terramoto de Lisboa, The Lisbon Earthquake''. Argumentum, Lisbon, 2004.\n* Gunn, A.M. \"Encyclopedia of Disasters\". Westport, Connecticut: Greenwood Publishing Group, 2008. {{ISBN|0-313-34002-1}}.\n* [[Werner Hamacher|Hamacher, Werner]]. \"The Quaking of Presentation.\" In ''Premises: Essays on Philosophy and Literature from Kant to Celan'', pp.&nbsp;261\u2013293. Stanford University Press, 1999. {{ISBN|0-8047-3620-0}}.\n* Kendrick, T.D. ''The Lisbon Earthquake''. Philadelphia and New York: J. B. Lippincott, 1957.\n* Molesky, Mark.  ''This Gulf of Fire: The Destruction of Lisbon, or Apocalypse in the Age of Science and Reason.''  New York: Knopf, 2015.\n* Neiman, Susan. ''Evil in Modern Thought: An Alternative History of Modern Philosophy''. Princeton University Press, 2002.  This book centers on philosophical reaction to the earthquake, arguing that the earthquake was responsible for modern conceptions of evil.\n* Paice, Edward. ''Wrath of God: The Great Lisbon Earthquake of 1755''. London: Quercus, 2008. {{ISBN|978-1-84724-623-3}}\n* Pereira, A.S. \"[http://www.york.ac.uk/media/economics/documents/cherrydiscussionpapers/0603.pdf The Opportunity of a Disaster: The Economic Impact of the 1755 Lisbon Earthquake]\". Discussion Paper 06/03, Centre for Historical Economics and Related Research at York, York University, 2006.\n* Quenet, Gr\u00e9gory. ''Les tremblements de terre en France aux XVIIe et XVIIIe si\u00e8cles. La naissance d'un risque''. Seyssel: Champ Vallon, 2005.\n* Ray, Gene. \"[http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/yale_journal_of_criticism/v017/17.1ray.html Reading the Lisbon Earthquake: Adorno, Lyotard, and the Contemporary Sublime].\" ''Yale Journal of Criticism'' 17.1 (2004): pp.&nbsp;1\u201318.\n* Seco e Pinto, P.S. (Editor). ''Earthquake Geotechnical Engineering: Proceedings of the Second International Conference, Lisbon, Portugal, 21\u201325 June 1999''. {{ISBN|90-5809-116-3}}\n* Shrady, Nicholas. ''The Last Day: Wrath, Ruin & Reason in The Great Lisbon Earthquake of 1755'', Penguin, 2008, {{ISBN|978-0-14-311460-4}}\n* Weinrich, Harald. \"Literaturgeschichte eines Weltereignisses: Das Erdbeben von Lissabon.\" In ''Literatur f\u00fcr Leser'', pp.&nbsp;64\u201376. Stuttgart: [[Kohlhammer Verlag]], 1971. {{ISBN|3-17-087225-7}}.  In German. Cited by Hamacher as a broad survey of philosophical and literary reactions to the Lisbon earthquake.\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{citation|doi = 10.1785/0120190198|title = A Reassessment of the Magnitude of the 1755 Lisbon Earthquake|journal = Bulletin of the Seismological Society of America|year = 2020|last1 = Fonseca|first1 = Joao F. B. D.|volume = 110|pages = 1\u201317}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Spoken Wikipedia|En-1755 Lisbon earthquake-article.oga|2005-04-30}}\n{{Commons category|Lisbon earthquake of 1755}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110405084546/http://lisbon-pre-1755-earthquake.org/the-lisbon-earthquake-of-1755-the-catastrophe-and-its-european-repercussions/ The Lisbon earthquake of 1755: the catastrophe and its European repercussions.]\n* [http://www.emidius.eu/AHEAD/main/info/?en=65228&page=2 The 1755 Lisbon Earthquake, available seismological studies from the European Archive of Historical Earthquake Data]\n* [https://archive.today/20121209043010/http://www.lisbon-and-portugal.com/travel/1755-lisbon-earthquake.html The 1755 Lisbon Earthquake]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20031204233731/http://nisee.berkeley.edu/lisbon/ Images and historical depictions of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake]\n* [http://nisee.berkeley.edu/elibrary/browse/kozak?eq=5234 More images of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake and tsunami]\n* [http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/mod/1755lisbonquake.html Contemporary eyewitness account of Rev. Charles Davy]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ht0W2E9g8cA Tsunami Forecast Model Animation: Lisbon 1755] \u2013 [[Pacific Tsunami Warning Center]]\n\n{{Lisbon}}\n{{Years in Portugal}}\n{{Portugal topics}}\n\n[[Category:Earthquakes in Portugal]]\n[[Category:18th-century in Lisbon|1755 Earthquake]]\n[[Category:1755 in Portugal|Lisbon Earthquake, 1755]]\n[[Category:1755 earthquakes|Lisbon earthquake, 1755]]\n[[Category:1755 tsunamis|Lisbon]]\n[[Category:Earthquakes in Spain]]\n[[Category:Earthquakes in Morocco]]\n[[Category:18th century in Morocco]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use American English|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{short description|Catastrophic earthquake that primarily affected Lisbon, Kingdom of Portugal}}\n{{Earthquake\n| title = 1755 Lisbon earthquake\n| pre-1900 = yes\n| map =1755_Lisbon_Earthquake_Location.png\n| local-date = {{start-date|1 November 1755|1 November 1755}}\n| local-time = 09:40\n| magnitude = 8.5\u20139.0 [[Moment magnitude scale|M<sub>w</sub>]] (est.)\n| depth =\n| countries affected = [[Kingdom of Portugal|Portugal]], [[Enlightenment in Spain|Spain]], and [[Morocco]]. The tsunami affected Southern [[Kingdom of Great Britain|Great Britain]] and [[Kingdom of Ireland|Ireland]]\n| location = {{Coord|36|N|11|W|display=inline, title}} <br /> About 200&nbsp;km (120 mi) west-southwest of [[Cape St. Vincent]]\n| intensity = [[Mercalli intensity scale|XI (''Extreme'')]] <ref name=NGDC/>\n| casualties = 10,000\u2013100,000 deaths\n}}\n\nThe '''1755 Lisbon earthquake''', also known as the '''Great Lisbon earthquake''', occurred in [[Kingdom of Portugal|Portugal]] on the morning of Saturday, 1 November, [[All Saints' Day|Feast of All Saints]], at around 09:40 local time.<ref>[http://www.brown.edu/Departments/Portuguese_Brazilian_Studies/ejph/html/issue4/html/belo_main.html Between History and Periodicity: Printed and Hand-Written News in 18th-Century Portugal]</ref> In combination with subsequent [[fire]]s and a [[tsunami]], the earthquake almost totally destroyed [[Lisbon]] and adjoining areas. [[Seismologist]]s today estimate the Lisbon earthquake had a magnitude in the range 8.5\u20139.0<ref name=\"Gutscher\">{{cite journal|last=Gutscher|first=M.-A.|author2=Baptista M.A. & Miranda J.M.|year=2006|title=The Gibraltar Arc seismogenic zone (part 2): Constraints on a shallow east dipping fault plane source for the 1755 Lisbon earthquake provided by tsunami modeling and seismic intensity|journal=Tectonophysics|volume=426|issue=1\u20132|pages=153\u2013166|doi=10.1016/j.tecto.2006.02.025|bibcode = 2006Tectp.426..153G |last3=Miranda|first3=J.M.}}</ref><ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20091220105221/https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/world/events/1755_11_01.php Historic Earthquakes \u2013 Lisbon, Portugal].\" [[U.S. Geological Survey]], 26 October 2009. {Estimate: 8.7}</ref> on the [[moment magnitude scale]], with its [[epicenter]] in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] about {{Convert|200|km|mi|abbr=on}} west-southwest of [[Cape St. Vincent]]. Chronologically it was the third known large scale earthquake to hit the city (one in 1321 and another in [[1531 Lisbon earthquake|1531]]). Estimates place the death toll in Lisbon alone between 10,000 and 100,000 people,<ref>Pereira (2006), p. 5.</ref> making it one of the [[Lists of earthquakes#Deadliest earthquakes|deadliest earthquakes in history]].\n\nThe earthquake accentuated political tensions in Portugal and profoundly disrupted the country's [[Portuguese empire|colonial ambitions]]. The event was widely discussed and dwelt upon by European [[The Age of Enlightenment|Enlightenment]] [[philosophy|philosophers]], and inspired major developments in [[theodicy]]. As the first earthquake studied scientifically for its effects over a large area, it led to the birth of modern [[seismology]] and [[earthquake engineering]].\n\n==Earthquake and tsunami==\n[[File:1755 Lisbon earthquake.jpg|thumb|left|1755 copper engraving showing [[Lisbon]] in flames and a [[tsunami]] overwhelming the ships in the harbor]]\n\nThe earthquake struck on the morning of 1 November 1755, [[All Saints' Day]]. Contemporary reports state that the earthquake lasted between three and a half and six minutes, causing fissures 5 meters (16 feet) wide in the city center. Survivors rushed to the open space of the docks for safety and watched as the sea receded, revealing a plain of mud littered with lost cargo and shipwrecks. Approximately 40 minutes after the earthquake, a [[tsunami]] engulfed the harbor and downtown area, rushing up the [[Tagus]] river<ref>Viana-Baptista MA, Soares PM. Tsunami propagation along Tagus estuary (Lisbon, Portugal) preliminary results. ''[[Science of Tsunami Hazards]]'' 2006; 24(5):329 [http://www.sthjournal.org/245/baptista.pdf Online PDF]. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011111854/http://www.sthjournal.org/245/baptista.pdf |date=11 October 2008 }} 27 May 2009.</ref> \"so fast that several people riding on horseback&nbsp;... were forced to gallop as fast as possible to the upper grounds for fear of being carried away.\" It was followed by two more waves. Candles lit in homes and churches all around the city for All Saints' Day were knocked over, starting a fire that developed into a [[firestorm]] which burned for hours in the city, asphyxiating people up to 30 meters (100 feet) from the blaze.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2015/11/02/454051690/this-gulf-of-fire-examines-the-lisbon-portugal-earthquake-in-1755|title='This Gulf Of Fire' Examines The Lisbon, Portugal, Earthquake In 1755|publisher=NPR|date=2 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Lissabon-2.jpg|thumb|A depiction of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake as seen from across the Tagus River]]\n\nLisbon was not the only [[Portugal|Portuguese]] city affected by the catastrophe. Throughout the south of the country, in particular the [[Algarve]], destruction was rampant. The tsunami destroyed some coastal fortresses in the Algarve and, in the lower levels, it razed several houses. Almost all the coastal towns and villages of the Algarve were heavily damaged, except [[Faro, Portugal|Faro]], which was protected by the sandy banks of [[Ria Formosa]]. In [[Lagos, Portugal|Lagos]], the waves reached the top of the city walls. Other towns of different Portuguese regions, such as [[Peniche, Portugal|Peniche]], [[Cascais]], and even [[Covilh\u00e3]], which is located near the [[Serra da Estrela]] mountain range in central inland Portugal, were affected. The shock waves of the earthquake destroyed part of Covilh\u00e3's castle walls and its large towers. On the island of [[Madeira]], [[Funchal]] and many smaller settlements suffered significant damage. Almost all of the ports in the [[Azores]] archipelago suffered most of their destruction from the tsunami, with the sea penetrating about 150 m inland. Portuguese towns in northern Africa were also affected by the earthquake, such as [[Ceuta]] and [[El Jadida|Mazagon]], where the tsunami hit hard the coastal fortifications of both towns, in some cases going over it, and flooding the harbor area. In Spain, the tsunamis swept the [[Andalusia]]n Atlantic Coast, nearly destroying the city of [[C\u00e1diz|Cadiz]], killing at least 1/3 of its population.\n\n[[File:Tsunami Forecast Model Animation- Lisbon 1755.webm|thumb|left|2016 animation from [[NOAA]]]]\n[[File:Lisbon 1755 tsunami travel times.jpg|thumb|left|Calculated travel times (in hours) for the tsunami waves of 1 November 1755]]\n\nShocks from the earthquake were felt throughout [[Europe]]<ref>{{citation|jstor=104951|title=An Extraordinary and Surprising Agitation of the Waters, though without Any Perceptible Motion of the Earth, Having Been Observed in Various Parts of This Island, Both Maritime and Inland, on the Same Day, and Chiefly about the Time, That the More Violent Commotions of Both Earth and Waters so Extensively Affected Many Very Distant Parts of the Globe; the Following Accounts, Relating to the Former, Have Been Transmitted to the Society; in Which are Specified the Times and Places when and Where They Happened|journal=  Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London |series=Series I|volume=49|pages=351\u2013398|last1=Robertson|first1=John|last2=Webb|first2=Philip Carteret|last3=Adee|first3=Swithin|last4=Hodgson|first4=John|author5=Cranbrook|last6=Pringle|first6=John|last7=Mills|first7=Henry|last8=Birch|first8=Thomas|last9=Thomlinson|first9=Mr|last10=Philips|first10=Richard|last11=Crusius|first11=Lewis|last12=Blair|first12=John|last13=Parker|first13=Viscount|last14=Huxham|first14=John|last15=Borlase|first15=William|author16=Swanzey|last17=Arderon|first17=William|last18=Barber|first18=Thomas|last19=Harrison|first19=John|last20=Cowper|first20=Spencer|last21=Gardener|first21=Robert|last22=Colquhoun|first22=James|last23=Nicola|first23=L.|last24=Brocklesby|first24=Richard|author25=HEN TOM|last26=Steplin|first26=Joseph|last27=Hondt|first27=De|last28=Allamond|first28=Mons|year=1755|doi=10.1098/rstl.1755.0059|bibcode=1755RSPT...49..351R}}</ref><ref>''[[Memoirs of Jacques Casanova]]'', Book 2, Ch. XXVI; [[Casanova]] himself noted feeling the shocks when he was imprisoned in \"[[The Leads]]\" in Venice and specifically states they were the same ones that destroyed Lisbon</ref> as far as [[Finland]] and [[North Africa]], and according to some sources even in [[Greenland]],<ref>[[Brockhaus' Konversations-Lexikon]]. 14th ed., Leipzig, Berlin and Vienna 1894; Vol. 6, p. 248</ref> and the [[Caribbean]].<ref name=\"Lyell\">[[Charles Lyell|Lyell, Charles]]. ''[[Principles of Geology]]''. 1830. Vol. 1, chapter 25, p. 439 [http://www.esp.org/books/lyell/principles/facsimile/contents/lyell-v1-ch25.pdf Online electronic edition]. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080720151125/http://www.esp.org/books/lyell/principles/facsimile/contents/lyell-v1-ch25.pdf |date=20 July 2008 }} 21 May 2009.</ref> Tsunamis as tall as 20&nbsp;metres (66&nbsp;ft) swept the coast of [[North Africa]], and struck [[Martinique]] and [[Barbados]] across the [[Atlantic Ocean|Atlantic]]. A three-metre (ten-foot) [[tsunami]] hit [[Cornwall]] on the southern [[England|English]] coast. [[Galway]], on the west coast of [[Ireland]], was also hit, resulting in partial destruction of the \"[[Spanish Arch]]\" section of the city wall. In County Clare there was the creation of [[Aughinish, County Clare|Aughinish Island]] when a low lying connection to the mainland was washed away. At [[Kinsale]], several vessels were whirled round in the harbor, and water poured into the marketplace.<ref name=\"Lyell\" />\n\nIn 2015, it was revealed that the tsunami waves may have reached the coast of [[Colonial Brazil|Brazil]], then a colony of Portugal. Letters sent by Brazilian authorities at the time of the earthquake describe damage and destruction caused by gigantic waves.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Losekann|first1=Marcos|authorlink1=Marcos Losekann|title=Documentos mostram que tsunami atingiu costa brasileira s\u00e9culo XVIII|url=http://g1.globo.com/fantastico/noticia/2015/10/documentos-mostram-que-tsunami-atingiu-costa-brasileira-seculo-xviii.html|website=[[Fant\u00e1stico]]|publisher=[[Rede Globo]]|accessdate=27 October 2015|language=Portuguese|date=18 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nAlthough seismologists and geologists have always agreed that the epicenter was in the Atlantic to the West of the [[Iberian Peninsula]], its exact location has been a subject of considerable debate. Early hypotheses had proposed the [[Gorringe Ridge]] until [[earthquake simulation|simulations]] showed that a source closer to the shore of Portugal was required to comply with the observed effects of the tsunami. A 1992 seismic reflection survey of the ocean floor along the [[Azores\u2013Gibraltar Transform Fault]] detected a 50&nbsp;km-long [[thrust fault]] southwest of [[Cape St. Vincent]], with a [[dip-slip]] throw of more than 1&nbsp;km. This structure may have created the primary [[tectonic]] event.<ref>Zitellini N. et al., The tectonic source of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake and tsunami. Anali di Geofisica 1999; 42(1): 49. [http://www.earth-prints.org/bitstream/2122/1344/1/06%20zitellini.pdf Online PDF]. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011033749/http://www.earth-prints.org/bitstream/2122/1344/1/06%20zitellini.pdf |date=11 October 2007 }} 27 May 2009.</ref>\n\n==Casualties and damage==\n[[File:Convento do Carmo ruins in Lisbon.jpg|thumb|The [[ruins]] of the [[Carmo Convent (Lisbon)|Carmo Convent]], which was destroyed in the Lisbon earthquake.]]\n\nEconomic historian \u00c1lvaro Pereira estimated that of Lisbon's population at the time, of approximately 200,000 people, some 30,000\u201340,000 were killed; another 10,000 may have lost their lives in [[Morocco]]. However, a 2009 study of contemporary reports relating to the 1 November event found them vague and difficult to separate from reports of another local series of earthquakes on 18\u201319 November.<ref>Blanc P.-L. (2009) [https://www.nat-hazards-earth-syst-sci.net/9/725/2009/nhess-9-725-2009.pdf Earthquakes and tsunami in November 1755 in Morocco: a different reading of contemporaneous documentary sources]. ''[[Nat. Hazards Earth Syst. Sci.]]'' 2009; 9: 725\u2013738.</ref> Pereira estimated the total death toll in Portugal, Spain and Morocco from the earthquake and the resulting fires and tsunami at 40,000 to 50,000 people.<ref>Pereira (2006), pp. 8\u20139, 33\u20139921.</ref>\n\nEighty-five percent of Lisbon's buildings were destroyed, including famous palaces and libraries, as well as most examples of Portugal's distinctive 16th-century [[Manueline]] architecture. Several buildings that had suffered little earthquake damage were destroyed by the subsequent fire. The new Lisbon opera house (the \"[[\u00d3pera do Tejo]]\"), opened just six months before, burned to the ground. The [[Ribeira Palace|Royal Ribeira Palace]], which stood just beside the [[Tagus]] river in the modern square of ''[[Terreiro do Pa\u00e7o]]'', was destroyed by the earthquake and tsunami. Inside, the 70,000-volume royal library as well as hundreds of works of art, including paintings by [[Titian]], [[Peter Paul Rubens|Rubens]], and [[Antonio da Correggio|Correggio]], were lost. The royal archives disappeared together with detailed historical records of explorations by [[Vasco da Gama]] and other early navigators. The palace of [[Henrique de Meneses, 3rd Marquis of Louri\u00e7al]], which housed an invaluable library of 18,000 books, was also destroyed.<ref name=\"Li&Lin\">{{cite web|url=https://academics.tjhsst.edu/canoe/hum/gw/WesternEU/group7/lisbonearthquake.doc|title=A Comprehensive Report of the Great Lisbon Earthquake|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121222021717/http://academics.tjhsst.edu/canoe/hum/gw/WesternEU/group7/lisbonearthquake.doc|archive-date=22 December 2012|url-status=dead|accessdate=11 March 2018}}</ref> The earthquake damaged several major churches in Lisbon, namely the [[Lisbon Cathedral]], the [[Basilica]]s of S\u00e3o Paulo, Santa Catarina, [[Monastery of S\u00e3o Vicente de Fora|S\u00e3o Vicente de Fora]], and the [[Church of Nossa Senhora da Concei\u00e7\u00e3o Velha|Miseric\u00f3rdia Church]]. The [[Hospital Real de Todos os Santos|Royal Hospital of All Saints]] (the largest public hospital at the time) in the [[Rossio]] square was consumed by fire and hundreds of patients burned to death. The tomb of national hero [[Nuno \u00c1lvares Pereira]] was also lost. Visitors to Lisbon may still walk the ruins of the [[Carmo Convent (Lisbon)|Carmo Convent]], which were preserved to remind Lisboners of the destruction.\n\n==Relief and reconstruction efforts==\n{{Further|Pombaline style}}\n[[File:Lisbon1755hangingdetail.JPG|thumb|left|''Detail from above'': Executions in the aftermath of the Lisbon earthquake.  At least 34 looters were hanged in the chaotic aftermath of the disaster.  As a warning against looting, King [[Joseph I of Portugal]] ordered [[gallows]] to be constructed in several parts of the city.]]\n\nThe royal family escaped unharmed from the catastrophe: King [[Joseph I of Portugal]] and the court had left the city, after attending mass at sunrise, fulfilling the wish of one of the king's daughters to spend the holiday away from Lisbon. After the catastrophe, Joseph I developed a fear of living within walls, and the court was accommodated in a huge complex of tents and pavilions in the hills of [[Ajuda]], then on the outskirts of Lisbon. The king's [[claustrophobia]] never waned, and it was only after Joseph's death that his daughter [[Maria I of Portugal]] began building the royal [[Ajuda Palace]], which still stands on the site of the old tented camp. Like the king, the prime minister [[Sebasti\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 de Carvalho e Melo, 1st Marquis of Pombal|Sebasti\u00e3o de Melo]] (1st Marquis of Pombal) survived the earthquake. When asked what was to be done, Pombal reportedly replied \"Bury the dead and heal the living\",<ref>{{cite book |author=T. D. Kendrick|title= The Lisbon Earthquake |page=75|author-link= T. D. Kendrick }} Kendrick writes that the remark is apocryphal and is attributed to other sources in anti-Pombal literature.</ref> and set about organizing relief and rehabilitation efforts. Firefighters were sent to extinguish the raging flames, and teams of workers and ordinary citizens were ordered to remove the thousands of corpses before disease could spread. Contrary to custom and against the wishes of the Church, many corpses were loaded onto [[barge]]s and [[burial at sea|buried at sea]] beyond the mouth of the Tagus. To prevent disorder in the ruined city, the [[Portuguese Army]] was deployed and [[gallows]] were constructed at high points around the city to deter looters; more than thirty people were publicly executed.<ref>Gunn (2008), p. 77.</ref> The army prevented many able-bodied citizens from fleeing, pressing them into relief and reconstruction work.\n\nThe [[Project for the Royal Palace in Campo de Ourique]] was proposed as the new royal residence in 1760, but the plans were later abandoned due to a lack of priority or interest in a palace being built in the [[Campo de Ourique]] neighborhood of Lisbon.\n\nThe king and the prime minister immediately launched efforts to rebuild the city. On 4 December 1755, little more than a month after the earthquake, Manuel da Maia, chief engineer to the realm, presented his plans for the re-building of Lisbon. Maia presented four options from abandoning Lisbon to building a completely new city. The first plan was to rebuild the old city using re-cycled materials; this was the cheapest option. The second and third plans proposed widening certain streets. The fourth option boldly proposed razing the entire Baixa quarter and \"laying out new streets without restraint\". This last option was chosen by the king and his minister.<ref>Shrady, ''The Last Day'' pp. 152\u2013155.</ref>\n\n[[File:Gaiola pombalina.jpg|thumb|Model of the [[seismology|seismically]] protective wooden structure called \"[[gaiola (construction)|gaiola]] pombalina\" (pombaline cage), developed for the reconstruction of [[Pombaline Lower Town]] ]]\n\nIn less than a year, the city was cleared of debris. Keen to have a new and perfectly ordered city, the king commissioned the construction of big squares, rectilinear, large avenues and widened streets&nbsp;\u2013 the new ''mottos'' of Lisbon.\n\nThe [[Pombaline style|Pombaline]] buildings are among the earliest [[seismology|seismically]] protected constructions in Europe. Small wooden models were built for testing, and earthquakes were simulated by marching troops around them. Lisbon's \"new\" Lower Town, known today as the [[Pombaline Lower Town]] (''Baixa Pombalina''), is one of the city's famed attractions. Sections of other Portuguese cities, such as the [[Vila Real de Santo Ant\u00f3nio Municipality|Vila Real de Santo Ant\u00f3nio]] in [[Algarve]], were also rebuilt along Pombaline principles.\n\nThe [[Casa Pia]], a Portuguese institution founded by Maria I (known as ''A Pia'', \"Maria the Pious\"), and organized by Police Intendant Pina Manique in 1780, was founded following the social disarray of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake.\n\n==Effect on society, economy and philosophy==\n{{refimprove section|date=October 2016}}\nThe earthquake had wide-ranging effects on the lives of the populace and intelligentsia. The earthquake had struck on an important religious holiday and had destroyed almost every important church in the city, causing anxiety and confusion amongst the citizens of a staunch and devout [[Roman Catholic]] country. Theologians and philosophers focused and speculated on the religious cause and message, seeing the earthquake as a manifestation of [[divine judgment]].<ref name=\"Kendrick\">{{cite book | url=https://archive.org/stream/lisbonearthquake010555mbp/lisbonearthquake010555mbp_djvu.txt | title=The Lisbon Earthquake | accessdate=7 May 2014| publisher=J.B. Lippincott Company }}</ref>\n\n=== Economy ===\nA 2009 study estimated that the earthquake cost between 32 and 48 percent of Portugal's GDP.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Pereira|first=Alvaro S.|date=1 June 2009|title=The Opportunity of a Disaster: The Economic Impact of the 1755 Lisbon Earthquake|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-economic-history/article/div-classtitlethe-opportunity-of-a-disaster-the-economic-impact-of-the-1755-lisbon-earthquakediv/1B56CD03A5683C8A9452DE69E871BB54|journal=The Journal of Economic History|volume=69|issue=2|pages=466\u2013499|doi=10.1017/S0022050709000850|issn=1471-6372}}</ref> Also, \"in spite of strict controls, prices and wages remained volatile in the years after the tragedy. The recovery from the earthquake also led to a rise in the wage premium of construction workers. More significantly, the earthquake became an opportunity to reform the economy and to reduce the economic semi-dependency vis-\u00e0-vis Britain.\"<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n=== Philosophy ===\n[[File:O Terramoto de 1755 (1756-92) - Jo\u00e3o Glama (MNAA).png|thumb|300px|''Allegory of the 1755 Earthquake'', by Jo\u00e3o Glama Strob\u00ebrle (who depicted himself standing on a pile of rubble on the lower-right corner). In the upper-left corner is an angel holding a fiery sword, personifying divine judgement.]]\n\nThe earthquake and its aftermath strongly influenced the intelligentsia of the [[Europe]]an [[The Age of Enlightenment|Age of Enlightenment]]. The noted writer-philosopher [[Voltaire]] used the earthquake in ''[[Candide]]'' and in his ''[[Po\u00e8me sur le d\u00e9sastre de Lisbonne]]'' (\"Poem on the Lisbon disaster\"). Voltaire's ''Candide'' attacks the notion that all is for the best in this, \"[[the best of all possible worlds]]\", a world closely supervised by a benevolent deity.  The Lisbon disaster provided a counterexample. As [[Theodor Adorno]] wrote, \"[t]he earthquake of Lisbon sufficed to cure Voltaire of the [[theodicy]] of [[Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz|Leibniz]]\" (''[[Negative Dialectics]]'' 361).  [[Jean-Jacques Rousseau]] was also influenced by the devastation following the earthquake, whose severity he believed was due to too many people living within the close quarters of the city. Rousseau used the earthquake as an argument against cities as part of his desire for a more naturalistic way of life.<ref name=\"Csmonitor.com\">{{cite journal | url=http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Global-Issues/2010/1028/Japan-tsunami-is-small-compared-to-five-of-world-s-biggest-tsunamis/1755-Lisbon-tsunami | title=Japan tsunami is small compared to five of world's biggest tsunamis | journal=Christian Science Monitor| date=28 October 2010 }}</ref>\n\n[[Immanuel Kant]] published three separate texts on the Lisbon earthquake.<ref>See:\n* Kant, I. (1756a) [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951001073880s;view=1up;seq=448 \"Von den Ursachen der Erdersch\u00fctterungen bei Gelegenheit des Ungl\u00fccks, welches die westliche L\u00e4nder von Europa gegen das Ende des vorigen Jahres betroffen hat\"] [On the causes of the earthquakes on the occasion of the disaster which affected the western countries of Europe towards the end of last year] In:  K\u00f6niglich Preussischen Akademie der Wissenschaften (Royal Prussian Academy of Sciences), ed.s (1902) ''Kant's gesammelte Schriften'' [Kant's collected writings] (in German) Berlin, Germany:  G. Reimer.  vol. 1, pp. 417\u2013427. \n* Kant, I. (1756b) [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951001073880s;view=1up;seq=460 \"Geschichte und Naturbeschreibung der merkw\u00fcrdigsten Vorf\u00e4lle des Erdbebens, welches an dem Ende des 1755sten Jahres einen gro\u00dfen Theil der Erde ersch\u00fcttert hat\"] [History and description of the nature of the most remarkable events of the earthquake which shook a large part of the Earth at the end of the year 1755], ibid. pp. 429\u2013461.\n* Kant, I. (1756c) [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=umn.31951001073880s;view=1up;seq=494 \"Immanuel Kants fortgesetzte Betrachtung der seit einiger Zeit wahrgenommenen Erdersch\u00fctterungen\"] [Immanuel Kant's continued consideration of the earthquakes that were felt some time ago], ibid. pp. 463\u2013472.\n* Amador, Filomena (2004) \"The causes of 1755 Lisbon earthquake on Kant\" In:  Escribano Benito, J.J.; Espa\u00f1ol Gonz\u00e1lez, L.; Mart\u00ednez Garc\u00eda, M.A., ed.s.  ''Actas VIII Congreso de la Sociedad Espa\u00f1ola de Historia de las Ciencias y de las T\u00e9cnicas'' [Proceedings of the Eighth Congress of the Spanish Society of the History of the Sciences and Technology] (in English) Logro\u00f1o, Spain: Sociedad Espa\u00f1ola de Historia de las Ciencias y de las T\u00e9cnicas (Universidad de la Rioja), vol. 2, pp. 485\u2013495.</ref> As a younger man, fascinated with the earthquake, he collected all the information available in news pamphlets and formulated a theory of the causes of earthquakes. Kant's theory, which involved shifts in huge caverns filled with hot gases, was incorrect, but was one of the first systematic attempts to explain earthquakes in natural rather than supernatural terms. According to [[Walter Benjamin]], Kant's slim early book on the earthquake \"probably represents the beginnings of scientific geography in Germany. And certainly the beginnings of seismology\".\n\n[[Werner Hamacher]] has claimed that the earthquake's consequences extended into the vocabulary of philosophy, making the common metaphor of firm \"grounding\" for philosophers' arguments shaky and uncertain: \"Under the impression exerted by the Lisbon earthquake, which touched the European mind in one [of] its more sensitive epochs, the metaphor of ground and tremor completely lost their apparent innocence; they were no longer merely figures of speech\" (263).  Hamacher claims that the foundational certainty of [[Ren\u00e9 Descartes]]' philosophy began to shake following the Lisbon earthquake.\n\n=== Politics ===\n[[File:Retrato do Marqu\u00eas de Pombal - escola portuguesa, s\u00e9c. XVIII.png|thumb|[[Sebasti\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 de Carvalho e Melo, 1st Marquis of Pombal]]]]\nThe earthquake had a major impact on politics. The prime minister, [[Sebasti\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 de Carvalho e Melo, 1st Marquis of Pombal]], was the favorite of the king, but the [[Portuguese nobility|aristocracy]] despised him as an upstart son of a country squire. The prime minister, in turn, disliked the old nobles, whom he considered corrupt and incapable of practical action. Before 1 November 1755 there was a constant struggle for power and royal favor, but the competent response of the Marquis of Pombal effectively severed the power of the old aristocratic factions. However, silent opposition and resentment of King Joseph I began to rise, which would culminate with the attempted assassination of the king in 1758 and the subsequent elimination of the powerful [[Duke of Aveiro]] and the [[T\u00e1vora affair|T\u00e1vora family]].{{clarify|date=January 2017}}\n\n==Development of seismology==\n{{Main|Parochial Memories of 1758}}\nThe prime minister's response was not limited to the practicalities of reconstruction. He ordered a query sent to all [[parish]]es of the country regarding the earthquake and its effects. Questions included:\n* At what time did the earthquake begin, and how long did the earthquake last?\n* Did you perceive the shock to be greater from one direction than another? Example, from north to south? Did buildings seem to fall more to one side than the other?\n* How many people died and were any of them distinguished?\n* Did the sea rise or fall first, and how many [[Hand (unit)|hands]] did it rise above the normal?\n* If fire broke out, how long did it last and what damage did it cause?<ref>Shrady, ''The Last Day'', pp.145\u2013146</ref>\n\nThe answers to these and other questions are still archived in the [[Torre do Tombo]], the national historical archive. Studying and cross-referencing the priests' accounts, modern scientists were able to reconstruct the event from a scientific perspective. Without the questionnaire designed by the [[Sebasti\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 de Carvalho e Melo, 1st Marquess of Pombal|Marquis of Pombal]], this would have been impossible. Because the marquis was the first to attempt an objective scientific description of the broad causes and consequences of an earthquake, he is regarded as a forerunner of modern seismological scientists.{{by whom|date=October 2019}}\n\n==In popular culture==\nA fictionalized version of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake features as a main plot element of the 2014 [[video game]] ''[[Assassin's Creed Rogue]]'', developed and published by [[Ubisoft]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2014/8/5/5971421/assassins-creed-rogue-trailer-confirmed-ubisoft|title=Assassin's Creed Rogue confirmed by Ubisoft - here's the first trailer|last=McWhertor|first=Michael|date=5 August 2014|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=31 December 2019}}</ref> Notably, a similar earthquake occurs earlier in the story in [[Port-au-Prince]], [[Haiti]], and possibly coincides with a real-world earthquake recorded there in [[List of earthquakes in Haiti|1751]].<ref>{{citation|title=Significant Earthquake Database|url=https://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/nndc/struts/form?t=101650&s=1&d=1|author=NGDC|publisher=[[National Geophysical Data Center]], [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration|NOAA]]|doi=10.7289/V5TD9V7K|year=1972|type=Data Set}}</ref>\n\nThe album [[1755 (album)|1755]] by the Portuguese [[Gothic metal|Gothic Metal]] band [[Moonspell]] is a concept album detailing the story of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake. The album is entirely sung in Portuguese and explores not only the history but also its effects on Portuguese society, culture and spirituality.\n\n==See also==\n* {{Portal-inline|Portugal}}\n* [[1755 Cape Ann earthquake]]\n* [[Azores\u2013Gibraltar Transform Fault]]\n* [[Earthquake Baroque]]\n* [[List of historical earthquakes]]\n* [[List of historical tsunamis]]\n* [[Southwest Iberian Margin]]\n* {{illm|List of earthquakes in Portugal|pt|Lista de sismos em Portugal}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=NGDC>{{citation|title=Significant Earthquake Database|url=https://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/nndc/struts/form?t=101650&s=1&d=1|author=National Geophysical Data Center / World Data Service (NGDC/WDS)|publisher=[[National Geophysical Data Center]], [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration|NOAA]]|doi=10.7289/V5TD9V7K|year=1972|type = Data Set}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n* [[Walter Benjamin|Benjamin, Walter]]. \"The Lisbon Earthquake.\" In ''Selected Writings'' vol. 2. Belknap, 1999. {{ISBN|0-674-94586-7}}.  The often abstruse critic Benjamin gave a series of radio broadcasts for children in the early 1930s; this one, from 1931, discusses the Lisbon earthquake and summarizes some of its impact on European thought.\n* Braun, Theodore E. D., and John B. Radner, eds. ''The Lisbon Earthquake of 1755: Representations and Reactions'' (''SVEC'' 2005:02).  Oxford: Voltaire Foundation, 2005.  {{ISBN|0-7294-0857-4}}.  Recent scholarly essays on the earthquake and its representations in art, with a focus on Voltaire.  (In English and French.)\n* Brooks, Charles B. ''Disaster at Lisbon: The Great Earthquake of 1755''. Long Beach: Shangton Longley Press, 1994.  (No apparent ISBN.) A narrative history.\n* Chase, J. \"The Great Earthquake at Lisbon (1755)\". Colliers Magazine, 1920.\n* Dynes, Russell Rowe. \"The dialogue between Voltaire and Rousseau on the Lisbon earthquake: The emergence of a social science view.\" University of Delaware, Disaster Research Center, 1999.\n* Fonseca, J. D. ''1755, O Terramoto de Lisboa, The Lisbon Earthquake''. Argumentum, Lisbon, 2004.\n* Gunn, A.M. \"Encyclopedia of Disasters\". Westport, Connecticut: Greenwood Publishing Group, 2008. {{ISBN|0-313-34002-1}}.\n* [[Werner Hamacher|Hamacher, Werner]]. \"The Quaking of Presentation.\" In ''Premises: Essays on Philosophy and Literature from Kant to Celan'', pp.&nbsp;261\u2013293. Stanford University Press, 1999. {{ISBN|0-8047-3620-0}}.\n* Kendrick, T.D. ''The Lisbon Earthquake''. Philadelphia and New York: J. B. Lippincott, 1957.\n* Molesky, Mark.  ''This Gulf of Fire: The Destruction of Lisbon, or Apocalypse in the Age of Science and Reason.''  New York: Knopf, 2015.\n* Neiman, Susan. ''Evil in Modern Thought: An Alternative History of Modern Philosophy''. Princeton University Press, 2002.  This book centers on philosophical reaction to the earthquake, arguing that the earthquake was responsible for modern conceptions of evil.\n* Paice, Edward. ''Wrath of God: The Great Lisbon Earthquake of 1755''. London: Quercus, 2008. {{ISBN|978-1-84724-623-3}}\n* Pereira, A.S. \"[http://www.york.ac.uk/media/economics/documents/cherrydiscussionpapers/0603.pdf The Opportunity of a Disaster: The Economic Impact of the 1755 Lisbon Earthquake]\". Discussion Paper 06/03, Centre for Historical Economics and Related Research at York, York University, 2006.\n* Quenet, Gr\u00e9gory. ''Les tremblements de terre en France aux XVIIe et XVIIIe si\u00e8cles. La naissance d'un risque''. Seyssel: Champ Vallon, 2005.\n* Ray, Gene. \"[http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/yale_journal_of_criticism/v017/17.1ray.html Reading the Lisbon Earthquake: Adorno, Lyotard, and the Contemporary Sublime].\" ''Yale Journal of Criticism'' 17.1 (2004): pp.&nbsp;1\u201318.\n* Seco e Pinto, P.S. (Editor). ''Earthquake Geotechnical Engineering: Proceedings of the Second International Conference, Lisbon, Portugal, 21\u201325 June 1999''. {{ISBN|90-5809-116-3}}\n* Shrady, Nicholas. ''The Last Day: Wrath, Ruin & Reason in The Great Lisbon Earthquake of 1755'', Penguin, 2008, {{ISBN|978-0-14-311460-4}}\n* Weinrich, Harald. \"Literaturgeschichte eines Weltereignisses: Das Erdbeben von Lissabon.\" In ''Literatur f\u00fcr Leser'', pp.&nbsp;64\u201376. Stuttgart: [[Kohlhammer Verlag]], 1971. {{ISBN|3-17-087225-7}}.  In German. Cited by Hamacher as a broad survey of philosophical and literary reactions to the Lisbon earthquake.\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{citation|doi = 10.1785/0120190198|title = A Reassessment of the Magnitude of the 1755 Lisbon Earthquake|journal = Bulletin of the Seismological Society of America|year = 2020|last1 = Fonseca|first1 = Joao F. B. D.|volume = 110|pages = 1\u201317}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Spoken Wikipedia|En-1755 Lisbon earthquake-article.oga|2005-04-30}}\n{{Commons category|Lisbon earthquake of 1755}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110405084546/http://lisbon-pre-1755-earthquake.org/the-lisbon-earthquake-of-1755-the-catastrophe-and-its-european-repercussions/ The Lisbon earthquake of 1755: the catastrophe and its European repercussions.]\n* [http://www.emidius.eu/AHEAD/main/info/?en=65228&page=2 The 1755 Lisbon Earthquake, available seismological studies from the European Archive of Historical Earthquake Data]\n* [https://archive.today/20121209043010/http://www.lisbon-and-portugal.com/travel/1755-lisbon-earthquake.html The 1755 Lisbon Earthquake]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20031204233731/http://nisee.berkeley.edu/lisbon/ Images and historical depictions of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake]\n* [http://nisee.berkeley.edu/elibrary/browse/kozak?eq=5234 More images of the 1755 Lisbon earthquake and tsunami]\n* [http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/mod/1755lisbonquake.html Contemporary eyewitness account of Rev. Charles Davy]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ht0W2E9g8cA Tsunami Forecast Model Animation: Lisbon 1755] \u2013 [[Pacific Tsunami Warning Center]]\n\n{{Lisbon}}\n{{Years in Portugal}}\n{{Portugal topics}}\n\n[[Category:Earthquakes in Portugal]]\n[[Category:18th-century in Lisbon|1755 Earthquake]]\n[[Category:1755 in Portugal|Lisbon Earthquake, 1755]]\n[[Category:1755 earthquakes|Lisbon earthquake, 1755]]\n[[Category:1755 tsunamis|Lisbon]]\n[[Category:Earthquakes in Spain]]\n[[Category:Earthquakes in Morocco]]\n[[Category:18th century in Morocco]]\n", "name_user": "209.243.17.33", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eCasualties and damage)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1755_Lisbon_earthquake"}
{"title_page": "U.S. national anthem protests (2016\u2013present)", "text_new": "{{short description|Series of protests by American athletes}}\n{{for|the previous protests|U.S. national anthem protests}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox civil conflict\n| latitude =\n| longitude =\n| image = [[File:Colin Kaepernick in 2013.jpg|200px]]\n| caption = [[Colin Kaepernick]] with the [[San Francisco 49ers]] (2013)\n| date = August 14, 2016\u2013ongoing ({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|year1=2016|month1=8|day1=14}})\n| place = [[List of current National Football League stadiums|National Football League stadiums]] he \nlvuhj\n\n| coordinates =\n| goals = \n* To raise awareness of [[Racism in the United States|racism]] and [[Police brutality in the United States|police brutality]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benjamin |first1=Hoffman |last2=Minsberg |first2=Talya |title=The Deafening Silence of Colin Kaepernick |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/04/sports/colin-kaepernick-nfl-anthem-kneeling.html |accessdate=29 March 2019 |work=The New York Times |date=4 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180926034525/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/04/sports/colin-kaepernick-nfl-anthem-kneeling.html |archivedate=26 September 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"nytimes\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/04/sports/nike-protests-kaepernick-nfl-.html|newspaper=[[New York Times]]|accessdate=September 4, 2018|title=Nike's Deal With Kaepernick Draws Cheers and Pictures of Burning Shoes|date=September 4, 2018|first1=Jacey|last1=Fortin|first2=Matthew|last2=Haag|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905033557/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/04/sports/nike-protests-kaepernick-nfl-.html|archive-date=September 5, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* [[Freedom of speech]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=HOFFMAN |first1=BENJAMIN |last2=MATHER |first2=VICTOR |last3=FORTIN |first3=JACEY |title=After Trump Blasts N.F.L., Players Kneel and Lock Arms in Solidarity |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html |accessdate=30 March 2019 |work=The New York Times |date=24 September 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180406033924/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html |archivedate=6 April 2018}}</ref>\n* In opposition to U.S. President Donald Trump's [[Presidency of Donald Trump|policies]].<ref name=\"insider.foxnews.com\"/> \n| methods = [[Peaceful protest]]\n| status =\n| result =\n| concessions =\n| side1 =\n| side2 =\n| leadfigures1 =\n| leadfigures2 =\n| casualties1 =\n| casualties2 =\n| casualties_label =\n| howmany1 =\n| howmany2 =\n}}\n\nSince August 2016, some [[United States|American]] [[athlete]]s have protested against [[Police brutality in the United States|police brutality]] and [[Racism in the United States|racism]]<ref name=\"nytimes\"/><ref name=\"Sporting News\">{{cite magazine|title=NFL players protest during anthem; Colin Kaepernick, President Trump respond'|url=http://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/news/nfl-players-protest-during-national-anthem-colin-kaepernick-tweets-support/o3v0jxys8jbc1cr2gkzxpcb9n/|magazine=[[Sporting News]]|accessdate=10 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811110938/http://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/news/nfl-players-protest-during-national-anthem-colin-kaepernick-tweets-support/o3v0jxys8jbc1cr2gkzxpcb9n|archive-date=August 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"USAToday\">{{cite web|title=Aaron Rodgers sticks up for player protests during national anthem'|url=https://packerswire.usatoday.com/2018/08/08/aaron-rodgers-sticks-up-for-player-protests-during-national-anthem//|publisher=[[USAToday]]|accessdate=13 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813210402/https://packerswire.usatoday.com/2018/08/08/aaron-rodgers-sticks-up-for-player-protests-during-national-anthem/|archive-date=August 13, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=August 8, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"FoxNews\">{{cite web|title=Hillary Clinton defends kneeling NFL players, says 'that's not against our anthem or flag'|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2017/10/16/hillary-clinton-defends-kneeling-nfl-players-says-thats-not-against-our-anthem-or-flag.html/|publisher=[[Fox News]]|accessdate=10 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811195959/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2017/10/16/hillary-clinton-defends-kneeling-nfl-players-says-thats-not-against-our-anthem-or-flag.html|archive-date=August 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"SBNation\">{{cite web|title=Everything you need to know about NFL protests during the national anthem|url=https://www.sbnation.com/2017/9/29/16380080/donald-trump-nfl-colin-kaepernick-protests-national-anthem/|publisher=[[SBNation]]|accessdate=10 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811032759/https://www.sbnation.com/2017/9/29/16380080/donald-trump-nfl-colin-kaepernick-protests-national-anthem/|archive-date=August 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 29, 2017}}</ref> by [[kneeling]] on one knee during the [[U.S. national anthem]].<ref name=\"insider.foxnews.com\">{{cite news|title=Kevin Jackson: 'Kaepernick Effect' to Blame for NFL's Ratings Decline|date=September 23, 2017|website=FoxNews.com|url=http://insider.foxnews.com/2017/09/23/president-trump-slams-colin-kaepernick-nfl-national-anthem-protests-kevin-jackson-reacts|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924064351/http://insider.foxnews.com/2017/09/23/president-trump-slams-colin-kaepernick-nfl-national-anthem-protests-kevin-jackson-reacts|archivedate=September 28, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Since 2017, many players also began protesting against President [[Donald Trump]]'s<ref name=\"insider.foxnews.com\"/> criticisms of those involved in the protest as well as against Trump's policies since taking office.<ref name=\"insider.foxnews.com\"/> Some observers have described the protests as politically motivated or patriotic, while others have criticized the attention to [[social issue]]s during [[sport|sporting events]], and others have called the protests unpatriotic or disrespectful. The act itself is referred to as \"taking a knee\" or \"taking the knee\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Mindock|first=Clark|title=Taking a knee: Why are NFL players protesting and when did they start kneeling?|date=September 26, 2017|newspaper=The Independent|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/taking-a-knee-national-anthem-nfl-trump-why-meaning-origins-racism-us-colin-kaepernick-a7966961.html|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Hafner|first=Josh|title=Anthem kneeling isn't aimed at veterans, and other NFL protest misconceptions|date=September 25, 2017|newspaper=USA Today|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2017/09/25/anthem-kneeling-isnt-aimed-veterans-and-other-nfl-protest-misconceptions/701409001/|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe protests began in the [[National Football League]] (NFL) after [[San Francisco 49ers]] [[quarterback]] [[Colin Kaepernick]] sat and later [[knelt]] during the anthem, before his team's [[National Football League preseason|preseason]] games of [[2016 NFL season|2016]].<ref name=\"SB\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sbnation.com/2016/9/11/12869726/colin-kaepernick-national-anthem-protest-seahawks-brandon-marshall-nfl|title=A timeline of Colin Kaepernick's national anthem protest and the NFL players who joined him|last1=Sandritter|first1=Mark|publisher=SB Nation|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160912110107/https://www.sbnation.com/2016/9/11/12869726/colin-kaepernick-national-anthem-protest-seahawks-brandon-marshall-nfl|archive-date=September 12, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 11, 2016}}</ref> Throughout the following seasons, members of various NFL and other sports teams have engaged in similar silent protests. On September 24, 2017, the NFL protests became more widespread when over 200 players sat or knelt in response to President Trump's calling for owners to \"fire\" the protesting players.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/24/donald-trump-nfl-player-protests-national-anthem-week-3-response/697609001/|title=NFL player protests sweep league after President Donald Trump's hostile remarks|work=USA Today|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925041022/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/24/donald-trump-nfl-player-protests-national-anthem-week-3-response/697609001/|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\n{{further|U.S. national anthem protests}}\nIt is a tradition in the United States to play \"[[The Star-Spangled Banner]]\", the [[national anthem]], before sporting events.<ref name=\":2\" /> According to the [[United States Code]], those present should stand at attention with right hand over heart.<ref>{{usc|36|301}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Title 36 United States Code: \u00a7 301. National Anthem.|url= https://www.senate.gov/reference/resources/pdf/RL30243.pdf#page=11|publisher= [[United States Senate]]|date= October 31, 2016|accessdate= June 5, 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180710143658/https://www.senate.gov/reference/resources/pdf/RL30243.pdf#page=11|archive-date= July 10, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-37208404|title= What must Americans do during the anthem?|date= September 25, 2017|work= BBC News|access-date= September 27, 2017|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170924150335/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-37208404|archive-date= September 24, 2017|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref> [[National Football League]] (NFL) players were not mandated to be on the field for the playing of the national anthem until 2009.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite news|last= Willingham|first= AJ|title= The national anthem in sports (spoiler: it wasn't always this way)|url= http://www.cnn.com/2017/09/25/us/nfl-national-anthem-trump-kaepernick-history-trnd/index.html|publisher= [[Time Warner]]|website= CNN.com|date= September 25, 2017|accessdate= June 5, 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180605102013/https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/25/us/nfl-national-anthem-trump-kaepernick-history-trnd/index.html|archive-date= June 5, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref>  In 2016 the NFL stated that \"players are encouraged but not required to stand during the playing of the National Anthem\"; its game operations manual reads that players \"should stand\" for the anthem.<ref>{{cite news|last= O'Malley|first= Nick|title= NFL rulebook does not require players to stand for national anthem; Game Operations manual does|date= September 26, 2017|work= MassLive.com|url= http://blog.masslive.com/patriots/2017/09/facebook_post_citing_nfl_playe.html|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20171010060237/http://blog.masslive.com/patriots/2017/09/facebook_post_citing_nfl_playe.html|archivedate= October 10, 2017|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nThe people of the United States are divided on the intended meaning of the anthem. Some believe it salutes military and police officers who have died on duty; for others, it honors the United States generally.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite news|last= Brady|first= Erik|title= How national anthem became essential part of sports|url= https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/26/how-national-anthem-become-essential-part-sports/706243001/|newspaper= USA Today|date= September 27, 2017|accessdate= June 5, 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180618180904/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/26/how-national-anthem-become-essential-part-sports/706243001/|archive-date= June 18, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1= Har|first1= Janie|last2= Contreras|first2= Russell|title= Diverse America divided on flag, anthem, other symbols|date= September 16, 2016|publisher= Associated Press|url= https://apnews.com/1959daeed38b466395f053f6f9b2dc52/diverse-america-divided-flag-anthem-other-symbols|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20171207181301/https://apnews.com/1959daeed38b466395f053f6f9b2dc52/diverse-america-divided-flag-anthem-other-symbols|archivedate= December 7, 2017|url-status= live}}</ref> Between 2012 and 2015, the [[United States Department of Defense|Department of Defense]] gave $6.8 million to teams across all major sports in exchange for holding various military and patriotic events at their games, including the performance of the national anthem.<ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.mccain.senate.gov/public/_cache/files/12de6dcb-d8d8-4a58-8795-562297f948c1/tackling-paid-patriotism-oversight-report.pdf|title= Tackling Paid Patriotism|last= McCain|first= John|last2= Flake|first2= Jeff|date= 2015|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180804100831/https://www.mccain.senate.gov/public/_cache/files/12de6dcb-d8d8-4a58-8795-562297f948c1/tackling-paid-patriotism-oversight-report.pdf|archive-date= August 4, 2018|url-status= dead|df= mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nKaepernick and his 49ers teammate [[Eric Reid (American football)|Eric Reid]] say they choose to kneel during the anthem to call attention to the issues of racial inequality and police brutality. \"After hours of careful consideration, and even a visit from [[Nate Boyer]], a retired [[Special Forces (United States Army)|Green Beret]] and former NFL player, we came to the conclusion that we should kneel, rather than sit, ... during the anthem as a peaceful protest,\" said Reid. \"We chose to kneel because it's a [[respect]]ful gesture.  I remember thinking our posture was like a flag flown at half-mast to mark a tragedy.\"<ref>{{cite news|last= Reid|first= Eric|title= Opinion {{!}} Eric Reid: Why Colin Kaepernick and I Decided to Take a Knee|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/25/opinion/colin-kaepernick-football-protests.html|newspaper= [[The New York Times]]|date= September 25, 2017|access-date= September 27, 2017|issn= 0362-4331|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170926221519/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/25/opinion/colin-kaepernick-football-protests.html|archive-date= September 26, 2017|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref> Some regard kneeling as disrespectful to those who have died or been wounded in service of the United States, such as police officers or military veterans.<ref>{{cite news|last= MacQuarrie|first= Brian|title= Military veterans divided over NFL protests|url= https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2017/09/25/military/MLjykBWSTbMlWqbaVUAGzI/story.html|newspaper= The Boston Globe|date= September 27, 2017|access-date= June 5, 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180618175552/https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2017/09/25/military/MLjykBWSTbMlWqbaVUAGzI/story.html|archive-date= June 18, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref> [[Torrey Smith]], a wide receiver for the [[Carolina Panthers]], said in an interview: \"I understand why people are offended by people protesting the National Anthem. My father served 25 years. When he dies, he's going to be wrapped in an American flag. But my dad is also out of the Army, and he drives trucks all over the country, and he's a black man everywhere he goes, and sometimes he has racial incidents still today. That doesn't protect him, just because he served our country. And I think that's important.\"<ref>\n{{Cite news|url= https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/27/us/nfl-anthem-protest-race-trump-trnd/index.html|title= The #TakeAKnee protests have always been about race. Period.|last= CNN|first= AJ Willingham|work= CNN|access-date= 2018-06-18|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180618175526/https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/27/us/nfl-anthem-protest-race-trump-trnd/index.html|archive-date= June 18, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}\n</ref>\n\nKaepernick has mentioned before that the sole purpose of kneeling during the national anthem is not to disrespect the military personnel at all, instead Kaepernick's goal is to use his social platform to bring topics regarding police brutality and  oppression of people of color to light. \"I am not going to get up to show pride in a country that oppresses black people and people of color.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/25/opinion/football-protests-police-violence-anthem.html|title=Opinion {{!}} Football Players Are Protesting Police Violence, Not the Anthem|last=Cauley|first=Kashana|date=2018-08-25|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-04-10|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Kaepernick even went ahead an express his concerns about how his action have been labeled as \"anthem protest\" since he considers this to be a shameful strategy from his critics to deviate the discussion from what really matters. \"To me, this is bigger than football and it would be selfish to look the other way. There are bodies in the street and people getting paid leave and getting away with murder.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|title=getting-away-with-murder|doi = 10.1163/2210-7975_hrd-1323-0125}}</ref>\n\nBy labelling the action of kneeling as anthem protest, critics have been successful at switching the topic of discussion to anything except police brutality. After Kaepernick started his campaign to create awareness about excess police brutality towards minorities, especially African-Americans, commentators have mainly shifted focus to the patriotic aspect of kneeling rather than the meaning behind it; thus weakening Kaepernick's primary goal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2016/sep/16/colin-kaepernick-protest-racial-iniquity-nfl-american-football|title=Colin Kaepernick's critics are ignoring the target of his protest|last=Graham|first=Bryan Armen|date=2016-09-16|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-04-10|last2=Carpenter|first2=Les|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> One political person that players believe completely misinterpreted the act of kneeling was President Trump, since he believes that players are protesting the flag and the national anthem; however, players are for the most part protesting the lack of accountability in the judicial system, and the way police officers can easily get away with police brutality towards African-Americans.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2017/09/why-the-nfl-is-protesting/540927/|title=They Took a Knee|last=Garber|first=Megan|date=2017-09-24|website=The Atlantic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref>\n\nKaepernick was not able to sign a contract with any NFL team even after he opted out of his contract with the 49ers and became a free agent in 2017, presumably because of his actions of taking a knee.<ref name=\"Reid\">{{Cite web|url=https://theundefeated.com/features/how-colin-kaepernick-became-a-cause-for-activists-civil-rights-groups/|title=How Colin Kaepernick became a cause for activists, civil rights groups and others|last=Reid|first=Jason|date=2017-08-22|website=The Undefeated|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref> Nevertheless, even though Kaepernick was no longer on the sideline, his movement did not stop but rather gained more participants.<ref name=\"Reid\"/>\n\n== Causes ==\n[[File:Police_protest.jpg|thumb|left|Protestors demanding police accountability.]]\n[[Criminal justice reform in the United States|Criminal justice reform]] is one of the top issues that NFL players have been supporting in their protests.<ref>{{cite news|last=Reid|first=Jason|title=NFL owners, players are moving in the wrong direction|date=October 30, 2017|work=The Undefeated|url=https://theundefeated.com/features/nfl-owners-players-are-moving-in-the-wrong-direction/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030163548/https://theundefeated.com/features/nfl-owners-players-are-moving-in-the-wrong-direction/|archivedate=October 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Kaepernick was initially moved to protest by the deaths of African-Americans at the hands of police or while in police custody. These deaths gained prominence through the media and the [[Black Lives Matter]] movement in the years immediately preceding the protest.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/news_and_politics/jurisprudence/2016/10/ruth_bader_ginsburg_s_kaepernick_comments_end_the_notorious_rbg_myth.html|title=Ruth Bader Ginsburg Was Never Really \"Notorious RBG\"|last=Stern|first=Mark Joseph|date=October 11, 2016|work=Slate|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> During a post-game interview on August 26, 2016, he stated, \"I am not going to stand up to show pride in a flag for a country that oppresses [[black people]] and [[people of color]]. To me, this is bigger than football and it would be selfish on my part to look the other way. There are bodies in the street and people getting paid leave and getting away with murder\", adding that he would continue to protest during the anthem until he feels like \"[the United States flag] represents what it's supposed to represent.\"<ref name=\"wyche\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000691077/article/colin-kaepernick-explains-protest-of-national-anthem|title=Colin Kaepernick explains why he sat during national anthem|last=Wyche|first=Steve|date=August 27, 2016|publisher=National Football League|accessdate=August 27, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827165405/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000691077/article/colin-kaepernick-explains-protest-of-national-anthem|archive-date=August 27, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/09/18/colin-kaepernick-nfl-black-lives-matter-protests-recall-rebellio/|title=Colin Kaepernick: NFL Black Lives Matter protests recall rebellious spirit of 1960s sporting greats|author=Nick Allen|date=September 18, 2016|newspaper=The Telegraph|accessdate=November 8, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161130224836/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/09/18/colin-kaepernick-nfl-black-lives-matter-protests-recall-rebellio/|archive-date=November 30, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAfter that interview, Kaepernick pledged to donate the first $1 million of his $11.9 million salary from the 2016\u20132017 season to different organizations that help communities in need.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/colin-kaepernick-says-hell-donate-1-million-to-charities-that-help-communities-in-need/|title=Colin Kaepernick to donate $1&nbsp;million to charities that aid communities in need|last1=Wagner-McGough|first1=Sean|date=September 2, 2016|publisher=cbssports.com|accessdate=October 17, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017042221/http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/colin-kaepernick-says-hell-donate-1-million-to-charities-that-help-communities-in-need/|archive-date=October 17, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He pledged to donate $100,000 per month for 10 months to various organizations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ninerswire.usatoday.com/2016/09/20/colin-kaepernick-to-donate-100k-a-month-for-10-months/|title=Colin Kaepernick to donate $100k a month for 10 months|last1=Biderman|first1=Chris|work=USA Today|format=September 20, 2016|accessdate=October 17, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018213014/http://ninerswire.usatoday.com/2016/09/20/colin-kaepernick-to-donate-100k-a-month-for-10-months/|archive-date=October 18, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 20, 2016}}</ref> Days later, the San Francisco 49ers matched Kaepernick by pledging $1 million to two organizations addressing racial and social inequality.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/nfl/la-sp-colin-kaepernick-49ers-donation-20160908-snap-story.html|title=49ers to donate $1&nbsp;million to charities that focus on racial issues cited by Colin Kaepernick|last1=Loumena|first1=Dan|date=September 9, 2016|work=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=October 17, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018225111/http://www.latimes.com/sports/nfl/la-sp-colin-kaepernick-49ers-donation-20160908-snap-story.html|archive-date=October 18, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick has been following through on his commitment and has donated $900,000 as of September 2017 to groups including [[Meals on Wheels]], United We Dream, Black Veterans for Social Justice and many others.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/08/colin-kaepernick-nfl-national-anthem-protest-one-million-dollar-pledge-donations-empower-communities|title=Colin Kaepernick has donated $800k to empower oppressed communities|date=August 23, 2017|work=For The Win|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928010003/http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/08/colin-kaepernick-nfl-national-anthem-protest-one-million-dollar-pledge-donations-empower-communities|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/maurybrown/2017/09/15/dont-ignore-this-positive-pr-twist-to-colin-kaepernick/#77a7a1d35740|title=Don't Ignore This Positive PR Twist To Colin Kaepernick|last=Brown|first=Maury|work=Forbes|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928010447/https://www.forbes.com/sites/maurybrown/2017/09/15/dont-ignore-this-positive-pr-twist-to-colin-kaepernick/#77a7a1d35740|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick has also held \"Know Your Rights\" camps for young [[People of Color|people of color]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://knowyourrightscamp.com/about/|title=About Us \u2013 Know Your Rights Camp|website=knowyourrightscamp.com|access-date=2017-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107012755/http://knowyourrightscamp.com/about/|archive-date=November 7, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>  The camps include legal education from attorneys that give advice on how to interact with police when being detained and lectures from prominent academics on the history of the [[Civil Rights Movement]] in the United States.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenation.com/article/colin-kaepernicks-message-to-chicago-youth-know-your-rights/|title=Colin Kaepernick's Message to Chicago Youth: 'Know Your Rights'|last=Zirin|first=Dave|date=May 10, 2017|work=The Nation|access-date=September 27, 2017|issn=0027-8378|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928010247/https://www.thenation.com/article/colin-kaepernicks-message-to-chicago-youth-know-your-rights/|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2016/10/30/colin-kaepernick-holds-know-your-rights-camp-for-underprivileged-bay-area-kids/|title=Colin Kaepernick holds 'Know Your Rights' camp for underprivileged Bay Area kids|last=Bieler|first=Des|date=October 30, 2016|work=Washington Post|access-date=September 27, 2017|issn=0190-8286|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928005714/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2016/10/30/colin-kaepernick-holds-know-your-rights-camp-for-underprivileged-bay-area-kids/|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The [[National Football League Players Association]] (NFLPA) named Kaepernick the Week One MVP in September 2017 for his charity work related to the protest.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/15/nfl-players-union-names-colin-kaepernick-its-week-1-mvp-for-his-charity-work/|title=NFL players' union names Colin Kaepernick its Week 1 MVP for his charity work|last=Payne|first=Marissa|date=September 15, 2017|work=Washington Post|access-date=September 27, 2017|issn=0190-8286|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928005350/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/15/nfl-players-union-names-colin-kaepernick-its-week-1-mvp-for-his-charity-work/|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick also joined the 10 for 10 challenge, which basically consists of donating ten thousand dollars for ten consecutive days. Some major celebrities that matched Kaepernick's donations include basketball players [[Steph Curry]] and [[Kevin Durant]], tennis player [[Serena Williams]], and rappers [[Snoop Dogg]], [[Meek Mill]], and [[Usher (musician)|Usher]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/jan/31/colin-kaepernick-million-dollar-pledge-goal|title=Colin Kaepernick reaches $1m pledge goal with help from famous friends|last=sport|first=Guardian|date=2018-01-31|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-04-10|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\n=== Trump calls for firing protesting players===\n{{see also|Protests against Donald Trump}}\n[[File:Donald Trump with jersey, helmet and football of New England Patriots.jpg|thumb|President Trump meeting with the players and staff of [[New England Patriots]] at the [[White House]] on April 19, 2017 following their [[Super Bowl LI]] win over the [[Atlanta Falcons]].]]\nIn September 2017 at a rally in [[Huntsville, Alabama]], President Trump said NFL owners should fire players who kneel during the national anthem and encouraged fans to walk out. Trump advised NFL owners, \"get that son of a bitch off the field right now, out, he's fired. He's fired!\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/09/23/media/donald-trump-nfl-protest-backlash/index.html|title=With 'son of a bitch' comments, Trump tried to divide NFL and its players|last=Stelter|first=Brian|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924064744/http://money.cnn.com/2017/09/23/media/donald-trump-nfl-protest-backlash/index.html|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 23, 2017}}</ref> He called the players' protest \"a total disrespect of our heritage\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trump-to-nfl-owners-fire-players-who-kneel-during-national-anthem/|title=Trump to NFL owners: Fire players who kneel during national anthem|date=September 23, 2017|publisher=CBS News|access-date=September 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923151054/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trump-to-nfl-owners-fire-players-who-kneel-during-national-anthem/|archive-date=September 23, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Trump added on that the new NFL safety rules created to protect players from [[Concussions in American football|concussions]] were ruining the game for the public.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/26/congresswoman-trump-endangering-nfl-players-with-reckless-comments-about-safety/|title=Congresswoman: Trump endangering NFL players with 'reckless' comments about safety|last=Payne|first=Marissa|date=September 26, 2017|work=Washington Post|access-date=September 27, 2017|issn=0190-8286|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928005425/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/26/congresswoman-trump-endangering-nfl-players-with-reckless-comments-about-safety/|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> His statement came after a new research indicated that NFL players are at high risk for [[chronic traumatic encephalopathy]] (CTE) due to the likelihood of multiple head injuries.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2017/07/25/539198429/study-cte-found-in-nearly-all-donated-nfl-player-brains|title=Study: CTE Found In Nearly All Donated NFL Player Brains|work=NPR.org|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002145718/http://www.npr.org/2017/07/25/539198429/study-cte-found-in-nearly-all-donated-nfl-player-brains|archive-date=October 2, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nTrump said his criticism of the protesters was not related to race. \"This has to do with respect for our country and respect for our flag,\" he said.<ref>{{cite news|first1=Bryan Armen|last1=Graham|first2=Martin|last2=Pengelly|title=NFL players kneel for anthem in unprecedented defiance of Trump|date=September 24, 2017|newspaper=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/sep/24/donald-trump-nfl-protests-kneel-anthem|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171026045803/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/sep/24/donald-trump-nfl-protests-kneel-anthem|archivedate=October 26, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In the games immediately following Trump's statements, the protest gained broader participation when over 200 players sat or knelt during the anthem, others linked arms with their teammates or raised fists, and three teams chose to stay in the locker room for the anthem.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\"SB\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html|title=After Trump Blasts N.F.L., Players Kneel and Lock Arms in Solidarity|last=Hoffman|first=Benjamin|date=September 24, 2017|work=The New York Times|access-date=September 27, 2017|last2=Mather|first2=Victor|issn=0362-4331|last3=Fortin|first3=Jacey|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927160450/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html|archive-date=September 27, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> However, the response quickly turned into one towards Trump, rather than Kaepernick's original protests of racial injustice.<ref name=\":4\"/><ref name=\"latimes.com\">{{cite news|last1=Farmer|first1=Sam|last2=King|first2=Laura|title=As Trump continues his attacks, NFL players protest by kneeling or locking arms|date=September 24, 2017|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/nfl/la-sp-nfl-players-protest-trump-20170924-story.html|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Jones|first=Jonathan|title=A Gesture of Support by NFL Owners Is Meaningless without Them Taking Real Action|date=September 26, 2017|website=SI.com|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2017/09/26/nfl-anthem-protests-team-owners-shad-khan-dan-snyder|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Reasons cited by players, owners, and coaches included supporting freedom of speech and opposing what they considered intimidation by Trump.<ref name=\":4\" /> Others said they took offense to Trump demeaning the integrity of their primarily African American colleagues, when a month earlier he had hesitated to condemn the  [[white nationalists]] who [[Unite the Right rally|protested in Charlottesville, Virginia]] and murdered a counter protester.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sbnation.com/2017/9/23/16354502/donald-trump-nfl-players-reactions-national-anthem-protests-twitter|title=NFL players respond with heat to Donald Trump's comments about protests|work=SBNation.com|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928010201/https://www.sbnation.com/2017/9/23/16354502/donald-trump-nfl-players-reactions-national-anthem-protests-twitter|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/nfl-eric-reid-donald-trump-race-row-neo-nazis-charlottesville-fine-people-president-us-latest-a7967811.html|title=NFL player who started anti-Trump movement: 'He refers to us with slurs but Charlottesville neo-Nazis as 'very fine people'|date=September 26, 2017|work=The Independent|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928103059/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/nfl-eric-reid-donald-trump-race-row-neo-nazis-charlottesville-fine-people-president-us-latest-a7967811.html|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The reaction to Trump's remarks were amidst other ongoing issues his administration was facing, including failed [[American Health Care Act of 2017|attempts at healthcare reform]], the primary election loss of Trump-backed candidate [[Luther Strange]] for the [[United States Senate special election in Alabama, 2017|Alabama seat in the U.S. Senate]], recovery efforts for [[Hurricane Maria]] in Puerto Rico, [[Hurricane Irma]] in Florida, and [[Hurricane Harvey]] in [[Houston]], and [[North Korea\u2013United States relations|relations with North Korea]] over their [[2017 North Korean nuclear test|nuclear]] and [[2017 North Korean missile tests|missile testing]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Donald Trump fuels NFL anthem row by tweeting year old video|date=October 1, 2017|newspaper=The Telegraph|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/10/01/donald-trump-fuels-nfl-anthem-row-tweeting-year-old-video/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171001063651/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/10/01/donald-trump-fuels-nfl-anthem-row-tweeting-year-old-video/|archivedate=October 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMany players beyond the 2017 season have knelt or raised fists in protest against Trump's policies.<ref name=\":4\"/><ref name=\"latimes.com\"/> Other Republicans such as Florida senator [[Marco Rubio]] also expressed their discomforts against these policies as well. While Rubio's objections were not aimed directly to President Trump directly, he did support the rights of players of kneeling during the national anthem, especially [[Miami Dolphins]] player [[Kenny Stills]]. Rubio tweeted, \"No @NFL player does more community service than @KStills of the @MiamiDolphins. You don\u2019t have to agree with how or why he has chosen to exercise the 1st Amendment before every game to acknowledge the hours he gives voluntarily, on his day off, to serve his fellow Americans.\"<ref name=\"Deen\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/fl-sp-dolphins-marco-rubio-kenny-stills-20180913-story.html|title=Sen. Marco Rubio praises Dolphins receiver Kenny Stills for community service|last=Deen|first=Safid|date=|website=latimes.com|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190427002116/https://www.latimes.com/fl-sp-dolphins-marco-rubio-kenny-stills-20180913-story.html|archive-date=2018-04-27|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> Senator Marco Rubio has also expressed his feeling about Kaepernick, and while he publicly stated that he does not agree with what Kaepernick does (taking a knee during the national anthem), he does support his rights that allows him to do so and he believes that the NFL should not prohibit him from playing in the league again.<ref name=\"Deen\"/>\n\nIn a May 2018 interview, Trump stated \"You have to stand proudly for the national anthem, or you shouldn't be playing, you shouldn't be there. Maybe you shouldn't be in the country\". He applauded\u00a0the new policy that NFL players must either stand for the anthem or stay back in the locker room, but felt that this policy was not strict enough.<ref name=\"nbcnews.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/donald-trump/trump-says-nfl-players-who-kneel-during-national-anthem-maybe-n876996|title=Trump says athletes who kneel during anthem 'maybe shouldn't be in the country'|website=NBC News|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120225813/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/donald-trump/trump-says-nfl-players-who-kneel-during-national-anthem-maybe-n876996|archive-date=January 20, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==NFL protests==\n\n===2016 preseason===\nKaepernick began sitting during the national anthem at the start of the 2016 NFL preseason. His actions went unnoticed for two weeks before he was questioned by the media.<ref>{{cite news|last=Levin|first=Josh|title=Colin Kaepernick's Protest Is Working|date=September 12, 2016|work=Slate|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/sports/sports_nut/2016/09/colin_kaepernick_s_protest_is_working.html|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In the 49ers' final 2016 preseason game on September 1, 2016, after talking to Boyer, Kaepernick opted to kneel during the U.S. national anthem rather than sit as he did in their previous games. He explained his decision to switch was an attempt to show more respect to former and current U.S. military members while still protesting during the anthem.  [[Eric Reid (American football)|Eric Reid]] joined Kaepernick in kneeling during the national anthem during the final preseason game.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/sep/01/colin-kaepernick-eric-reid-kneel-national-anthem-protest-san-francisco-49ers|title=Colin Kaepernick joined by Eric Reid in kneeling for national anthem protest|last=Press|first=Associated|date=September 1, 2016|newspaper=The Guardian|issn=0261-3077|access-date=September 7, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160907050158/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/sep/01/colin-kaepernick-eric-reid-kneel-national-anthem-protest-san-francisco-49ers|archive-date=September 7, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Seattle Seahawks]] player [[Jeremy Lane]] also did not stand for the anthem during his final preseason game the same day, stating, \"It's something I plan to keep on doing until justice is being served.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/seahawks/2016/09/01/jeremy-lane-colin-kaepernick-national-anthem-protest/89752460/|title=Seahawks' Jeremy Lane joins Colin Kaepernick's protest, sits during national anthem|access-date=September 7, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160905103948/http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/seahawks/2016/09/01/jeremy-lane-colin-kaepernick-national-anthem-protest/89752460/|archive-date=September 5, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===2016 season===\nIn Week 1, eleven NFL players joined Kaepernick's protests.<ref name=\"breech\">{{cite web|last1=Breech|first1=John|title=Here are the 11 players who joined Colin Kaepernick's protest in Week 1|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/here-are-the-11-players-who-joined-colin-kaepernicks-protest-in-week-1/|publisher=CBS News|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918003249/http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/here-are-the-11-players-who-joined-colin-kaepernicks-protest-in-week-1/|archive-date=September 18, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Denver Broncos]] player [[Brandon Marshall (linebacker)|Brandon Marshall]] knelt during the national anthem prior to the start of the [[National Football League Kickoff game|Kickoff game]], which was broadcast on [[NBC Sunday Night Football|NBC]].<ref name=\"money\">{{cite web|last1=Scott|first1=Nate|title=Broncos linebacker Brandon Marshall takes knee during national anthem|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2016/09/broncos-brandon-marshall-takes-knee-national-anthem-colin-kaepernick|work=USA Today|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923104532/http://ftw.usatoday.com/2016/09/broncos-brandon-marshall-takes-knee-national-anthem-colin-kaepernick|archive-date=September 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 9, 2016}}</ref> The act of kneeling as protest has been referred to as \"taking a knee\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/what-the-nfl-take-a-knee-protests-mean/2017/09/26/4915930e-a210-11e7-b573-8ec86cdfe1ed_story.html|title=Opinion {{!}} What the NFL take-a-knee protests mean|website=Washington Post|access-date=2017-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171003075819/https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/what-the-nfl-take-a-knee-protests-mean/2017/09/26/4915930e-a210-11e7-b573-8ec86cdfe1ed_story.html|archive-date=October 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/09/30/us/costas-nfl-cnntv/index.html|title=Bob Costas: Stand for anthem, then take a knee|first=Alexandra |last=King|work=CNN|access-date=2017-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171003124816/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/09/30/us/costas-nfl-cnntv/index.html|archive-date=October 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/taking-a-knee-national-anthem-nfl-trump-why-meaning-origins-racism-us-colin-kaepernick-a7966961.html|title=All you need to know about why NFL players are taking a knee and where it came from|date=2017-09-25|work=The Independent|access-date=2017-10-03|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archive-date=September 27, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick and Marshall were teammates at the [[University of Nevada]].<ref name=\"money\"/>\n\nKaepernick and Marshall were by no means the first pro football players to be seen kneeling on the field.  Beginning in 2011, a white quarterback named [[Tim Tebow]] was seen kneeling on the sidelines, as if in prayer, often enough to inspire the [[neologism]] \"Tebowing.\"  Tebow was awarded a trademark for that term in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap1000000082438/article/tim-tebow-awarded-trademark-to-tebowing|title=Tim Tebow awarded trademark to Tebowing|work=[[National Football League]]|date=October 19, 2012|accessdate=October 19, 2012}}</ref> (Tebow's actions were not considered controversial at the time.)\n\nOn September 11, [[Kansas City Chiefs]] cornerback [[Marcus Peters]] [[raised fist|raised his fist]] while the rest of the team interlocked their arms showing [[solidarity]].<ref name=\"time\">{{cite news|last1=Gajanan|first1=Mahita|title=Kansas City Chiefs Cornerback Marcus Peters Raises Fist During National Anthem|url=http://time.com/4486853/kansas-city-chiefs-marcus-peters-national-anthem/|work=Time|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160917233412/http://time.com/4486853/kansas-city-chiefs-marcus-peters-national-anthem/|archive-date=September 17, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Two members of the [[New England Patriots]], [[Devin McCourty]] and [[Martellus Bennett]], raised their fists on ''[[NBC Sunday Night Football|Sunday Night Football]]''. The entire Seattle Seahawks team stood and interlocked arms.<ref name=\"arnold\">{{cite web|last1=Arnold|first1=Geoffrey|title=Seattle Seahawks lock arms during national anthem|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/nfl/index.ssf/2016/09/seattle_seahawks_lock_arms_dur.html|work=The Oregonian|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923114745/http://www.oregonlive.com/nfl/index.ssf/2016/09/seattle_seahawks_lock_arms_dur.html|archive-date=September 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 12, 2016}}</ref> [[Jelani Jenkins]], [[Arian Foster]], [[Kenny Stills]], and [[Michael Thomas (defensive back)|Michael Thomas]] of the [[Miami Dolphins]] all knelt during the National Anthem.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ajc.com/sports/miami-dolphins-kneel-during-national-anthem/tVERFq0ty4uFmEqT2ULKCL/|title=4 Miami Dolphins kneel during national anthem|first=Hal|last=Habib|website=ajc|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906141157/http://www.ajc.com/sports/miami-dolphins-kneel-during-national-anthem/tVERFq0ty4uFmEqT2ULKCL/|archive-date=September 6, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> At the same time, a group of [[Jacksonville Jaguars]] players, led by cornerback [[Prince Amukamara]], initially planned to join the protest but chose not to do so after photographs of Kaepernick wearing socks with a crude anti-police message during training camp were made public.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/jacksonville-jaguars/post/_/id/19870/jaguars-players-considered-protest-but-pig-socks-derailed-plans|title=Jaguars players considered protest, but pig socks scuttled plans|accessdate=December 16, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123201306/http://www.espn.com/blog/jacksonville-jaguars/post/_/id/19870/jaguars-players-considered-protest-but-pig-socks-derailed-plans|archive-date=November 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=November 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn November 13, 2016, five days after Donald Trump was [[2016 United States presidential election|elected]] [[President of the United States|President]], [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] wide-receiver [[Mike Evans (wide receiver)|Mike Evans]] decided to sit during the national anthem. According to ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'', Evans said, \"If this happens, then America's not right right now. I said this a long time ago. When he ran, I thought it was a joke, and the joke continues. I'm not a political person that much, but I got common sense. And I know when something's not right.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/mike-evans-sat-during-anthem-to-protest-donald-trump-presidency/ |title=Mike Evans sat during anthem to protest Donald Trump presidency |publisher=CBSSports.com |access-date=November 27, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128133213/http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/mike-evans-sat-during-anthem-to-protest-donald-trump-presidency/ |archive-date=November 28, 2016 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> However, his protest began the day following [[Veterans Day]], so he received criticism. He quickly changed his method of protesting and joined his teammates during the following game against the Kansas City Chiefs. He apologized to veterans and other members of the military for his actions \u2013 citing that the timing of his protest was poor. \"On the field, I'm going to continue to do what I do \u2013 play hard. I'm playing hard because I've got this right \u2013 freedom, because of the vets. I'm going to reach out to organizations, organizations that I feel are doing the best job to help the minority ... women, LGBT, African Americans, Latinos, people that are in fear of Donald Trump and his presidency.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/tampa-bay-buccaneers/post/_/id/15124/bucs-mike-evans-stands-for-national-anthem |title=Bucs' Mike Evans ends protest, stands for national anthem |publisher=ESPN |access-date=November 27, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128050728/http://www.espn.com/blog/tampa-bay-buccaneers/post/_/id/15124/bucs-mike-evans-stands-for-national-anthem |archive-date=November 28, 2016 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n===2017 season===\n[[File:Oakland Raiders National Anthem Kneeling (37444579735).jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Oakland Raiders players [[kneeling]] in week{{nbsp}}3]]\n[[Cleveland Browns]] tight end [[Seth DeValve]] became the first white football player to kneel or sit during the anthem on the team's August 21, 2017 preseason game against the [[New York Giants]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadspin.com/seth-devalve-is-the-first-white-player-to-kneel-for-the-1798295618|title=Seth DeValve Is The First White Player To Kneel for the National Anthem|last=Baccellieri|first=Emma|access-date=August 22, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170822053647/http://deadspin.com/seth-devalve-is-the-first-white-player-to-kneel-for-the-1798295618|archive-date=August 22, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> \n[[File:Washington Redskins National Anthem Kneeling (37301887651) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=1.85|Washington Redskins players kneeling before the game with the Oakland Raiders]]\n[[File:San Francisco 49ers National Anthem Kneeling (37721041581).jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Members of the San Francisco 49ers kneeling during the National Anthem before a game against the Washington Redskins in week 6]]\n<!-- See talk page for a discussion regarding this list. -->\nIn Week 3 of the season the majority of games were played two days after Trump made his statements.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Graham|first1=Bryan|title=Donald Trump blasts NFL anthem protesters: 'Get that son of a bitch off the field'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/sep/22/donald-trump-nfl-national-anthem-protests|website=theguardian|publisher=Guardian News|accessdate=3 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923222421/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/sep/22/donald-trump-nfl-national-anthem-protests|archive-date=September 23, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The protest gained broader participation when over 200 players sat or knelt during the anthem.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"SB\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{cite news|title=Cowboys are one of six NFL teams that haven't had a player kneel, sit or raise a fist during national anthem|date=September 25, 2017|newspaper=The Dallas Morning News|url=https://sportsday.dallasnews.com/dallas-cowboys/cowboys/2017/09/25/cowboys-one-six-nfl-teams-player-kneel-sit-national-anthem|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Many players, coaches and NFL teams protested and/or issued statements expressing dismay with Trump's comments:<ref name=\"ESPN.com\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/nflnation/post/_/id/249755/nfl-players-who-protested-during-the-national-anthem-in-week-3|title=NFL players who protested during the national anthem in Week 3|publisher=ESPN|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925014751/http://www.espn.com/blog/nflnation/post/_/id/249755/nfl-players-who-protested-during-the-national-anthem-in-week-3|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* Twenty-seven members of the [[Baltimore Ravens]] and [[Jacksonville Jaguars]] knelt during the American National Anthem at their game at [[Wembley Stadium]] in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/sep/24/donald-trump-defied-wembley-jaguars-ravens-nfl-kneel-anthem|title=Donald Trump defied at Wembley as Jaguars and Ravens kneel for anthem|last=Wembley|first=Sean Ingle at|date=September 24, 2017|work=The Guardian|access-date=September 25, 2017|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924205616/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/sep/24/donald-trump-defied-wembley-jaguars-ravens-nfl-kneel-anthem|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Retired Ravens star and honorary Team Captain [[Ray Lewis]] knelt with members of his team.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/ravens/ravens-insider/bs-sp-ravens-anthem-protest-20170924-story.html|title=Some Ravens and Jaguars take knee during national anthem in wake of comments by President Trump|last=Zrebiec|first=Jeff|work=The Baltimore Sun|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083233/http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/ravens/ravens-insider/bs-sp-ravens-anthem-protest-20170924-story.html|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> All of the players stood for the British national anthem \"[[God Save the Queen]]\", with many remaining in locked arms.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Sweeney|first=Don|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/nation-world/world/article175130091.html|title=NFL players in London kneel for the US national anthem but stand for the British one|work=The Miami Herald|date=September 24, 2017|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924183619/http://www.miamiherald.com/news/nation-world/world/article175130091.html|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* Several members of the [[Philadelphia Eagles]] raised their fists during the anthem before their game against the [[New York Giants]]. Before the same game, various Giants players stood with arms locked while others knelt.<ref name=\"NYTimes\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html |title=Tom Brady Joins Anthem Demonstration as N.F.L. Protests Trump Comments |last=Belson |first=Ken |last2=Manchester |first2=Sam |date=September 24, 2017 |website=The New York Times |access-date=September 24, 2017 |last3=Mather |first3=Victor |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924165431/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html |archive-date=September 24, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n* The [[Seattle Seahawks]] and the [[Tennessee Titans]] did not take the field during the playing of the anthem, staying in their locker rooms until it concluded. The players of the Seahawks released a statement saying, \"We will not stand for the injustice that has plagued people of color in this country. Out of love for our country and in honor of the sacrifices made on our behalf, we unite to oppose those that would deny our most basic freedoms.\"<ref name=\"ESPN.com\"/> [[Meghan Linsey]], the Nashville singer who performed the anthem, knelt when she completed the song.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tennessean.com/story/sports/nfl/titans/2017/09/24/meghan-linsey-kneels-after-singing-national-anthem-titans-seahawks-game/698362001/|title=Meghan Linsey kneels after singing national anthem at Titans-Seahawks game|work=The Tennessean|access-date=September 25, 2017}}</ref>\n* Before the opening of their game against the [[Houston Texans]], various [[New England Patriots]] players and staff also expressed their concerns, including quarterback [[Tom Brady]] locking arms with [[Phillip Dorsett]], and head coach [[Bill Belichick]] crossing his arms in front of him. Sixteen members of the Patriots knelt during the anthem.<ref name=\":0\" /> Patriots owner [[Robert Kraft]] said he was disappointed at the tone in which Trump's comments were made.<ref name=\"NYTimes\"/><ref name=\"LAT 2019-02-01\">{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/politics/la-na-pol-trump-nfl-20190201-story.html|title=For years, Trump bashed the NFL and players who protested racial injustice. Here's why he stopped|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|first=Noah|last=Bierman|date=February 2, 2019|accessdate=February 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190201163650/https://www.latimes.com/politics/la-na-pol-trump-nfl-20190201-story.html|archive-date=February 1, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* Several members of the [[Miami Dolphins]] wore \"#IMWITHKAP\" T-shirts on the field during the pregame warmup, in support of Kaepernick's actions.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/24/donald-trump-nfl-player-protests-national-anthem-week-3-response/697609001/|title=NFL player protests sweep league after President Donald Trump's hostile remarks|work=USA Today|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925041022/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/24/donald-trump-nfl-player-protests-national-anthem-week-3-response/697609001/|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The team locked arms during the anthem, with five members kneeling. The opposing team, the [[New York Jets]], also linked arms during the anthem.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/sports/nfl/miami-dolphins/article175171896.html|title=Why did Stills kneel Sunday? Because he felt Trump tried to 'scare' or 'intimidate' him|work=The Miami Herald|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083418/http://www.miamiherald.com/sports/nfl/miami-dolphins/article175171896.html|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> \n* All [[Pittsburgh Steelers]] players except [[Alejandro Villanueva (American football)|Alejandro Villanueva]], who served as an [[United States Army Rangers|Army Ranger]], refused to leave the locker room during the anthem. On the sideline, the [[Chicago Bears]] players locked their arms while the anthem was performed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wgntv.com/2017/09/24/nfl-sunday-kicks-off-amid-beef-between-players-trump/|title=From Chicago to London, NFL players react to Trump's protest critiques|date=September 24, 2017|publisher=WGN-TV|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924233654/http://wgntv.com/2017/09/24/nfl-sunday-kicks-off-amid-beef-between-players-trump/|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Villanueva has since expressed regret for his actions.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.journalnow.com/news/nation_world/villanueva-on-anthem-flap-it-wasn-t-me-stepping-forward/article_62177918-7571-5d91-9bbf-f2337ea908ef.html|title=Villanueva on anthem flap: 'It wasn't me stepping forward'|last=Press|first=Associated|work=Winston-Salem Journal|access-date=2017-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926235724/http://www.journalnow.com/news/nation_world/villanueva-on-anthem-flap-it-wasn-t-me-stepping-forward/article_62177918-7571-5d91-9bbf-f2337ea908ef.html|archive-date=September 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* The majority of the [[Oakland Raiders]] either sat or knelt during the anthem, with several members of the opposing [[Washington Redskins]] either kneeling or joining arms as well.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2017/09/24/raiders-sit-during-national-anthem-they-couldnt-stay-locker-room|title=Most of the Raiders took a seat during national anthem|last=Rollins|first=Khadrice|work=Sports Illustrated|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925063442/https://www.si.com/nfl/2017/09/24/raiders-sit-during-national-anthem-they-couldnt-stay-locker-room|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* Thirty-two members of the [[Denver Broncos]] knelt during the anthem.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.denverpost.com/2017/09/24/von-miller-broncos-kneel-national-anthem/|title=Von Miller among 32 Broncos players who take a knee for national anthem|date=September 24, 2017|work=The Denver Post|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924214352/http://www.denverpost.com/2017/09/24/von-miller-broncos-kneel-national-anthem/|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> At least ten members of the [[Buffalo Bills]] also knelt during the anthem, while other team members locked arms.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newyorkupstate.com/buffalo-bills/index.ssf/2017/09/buffalo_bills_national_anthem_protests_kneeling_racial_injustive_donald_trump.html|title=Buffalo Bills lock arms during national anthem in response to Donald Trump|publisher=NewYorkUpstate.com|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083529/http://www.newyorkupstate.com/buffalo-bills/index.ssf/2017/09/buffalo_bills_national_anthem_protests_kneeling_racial_injustive_donald_trump.html|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Running back [[LeSean McCoy]] said \"My message to him (Trump) is, be a president, be respectful, man. You know, us Americans, we are together. Stop trying to divide us.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pennlive.com/sports/index.ssf/2017/09/lesean_mccoy_says_donald_trump.html|title=LeSean McCoy says Donald Trump should 'be a president,' 'be respectful'|publisher=PennLive.com|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083252/http://www.pennlive.com/sports/index.ssf/2017/09/lesean_mccoy_says_donald_trump.html|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> McCoy performed stretches during the national anthem.\n* The [[Dallas Cowboys]] and [[Arizona Cardinals]] players locked arms during the anthem, while everyone on the Cowboys, including owner and general manager [[Jerry Jones]], knelt before the anthem was played.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Archer|first1=Todd|last2=Weinfuss|first2=Josh|title=Cowboys, Cardinals lock arms for national anthem in show of unity|publisher=ESPN|date=September 26, 2017|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20819786/dallas-cowboys-arizona-cardinals-lock-arms-monday-night-football-game|accessdate=September 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926155554/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20819786/dallas-cowboys-arizona-cardinals-lock-arms-monday-night-football-game|archive-date=September 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* The [[New Orleans Saints]] established a plan with their team prior to their game against the [[Miami Dolphins]] on how they will handle the national anthem before the game. [[Drew Brees]] stood and stated the thoughts of his team as a whole by tweeting \"As a way to show respect to all, our #Saints team will kneel in solidarity prior to the national anthem & stand together during the anthem.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nola.com/saints/index.ssf/2017/09/saints_protest_national_anthem.html|title=Drew Brees: Saints plan to kneel before national anthem, stand during it on Sunday|publisher=2017 NOLA media group|accessdate=October 1, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171001222125/http://www.nola.com/saints/index.ssf/2017/09/saints_protest_national_anthem.html|archive-date=October 1, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* More than ten [[Indianapolis Colts]] and about 20 [[Cleveland Browns]] players knelt on one knee while the remaining players locked arms during the playing of \"[[The Star-Spangled Banner]]\" in [[Indianapolis, Indiana]]. The actions were met by boos from the crowd at [[Lucas Oil Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theindychannel.com/sports/colts/colts-kneel-lock-arms-in-show-of-unity-against-donald-trumps-comments |title=Colts kneel, lock arms in show of unity against Donald Trump's comments |publisher=[[WRTV]] |date=September 24, 2017 |accessdate=October 20, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027205631/http://www.theindychannel.com/sports/colts/colts-kneel-lock-arms-in-show-of-unity-against-donald-trumps-comments |archive-date=October 27, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/nflnation/post/_/id/249755/nfl-players-who-protested-during-the-national-anthem-in-week-3 |title=NFL players who protested during the national anthem in Week 3 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |date=September 25, 2017 |accessdate=October 20, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018233550/http://www.espn.com/blog/nflnation/post/_/id/249755/nfl-players-who-protested-during-the-national-anthem-in-week-3 |archive-date=October 18, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>  Indiana is the home state of Vice President [[Mike Pence]], who weeks later intentionally walked out of a Colts game against the 49ers.<ref>{{cite news|last=Crawford|first=Dakota|title=What is cost for Mike Pence to leave the Colts-49ers game|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/sports/nfl/colts/2017/10/08/vice-president-mike-pences-quick-and-costly-exit-colts-49-ers-game/744668001/|newspaper=[[The Indianapolis Star]]|date=October 8, 2017|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181009073220/https://www.indystar.com/story/sports/nfl/colts/2017/10/08/vice-president-mike-pences-quick-and-costly-exit-colts-49-ers-game/744668001/|archive-date=October 9, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 16, 2017 Colin Kaepernick filed a grievance for collusion against NFL owners. Instead of using the NFLPA, Kaepernick hired Mark Geragos to be his attorney.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21035352/colin-kaepernick-files-grievance-nfl-owners-collusion|title=Kaepernick files grievance claiming collusion|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929000504/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21035352/colin-kaepernick-files-grievance-nfl-owners-collusion|archive-date=September 29, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> As of August 31, 2018, an arbitrator ruled that there is sufficient evidence that the case can continue.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/08/31/643582437/colin-kaepernicks-grievance-against-nfl-moves-forward|title=Colin Kaepernick's Grievance Against NFL Moves Forward|work=NPR.org|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929000443/https://www.npr.org/2018/08/31/643582437/colin-kaepernicks-grievance-against-nfl-moves-forward|archive-date=September 29, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn Week 8 at Seattle, the majority of the Texans players knelt during the anthem after Houston owner [[Bob McNair]] had commented about having the \"inmates running the prison\" during a league owner meeting regarding the ongoing protest. McNair had apologized, stating that he was not referring to the players, but rather to the \"relationship between the league office and team owners\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Barshop|first=Sarah|title=Texans' Duane Brown on kneeling for anthem: Team felt sense of unity playing for each other|date=October 29, 2017|website=ESPN.com|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21215907/majority-houston-texans-players-kneeled-linked-arms-national-anthem|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030025608/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21215907/majority-houston-texans-players-kneeled-linked-arms-national-anthem|archivedate=October 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first1=Seth|last1=Wickersham|first2=Don|last2=Van Natta Jr.|title=Gaffes, TV ratings concerns dominated as NFL, players forged anthem peace|date=October 27, 2017|website=ESPN.com|url=http://www.espn.com/espn/otl/story/_/id/21170410/gaffes-tv-ratings-concerns-dominated-nfl-players-forged-anthem-peace-league-meetings|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171029050500/http://www.espn.com/espn/otl/story/_/id/21170410/gaffes-tv-ratings-concerns-dominated-nfl-players-forged-anthem-peace-league-meetings|archivedate=October 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> It was the first time a Texans player had knelt during the anthem.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wilson|first=Aaron|title=Texans' Duane Brown says Bob McNair meeting 'didn't go too well'|date=October 29, 2017|newspaper=Houston Chronicle|url=http://www.chron.com/sports/texans/article/Majority-of-Texans-kneel-for-national-anthem-12315599.php|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030132035/http://www.chron.com/sports/texans/article/Majority-of-Texans-kneel-for-national-anthem-12315599.php|archivedate=October 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===2018 preseason===\nOn May 23, 2018, NFL Commissioner [[Roger Goodell]] and all NFL team owners, except for two that abstained from voting in a show of hand voting process, approved a new policy that would require all players to stand during the national anthem or be given the option to stay in the locker room during the national anthem. The vote took place without consulting the NFLPA.<ref>{{cite news|last=Healy|first=John|title=NFL admits there was no official vote on national anthem policy, instead informal show of hands|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/football/nfl-admits-no-official-vote-national-anthem-policy-article-1.4009450|newspaper=[[New York Daily News]]|date=May 25, 2018|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526043054/http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/football/nfl-admits-no-official-vote-national-anthem-policy-article-1.4009450|archive-date=May 26, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The policy also stated that any players from all NFL teams who protested the anthem while on the field would become subject to discipline from the league. In addition, the teams as a whole would be subject to punishment and other forms of discipline from the NFL as a result.<ref>{{cite news|last=Knoblauch|first=Austin|title=NFL expected to enact national anthem policy for '18|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000933952/article/nfl-expected-to-enact-national-anthem-policy-for-18|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=NFL.com|date=May 23, 2018|accessdate=May 23, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524003621/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000933952/article/nfl-expected-to-enact-national-anthem-policy-for-18|archive-date=May 24, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Roger Goodell's statement on national anthem policy|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000933962/article/roger-goodells-statement-on-national-anthem-policy|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=NFL.com|date=May 23, 2018|accessdate=May 23, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180523184943/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000933962/article/roger-goodells-statement-on-national-anthem-policy|archive-date=May 23, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn disagreement with the policy, several players on the Super Bowl champions [[Philadelphia Eagles]] indicated that they would decline an invitation from Trump to visit the [[White House]] on June 5, leading the President to rescind the offer the day before the event.<ref>{{cite news|title=Donald Trump calls off Eagles' White House visit over national anthem dispute|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/donald-trump-calls-off-eagles-white-house-visit-players-decline-invitation-232323202.html|publisher=Oath Inc. (Verizon)|website=Yahoo Sports|date=June 4, 2018|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180604235948/https://sports.yahoo.com/donald-trump-calls-off-eagles-white-house-visit-players-decline-invitation-232323202.html|archive-date=June 4, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The Eagles were the second sports franchise that Trump had uninvited, joining the 2017 [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA) champion [[Golden State Warriors]], whose visit was cancelled after several players publicly declined to attend.<ref>{{cite news|title='Fragile egomaniac': Philly Mayor responds to Trump's White House snub|date=June 5, 2018|work=Fox Sports|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/nfl/donald-trump-cancels-the-philadelphia-eagles-visit-to-the-white-house/news-story/e6a2b3c5b5ee2a9f7f0a8b42633e0706|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718112114/https://www.foxsports.com.au/nfl/donald-trump-cancels-the-philadelphia-eagles-visit-to-the-white-house/news-story/e6a2b3c5b5ee2a9f7f0a8b42633e0706|archivedate=July 18, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn July 19, the NFL and the players association issued a joint statement that \"no rules relating to the anthem will be issued for the next several weeks.\" This came after the [[Associated Press]] had reported earlier in the day that Miami team rules stated that improper anthem conduct could result in a player suspension of up to four games, more than some players receive for violating the [[NFL domestic violence policy|league's domestic violence policy]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Orr|first=Connor|title=The Five Hours That Forced the NFL to Reconsider Its Anthem Policy|date=July 20, 2018|website=SI.com|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/07/19/miami-dolphins-national-anthem-policy-rule-nfl-training-camp|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721123241/https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/07/19/miami-dolphins-national-anthem-policy-rule-nfl-training-camp|archivedate=July 21, 2018}}</ref> The following day, Trump tweeted that players should be suspended for one game the first time kneeling, and for the entire season without pay after a second offense.<ref>{{cite news|last=West|first=Jenna|title=Donald Trump Suggests Players Kneeling for Anthem Should Be Suspended for Entire Season|date=July 20, 2018|website=SI.com|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/07/20/donald-trump-national-anthem-policy-players-kneel-no-pay-suspended|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721105831/https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/07/20/donald-trump-national-anthem-policy-players-kneel-no-pay-suspended|archivedate=July 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===2019 Season===\nAs of 2019, only three players in the NFL continue to protest.\n\n[[Eric Reid]] of the [[Carolina Panthers]] continues to kneel and says he will continue to do so in the future. Reid is the first player on the Carolina Panthers to kneel during the playing of the national anthem. <ref>https://www.si.com/nfl/2019/07/29/carolina-panthers-eric-reid-anthem-kneeling</ref>\n\n[[Kenny Stills]] who was traded to the [[Houston Texans]] continues to kneel during the playing of the anthem.<ref>https://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2019/09/09/kenny-stills-took-a-knee-for-the-national-anthem/</ref> Stills says that he will continue to do so even if his job is threatened as a result.<ref>https://sports.yahoo.com/kenny-stills-continue-kneel-during-153502355.html</ref>\n\n[[Albert Wilson (American football)|Albert Wilson]] of the [[Miami Dolphins]] continues to kneel during the playing of the national anthem.<ref>https://thegrio.com/2019/09/11/miami-dolphins-albert-wilson-still-kneels-on-the-field/</ref>\n\n==Other athletes join==\n\n===Soccer===\n[[File:Megan_Rapinoe_USA_vs_Can_Sep17.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Megan Rapinoe]] in 2011]]\n[[Seattle Reign FC]] and [[United States women's national soccer team|U.S. women's national soccer team]] player [[Megan Rapinoe]] knelt during the national anthem in a game on September 5, 2016, explaining that her decision was a \"nod to Kaepernick and everything that he's standing for right now\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/09/05/sport/megan-rapinoe-colin-kaepernick-anthem-kneel/index.html|title=Megan Rapinoe takes knee in solidarity with Kaepernick|last=McKirdy|first=Euan|date=September 5, 2016|publisher=CNN|access-date=September 7, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160906214457/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/09/05/sport/megan-rapinoe-colin-kaepernick-anthem-kneel/index.html|archive-date=September 6, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In a subsequent match at the [[Washington Spirit]], Spirit owner Bill Lynch \u2013 anticipating Rapinoe's protest \u2013 moved the national anthem's performance without warning or notice to occur before the players' appearances on the pitch. [[Jeff Plush]], the league's commissioner, was present at the game and told reporters that he was unaware of Lynch's plans and disagreed with the act of moving the anthem's performance.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/09/07/megan-rapinoe-doesnt-get-chance-to-kneel-for-national-anthem-it-was-played-with-teams-in-locker-room/?tid=a_inl|title=Megan Rapinoe doesn't get chance to kneel for national anthem. It was played with teams in locker room.|date=September 7, 2016|access-date=November 1, 2016|work=The Washington Post|author=Steven Goff|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104003223/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/09/07/megan-rapinoe-doesnt-get-chance-to-kneel-for-national-anthem-it-was-played-with-teams-in-locker-room/?tid=a_inl|archive-date=November 4, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The Spirit's players issued a joint statement also disagreeing with Lynch's decision to move the anthem without first consulting the team's players or coaches.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/09/09/washington-spirit-players-unhappy-with-owners-anthem-move/|title=Washington Spirit players unhappy with owner's anthem move|author=Steven Goff|work=The Washington Post|date=September 9, 2016|access-date=November 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103235815/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/09/09/washington-spirit-players-unhappy-with-owners-anthem-move/|archive-date=November 3, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAs a member of the U.S. women's national soccer team, Rapinoe also knelt before an international [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Thailand women's national football team|Thailand]] on September 16, despite public statements of disagreement with her protest methods issued before the match by the [[U.S. Soccer Federation]] and her coach [[Jill Ellis]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2016/09/15/megan-rapinoe-uswnt-thailand-national-anthem-kneels|title=USWNT's Megan Rapinoe kneels for national anthem before Thailand match|work=[[Sports Illustrated]]|date=September 19, 2016|access-date=November 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026221809/http://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2016/09/15/megan-rapinoe-uswnt-thailand-national-anthem-kneels|archive-date=October 26, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> U.S. Soccer proceeded to pass a policy that now requires all of its players to stand \"respectfully\" during the national anthem, making it the first American sports league or governing body to do so.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sbnation.com/soccer/2017/3/6/14825652/united-states-soccer-national-anthem-policy-megan-rapinoe-protest-ban|title=U.S. Soccer banned Megan Rapinoe's national anthem protest without caring to understand it|work=SBNation.com|access-date=2017-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011073441/https://www.sbnation.com/soccer/2017/3/6/14825652/united-states-soccer-national-anthem-policy-megan-rapinoe-protest-ban|archive-date=October 11, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[Major League Soccer]] (MLS) have released a statement in September 2017 regarding any potential protests \"The march of players, officials and children into our stadiums and singing of the anthem has been a pre-match tradition since our first game in 1996. The National Anthem provides our clubs and fans an important and time-honored opportunity to salute our country and stand up for its principles -- whether in the United States or in Canada.\"<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20848575|title=How national anthem rules differ across sports leagues|date=May 24, 2018|website=ESPN.com|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128082914/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20848575|archive-date=January 28, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> MLS to date, has yet to encounter national anthem protests.\n\nThe protest had supporters outside the U.S. as well; in an October 2017 match against [[Schalke 04]], players and staff of German soccer club [[Hertha Berlin]] took the knee in solidarity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2017/10/14/hertha-berlin-kneel-german-national-anthem-protest|title=Hertha Berlin players take knee during German anthem|last=Rapaport|first=Daniel|date=October 14, 2017|work=Sports Illustrated|access-date=May 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180527202642/https://www.si.com/soccer/2017/10/14/hertha-berlin-kneel-german-national-anthem-protest|archive-date=May 27, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Hertha Berlin has several American players on their roster.\n\n===College===\nOn September 7, 2016, three volleyball players from [[West Virginia University Institute of Technology|West Virginia Tech]] knelt during the national anthem.<ref name=\"kalea\">{{cite web|last1=Gunderson|first1=Kalea|title=West Virginia Tech volleyball players kneel during national anthem|url=http://wchstv.com/news/local/west-virginia-tech-volleyball-players-kneel-during-national-anthem|date=September 7, 2016|publisher=ABC|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921150727/http://wchstv.com/news/local/west-virginia-tech-volleyball-players-kneel-during-national-anthem|archive-date=September 21, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"gibbs\"/>\n\nOn October 1, at [[East Carolina University]], about 19 members of the band knelt, while about another two held the American flag during the national anthem at the beginning of the football game against the [[University of Central Florida]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.witn.com/content/news/395523401.html |title=ECU chancellor, Gov. McCrory speak out about band members kneeling |publisher=WITN-TV |accessdate=November 8, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031084445/http://www.witn.com/content/news/395523401.html |archive-date=October 31, 2016 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> There have been almost no such incidents involving college football players, for the simple reason that college players and coaches are typically in the locker room when the anthem is played. There has been at least one exception to the rule, however. During a September 2016 away game at [[Northwestern Wildcats football|Northwestern]], where players are traditionally on the field during the anthem, three [[Nebraska Cornhuskers football|Nebraska]] players knelt on the sideline.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbnation.com/college-football/2017/9/26/16354940/protests-college-football-nfl-national-anthem|title=Why protests aren't as common in college football|last=Kirshner|first=Alex|date=September 28, 2017|publisher=SB Nation|access-date=October 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008231719/https://www.sbnation.com/college-football/2017/9/26/16354940/protests-college-football-nfl-national-anthem|archive-date=October 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://journalstar.com/sports/huskers/football/prior-to-game-rose-ivey-told-team-of-his-decision/article_781e987e-82b0-11e6-93cc-53559523f8fe.html|title=Prior to game, Rose-Ivey told team of his decision to kneel for anthem|last=Christopherson|first=Brian|work=Lincoln Journal Star|access-date=October 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008231552/http://journalstar.com/sports/huskers/football/prior-to-game-rose-ivey-told-team-of-his-decision/article_781e987e-82b0-11e6-93cc-53559523f8fe.html|archive-date=October 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The NCAA football rulebook does not address the issue of pregame ceremonies (patriotic or otherwise) at all, except to say that team captains must be present for a [[coin toss]] three minutes before the first-half kickoff.\n\n[[College of the Ozarks]] president Jerry Davis announced in September 2017 that his college's teams would [[Forfeit (sport)|refuse to play]] any team whose players knelt during the anthem.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news-leader.com/story/news/education/2017/09/29/no-pledge-no-play-policy-college-ozarks-student-athletes/717937001/|title=If you kneel, the game is over, C of O tells opposing teams|last=Riley|first=Claudette|date=September 29, 2017|work=Springfield News-Leader|access-date=January 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180106010320/http://www.news-leader.com/story/news/education/2017/09/29/no-pledge-no-play-policy-college-ozarks-student-athletes/717937001/|archive-date=January 6, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In response, the [[National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics|NAIA]] chose to move its [[NAIA Men's Basketball Championships#Division II|Division II men's basketball champion game]] away from College of the Ozarks' [[Keeter Gymnasium]] (where the championship game had been held since 2000) to [[Sanford Pentagon]] in [[Sioux Falls, South Dakota|Sioux Falls]], [[South Dakota]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news-leader.com/story/sports/college/2017/10/27/anthem-protest-policy-moves-naia-basketball-tournament-away-college-ozarks/807857001/|title=Anthem protest policy moves NAIA basketball tournament away from College of the Ozarks|date=October 27, 2017|work=Springfield News-Leader}}</ref>\n\nOn February 23, 2019, eight players of the [[Ole Miss Rebels men's basketball|Ole Miss men's basketball]] team took a knee during the national anthem at their home-game against [[University of Georgia|Georgia]]. The players took a knee to protest the pro-confederate rally that was happening on campus at the time.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/23/sports/ole-miss-anthem-protest-kneel.html|title=Ole Miss Players Kneel in Response to Pro-Confederate Rally|last=Press|first=The Associated|date=2019-02-23|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-03-07|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The players previously stood during the national anthem, with this being the first time they took the knee. The athletes were upset by a video posted online by the rally organizers a few days prior.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Paul|first=Maman|date=2019|title=Emotional Intelligence: A Analytical Study of Basketball Players|journal=International Journal of Current Research and Review|volume=11|issue=3|pages=01\u201305|doi=10.31782/ijcrr.2019.11301|issn=2231-2196}}</ref> The protest reached national attention and received negative backlash. However, the athletes received public support from University officials.<ref>{{Cite news|title=27733, 1864-03-07, KERR (Miss) \u2020|doi = 10.1163/2210-7886_asc-27733}}</ref>\n\nOn December 24, 2016 Michigan players Jordan Lewis and Khalid Hill raised their right arms in the air in support of the Anthem Protests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/17626402/college-football-players-protest-anthem|title=UM, MSU players raise fists during anthem|date=2016-09-24|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref>\n\n===High school===\nOn September 2, 2016, a football player at [[Brunswick High School (Ohio)|Brunswick High School]] in [[Ohio]] knelt during the national anthem after he heard his teammates saying \"[[nigger]]\".<ref name=\"gibbs\">{{cite web|last1=Gibbs|first1=Lindsay|title=Tracking the Kaepernick Effect: The anthem protests are spreading|url=https://thinkprogress.org/national-anthem-sports-protest-tracker-kaepernick-284ff1d1ab3e#.c5u4c1quw|publisher=think progress|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103035700/https://thinkprogress.org/national-anthem-sports-protest-tracker-kaepernick-284ff1d1ab3e#.c5u4c1quw|archive-date=January 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> After his protest, the player received racial threats.<ref name=\"fox\">{{cite web|last1=Freeman|first1=Kevin|title=First home game for Brunswick High School since player said he received racial threats|url=http://fox8.com/2016/09/16/first-home-game-for-brunswick-high-school-since-player-said-he-received-racial-threats/|publisher=Fox|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919062749/http://fox8.com/2016/09/16/first-home-game-for-brunswick-high-school-since-player-said-he-received-racial-threats/|archive-date=September 19, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On September 9, high school players across the country knelt during the national anthem. On September 23, four players from [[Withrow High School]], three black and one white, in [[Cincinnati]] knelt during the national anthem before their football game.<ref name=\"gibbs\"/>\n\nIn September 2017, Principal Waylon Bates of [[Parkway High School (Louisiana)|Parkway High School]] in [[Louisiana]] referred to the national anthem protests as a \"disruption\" and threatened to kick any player out of the football team if he knelt during the national anthem.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/28/louisiana-high-school-will-kick-students-off-team-if-they-dont-stand-for-national-anthem/|title=Louisiana high school will kick students off team if they don't stand for national anthem|first=Jacob|last=Bogage|date=September 28, 2017|accessdate=October 4, 2017|via=www.washingtonpost.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171003180303/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/28/louisiana-high-school-will-kick-students-off-team-if-they-dont-stand-for-national-anthem/|archive-date=October 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Two black students on the Victory & Praise Christian Academy football team protested during the anthem. Immediately after the anthem concluded, their coach removed them from the team, having them take off their uniforms on the [[sidelines]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfgate.com/sports/highschool/article/High-school-football-kicked-off-team-anthem-kneel-12242713.php|title=Local high school football players kicked off team after protest during anthem|website=sfgate.com|accessdate=October 4, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171004112646/http://www.sfgate.com/sports/highschool/article/High-school-football-kicked-off-team-anthem-kneel-12242713.php|archive-date=October 4, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 2018, the 32 players of the Christian Capital Academy football team as well as the coaching staff decided to take a knee during the national anthem. When asked about their reasons, the team collectively responded that they took a knee as a way to protest for the excessive use of police brutality against minorities, especially against African Americans.<ref>{{Cite news|title=High School Football team|doi=10.31096/wua033-pls90b070}}</ref> The two players did not receive any punishment for their protest.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=January 2017|title=Student-athlete wasn't defamed by being kicked off team|journal=College Athletics and the Law|volume=13|issue=10|pages=10\u201311|doi=10.1002/catl.30300|issn=1552-8774}}</ref>\n\nOn December 2017, Ninth Circuit Court for the Southern District of California ruled in favor of high school players, and stated that no high school football player can be forced to stand during the national anthem or cannot be forced out of the team by refusing to do so.<ref name=\"Stratmoen 204\u2013213\">{{Cite journal|last=Stratmoen|first=Evelyn|last2=Lawless|first2=Tiffany J.|last3=Saucier|first3=Donald A.|date=January 2019|title=Taking a knee: Perceptions of NFL player protests during the National Anthem|journal=Personality and Individual Differences|volume=137|pages=204\u2013213|doi=10.1016/j.paid.2018.09.009|issn=0191-8869}}</ref> The basis for such ruling is that \u201closs of First Amendment freedoms unquestionably constitutes irreparable harm and that the mandate issued by the district superintendent is a violation of the athlete\u2019s First Amendment rights.\u201d<ref name=\"Stratmoen 204\u2013213\"/>\n\n===Baseball===\nOn September 23, 2017, [[Bruce Maxwell]] of the [[Oakland Athletics]] knelt during the national anthem, becoming the first MLB player to join the protest. His team backed him up by saying, \"The Oakland A's pride ourselves on being inclusive. We respect and support all of our players' constitutional rights and freedom of expression.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfgate.com/athletics/article/A-s-Bruce-Maxwell-first-MLB-player-to-kneel-for-12223798.php|title=A's Bruce Maxwell first MLB player to kneel for anthem|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924023030/http://www.sfgate.com/athletics/article/A-s-Bruce-Maxwell-first-MLB-player-to-kneel-for-12223798.php|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/trump-baseball-first-take-national-anthem_us_59c7051ae4b01cc57ff2a61e|title=MLB's First Player Just Took A Knee During The National Anthem|last=Madani|first=Doha|date=September 24, 2017|work=HuffPost|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926184529/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/trump-baseball-first-take-national-anthem_us_59c7051ae4b01cc57ff2a61e|archive-date=September 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Maxwell received a standing ovation from A's fans before his first at-bat following his protest.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sbnation.com/mlb/2017/9/25/16364924/bruce-maxwell-standing-ovation-protest-fans-oakland|title=In his first at-bat after taking a knee, Bruce Maxwell got a standing ovation from fans|work=SBNation.com|access-date=September 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927052806/https://www.sbnation.com/mlb/2017/9/25/16364924/bruce-maxwell-standing-ovation-protest-fans-oakland|archive-date=September 27, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe MLB has no policy regarding the national anthem other than it has to be played before games.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\n===Basketball===\nOn September 24, 2017, prior to Game 1 of the [[2017 WNBA Finals]], players from the [[Los Angeles Sparks]] chose to stay in the locker room during the national anthem, while members of the [[Minnesota Lynx]] locked arms on the court.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadspin.com/los-angeles-sparks-leave-court-before-national-anthem-i-1818709276|title=Los Angeles Sparks Leave Court Before National Anthem in Game 1 of WNBA Finals|last=Theisen|first=Lauren|date=September 24, 2017|work=Deadspin|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925012416/http://deadspin.com/los-angeles-sparks-leave-court-before-national-anthem-i-1818709276|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe [[NBA]] has a policy that requires players to stand up during the national anthem in their CBA, however many prominent players have expressed support for the NFL protests on social media or in interviews.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/celtics/2018/06/04/why-don-players-have-problem-with-nba-national-anthem-policy/RDqhgKaScJL2DPLLSuWiVM/story.html|title=Why don't players have a problem with the NBA's national anthem policy?|newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]]|first=Gary|last=Washburn|accessdate=February 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828071305/https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/celtics/2018/06/04/why-don-players-have-problem-with-nba-national-anthem-policy/RDqhgKaScJL2DPLLSuWiVM/story.html|archive-date=August 28, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Ice hockey===\nOn October 7, 2017, [[J. T. Brown (ice hockey)|J. T. Brown]] of the [[Tampa Bay Lightning]] raised his fist while standing on the bench during the national anthem. He had also done the same in a preseason game, in an attempt to \"bring awareness to police brutality against minorities and racial inequality\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tampabay.com/sports/hockey/lightning/lightnings-jt-brown-raises-fist-in-protest-during-anthem-before-panthers/2340305|title=Lightning's J.T. Brown raises fist in protest during anthem before Panthers game|last=Smith|first=Joe|date=October 7, 2017|work=tampabay.com|publisher=Tampa Bay Times|accessdate=October 7, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008080405/http://www.tampabay.com/sports/hockey/lightning/lightnings-jt-brown-raises-fist-in-protest-during-anthem-before-panthers/2340305|archive-date=October 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He stated that he had \"received death threats\" after the protest.<ref name=thescore>{{cite web|url=https://www.thescore.com/nhl/news/1393535-lightning-s-brown-i-have-received-death-threats-after-protest|title=Lightning's Brown: 'I have received death threats' after protest|last=Livingstone|first=Flip|date=October 8, 2017|work=[[TheScore Inc.|TheScore.com]]|publisher=Score Media Ventures Inc.|accessdate=October 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Pan American Games===\nAt the [[2019 Pan American Games]] in [[Lima]], Peru, team fencing gold medalist [[Race Imboden]] kneeled and women's hammer throw champion [[Gwen Berry]] raised a fist on the awards stand during the American national anthem.<ref>{{cite news|last=Taylor|first=Derrick Bryson|title=U.S. Fencer, Race Imboden, Takes a Knee at Pan-American Games|date=August 11, 2019|newspaper=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/11/sports/race-imboden-fencer-kneels.html|accessdate=August 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>https://www.chicagotribune.com/sports/breaking/ct-race-imboden-gwen-berry-athlete-protest-20190811-gceardedn5fyjclxim5b7qexta-story.html</ref>\n{{quote|\"Racism, gun control, mistreatment of immigrants, and a president who spreads hate are at the top of a long list.  I chose to sacrifice my moment today at the top of the podium to call attention to issues that I believe need to be addressed.  I encourage others to please use your platforms for empowerment and change.\"|Race Imboden}}\n{{quote|\"It's too important to not say something. Something has to be said. If nothing is said, nothing will be done, and nothing will be fixed, and nothing will be changed.\"|Gwen Berry}}\n\n==Role of Russian bots in amplifying controversy==\nA [[Clemson University]] research paper found that Russian bots played a role in amplifying the controversy over kneeling during the national anthem. Some 12,000 tweets linked to 491 accounts linked to Russia's [[Internet Research Agency]] were sent from the end of 2014 to mid-2018; those tweets peaked on September 22, 2017, after President Donald Trump's speech in Huntsville, Alabama.<ref>Gardner, Steve (October 22, 2018). [https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2018/10/22/russian-bots-twitter-trolls-nfl-national-anthem-controversy/1732873002/ \"Report: Russian Twitter trolls helped fan flames of NFL's national anthem controversy\"]. ''USAToday NFL''. Retrieved November 17, 2019.</ref><ref>Andrew Beaton, [https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-russian-trolls-inflamed-nfls-anthem-controversy-1540233979 How Russian Trolls Inflamed the NFL's Anthem Controversy], ''Wall Street Journal'' (October 22, 2018).</ref>\n\nU.S. Senator [[James Lankford]] of [[Oklahoma]] said [[Trolls from Olgino|Russian internet trolls]], seeking to polarize Americans, helped fuel online discord.<ref>{{cite web|author=Devlin Barrett|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/lawmaker-russian-trolls-trying-to-sow-discord-in-nfl-kneeling-debate/2017/09/27/5f46dce0-a3b0-11e7-ade1-76d061d56efa_story.html|title=Lawmaker: Russian trolls trying to sow discord in NFL kneeling debate|publisher=washingtonpost.com|date=September 27, 2017|accessdate=December 1, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171128103832/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/lawmaker-russian-trolls-trying-to-sow-discord-in-nfl-kneeling-debate/2017/09/27/5f46dce0-a3b0-11e7-ade1-76d061d56efa_story.html|archive-date=November 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/russian-trolls-using-nfl-protests-sow-discord-online-republican-senator-n805296|title=Russian trolls using NFL protests to sow discord online, GOP senator says|access-date=December 10, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171205035419/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/russian-trolls-using-nfl-protests-sow-discord-online-republican-senator-n805296|archive-date=December 5, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/russian-internet-trolls-calling-takeaknee-boycottnf-sow-discord/story?id=50132807|title=Russian internet trolls pushed national anthem controversy, #TakeAKnee: Senator|date=September 27, 2017|publisher=ABC News|access-date=May 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526041155/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/russian-internet-trolls-calling-takeaknee-boycottnf-sow-discord/story?id=50132807|archive-date=May 26, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> During a Senate hearing, Lankford said: \"We watched, even this weekend, the Russians and their troll farms, their internet folks, start hashtagging out #TakeAKnee and also hashtagging out #BoycottNFL. They were taking both sides of the argument this weekend ... to try to raise the noise level of America and make a big issue seem like an even bigger issue as they are trying to push divisiveness in this country.\"<ref>Phillip Ewing, [https://www.npr.org/2017/09/28/554024047/as-scrutiny-of-social-networks-grows-influence-attacks-continue-in-real-time As Scrutiny Of Social Networks Grows, Influence Attacks Continue In Real Time], NPR (September 28, 2017).</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\n\n===Political figures===\n[[File:Mike Pence NFL Protests 2017.jpg|thumb|Vice President Pence stands for anthem prior to leaving after players knelt]]\nIn September 2016, President [[Barack Obama]] stated that Kaepernick was \"exercising his constitutional right\" to protest. He went on: \"I don't doubt his sincerity. I think he cares about some real, legitimate issues that have to be talked about. If nothing else, he's generated more conversation about issues that have to be talked about.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hjelmgaard|first1=Kim|title=24095 924 494 Obama defends Kaepernick's national anthem protest|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2016/09/05/obama-defends-kaepernicks-national-anthem-protest/89879478/|work=USA Today|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923102513/http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2016/09/05/obama-defends-kaepernicks-national-anthem-protest/89879478/|archive-date=September 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[U.S. Supreme Court|Supreme Court]] Justice [[Ruth Bader Ginsburg]] criticized the protest as \"dumb and disrespectful\", stating that athletes have the right to protest \"if they want to be stupid\". The Supreme Court later issued a statement from Ginsburg stating that her comments were \"inappropriately dismissive and harsh. I should have declined to respond.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Ruth Bader Ginsburg apologizes for criticizing anthem protests|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/17795159/ruth-bader-ginsburg-apologizes-criticizing-colin-kaepernick-anthem-protest|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=October 14, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015193145/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/17795159/ruth-bader-ginsburg-apologizes-criticizing-colin-kaepernick-anthem-protest|archive-date=October 15, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn September 25, 2017, [[U.S. Representative]] [[Sheila Jackson Lee]] knelt on the floor of the House of Representatives.<ref>{{cite news |last=Chason |first=Rachel |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/09/26/that-is-racism-black-lawmaker-condemns-trump-kneels-in-congress-to-honor-nfl-players/ |title='That is racism': Black lawmaker condemns Trump, kneels in Congress to honor NFL players |newspaper=The Washington Post |accessdate=September 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927001132/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/09/26/that-is-racism-black-lawmaker-condemns-trump-kneels-in-congress-to-honor-nfl-players/ |archive-date=September 27, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Fellow congressman [[Mark Pocan]] knelt on the floor of the House the next day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thehill.com/blogs/floor-action/house/352448-another-democrat-takes-a-knee-on-house-floor-to-support-nfl-protests |title=Another Democrat takes a knee on House floor to support NFL protests |publisher=TheHill |accessdate=September 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928014606/http://thehill.com/blogs/floor-action/house/352448-another-democrat-takes-a-knee-on-house-floor-to-support-nfl-protests |archive-date=September 28, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn September 26, 2017, Louisiana Lt. Gov. [[Billy Nungesser]] told ''[[The Times-Picayune]]'' that he would not be attending the [[New Orleans Saints]] game against the [[Miami Dolphins]], which was going to be taking place in London. Although he was going to be in London during the time of the game, he told the newspaper that he would not attend because he was \"disappointed in the NFL.\" He added that \"it is disgraceful that anybody would use that as a time to protest.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Seraaj |first1=Intisar |last2=Zdanowicz |first2=Christina |title=From Jersey burnings to players being uninvited, backlash to the #TakeAKnee protest grows |url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/25/us/anthem-protests-burning-nfl-jerseys-trnd/index.html |website=CNN |accessdate=28 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928201044/https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/25/us/anthem-protests-burning-nfl-jerseys-trnd/index.html |archive-date=September 28, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn October 8, 2017, [[United States Vice President|Vice President]] [[Mike Pence]] left a game between the NFL's [[Indianapolis Colts]] and the San Francisco 49ers, members of which had knelt during the anthem, \"because President Trump and I will not dignify any event that disrespects our soldiers, our Flag, or our National Anthem.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/10/08/556531518/vp-pence-takes-a-stand-and-walks-away-after-nfl-players-kneel|title=Trump Defends Pence's NFL Protest Amid Claims It Was A Publicity Stunt|last=Romo|first=Vanessa|publisher=NPR|date=October 8, 2017|accessdate=October 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008230746/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/10/08/556531518/vp-pence-takes-a-stand-and-walks-away-after-nfl-players-kneel|archive-date=October 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Corporations===\nMajor sports sponsors [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]], [[Under Armour]], and [[Ford]] all issued statements in support of athletes' freedom of expression after Trump's comments regarding the NFL.  Nike's statement read, \"Nike supports athletes and their right to freedom of expression on issues that are of great importance to our society.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nike-becomes-first-nfl-sponsor-take-side-trump-vs-nfl-193639102.html|title=Nike, an NFL sponsor, takes clear side in Trump vs NFL|access-date=2017-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170929000415/https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nike-becomes-first-nfl-sponsor-take-side-trump-vs-nfl-193639102.html|archive-date=September 29, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Nike's ad featuring Kaepernick read \"Believe in something. Even if it means sacrificing everything.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/09/07/sport/colin-kaepernick-protest-taking-the-knee-nate-boyer-spt-intl/index.html|title=Colin Kaepernick: A cultural star fast turning into a global icon|first=Aimee |last=Lewis|website=CNN|access-date=2019-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190117040007/https://edition.cnn.com/2018/09/07/sport/colin-kaepernick-protest-taking-the-knee-nate-boyer-spt-intl/index.html|archive-date=January 17, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In September 2016, after [[Brandon Marshall (linebacker)|Brandon Marshall]] knelt during the national anthem, [[Century Link]] and [[Air Academy Federal Credit Union]] dropped him as a paid sponsor.<ref name=\"crab\">{{cite web|last1=Crabtree|first1=Curtis|title=Brandon Marshall picks up new endorsement after losing two following anthem kneel|url=http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2016/09/15/brandon-marshall-picks-up-new-endorsement-after-losing-two-following-anthem-kneel/|publisher=NBC Sports|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919144007/http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2016/09/15/brandon-marshall-picks-up-new-endorsement-after-losing-two-following-anthem-kneel/|archive-date=September 19, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Radio station [[WFAY]] dropped a broadcast of an [[East Carolina University]] football game on the station after the marching band took part in the protest, calling it an insult to the U.S. Armed Forces.<ref>Martin, Nick (October 6, 2016). [http://deadspin.com/local-espn-radio-station-to-drop-ecu-game-after-band-pr-1787404764 Local ESPN Radio Station To Drop ECU Game After Band Protest] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161007121144/http://deadspin.com/local-espn-radio-station-to-drop-ecu-game-after-band-pr-1787404764 |date=October 7, 2016 }}. ''Deadspin''. Retrieved October 6, 2016.</ref> [[John Schnatter]] of sponsor [[Papa John's Pizza]] blamed the protests for a drop in sales and a 24% fall in stock during 2017, saying that the \"controversy is polarizing the customer, polarizing the country\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/11/01/media/nfl-papa-johns-protests/index.html|title=Papa John's says NFL protests are hurting sales|last=Meyersohn|first=Nathaniel|date=November 1, 2017|access-date=November 2, 2017|work=CNN Money|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171101230132/http://money.cnn.com/2017/11/01/media/nfl-papa-johns-protests/index.html|archive-date=November 1, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Later that day, the company announced that the NFL shield or \"official sponsor\" designation on Papa John's commercials and advertising would be removed.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21250448/nfl-sponsor-papa-john-not-happy-anthem-protests|title=Papa John's says anthem protests are hurting deal with NFL|first=Darren|last=Rovell|work=ESPN.com|date=November 1, 2017|accessdate=November 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171102011930/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21250448/nfl-sponsor-papa-john-not-happy-anthem-protests|archive-date=November 2, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In December 2017 [[Sanderson Farms]] CEO questioned whether the NFL protests were to blame for falling [[Buffalo wing|chicken wing]] prices.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-12-14/nfl-player-protests-hurting-chicken-wing-sales-producer-says|title=Chicken Wing Company Says NFL Player Protests Are Hurting Sales|first=Megan|last=Durisin|work=Bloomberg.com|date=December 15, 2017|accessdate=January 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180111132819/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-12-14/nfl-player-protests-hurting-chicken-wing-sales-producer-says|archive-date=January 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAfter his first kneel in 2016, Nike was well on its way to severing its four year long partnership with Kaepernick.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/26/sports/nike-colin-kaepernick.html|title=Nike Nearly Dropped Colin Kaepernick Before Embracing Him|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928032659/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/26/sports/nike-colin-kaepernick.html|archive-date=September 28, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Nigel Powell, chief communications executive of Nike, convinced the company to maintain their partnership with Kaepernick which eventually led to the launch of the politically and socially controversial advertisement released in 2018, \"Nike - Dream Crazy\", with Kaepernick as their face of their 30th anniversary campaign.<ref>{{Citation|last=Nike|title=Nike - Dream Crazy|date=2018-09-05|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fq2CvmgoO7I|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928094000/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fq2CvmgoO7I|archive-date=September 28, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Despite the prevalent backlash on social media of people who criticized Kaepernick's actions by burning and cutting up their Nike brand clothing, and even attracting the attention of President Trump, who then tweeted against the company's campaign,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/30/business/nike-colin-kaepernick-nfl-just-do-it/index.html|title=Why Nike is betting its slogan on Colin Kaepernick|last=Business|first=Nathaniel Meyersohn, CNN|website=CNN|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref> Nike sales increased by 31% within five days after the advertisement was released. However, the campaign did result in a temporary drop of 2.2% in the company's stock price.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/5390884/nike-sales-go-up-kaepernick-ad/|title=Nike Sales Increase 31% After Kaepernick Ad Despite Backlash|website=Time|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180930162220/http://time.com/5390884/nike-sales-go-up-kaepernick-ad/|archive-date=September 30, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/09/19/nike-colin-kaepernick-ads-national-anthem-protest-controversy.html|title=Some people may hate Nike's marketing campaigns\u2014but the brand keeps adding billions to its bottom line|last=Turner|first=Dymond Green, Ashley|date=2018-09-19|work=CNBC|access-date=2018-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180927204349/https://www.cnbc.com/2018/09/19/nike-colin-kaepernick-ads-national-anthem-protest-controversy.html|archive-date=September 27, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By September 13, 2018, Nike's stock price closed at $83.47, which at the time was the highest in the company's history.<ref name=\"https://www.facebook.com/CindyBoren\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2018/09/13/colin-kaepernicks-nike-ad-campaign-gets-more-yeahs-than-nays-from-young-people/|title=Nike's Colin Kaepernick ad campaign gets more yeas than nays from young people|last=Boren|first=Cindy|website=Washington Post|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref> Nike took this backlash and converted it into a meme by releasing an ad that provided instructions to their customer on how to burn their products \"properly\".<ref name=\"https://www.facebook.com/CindyBoren\"/>\n\n===Athletes and sports media===\nThroughout the remainder of the 2016 season, Kaepernick received public backlash for his protest, with an anonymous [[NFL]] executive calling Kaepernick \"a traitor\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2651681-mike-freemans-10-point-stance-kaepernick-anger-intense-in-nfl-front-offices|title=Kaepernick Anger Intense in NFL Front Offices|first=Mike|last=Freeman|accessdate=September 8, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160908034911/http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2651681-mike-freemans-10-point-stance-kaepernick-anger-intense-in-nfl-front-offices|archive-date=September 8, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On September 20, 2016, Kaepernick also stated that he received death threats primarily through social media.<ref name=\"deaththreats\">[http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/09/nfl-kaepernick-received-death-threats-160921152934415.html US: Colin Kaepernick says he has received death threats] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160922124538/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/09/nfl-kaepernick-received-death-threats-160921152934415.html |date=September 22, 2016 }}. [[Al Jazeera]]. September 22, 2016.</ref>\n\nSportscaster [[Bob Costas]] offered support for Kaepernick stating, \"Patriotism comes in many forms and what has happened is it's been conflated with a bumper-style kind of flag-waving and with the military only so that people cannot see that in his own way Colin Kaepernick, however imperfectly, is doing a [[patriotic]] thing.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/09/bob-costas-trump-nfl|title=Bob Costas puts the entire national anthem debate in perspective with one powerful segment|date=September 25, 2017|work=For The Win|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925161813/http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/09/bob-costas-trump-nfl|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[Trent Dilfer]] criticized Kaepernick. \"The big thing that hit me through all this was this is a backup quarterback whose job is to be quiet, and sit in the shadows and get the starter ready to play Week 1,\" Dilfer said on ''[[Sunday NFL Countdown]]''. \"Yet he chose a time where all of a sudden he became the center of attention. And it has disrupted that organization. It has caused friction. And it's torn at the fabric of the team.\"<ref name=\"mercury\">{{cite news|last1=Inman|first1=Cam|title=Colin Kaepernick told by ESPN's Trent Dilfer to 'be quiet, sit in the shadows'|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/2016/09/11/colin-kaepernick-told-by-espns-trent-dilfer-to-be-quiet-sit-in-the-shadows/|website=The Mercury News|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924014013/http://www.mercurynews.com/2016/09/11/colin-kaepernick-told-by-espns-trent-dilfer-to-be-quiet-sit-in-the-shadows/|archive-date=September 24, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nStemming from the Kaepernick controversy, before the beginning of the [[2016 World Cup of Hockey]] tournament in [[Toronto|Toronto, Canada]], Team USA coach [[John Tortorella]] told in an interview that if any one of his players were to sit out during the anthem, they would sit on the bench for the entire duration of the game.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/world-cup-of-hockey/tortorella-will-sit-anthem-protests-team-usa/|title=Tortorella 'will sit' any Team USA player who protests anthem - Sportsnet.ca|newspaper=Sportsnet.ca|access-date=2017-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180806024405/https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/world-cup-of-hockey/tortorella-will-sit-anthem-protests-team-usa/|archive-date=August 6, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe September 2016 police shootings of [[Shooting of Terence Crutcher|Terence Crutcher]] and [[Shooting of Keith Lamont Scott|Keith Lamont Scott]] bolstered support for his protest.<ref>{{cite news|last=Maxwell|first=Francis|title=Silence From Kaepernick Critics Speaks Volumes|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/57e2f47fe4b05d3737be53de?timestamp=1474507429354|website=[[HuffPost]]|date=September 21, 2016|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923064107/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/57e2f47fe4b05d3737be53de?timestamp=1474507429354|archive-date=September 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick said of the Terence Crutcher shooting, \"this is a perfect example of what this is about.\"<ref name=\"deaththreats\"/> Boxer [[Floyd Mayweather]] criticized Kaepernick, stating, \"You know, a lot of times, we get stuck, and we are followers. When you hear one person say 'black lives matter' or 'blue lives matter,' all lives matter.\" Adding moments later, \"With me being a fighter, and my hands being registered, if I hit a guy for breaking in my house, or breaking in my car, it's gonna cost me more money, so I gotta work smarter, not harder. I'm gonna call the cops.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Payne|first=Marissa|title=Floyd Mayweather advises people to 'follow order' because 'all lives matter'|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2016/10/11/floyd-mayweather-advises-people-to-follow-order-because-all-lives-matter/|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=October 11, 2016|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180824134922/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2016/10/11/floyd-mayweather-advises-people-to-follow-order-because-all-lives-matter/|archive-date=August 24, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nDiscussion continued throughout August 2017. [[National Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum|Baseball Hall of Famer]] [[Hank Aaron]] said, \"I think he's getting a raw deal\" from the NFL.<ref>{{cite news|last=Axisa|first=Mike|title=MLB Hall of Famer Hank Aaron says Colin Kaepernick is 'getting a raw deal' from NFL|url=https://www.cbssports.com/mlb/news/mlb-hall-of-famer-hank-aaron-says-colin-kaepernick-is-getting-a-raw-deal-from-nfl/|publisher=CBS Sports|website=CBSSports.com|date=August 26, 2017|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180821160522/https://www.cbssports.com/mlb/news/mlb-hall-of-famer-hank-aaron-says-colin-kaepernick-is-getting-a-raw-deal-from-nfl/|archive-date=August 21, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> That same month, [[Pro Football Hall of Fame]]r and longtime [[Civil and political rights|civil rights activist]] [[Jim Brown]], who a year earlier supported Kaepernick \"100 percent\",<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000692374/article/jim-brown-im-with-colin-kaepernick-100-percent|title=Jim Brown: I'm with Colin Kaepernick '100 percent'|publisher=National Football League|date=August 29, 2016|access-date=August 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826174257/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000692374/article/jim-brown-im-with-colin-kaepernick-100-percent|archive-date=August 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> now criticized him, suggesting Kaepernick ought to decide whether to be an athlete or an activist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/08/25/jim-brown-says-i-dont-desecrate-my-flag-thinks-colin-kaepernick-should-pick-football-or-activism/|title=Jim Brown says 'I don't desecrate my flag,' thinks Colin Kaepernick should pick football or activism|website=The Washington Post|access-date=August 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826030425/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/08/25/jim-brown-says-i-dont-desecrate-my-flag-thinks-colin-kaepernick-should-pick-football-or-activism/|archive-date=August 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> \"I'm an American,\" said Brown. \"I don't desecrate my flag and my national anthem. ... This is my country, and I'll work out the problems, but I'll do it in an intelligent manner.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/08/25/jim-brown-colin-kaepernick-i-dont-desecrate-my-flag-and-my-national-anthem/602349001/|title=Jim Brown on Colin Kaepernick: 'I don't desecrate my flag and my national anthem'|date=August 25, 2017|website=USA Today|accessdate=August 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826022704/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/08/25/jim-brown-colin-kaepernick-i-dont-desecrate-my-flag-and-my-national-anthem/602349001/|archive-date=August 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[Jim Harbaugh]], Kaepernick's former coach, penned a strong statement of support for him as part of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''{{'}}s \"[[Time 100|100 Most Influential People]]\" series. Harbaugh wrote, \"His willingness to take a position at personal cost is now part of our American story. How lucky for us all and for our country to have among our citizens someone as remarkable as Colin Kaepernick.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/collection/2017-time-100/4736257/colin-kaepernick/|title=Colin Kaepernick: The World's 100 Most Influential People|website=Time|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924062914/http://time.com/collection/2017-time-100/4736257/colin-kaepernick/|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[NASCAR]] team owners [[Richard Petty]] and [[Richard Childress]] have supported Trump and said that they would fire drivers and employees who would not stand for the national anthem.<ref>{{cite news|last=Parco|first=Nicholas|title=NASCAR owners threaten to fire any drivers who kneel during national anthem|work=Daily News|location=New York|date=September 24, 2017|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/more-sports/nascar-owners-threaten-fire-drivers-protest-anthem-article-1.3518424|accessdate=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925081415/http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/more-sports/nascar-owners-threaten-fire-drivers-protest-anthem-article-1.3518424|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Petty said, \"Anybody that don't stand up for the anthem ought to be out of the country. Period.\" Childress said, \"It'll get you a ride on a Greyhound bus\" if anyone on his team protested the anthem.<ref>{{cite news | last2=Hamilton | last1=Bieler | first2=Tracee | first1=Des | title=Richard Petty, other NASCAR owners decry protests, but Dale Earnhardt Jr. offers support | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/24/richard-petty-among-nascar-owners-saying-anthem-protests-will-get-employees-fired/ | work=Washington Post | date=September 25, 2017 | accessdate=September 26, 2017 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926000633/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/24/richard-petty-among-nascar-owners-saying-anthem-protests-will-get-employees-fired/ | archive-date=September 26, 2017 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Driver [[Dale Earnhardt Jr.]], however, expressed support for the peaceful protests, quoting President [[John F. Kennedy]], \"Those who make peaceful revolution impossible will make violent revolution inevitable.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbssports.com/general/news/nascars-dale-earnhardt-jr-voices-support-for-peaceful-protests-in-america/|title=NASCAR's Dale Earnhardt Jr. voices support for peaceful protests in America|publisher=CBSSports.com|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925230434/https://www.cbssports.com/general/news/nascars-dale-earnhardt-jr-voices-support-for-peaceful-protests-in-america/|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> NASCAR released a statement on September 25 in response to the protests that said, \"Sports are a unifying influence in our society, bringing people of differing backgrounds and beliefs together. Our respect for the national anthem has always been a hallmark of our pre-race events. Thanks to the sacrifices of many, we live in a country of unparalleled freedoms and countless liberties, including the right to peacefully express one's opinion.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=NASCAR statement|publisher=NASCAR.com|date=September 25, 2017|url=https://www.nascar.com/news-media/2017/09/25/nascar-statement-september-25/|accessdate=September 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927112541/https://www.nascar.com/news-media/2017/09/25/nascar-statement-september-25/|archive-date=September 27, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[Jemele Hill]] tweeted, \"Just so we're clear: the president's comments will only incite more player protests, not quell them.\" following Trump's initial response to the protests.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/09/13/media/jemele-hill-espn-white-house/index.html|title=ESPN says it accepts Jemele Hill's apology after anti-Trump tweets|publisher=CNN|date=September 14, 2017|access-date=October 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009214059/http://money.cnn.com/2017/09/13/media/jemele-hill-espn-white-house/index.html|archive-date=October 9, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/media/352026-espns-jemele-hill-trumps-nfl-remarks-will-only-make-more-players-protest|title=ESPN's Jemele Hill: Trump's NFL remarks will only make more players protest|newspaper=The Hill|date=September 9, 2017|access-date=October 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171010004627/http://thehill.com/homenews/media/352026-espns-jemele-hill-trumps-nfl-remarks-will-only-make-more-players-protest|archive-date=October 10, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Hill was later put on a two-week suspension for \"a second violation of our social media guidelines\", after Hill suggested people direct their disagreements towards advertisers of Dallas Cowboys owner [[Jerry Jones]], after Jones stated he would bench any player who protested the national anthem on October 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20961541/dallas-cowboys-owner-jerry-jones-says-player-disrespects-flag-play|title=Jerry Jones: Cowboys will bench any player who 'disrespects' flag|publisher=ESPN|date=October 9, 2017|access-date=October 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009233903/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20961541/dallas-cowboys-owner-jerry-jones-says-player-disrespects-flag-play|archive-date=October 9, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/10/09/media/jemele-hill-espn-suspended/index.html|title=ESPN suspends Jemele Hill over tweets|publisher=CNNMoney|date=October 9, 2017|access-date=October 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009202340/http://money.cnn.com/2017/10/09/media/jemele-hill-espn-suspended/index.html|archive-date=October 9, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn September 25, 2017, [[Bill Russell]] posted a photo to Twitter while kneeling and wearing his [[Presidential Medal of Freedom]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://whdh.com/news/celtics-legend-bill-russell-takes-knee-in-photo-with-presidential-medal-of-freedom/ |title=Celtics legend Bill Russell takes knee in photo with Presidential Medal of Freedom |publisher=WHDH 7News |date=February 13, 2011 |accessdate=September 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927000037/http://whdh.com/news/celtics-legend-bill-russell-takes-knee-in-photo-with-presidential-medal-of-freedom/ |archive-date=September 27, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> On September 26, 2017, Joey Odoms, the national anthem singer for the home games of the Ravens, resigned citing the \"tone/actions of a large number of NFL fans in the midst of our country's cultural crisis\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Zrebiec |first1=Jeff |title=Ravens national anthem singer Joey Odoms, a combat veteran, informs team he is resigning |url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/ravens/ravens-insider/bs-sp-odoms-resigning-20170926-story.html |accessdate=September 27, 2017 |work=The Baltimore Sun |date=September 26, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927112842/http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/ravens/ravens-insider/bs-sp-odoms-resigning-20170926-story.html |archive-date=September 27, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nFormer [[Chicago Bears]] coach [[Mike Ditka]] commented, \"If you don't respect our country, then you shouldn't be in this country playing football ... So I would say, adios.\" He added that he was \"not condemning anybody or criticizing anybody\" in his remarks. According to Ditka, \"there has been no oppression in the last 100 years that I know of.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/sports/mike-ditka-nfl-protests-there-s-been-no-oppression-u-n809566|title=Mike Ditka on NFL Protests: There's Been No Oppression in U.S. in Last 100 Years|publisher=NBC News|date=October 10, 2017|access-date=October 11, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011012733/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/sports/mike-ditka-nfl-protests-there-s-been-no-oppression-u-n809566|archive-date=October 11, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Entertainment===\nNFL ratings have been in decline for the past couple years, except for the 2018 season, which saw an increase of 4%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/what-drove-the-nfls-tv-ratings-increase-in-2018/|title=What Drove the NFL's TV Ratings Increase in 2018?|date=2019-01-05|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> However, during the 2016 and 2017 seasons ratings were down by 8% and 9.7% respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2685400-nfl-tv-ratings-reportedly-down-8-percent-for-2016-17-season|title=NFL TV Ratings Reportedly Down 8 Percent for 2016 Season|last=Chiari|first=Mike|website=Bleacher Report|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21960086|title=TV ratings for NFL down 9.7 percent during '17|date=2018-01-04|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> A UBS securities analysis show that the primary cause of the drop in the ratings from the NFL is mainly due to players protesting the national anthem. According to the same survey, 50% of the decline in rating in 2017 is because of players taking a knee before the game, whereas this action only accounts for 18% of the decline of rating in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2018/feb/6/nfl-ratings-down-due-anthem-protests-survey/|title=NFL ratings down due to anthem protests: survey|last=http://www.washingtontimes.com|first=The Washington Times|website=The Washington Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> The decline in ratings have had a huge impact on the ad revenue from major television companies, especially CBS and Fox.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/mikeozanian/2017/11/03/nfl-anthem-protests-smack-leagues-broadcasters-and-sponsors/|title=NFL Anthem Protests Continue To Smack League's Broadcasters And Sponsors|last=Ozanian|first=Mike|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>\n\n[[Stevie Wonder]] knelt during the 2017 [[Global Citizen Festival]] on September 23, saying \"Tonight, I'm taking a knee for America\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Phillips |first=Kristine |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2017/09/24/im-taking-a-knee-for-america-stevie-wonder-joins-a-movement-trump-deplores/ |title='I'm taking a knee for America': Stevie Wonder joins a movement Trump deplores |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=September 24, 2017 |accessdate=September 25, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102101044/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2017/09/24/im-taking-a-knee-for-america-stevie-wonder-joins-a-movement-trump-deplores/ |archive-date=January 2, 2019 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n[[Eddie Vedder]], [[Pharrell Williams]], [[Dave Matthews]], [[John Legend]] and [[Roger Waters]] knelt to support the protests during concerts on September 24.<ref>{{cite web |last=Kreps |first=Daniel |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/eddie-vedder-roger-waters-take-knee-onstage-in-protest-w505227 |title=Eddie Vedder, Roger Waters Take Knee Onstage in Protest |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=September 25, 2017 |accessdate=September 25, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925173143/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/eddie-vedder-roger-waters-take-knee-onstage-in-protest-w505227 |archive-date=September 25, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> The same day [[Sonequa Martin-Green]] posted in her [[Instagram]] account a picture of several members from ''[[Star Trek: Discovery]]''{{'}}s cast alongside producer [[Akiva Goldsman]] and herself kneeling.<ref>{{cite web |last=Hibberd |first=James |url=http://ew.com/tv/2017/09/25/star-trek-discovery-sonequa-takes-knee/ |title=Star Trek: Discovery cast takes a knee in premiere night protest |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=September 25, 2017 |accessdate=September 29, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928072419/http://ew.com/tv/2017/09/25/star-trek-discovery-sonequa-takes-knee/ |archive-date=September 28, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> [[Shonda Rhimes]] posted a photo kneeling with the cast of ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/greys-anatomy-take-a-knee-1202574019/|title='Grey's Anatomy' Cast, Creator Take a Knee in Instagram Post|first=Daniel|last=Holloway|date=September 27, 2017|website=variety.com|accessdate=October 4, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002145613/http://variety.com/2017/tv/news/greys-anatomy-take-a-knee-1202574019/|archive-date=October 2, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n''[[The X-Files]]'' actors [[Gillian Anderson]] and [[David Duchovny]] posted a photo on Twitter of themselves kneeling with arms locked on September 26.<ref>{{cite web |author=Gael Fashingbauer Cooper |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/x-files-gillian-anderson-david-duchovny-take-a-knee-nfl-colin-kaepernick-donald-trump/ |title='X-Files' stars Gillian Anderson, David Duchovny take a knee |website=CNET |date=September 19, 2017 |accessdate=September 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928204923/https://www.cnet.com/news/x-files-gillian-anderson-david-duchovny-take-a-knee-nfl-colin-kaepernick-donald-trump/ |archive-date=September 28, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nActor [[Damien Leake]] had been making a similar protest for almost 50 years, since the assassination of [[Martin Luther King Jr.]].  When asked to comment:\n\n{{quote|Does it ever occur to you that the playing of the national anthem has no place at a sporting event, period?  Those of you who know me from high school may remember that I decided to start sitting during the playing of the Star Spangled Banner on April 4th 1968, and have been sitting ever since.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mynewsla.com/hollywood/2017/10/03/trump-bashes-nfl-but-serpico-actor-sits-for-national-anthem-since-1968/|title='Serpico' actor: Why I've sat for national anthem since 1968|date=October 4, 2017|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211174230/https://mynewsla.com/hollywood/2017/10/03/trump-bashes-nfl-but-serpico-actor-sits-for-national-anthem-since-1968/|archive-date=February 11, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>|}}\n\n===Colleges===\nOn October 11, 2018, Colin Kaepernick was awarded the [[W. E. B. Du Bois|W.E.B. Du Bois]] Medal at [[Harvard University]] during the Hutchins Center Honors sponsored by the Hutchins Center for African & African American Research. The award is going to be given for his \"significant contributions and African-American history and culture\", and for his support \"for intercultural understanding and human rights in an increasingly global and interconnected world\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2018/09/kaepernick-and-chappelle-among-eight-du-bois-medalists-at-harvard/|title=Kaepernick and Chappelle among eight Du Bois medalists at Harvard|date=September 20, 2018|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181212065845/https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2018/09/kaepernick-and-chappelle-among-eight-du-bois-medalists-at-harvard/|archive-date=December 12, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Some might think that the award is significant because it shows what he has sacrificed for starting and upholding the national anthem protest, and gives credibility to him as an activist based on the criteria for the award and past honorees such as [[Muhammad Ali]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/21/us/harvard-honors-kaepernick-trnd/index.html|title=Harvard will honor Colin Kaepernick for contributions to African-American history and culture|author1=Christina Maxouris |author2=Saeed Ahmed|website=CNN|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929084511/https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/21/us/harvard-honors-kaepernick-trnd/index.html|archive-date=September 29, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Law enforcement===\n\nDue to Kaepernick's 2018 advertisement with Nike, both plaudits and denunciations have been voiced. On September 5, 2018 in response to the new Kaepernick-Nike campaign, the National Black Police Association provided a letter stating, \"The NBPA believes that Mr. Kaepernick's stance is in direct alignment with what law enforcement stands for \u2014 the protection of a people, their human rights, their dignity, their safety and their rights as American citizens.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/identities/2018/9/6/17827348/colin-kaepernick-nfl-protest-police-unions-boycott |title=A black police organization issued a powerful defense of Colin Kaepernick|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181216031205/https://www.vox.com/identities/2018/9/6/17827348/colin-kaepernick-nfl-protest-police-unions-boycott|archive-date=December 16, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Despite being police officers, the NBPA defends Kaepernick's actions because they feel that the issue of race must be addressed in order to tackle the ongoing issue.<ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2018/09/06/black-officers-group-issues-stirring-defense-kaepernick-says-values-directly-align-with-police/?noredirect=on|title=Why a black police group issued a stirring defense of Colin Kaepernick|first=Eli Rosenberg|last=Washington Post|website=Washington POst|accessdate=February 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190220181523/https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2018/09/06/black-officers-group-issues-stirring-defense-kaepernick-says-values-directly-align-with-police/?noredirect=on&utm_term=.fe7823e14721|archive-date=February 20, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}\n</ref>\n\nThere is a wide divide of agreement on this subject between law enforcement groups; especially between the NBPA and [http://www.napo.org/ The National Police Association] (who felt that Kaepernick's gestures regarding the national anthem were disrespectful).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/1380985/nikes-colin-kaepernick-ad-is-dividing-us-police/ |title=Nike's Colin Kaepernick ad is dividing US police|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181216031712/https://qz.com/1380985/nikes-colin-kaepernick-ad-is-dividing-us-police/|archive-date=December 16, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> NAPO has even called for a boycott of Nike products due to their recent partnership with Kaepernick.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.napo.org/washington-report/latest-news-updates/napo-calls-boycott-nike/ |title=NAPO Calls for Boycott of Nike|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181207150721/http://www.napo.org/washington-report/latest-news-updates/napo-calls-boycott-nike/|archive-date=December 7, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Social media ===\nKneeling during the national anthem became a symbol of resistance, similar to the [[Raised fist|black power fist]]. The act was discussed heavily on social media, with users on [[Twitter]] and [[Facebook]] using #TakeAKnee or #TakeTheKnee to discuss the act. The use of this [[hashtag]] exploded with 4 million tweets.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adweek.com/brand-marketing/this-social-analytics-firm-says-the-4-million-takeaknee-tweets-are-just-the-beginning/|title=This Social Analytics Firm Says the 4 Million #TakeAKnee Tweets Are Just the Beginning|last=Monllos{{!}}September 25|first=Kristina|last2=2017|website=www.adweek.com|access-date=2019-03-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adweek.com/digital/takeaknee-taketheknee-athletes-twitter-trump/|title=Twitter Saw 3.8 Million #TakeAKnee Tweets Amid Trump's Weekend Dust-Up With Pro Sports|website=www.adweek.com|access-date=2019-03-07}}</ref> The hashtag was often used with other hashtags such as #BoycottNFL and #BlackLivesMatter. #BoycottNFL is used in different states than #TakeAKnee, with those using #BoycottNFL wanting to boycott the NFL and those using #TakeAKnee supporting the players who choose to protest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.phillyvoice.com/twitter-numbers-boycott-nfl-vs-take-knee/|title=By the social-media numbers: Boycott NFL vs. Take a Knee|last=Hickey|first=Brian|website=www.phillyvoice.com|access-date=2019-03-07}}</ref>\n\n=== NFL national anthem policy ===\nThe previous national anthem policy by the NFL written about a decade before the new policy in May 2018 contained vocabulary that allotted more leeway in the players' behavior during the national anthem before games. It required players to be on the sideline but only stated that players should, not must, stand during the national anthem.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mannersmentor.com/12-months-of-holidays/u-s-flag-pledge-of-allegiance-and-national-anthem-etiquette/|title=U.S. Flag, Pledge of Allegiance, and National Anthem Etiquette}}</ref> Colin Kaepernick used this fact to an advantage and conducted his act of a peaceful protest which remained inconspicuous until President Trump posted his tweets on Twitter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/23/sports/national-anthem-nfl.html|title=N.F.L. Anthem Policy Bound to Please Only the N.F.L.|last=Belson|first=Ken|date=2018-05-23|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-04-26|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The tweets brought enormous amounts of media attention to the participating players and found people on two sides of the issue; one group that supported Kaepernick and many other players that were protesting to bring awareness to police brutality black people faced and the other group that believed kneeling was disrespectful to the country, flag, or the military.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/the-two-sides-of-the-us-national-anthem-protests-in-the-nfl/a-40673869|title=The two sides of the US national anthem protests in the NFL {{!}} DW {{!}} 25.09.2017|last=VanOpdorp|first=Davis|website=DW.COM|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>\n\nTo address the backlash, the NFL released a national anthem policy in May 2018, stating that players and team personnel were required to stand during the national anthem. Those who chose not to stand were required to remain in the locker room.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000941064/article/nfl-anthem-policy-on-hold-under-standstill-agreement|title=NFL anthem policy on hold under standstill agreement|website=NFL.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref> Though NFL commissioner [[Roger Goodell]] said the vote was unanimous among all NFL owners, [[Jed York]], the owner of the [[San Francisco 49ers]] and Kaepernick's previous team said he abstained.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/23582533|title=NFL owners pass new national anthem policy|last=Seifert|first=Kevin|last2=Graziano|first2=Dan|date=2018-05-23|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> During an interview, President Trump said that the NFL did \"the right thing\" of releasing the new policy. He added, \"You have to stand proudly for the national anthem or you shouldn\u2019t be playing. You shouldn\u2019t be there. Maybe you shouldn\u2019t be in the country.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ajc.com/news/nfl-new-national-anthem-policy-has-people-talking/JqNUUdBClTX9DNAn2UrgZL/|title=NFL's policy on flag, national anthem has people talking|last=Brett|first=Jennifer|website=AJC|language=English|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>\n\nSince passing the new national anthem policy in May 2018, the policy was put on hold in July 2018. This occurred when the [[National Football League Players Association|NFLPA]] filed a grievance against the NFL's national anthem policy, stating that the policy violated the players' rights because there were no prior discussions between the NFL and NFLPA. The policy remained suspended until [[Super Bowl LIII]] and will remain suspended until further notice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/the-super-bowl-2019-kneeling-policy-leaves-that-decision-up-to-players-15867537|title=What To Know About The NFL's Kneeling Policy Ahead Of The 2019 Super Bowl|last=Friedmann|first=Sarah|website=Bustle|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[1968 Olympics Black Power salute]]\n* [[United States Flag Code]]\n* [[Quarterback kneel]]\n* [[Tim Tebow]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Black Lives Matter}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:U.S. national anthem protests (2016-present)}}\n[[Category:U.S. national anthem protests (2016\u2013present)| ]]\n[[Category:2016 beginnings]]\n[[Category:2016 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:2016 in American sports]]\n[[Category:2016 protests]]\n[[Category:2017 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:2017 in American sports]]\n[[Category:2017 protests]]\n[[Category:2018 protests]]\n[[Category:2018 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:African-American sports history]]\n[[Category:Anti-racism in the United States]]\n[[Category:Civil rights protests in the United States]]\n[[Category:Criticism of police brutality]]\n[[Category:Flag controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Kneeling]]\n[[Category:African-American-related controversies]]\n[[Category:Race-related controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Media-related controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Music and politics]]\n[[Category:National Football League controversies]]\n[[Category:Ongoing protests]]\n[[Category:Police brutality in the United States]]\n[[Category:Politics and race in the United States]]\n[[Category:Politics and sports]]\n[[Category:Protests against Donald Trump]]\n[[Category:Sports controversies]]\n[[Category:The Star-Spangled Banner]]\n[[Category:Trump administration controversies]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Series of protests by American athletes}}\n{{for|the previous protests|U.S. national anthem protests}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox civil conflict\n| latitude =\n| longitude =\n| image = [[File:Colin Kaepernick in 2013.jpg|200px]]\n| caption = [[Colin Kaepernick]] with the [[San Francisco 49ers]] (2013)\n| date = August 14, 2016\u2013ongoing ({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|year1=2016|month1=8|day1=14}})\n| place = [[List of current National Football League stadiums|National Football League stadiums]]\n| coordinates =\n| goals = \n* To raise awareness of [[Racism in the United States|racism]] and [[Police brutality in the United States|police brutality]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benjamin |first1=Hoffman |last2=Minsberg |first2=Talya |title=The Deafening Silence of Colin Kaepernick |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/04/sports/colin-kaepernick-nfl-anthem-kneeling.html |accessdate=29 March 2019 |work=The New York Times |date=4 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180926034525/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/04/sports/colin-kaepernick-nfl-anthem-kneeling.html |archivedate=26 September 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"nytimes\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/04/sports/nike-protests-kaepernick-nfl-.html|newspaper=[[New York Times]]|accessdate=September 4, 2018|title=Nike's Deal With Kaepernick Draws Cheers and Pictures of Burning Shoes|date=September 4, 2018|first1=Jacey|last1=Fortin|first2=Matthew|last2=Haag|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905033557/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/04/sports/nike-protests-kaepernick-nfl-.html|archive-date=September 5, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* [[Freedom of speech]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=HOFFMAN |first1=BENJAMIN |last2=MATHER |first2=VICTOR |last3=FORTIN |first3=JACEY |title=After Trump Blasts N.F.L., Players Kneel and Lock Arms in Solidarity |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html |accessdate=30 March 2019 |work=The New York Times |date=24 September 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180406033924/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html |archivedate=6 April 2018}}</ref>\n* In opposition to U.S. President Donald Trump's [[Presidency of Donald Trump|policies]].<ref name=\"insider.foxnews.com\"/> \n| methods = [[Peaceful protest]]\n| status =\n| result =\n| concessions =\n| side1 =\n| side2 =\n| leadfigures1 =\n| leadfigures2 =\n| casualties1 =\n| casualties2 =\n| casualties_label =\n| howmany1 =\n| howmany2 =\n}}\n\nSince August 2016, some [[United States|American]] [[athlete]]s have protested against [[Police brutality in the United States|police brutality]] and [[Racism in the United States|racism]]<ref name=\"nytimes\"/><ref name=\"Sporting News\">{{cite magazine|title=NFL players protest during anthem; Colin Kaepernick, President Trump respond'|url=http://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/news/nfl-players-protest-during-national-anthem-colin-kaepernick-tweets-support/o3v0jxys8jbc1cr2gkzxpcb9n/|magazine=[[Sporting News]]|accessdate=10 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811110938/http://www.sportingnews.com/us/nfl/news/nfl-players-protest-during-national-anthem-colin-kaepernick-tweets-support/o3v0jxys8jbc1cr2gkzxpcb9n|archive-date=August 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"USAToday\">{{cite web|title=Aaron Rodgers sticks up for player protests during national anthem'|url=https://packerswire.usatoday.com/2018/08/08/aaron-rodgers-sticks-up-for-player-protests-during-national-anthem//|publisher=[[USAToday]]|accessdate=13 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813210402/https://packerswire.usatoday.com/2018/08/08/aaron-rodgers-sticks-up-for-player-protests-during-national-anthem/|archive-date=August 13, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=August 8, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"FoxNews\">{{cite web|title=Hillary Clinton defends kneeling NFL players, says 'that's not against our anthem or flag'|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2017/10/16/hillary-clinton-defends-kneeling-nfl-players-says-thats-not-against-our-anthem-or-flag.html/|publisher=[[Fox News]]|accessdate=10 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811195959/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2017/10/16/hillary-clinton-defends-kneeling-nfl-players-says-thats-not-against-our-anthem-or-flag.html|archive-date=August 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"SBNation\">{{cite web|title=Everything you need to know about NFL protests during the national anthem|url=https://www.sbnation.com/2017/9/29/16380080/donald-trump-nfl-colin-kaepernick-protests-national-anthem/|publisher=[[SBNation]]|accessdate=10 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811032759/https://www.sbnation.com/2017/9/29/16380080/donald-trump-nfl-colin-kaepernick-protests-national-anthem/|archive-date=August 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 29, 2017}}</ref> by [[kneeling]] on one knee during the [[U.S. national anthem]].<ref name=\"insider.foxnews.com\">{{cite news|title=Kevin Jackson: 'Kaepernick Effect' to Blame for NFL's Ratings Decline|date=September 23, 2017|website=FoxNews.com|url=http://insider.foxnews.com/2017/09/23/president-trump-slams-colin-kaepernick-nfl-national-anthem-protests-kevin-jackson-reacts|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924064351/http://insider.foxnews.com/2017/09/23/president-trump-slams-colin-kaepernick-nfl-national-anthem-protests-kevin-jackson-reacts|archivedate=September 28, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Since 2017, many players also began protesting against President [[Donald Trump]]'s<ref name=\"insider.foxnews.com\"/> criticisms of those involved in the protest as well as against Trump's policies since taking office.<ref name=\"insider.foxnews.com\"/> Some observers have described the protests as politically motivated or patriotic, while others have criticized the attention to [[social issue]]s during [[sport|sporting events]], and others have called the protests unpatriotic or disrespectful. The act itself is referred to as \"taking a knee\" or \"taking the knee\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Mindock|first=Clark|title=Taking a knee: Why are NFL players protesting and when did they start kneeling?|date=September 26, 2017|newspaper=The Independent|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/taking-a-knee-national-anthem-nfl-trump-why-meaning-origins-racism-us-colin-kaepernick-a7966961.html|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Hafner|first=Josh|title=Anthem kneeling isn't aimed at veterans, and other NFL protest misconceptions|date=September 25, 2017|newspaper=USA Today|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2017/09/25/anthem-kneeling-isnt-aimed-veterans-and-other-nfl-protest-misconceptions/701409001/|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe protests began in the [[National Football League]] (NFL) after [[San Francisco 49ers]] [[quarterback]] [[Colin Kaepernick]] sat and later [[knelt]] during the anthem, before his team's [[National Football League preseason|preseason]] games of [[2016 NFL season|2016]].<ref name=\"SB\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sbnation.com/2016/9/11/12869726/colin-kaepernick-national-anthem-protest-seahawks-brandon-marshall-nfl|title=A timeline of Colin Kaepernick's national anthem protest and the NFL players who joined him|last1=Sandritter|first1=Mark|publisher=SB Nation|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160912110107/https://www.sbnation.com/2016/9/11/12869726/colin-kaepernick-national-anthem-protest-seahawks-brandon-marshall-nfl|archive-date=September 12, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 11, 2016}}</ref> Throughout the following seasons, members of various NFL and other sports teams have engaged in similar silent protests. On September 24, 2017, the NFL protests became more widespread when over 200 players sat or knelt in response to President Trump's calling for owners to \"fire\" the protesting players.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/24/donald-trump-nfl-player-protests-national-anthem-week-3-response/697609001/|title=NFL player protests sweep league after President Donald Trump's hostile remarks|work=USA Today|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925041022/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/24/donald-trump-nfl-player-protests-national-anthem-week-3-response/697609001/|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\n{{further|U.S. national anthem protests}}\nIt is a tradition in the United States to play \"[[The Star-Spangled Banner]]\", the [[national anthem]], before sporting events.<ref name=\":2\" /> According to the [[United States Code]], those present should stand at attention with right hand over heart.<ref>{{usc|36|301}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Title 36 United States Code: \u00a7 301. National Anthem.|url= https://www.senate.gov/reference/resources/pdf/RL30243.pdf#page=11|publisher= [[United States Senate]]|date= October 31, 2016|accessdate= June 5, 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180710143658/https://www.senate.gov/reference/resources/pdf/RL30243.pdf#page=11|archive-date= July 10, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-37208404|title= What must Americans do during the anthem?|date= September 25, 2017|work= BBC News|access-date= September 27, 2017|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170924150335/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-37208404|archive-date= September 24, 2017|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref> [[National Football League]] (NFL) players were not mandated to be on the field for the playing of the national anthem until 2009.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite news|last= Willingham|first= AJ|title= The national anthem in sports (spoiler: it wasn't always this way)|url= http://www.cnn.com/2017/09/25/us/nfl-national-anthem-trump-kaepernick-history-trnd/index.html|publisher= [[Time Warner]]|website= CNN.com|date= September 25, 2017|accessdate= June 5, 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180605102013/https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/25/us/nfl-national-anthem-trump-kaepernick-history-trnd/index.html|archive-date= June 5, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref>  In 2016 the NFL stated that \"players are encouraged but not required to stand during the playing of the National Anthem\"; its game operations manual reads that players \"should stand\" for the anthem.<ref>{{cite news|last= O'Malley|first= Nick|title= NFL rulebook does not require players to stand for national anthem; Game Operations manual does|date= September 26, 2017|work= MassLive.com|url= http://blog.masslive.com/patriots/2017/09/facebook_post_citing_nfl_playe.html|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20171010060237/http://blog.masslive.com/patriots/2017/09/facebook_post_citing_nfl_playe.html|archivedate= October 10, 2017|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nThe people of the United States are divided on the intended meaning of the anthem. Some believe it salutes military and police officers who have died on duty; for others, it honors the United States generally.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite news|last= Brady|first= Erik|title= How national anthem became essential part of sports|url= https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/26/how-national-anthem-become-essential-part-sports/706243001/|newspaper= USA Today|date= September 27, 2017|accessdate= June 5, 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180618180904/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/26/how-national-anthem-become-essential-part-sports/706243001/|archive-date= June 18, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1= Har|first1= Janie|last2= Contreras|first2= Russell|title= Diverse America divided on flag, anthem, other symbols|date= September 16, 2016|publisher= Associated Press|url= https://apnews.com/1959daeed38b466395f053f6f9b2dc52/diverse-america-divided-flag-anthem-other-symbols|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20171207181301/https://apnews.com/1959daeed38b466395f053f6f9b2dc52/diverse-america-divided-flag-anthem-other-symbols|archivedate= December 7, 2017|url-status= live}}</ref> Between 2012 and 2015, the [[United States Department of Defense|Department of Defense]] gave $6.8 million to teams across all major sports in exchange for holding various military and patriotic events at their games, including the performance of the national anthem.<ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.mccain.senate.gov/public/_cache/files/12de6dcb-d8d8-4a58-8795-562297f948c1/tackling-paid-patriotism-oversight-report.pdf|title= Tackling Paid Patriotism|last= McCain|first= John|last2= Flake|first2= Jeff|date= 2015|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180804100831/https://www.mccain.senate.gov/public/_cache/files/12de6dcb-d8d8-4a58-8795-562297f948c1/tackling-paid-patriotism-oversight-report.pdf|archive-date= August 4, 2018|url-status= dead|df= mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nKaepernick and his 49ers teammate [[Eric Reid (American football)|Eric Reid]] say they choose to kneel during the anthem to call attention to the issues of racial inequality and police brutality. \"After hours of careful consideration, and even a visit from [[Nate Boyer]], a retired [[Special Forces (United States Army)|Green Beret]] and former NFL player, we came to the conclusion that we should kneel, rather than sit, ... during the anthem as a peaceful protest,\" said Reid. \"We chose to kneel because it's a [[respect]]ful gesture.  I remember thinking our posture was like a flag flown at half-mast to mark a tragedy.\"<ref>{{cite news|last= Reid|first= Eric|title= Opinion {{!}} Eric Reid: Why Colin Kaepernick and I Decided to Take a Knee|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/25/opinion/colin-kaepernick-football-protests.html|newspaper= [[The New York Times]]|date= September 25, 2017|access-date= September 27, 2017|issn= 0362-4331|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170926221519/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/25/opinion/colin-kaepernick-football-protests.html|archive-date= September 26, 2017|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref> Some regard kneeling as disrespectful to those who have died or been wounded in service of the United States, such as police officers or military veterans.<ref>{{cite news|last= MacQuarrie|first= Brian|title= Military veterans divided over NFL protests|url= https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2017/09/25/military/MLjykBWSTbMlWqbaVUAGzI/story.html|newspaper= The Boston Globe|date= September 27, 2017|access-date= June 5, 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180618175552/https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2017/09/25/military/MLjykBWSTbMlWqbaVUAGzI/story.html|archive-date= June 18, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}</ref> [[Torrey Smith]], a wide receiver for the [[Carolina Panthers]], said in an interview: \"I understand why people are offended by people protesting the National Anthem. My father served 25 years. When he dies, he's going to be wrapped in an American flag. But my dad is also out of the Army, and he drives trucks all over the country, and he's a black man everywhere he goes, and sometimes he has racial incidents still today. That doesn't protect him, just because he served our country. And I think that's important.\"<ref>\n{{Cite news|url= https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/27/us/nfl-anthem-protest-race-trump-trnd/index.html|title= The #TakeAKnee protests have always been about race. Period.|last= CNN|first= AJ Willingham|work= CNN|access-date= 2018-06-18|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180618175526/https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/27/us/nfl-anthem-protest-race-trump-trnd/index.html|archive-date= June 18, 2018|url-status= live|df= mdy-all}}\n</ref>\n\nKaepernick has mentioned before that the sole purpose of kneeling during the national anthem is not to disrespect the military personnel at all, instead Kaepernick's goal is to use his social platform to bring topics regarding police brutality and  oppression of people of color to light. \"I am not going to get up to show pride in a country that oppresses black people and people of color.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/08/25/opinion/football-protests-police-violence-anthem.html|title=Opinion {{!}} Football Players Are Protesting Police Violence, Not the Anthem|last=Cauley|first=Kashana|date=2018-08-25|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-04-10|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Kaepernick even went ahead an express his concerns about how his action have been labeled as \"anthem protest\" since he considers this to be a shameful strategy from his critics to deviate the discussion from what really matters. \"To me, this is bigger than football and it would be selfish to look the other way. There are bodies in the street and people getting paid leave and getting away with murder.\u201d<ref>{{Cite news|title=getting-away-with-murder|doi = 10.1163/2210-7975_hrd-1323-0125}}</ref>\n\nBy labelling the action of kneeling as anthem protest, critics have been successful at switching the topic of discussion to anything except police brutality. After Kaepernick started his campaign to create awareness about excess police brutality towards minorities, especially African-Americans, commentators have mainly shifted focus to the patriotic aspect of kneeling rather than the meaning behind it; thus weakening Kaepernick's primary goal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2016/sep/16/colin-kaepernick-protest-racial-iniquity-nfl-american-football|title=Colin Kaepernick's critics are ignoring the target of his protest|last=Graham|first=Bryan Armen|date=2016-09-16|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-04-10|last2=Carpenter|first2=Les|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> One political person that players believe completely misinterpreted the act of kneeling was President Trump, since he believes that players are protesting the flag and the national anthem; however, players are for the most part protesting the lack of accountability in the judicial system, and the way police officers can easily get away with police brutality towards African-Americans.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2017/09/why-the-nfl-is-protesting/540927/|title=They Took a Knee|last=Garber|first=Megan|date=2017-09-24|website=The Atlantic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref>\n\nKaepernick was not able to sign a contract with any NFL team even after he opted out of his contract with the 49ers and became a free agent in 2017, presumably because of his actions of taking a knee.<ref name=\"Reid\">{{Cite web|url=https://theundefeated.com/features/how-colin-kaepernick-became-a-cause-for-activists-civil-rights-groups/|title=How Colin Kaepernick became a cause for activists, civil rights groups and others|last=Reid|first=Jason|date=2017-08-22|website=The Undefeated|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref> Nevertheless, even though Kaepernick was no longer on the sideline, his movement did not stop but rather gained more participants.<ref name=\"Reid\"/>\n\n== Causes ==\n[[File:Police_protest.jpg|thumb|left|Protestors demanding police accountability.]]\n[[Criminal justice reform in the United States|Criminal justice reform]] is one of the top issues that NFL players have been supporting in their protests.<ref>{{cite news|last=Reid|first=Jason|title=NFL owners, players are moving in the wrong direction|date=October 30, 2017|work=The Undefeated|url=https://theundefeated.com/features/nfl-owners-players-are-moving-in-the-wrong-direction/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030163548/https://theundefeated.com/features/nfl-owners-players-are-moving-in-the-wrong-direction/|archivedate=October 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Kaepernick was initially moved to protest by the deaths of African-Americans at the hands of police or while in police custody. These deaths gained prominence through the media and the [[Black Lives Matter]] movement in the years immediately preceding the protest.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/news_and_politics/jurisprudence/2016/10/ruth_bader_ginsburg_s_kaepernick_comments_end_the_notorious_rbg_myth.html|title=Ruth Bader Ginsburg Was Never Really \"Notorious RBG\"|last=Stern|first=Mark Joseph|date=October 11, 2016|work=Slate|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> During a post-game interview on August 26, 2016, he stated, \"I am not going to stand up to show pride in a flag for a country that oppresses [[black people]] and [[people of color]]. To me, this is bigger than football and it would be selfish on my part to look the other way. There are bodies in the street and people getting paid leave and getting away with murder\", adding that he would continue to protest during the anthem until he feels like \"[the United States flag] represents what it's supposed to represent.\"<ref name=\"wyche\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000691077/article/colin-kaepernick-explains-protest-of-national-anthem|title=Colin Kaepernick explains why he sat during national anthem|last=Wyche|first=Steve|date=August 27, 2016|publisher=National Football League|accessdate=August 27, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827165405/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000691077/article/colin-kaepernick-explains-protest-of-national-anthem|archive-date=August 27, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/09/18/colin-kaepernick-nfl-black-lives-matter-protests-recall-rebellio/|title=Colin Kaepernick: NFL Black Lives Matter protests recall rebellious spirit of 1960s sporting greats|author=Nick Allen|date=September 18, 2016|newspaper=The Telegraph|accessdate=November 8, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161130224836/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/09/18/colin-kaepernick-nfl-black-lives-matter-protests-recall-rebellio/|archive-date=November 30, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAfter that interview, Kaepernick pledged to donate the first $1 million of his $11.9 million salary from the 2016\u20132017 season to different organizations that help communities in need.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/colin-kaepernick-says-hell-donate-1-million-to-charities-that-help-communities-in-need/|title=Colin Kaepernick to donate $1&nbsp;million to charities that aid communities in need|last1=Wagner-McGough|first1=Sean|date=September 2, 2016|publisher=cbssports.com|accessdate=October 17, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017042221/http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/colin-kaepernick-says-hell-donate-1-million-to-charities-that-help-communities-in-need/|archive-date=October 17, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He pledged to donate $100,000 per month for 10 months to various organizations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ninerswire.usatoday.com/2016/09/20/colin-kaepernick-to-donate-100k-a-month-for-10-months/|title=Colin Kaepernick to donate $100k a month for 10 months|last1=Biderman|first1=Chris|work=USA Today|format=September 20, 2016|accessdate=October 17, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018213014/http://ninerswire.usatoday.com/2016/09/20/colin-kaepernick-to-donate-100k-a-month-for-10-months/|archive-date=October 18, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 20, 2016}}</ref> Days later, the San Francisco 49ers matched Kaepernick by pledging $1 million to two organizations addressing racial and social inequality.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/nfl/la-sp-colin-kaepernick-49ers-donation-20160908-snap-story.html|title=49ers to donate $1&nbsp;million to charities that focus on racial issues cited by Colin Kaepernick|last1=Loumena|first1=Dan|date=September 9, 2016|work=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=October 17, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018225111/http://www.latimes.com/sports/nfl/la-sp-colin-kaepernick-49ers-donation-20160908-snap-story.html|archive-date=October 18, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick has been following through on his commitment and has donated $900,000 as of September 2017 to groups including [[Meals on Wheels]], United We Dream, Black Veterans for Social Justice and many others.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/08/colin-kaepernick-nfl-national-anthem-protest-one-million-dollar-pledge-donations-empower-communities|title=Colin Kaepernick has donated $800k to empower oppressed communities|date=August 23, 2017|work=For The Win|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928010003/http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/08/colin-kaepernick-nfl-national-anthem-protest-one-million-dollar-pledge-donations-empower-communities|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/maurybrown/2017/09/15/dont-ignore-this-positive-pr-twist-to-colin-kaepernick/#77a7a1d35740|title=Don't Ignore This Positive PR Twist To Colin Kaepernick|last=Brown|first=Maury|work=Forbes|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928010447/https://www.forbes.com/sites/maurybrown/2017/09/15/dont-ignore-this-positive-pr-twist-to-colin-kaepernick/#77a7a1d35740|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick has also held \"Know Your Rights\" camps for young [[People of Color|people of color]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://knowyourrightscamp.com/about/|title=About Us \u2013 Know Your Rights Camp|website=knowyourrightscamp.com|access-date=2017-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107012755/http://knowyourrightscamp.com/about/|archive-date=November 7, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>  The camps include legal education from attorneys that give advice on how to interact with police when being detained and lectures from prominent academics on the history of the [[Civil Rights Movement]] in the United States.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenation.com/article/colin-kaepernicks-message-to-chicago-youth-know-your-rights/|title=Colin Kaepernick's Message to Chicago Youth: 'Know Your Rights'|last=Zirin|first=Dave|date=May 10, 2017|work=The Nation|access-date=September 27, 2017|issn=0027-8378|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928010247/https://www.thenation.com/article/colin-kaepernicks-message-to-chicago-youth-know-your-rights/|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2016/10/30/colin-kaepernick-holds-know-your-rights-camp-for-underprivileged-bay-area-kids/|title=Colin Kaepernick holds 'Know Your Rights' camp for underprivileged Bay Area kids|last=Bieler|first=Des|date=October 30, 2016|work=Washington Post|access-date=September 27, 2017|issn=0190-8286|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928005714/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2016/10/30/colin-kaepernick-holds-know-your-rights-camp-for-underprivileged-bay-area-kids/|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The [[National Football League Players Association]] (NFLPA) named Kaepernick the Week One MVP in September 2017 for his charity work related to the protest.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/15/nfl-players-union-names-colin-kaepernick-its-week-1-mvp-for-his-charity-work/|title=NFL players' union names Colin Kaepernick its Week 1 MVP for his charity work|last=Payne|first=Marissa|date=September 15, 2017|work=Washington Post|access-date=September 27, 2017|issn=0190-8286|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928005350/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/15/nfl-players-union-names-colin-kaepernick-its-week-1-mvp-for-his-charity-work/|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick also joined the 10 for 10 challenge, which basically consists of donating ten thousand dollars for ten consecutive days. Some major celebrities that matched Kaepernick's donations include basketball players [[Steph Curry]] and [[Kevin Durant]], tennis player [[Serena Williams]], and rappers [[Snoop Dogg]], [[Meek Mill]], and [[Usher (musician)|Usher]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/jan/31/colin-kaepernick-million-dollar-pledge-goal|title=Colin Kaepernick reaches $1m pledge goal with help from famous friends|last=sport|first=Guardian|date=2018-01-31|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-04-10|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\n=== Trump calls for firing protesting players===\n{{see also|Protests against Donald Trump}}\n[[File:Donald Trump with jersey, helmet and football of New England Patriots.jpg|thumb|President Trump meeting with the players and staff of [[New England Patriots]] at the [[White House]] on April 19, 2017 following their [[Super Bowl LI]] win over the [[Atlanta Falcons]].]]\nIn September 2017 at a rally in [[Huntsville, Alabama]], President Trump said NFL owners should fire players who kneel during the national anthem and encouraged fans to walk out. Trump advised NFL owners, \"get that son of a bitch off the field right now, out, he's fired. He's fired!\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/09/23/media/donald-trump-nfl-protest-backlash/index.html|title=With 'son of a bitch' comments, Trump tried to divide NFL and its players|last=Stelter|first=Brian|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924064744/http://money.cnn.com/2017/09/23/media/donald-trump-nfl-protest-backlash/index.html|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 23, 2017}}</ref> He called the players' protest \"a total disrespect of our heritage\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trump-to-nfl-owners-fire-players-who-kneel-during-national-anthem/|title=Trump to NFL owners: Fire players who kneel during national anthem|date=September 23, 2017|publisher=CBS News|access-date=September 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923151054/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trump-to-nfl-owners-fire-players-who-kneel-during-national-anthem/|archive-date=September 23, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Trump added on that the new NFL safety rules created to protect players from [[Concussions in American football|concussions]] were ruining the game for the public.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/26/congresswoman-trump-endangering-nfl-players-with-reckless-comments-about-safety/|title=Congresswoman: Trump endangering NFL players with 'reckless' comments about safety|last=Payne|first=Marissa|date=September 26, 2017|work=Washington Post|access-date=September 27, 2017|issn=0190-8286|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928005425/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/26/congresswoman-trump-endangering-nfl-players-with-reckless-comments-about-safety/|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> His statement came after a new research indicated that NFL players are at high risk for [[chronic traumatic encephalopathy]] (CTE) due to the likelihood of multiple head injuries.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2017/07/25/539198429/study-cte-found-in-nearly-all-donated-nfl-player-brains|title=Study: CTE Found In Nearly All Donated NFL Player Brains|work=NPR.org|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002145718/http://www.npr.org/2017/07/25/539198429/study-cte-found-in-nearly-all-donated-nfl-player-brains|archive-date=October 2, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nTrump said his criticism of the protesters was not related to race. \"This has to do with respect for our country and respect for our flag,\" he said.<ref>{{cite news|first1=Bryan Armen|last1=Graham|first2=Martin|last2=Pengelly|title=NFL players kneel for anthem in unprecedented defiance of Trump|date=September 24, 2017|newspaper=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/sep/24/donald-trump-nfl-protests-kneel-anthem|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171026045803/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/sep/24/donald-trump-nfl-protests-kneel-anthem|archivedate=October 26, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In the games immediately following Trump's statements, the protest gained broader participation when over 200 players sat or knelt during the anthem, others linked arms with their teammates or raised fists, and three teams chose to stay in the locker room for the anthem.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\"SB\" /><ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html|title=After Trump Blasts N.F.L., Players Kneel and Lock Arms in Solidarity|last=Hoffman|first=Benjamin|date=September 24, 2017|work=The New York Times|access-date=September 27, 2017|last2=Mather|first2=Victor|issn=0362-4331|last3=Fortin|first3=Jacey|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927160450/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html|archive-date=September 27, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> However, the response quickly turned into one towards Trump, rather than Kaepernick's original protests of racial injustice.<ref name=\":4\"/><ref name=\"latimes.com\">{{cite news|last1=Farmer|first1=Sam|last2=King|first2=Laura|title=As Trump continues his attacks, NFL players protest by kneeling or locking arms|date=September 24, 2017|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/nfl/la-sp-nfl-players-protest-trump-20170924-story.html|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Jones|first=Jonathan|title=A Gesture of Support by NFL Owners Is Meaningless without Them Taking Real Action|date=September 26, 2017|website=SI.com|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2017/09/26/nfl-anthem-protests-team-owners-shad-khan-dan-snyder|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Reasons cited by players, owners, and coaches included supporting freedom of speech and opposing what they considered intimidation by Trump.<ref name=\":4\" /> Others said they took offense to Trump demeaning the integrity of their primarily African American colleagues, when a month earlier he had hesitated to condemn the  [[white nationalists]] who [[Unite the Right rally|protested in Charlottesville, Virginia]] and murdered a counter protester.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sbnation.com/2017/9/23/16354502/donald-trump-nfl-players-reactions-national-anthem-protests-twitter|title=NFL players respond with heat to Donald Trump's comments about protests|work=SBNation.com|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928010201/https://www.sbnation.com/2017/9/23/16354502/donald-trump-nfl-players-reactions-national-anthem-protests-twitter|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/nfl-eric-reid-donald-trump-race-row-neo-nazis-charlottesville-fine-people-president-us-latest-a7967811.html|title=NFL player who started anti-Trump movement: 'He refers to us with slurs but Charlottesville neo-Nazis as 'very fine people'|date=September 26, 2017|work=The Independent|access-date=September 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928103059/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/nfl-eric-reid-donald-trump-race-row-neo-nazis-charlottesville-fine-people-president-us-latest-a7967811.html|archive-date=September 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The reaction to Trump's remarks were amidst other ongoing issues his administration was facing, including failed [[American Health Care Act of 2017|attempts at healthcare reform]], the primary election loss of Trump-backed candidate [[Luther Strange]] for the [[United States Senate special election in Alabama, 2017|Alabama seat in the U.S. Senate]], recovery efforts for [[Hurricane Maria]] in Puerto Rico, [[Hurricane Irma]] in Florida, and [[Hurricane Harvey]] in [[Houston]], and [[North Korea\u2013United States relations|relations with North Korea]] over their [[2017 North Korean nuclear test|nuclear]] and [[2017 North Korean missile tests|missile testing]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Donald Trump fuels NFL anthem row by tweeting year old video|date=October 1, 2017|newspaper=The Telegraph|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/10/01/donald-trump-fuels-nfl-anthem-row-tweeting-year-old-video/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171001063651/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/10/01/donald-trump-fuels-nfl-anthem-row-tweeting-year-old-video/|archivedate=October 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMany players beyond the 2017 season have knelt or raised fists in protest against Trump's policies.<ref name=\":4\"/><ref name=\"latimes.com\"/> Other Republicans such as Florida senator [[Marco Rubio]] also expressed their discomforts against these policies as well. While Rubio's objections were not aimed directly to President Trump directly, he did support the rights of players of kneeling during the national anthem, especially [[Miami Dolphins]] player [[Kenny Stills]]. Rubio tweeted, \"No @NFL player does more community service than @KStills of the @MiamiDolphins. You don\u2019t have to agree with how or why he has chosen to exercise the 1st Amendment before every game to acknowledge the hours he gives voluntarily, on his day off, to serve his fellow Americans.\"<ref name=\"Deen\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/fl-sp-dolphins-marco-rubio-kenny-stills-20180913-story.html|title=Sen. Marco Rubio praises Dolphins receiver Kenny Stills for community service|last=Deen|first=Safid|date=|website=latimes.com|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190427002116/https://www.latimes.com/fl-sp-dolphins-marco-rubio-kenny-stills-20180913-story.html|archive-date=2018-04-27|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> Senator Marco Rubio has also expressed his feeling about Kaepernick, and while he publicly stated that he does not agree with what Kaepernick does (taking a knee during the national anthem), he does support his rights that allows him to do so and he believes that the NFL should not prohibit him from playing in the league again.<ref name=\"Deen\"/>\n\nIn a May 2018 interview, Trump stated \"You have to stand proudly for the national anthem, or you shouldn't be playing, you shouldn't be there. Maybe you shouldn't be in the country\". He applauded\u00a0the new policy that NFL players must either stand for the anthem or stay back in the locker room, but felt that this policy was not strict enough.<ref name=\"nbcnews.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/donald-trump/trump-says-nfl-players-who-kneel-during-national-anthem-maybe-n876996|title=Trump says athletes who kneel during anthem 'maybe shouldn't be in the country'|website=NBC News|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120225813/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/donald-trump/trump-says-nfl-players-who-kneel-during-national-anthem-maybe-n876996|archive-date=January 20, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n==NFL protests==\n\n===2016 preseason===\nKaepernick began sitting during the national anthem at the start of the 2016 NFL preseason. His actions went unnoticed for two weeks before he was questioned by the media.<ref>{{cite news|last=Levin|first=Josh|title=Colin Kaepernick's Protest Is Working|date=September 12, 2016|work=Slate|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/sports/sports_nut/2016/09/colin_kaepernick_s_protest_is_working.html|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In the 49ers' final 2016 preseason game on September 1, 2016, after talking to Boyer, Kaepernick opted to kneel during the U.S. national anthem rather than sit as he did in their previous games. He explained his decision to switch was an attempt to show more respect to former and current U.S. military members while still protesting during the anthem.  [[Eric Reid (American football)|Eric Reid]] joined Kaepernick in kneeling during the national anthem during the final preseason game.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/sep/01/colin-kaepernick-eric-reid-kneel-national-anthem-protest-san-francisco-49ers|title=Colin Kaepernick joined by Eric Reid in kneeling for national anthem protest|last=Press|first=Associated|date=September 1, 2016|newspaper=The Guardian|issn=0261-3077|access-date=September 7, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160907050158/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/sep/01/colin-kaepernick-eric-reid-kneel-national-anthem-protest-san-francisco-49ers|archive-date=September 7, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Seattle Seahawks]] player [[Jeremy Lane]] also did not stand for the anthem during his final preseason game the same day, stating, \"It's something I plan to keep on doing until justice is being served.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/seahawks/2016/09/01/jeremy-lane-colin-kaepernick-national-anthem-protest/89752460/|title=Seahawks' Jeremy Lane joins Colin Kaepernick's protest, sits during national anthem|access-date=September 7, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160905103948/http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/seahawks/2016/09/01/jeremy-lane-colin-kaepernick-national-anthem-protest/89752460/|archive-date=September 5, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===2016 season===\nIn Week 1, eleven NFL players joined Kaepernick's protests.<ref name=\"breech\">{{cite web|last1=Breech|first1=John|title=Here are the 11 players who joined Colin Kaepernick's protest in Week 1|url=http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/here-are-the-11-players-who-joined-colin-kaepernicks-protest-in-week-1/|publisher=CBS News|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918003249/http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/here-are-the-11-players-who-joined-colin-kaepernicks-protest-in-week-1/|archive-date=September 18, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Denver Broncos]] player [[Brandon Marshall (linebacker)|Brandon Marshall]] knelt during the national anthem prior to the start of the [[National Football League Kickoff game|Kickoff game]], which was broadcast on [[NBC Sunday Night Football|NBC]].<ref name=\"money\">{{cite web|last1=Scott|first1=Nate|title=Broncos linebacker Brandon Marshall takes knee during national anthem|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2016/09/broncos-brandon-marshall-takes-knee-national-anthem-colin-kaepernick|work=USA Today|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923104532/http://ftw.usatoday.com/2016/09/broncos-brandon-marshall-takes-knee-national-anthem-colin-kaepernick|archive-date=September 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 9, 2016}}</ref> The act of kneeling as protest has been referred to as \"taking a knee\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/what-the-nfl-take-a-knee-protests-mean/2017/09/26/4915930e-a210-11e7-b573-8ec86cdfe1ed_story.html|title=Opinion {{!}} What the NFL take-a-knee protests mean|website=Washington Post|access-date=2017-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171003075819/https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/what-the-nfl-take-a-knee-protests-mean/2017/09/26/4915930e-a210-11e7-b573-8ec86cdfe1ed_story.html|archive-date=October 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/09/30/us/costas-nfl-cnntv/index.html|title=Bob Costas: Stand for anthem, then take a knee|first=Alexandra |last=King|work=CNN|access-date=2017-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171003124816/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/09/30/us/costas-nfl-cnntv/index.html|archive-date=October 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/taking-a-knee-national-anthem-nfl-trump-why-meaning-origins-racism-us-colin-kaepernick-a7966961.html|title=All you need to know about why NFL players are taking a knee and where it came from|date=2017-09-25|work=The Independent|access-date=2017-10-03|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archive-date=September 27, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick and Marshall were teammates at the [[University of Nevada]].<ref name=\"money\"/>\n\nKaepernick and Marshall were by no means the first pro football players to be seen kneeling on the field.  Beginning in 2011, a white quarterback named [[Tim Tebow]] was seen kneeling on the sidelines, as if in prayer, often enough to inspire the [[neologism]] \"Tebowing.\"  Tebow was awarded a trademark for that term in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap1000000082438/article/tim-tebow-awarded-trademark-to-tebowing|title=Tim Tebow awarded trademark to Tebowing|work=[[National Football League]]|date=October 19, 2012|accessdate=October 19, 2012}}</ref> (Tebow's actions were not considered controversial at the time.)\n\nOn September 11, [[Kansas City Chiefs]] cornerback [[Marcus Peters]] [[raised fist|raised his fist]] while the rest of the team interlocked their arms showing [[solidarity]].<ref name=\"time\">{{cite news|last1=Gajanan|first1=Mahita|title=Kansas City Chiefs Cornerback Marcus Peters Raises Fist During National Anthem|url=http://time.com/4486853/kansas-city-chiefs-marcus-peters-national-anthem/|work=Time|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160917233412/http://time.com/4486853/kansas-city-chiefs-marcus-peters-national-anthem/|archive-date=September 17, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Two members of the [[New England Patriots]], [[Devin McCourty]] and [[Martellus Bennett]], raised their fists on ''[[NBC Sunday Night Football|Sunday Night Football]]''. The entire Seattle Seahawks team stood and interlocked arms.<ref name=\"arnold\">{{cite web|last1=Arnold|first1=Geoffrey|title=Seattle Seahawks lock arms during national anthem|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/nfl/index.ssf/2016/09/seattle_seahawks_lock_arms_dur.html|work=The Oregonian|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923114745/http://www.oregonlive.com/nfl/index.ssf/2016/09/seattle_seahawks_lock_arms_dur.html|archive-date=September 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=September 12, 2016}}</ref> [[Jelani Jenkins]], [[Arian Foster]], [[Kenny Stills]], and [[Michael Thomas (defensive back)|Michael Thomas]] of the [[Miami Dolphins]] all knelt during the National Anthem.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ajc.com/sports/miami-dolphins-kneel-during-national-anthem/tVERFq0ty4uFmEqT2ULKCL/|title=4 Miami Dolphins kneel during national anthem|first=Hal|last=Habib|website=ajc|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906141157/http://www.ajc.com/sports/miami-dolphins-kneel-during-national-anthem/tVERFq0ty4uFmEqT2ULKCL/|archive-date=September 6, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> At the same time, a group of [[Jacksonville Jaguars]] players, led by cornerback [[Prince Amukamara]], initially planned to join the protest but chose not to do so after photographs of Kaepernick wearing socks with a crude anti-police message during training camp were made public.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/jacksonville-jaguars/post/_/id/19870/jaguars-players-considered-protest-but-pig-socks-derailed-plans|title=Jaguars players considered protest, but pig socks scuttled plans|accessdate=December 16, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123201306/http://www.espn.com/blog/jacksonville-jaguars/post/_/id/19870/jaguars-players-considered-protest-but-pig-socks-derailed-plans|archive-date=November 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=November 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn November 13, 2016, five days after Donald Trump was [[2016 United States presidential election|elected]] [[President of the United States|President]], [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] wide-receiver [[Mike Evans (wide receiver)|Mike Evans]] decided to sit during the national anthem. According to ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'', Evans said, \"If this happens, then America's not right right now. I said this a long time ago. When he ran, I thought it was a joke, and the joke continues. I'm not a political person that much, but I got common sense. And I know when something's not right.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/mike-evans-sat-during-anthem-to-protest-donald-trump-presidency/ |title=Mike Evans sat during anthem to protest Donald Trump presidency |publisher=CBSSports.com |access-date=November 27, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128133213/http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/mike-evans-sat-during-anthem-to-protest-donald-trump-presidency/ |archive-date=November 28, 2016 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> However, his protest began the day following [[Veterans Day]], so he received criticism. He quickly changed his method of protesting and joined his teammates during the following game against the Kansas City Chiefs. He apologized to veterans and other members of the military for his actions \u2013 citing that the timing of his protest was poor. \"On the field, I'm going to continue to do what I do \u2013 play hard. I'm playing hard because I've got this right \u2013 freedom, because of the vets. I'm going to reach out to organizations, organizations that I feel are doing the best job to help the minority ... women, LGBT, African Americans, Latinos, people that are in fear of Donald Trump and his presidency.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/tampa-bay-buccaneers/post/_/id/15124/bucs-mike-evans-stands-for-national-anthem |title=Bucs' Mike Evans ends protest, stands for national anthem |publisher=ESPN |access-date=November 27, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128050728/http://www.espn.com/blog/tampa-bay-buccaneers/post/_/id/15124/bucs-mike-evans-stands-for-national-anthem |archive-date=November 28, 2016 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n===2017 season===\n[[File:Oakland Raiders National Anthem Kneeling (37444579735).jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Oakland Raiders players [[kneeling]] in week{{nbsp}}3]]\n[[Cleveland Browns]] tight end [[Seth DeValve]] became the first white football player to kneel or sit during the anthem on the team's August 21, 2017 preseason game against the [[New York Giants]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadspin.com/seth-devalve-is-the-first-white-player-to-kneel-for-the-1798295618|title=Seth DeValve Is The First White Player To Kneel for the National Anthem|last=Baccellieri|first=Emma|access-date=August 22, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170822053647/http://deadspin.com/seth-devalve-is-the-first-white-player-to-kneel-for-the-1798295618|archive-date=August 22, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> \n[[File:Washington Redskins National Anthem Kneeling (37301887651) (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=1.85|Washington Redskins players kneeling before the game with the Oakland Raiders]]\n[[File:San Francisco 49ers National Anthem Kneeling (37721041581).jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Members of the San Francisco 49ers kneeling during the National Anthem before a game against the Washington Redskins in week 6]]\n<!-- See talk page for a discussion regarding this list. -->\nIn Week 3 of the season the majority of games were played two days after Trump made his statements.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Graham|first1=Bryan|title=Donald Trump blasts NFL anthem protesters: 'Get that son of a bitch off the field'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/sep/22/donald-trump-nfl-national-anthem-protests|website=theguardian|publisher=Guardian News|accessdate=3 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170923222421/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/sep/22/donald-trump-nfl-national-anthem-protests|archive-date=September 23, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The protest gained broader participation when over 200 players sat or knelt during the anthem.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"SB\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{cite news|title=Cowboys are one of six NFL teams that haven't had a player kneel, sit or raise a fist during national anthem|date=September 25, 2017|newspaper=The Dallas Morning News|url=https://sportsday.dallasnews.com/dallas-cowboys/cowboys/2017/09/25/cowboys-one-six-nfl-teams-player-kneel-sit-national-anthem|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query|archivedate=September 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Many players, coaches and NFL teams protested and/or issued statements expressing dismay with Trump's comments:<ref name=\"ESPN.com\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/nflnation/post/_/id/249755/nfl-players-who-protested-during-the-national-anthem-in-week-3|title=NFL players who protested during the national anthem in Week 3|publisher=ESPN|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925014751/http://www.espn.com/blog/nflnation/post/_/id/249755/nfl-players-who-protested-during-the-national-anthem-in-week-3|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* Twenty-seven members of the [[Baltimore Ravens]] and [[Jacksonville Jaguars]] knelt during the American National Anthem at their game at [[Wembley Stadium]] in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/sep/24/donald-trump-defied-wembley-jaguars-ravens-nfl-kneel-anthem|title=Donald Trump defied at Wembley as Jaguars and Ravens kneel for anthem|last=Wembley|first=Sean Ingle at|date=September 24, 2017|work=The Guardian|access-date=September 25, 2017|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924205616/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/sep/24/donald-trump-defied-wembley-jaguars-ravens-nfl-kneel-anthem|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Retired Ravens star and honorary Team Captain [[Ray Lewis]] knelt with members of his team.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/ravens/ravens-insider/bs-sp-ravens-anthem-protest-20170924-story.html|title=Some Ravens and Jaguars take knee during national anthem in wake of comments by President Trump|last=Zrebiec|first=Jeff|work=The Baltimore Sun|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083233/http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/ravens/ravens-insider/bs-sp-ravens-anthem-protest-20170924-story.html|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> All of the players stood for the British national anthem \"[[God Save the Queen]]\", with many remaining in locked arms.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Sweeney|first=Don|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/nation-world/world/article175130091.html|title=NFL players in London kneel for the US national anthem but stand for the British one|work=The Miami Herald|date=September 24, 2017|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924183619/http://www.miamiherald.com/news/nation-world/world/article175130091.html|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* Several members of the [[Philadelphia Eagles]] raised their fists during the anthem before their game against the [[New York Giants]]. Before the same game, various Giants players stood with arms locked while others knelt.<ref name=\"NYTimes\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html |title=Tom Brady Joins Anthem Demonstration as N.F.L. Protests Trump Comments |last=Belson |first=Ken |last2=Manchester |first2=Sam |date=September 24, 2017 |website=The New York Times |access-date=September 24, 2017 |last3=Mather |first3=Victor |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924165431/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/24/sports/nfl-trump-anthem-protests.html |archive-date=September 24, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n* The [[Seattle Seahawks]] and the [[Tennessee Titans]] did not take the field during the playing of the anthem, staying in their locker rooms until it concluded. The players of the Seahawks released a statement saying, \"We will not stand for the injustice that has plagued people of color in this country. Out of love for our country and in honor of the sacrifices made on our behalf, we unite to oppose those that would deny our most basic freedoms.\"<ref name=\"ESPN.com\"/> [[Meghan Linsey]], the Nashville singer who performed the anthem, knelt when she completed the song.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tennessean.com/story/sports/nfl/titans/2017/09/24/meghan-linsey-kneels-after-singing-national-anthem-titans-seahawks-game/698362001/|title=Meghan Linsey kneels after singing national anthem at Titans-Seahawks game|work=The Tennessean|access-date=September 25, 2017}}</ref>\n* Before the opening of their game against the [[Houston Texans]], various [[New England Patriots]] players and staff also expressed their concerns, including quarterback [[Tom Brady]] locking arms with [[Phillip Dorsett]], and head coach [[Bill Belichick]] crossing his arms in front of him. Sixteen members of the Patriots knelt during the anthem.<ref name=\":0\" /> Patriots owner [[Robert Kraft]] said he was disappointed at the tone in which Trump's comments were made.<ref name=\"NYTimes\"/><ref name=\"LAT 2019-02-01\">{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/politics/la-na-pol-trump-nfl-20190201-story.html|title=For years, Trump bashed the NFL and players who protested racial injustice. Here's why he stopped|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|first=Noah|last=Bierman|date=February 2, 2019|accessdate=February 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190201163650/https://www.latimes.com/politics/la-na-pol-trump-nfl-20190201-story.html|archive-date=February 1, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* Several members of the [[Miami Dolphins]] wore \"#IMWITHKAP\" T-shirts on the field during the pregame warmup, in support of Kaepernick's actions.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/24/donald-trump-nfl-player-protests-national-anthem-week-3-response/697609001/|title=NFL player protests sweep league after President Donald Trump's hostile remarks|work=USA Today|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925041022/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/09/24/donald-trump-nfl-player-protests-national-anthem-week-3-response/697609001/|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The team locked arms during the anthem, with five members kneeling. The opposing team, the [[New York Jets]], also linked arms during the anthem.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/sports/nfl/miami-dolphins/article175171896.html|title=Why did Stills kneel Sunday? Because he felt Trump tried to 'scare' or 'intimidate' him|work=The Miami Herald|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083418/http://www.miamiherald.com/sports/nfl/miami-dolphins/article175171896.html|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> \n* All [[Pittsburgh Steelers]] players except [[Alejandro Villanueva (American football)|Alejandro Villanueva]], who served as an [[United States Army Rangers|Army Ranger]], refused to leave the locker room during the anthem. On the sideline, the [[Chicago Bears]] players locked their arms while the anthem was performed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wgntv.com/2017/09/24/nfl-sunday-kicks-off-amid-beef-between-players-trump/|title=From Chicago to London, NFL players react to Trump's protest critiques|date=September 24, 2017|publisher=WGN-TV|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924233654/http://wgntv.com/2017/09/24/nfl-sunday-kicks-off-amid-beef-between-players-trump/|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Villanueva has since expressed regret for his actions.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.journalnow.com/news/nation_world/villanueva-on-anthem-flap-it-wasn-t-me-stepping-forward/article_62177918-7571-5d91-9bbf-f2337ea908ef.html|title=Villanueva on anthem flap: 'It wasn't me stepping forward'|last=Press|first=Associated|work=Winston-Salem Journal|access-date=2017-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926235724/http://www.journalnow.com/news/nation_world/villanueva-on-anthem-flap-it-wasn-t-me-stepping-forward/article_62177918-7571-5d91-9bbf-f2337ea908ef.html|archive-date=September 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* The majority of the [[Oakland Raiders]] either sat or knelt during the anthem, with several members of the opposing [[Washington Redskins]] either kneeling or joining arms as well.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2017/09/24/raiders-sit-during-national-anthem-they-couldnt-stay-locker-room|title=Most of the Raiders took a seat during national anthem|last=Rollins|first=Khadrice|work=Sports Illustrated|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925063442/https://www.si.com/nfl/2017/09/24/raiders-sit-during-national-anthem-they-couldnt-stay-locker-room|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* Thirty-two members of the [[Denver Broncos]] knelt during the anthem.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.denverpost.com/2017/09/24/von-miller-broncos-kneel-national-anthem/|title=Von Miller among 32 Broncos players who take a knee for national anthem|date=September 24, 2017|work=The Denver Post|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924214352/http://www.denverpost.com/2017/09/24/von-miller-broncos-kneel-national-anthem/|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> At least ten members of the [[Buffalo Bills]] also knelt during the anthem, while other team members locked arms.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newyorkupstate.com/buffalo-bills/index.ssf/2017/09/buffalo_bills_national_anthem_protests_kneeling_racial_injustive_donald_trump.html|title=Buffalo Bills lock arms during national anthem in response to Donald Trump|publisher=NewYorkUpstate.com|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083529/http://www.newyorkupstate.com/buffalo-bills/index.ssf/2017/09/buffalo_bills_national_anthem_protests_kneeling_racial_injustive_donald_trump.html|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Running back [[LeSean McCoy]] said \"My message to him (Trump) is, be a president, be respectful, man. You know, us Americans, we are together. Stop trying to divide us.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pennlive.com/sports/index.ssf/2017/09/lesean_mccoy_says_donald_trump.html|title=LeSean McCoy says Donald Trump should 'be a president,' 'be respectful'|publisher=PennLive.com|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925083252/http://www.pennlive.com/sports/index.ssf/2017/09/lesean_mccoy_says_donald_trump.html|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> McCoy performed stretches during the national anthem.\n* The [[Dallas Cowboys]] and [[Arizona Cardinals]] players locked arms during the anthem, while everyone on the Cowboys, including owner and general manager [[Jerry Jones]], knelt before the anthem was played.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Archer|first1=Todd|last2=Weinfuss|first2=Josh|title=Cowboys, Cardinals lock arms for national anthem in show of unity|publisher=ESPN|date=September 26, 2017|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20819786/dallas-cowboys-arizona-cardinals-lock-arms-monday-night-football-game|accessdate=September 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926155554/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20819786/dallas-cowboys-arizona-cardinals-lock-arms-monday-night-football-game|archive-date=September 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* The [[New Orleans Saints]] established a plan with their team prior to their game against the [[Miami Dolphins]] on how they will handle the national anthem before the game. [[Drew Brees]] stood and stated the thoughts of his team as a whole by tweeting \"As a way to show respect to all, our #Saints team will kneel in solidarity prior to the national anthem & stand together during the anthem.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nola.com/saints/index.ssf/2017/09/saints_protest_national_anthem.html|title=Drew Brees: Saints plan to kneel before national anthem, stand during it on Sunday|publisher=2017 NOLA media group|accessdate=October 1, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171001222125/http://www.nola.com/saints/index.ssf/2017/09/saints_protest_national_anthem.html|archive-date=October 1, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n* More than ten [[Indianapolis Colts]] and about 20 [[Cleveland Browns]] players knelt on one knee while the remaining players locked arms during the playing of \"[[The Star-Spangled Banner]]\" in [[Indianapolis, Indiana]]. The actions were met by boos from the crowd at [[Lucas Oil Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theindychannel.com/sports/colts/colts-kneel-lock-arms-in-show-of-unity-against-donald-trumps-comments |title=Colts kneel, lock arms in show of unity against Donald Trump's comments |publisher=[[WRTV]] |date=September 24, 2017 |accessdate=October 20, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027205631/http://www.theindychannel.com/sports/colts/colts-kneel-lock-arms-in-show-of-unity-against-donald-trumps-comments |archive-date=October 27, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/nflnation/post/_/id/249755/nfl-players-who-protested-during-the-national-anthem-in-week-3 |title=NFL players who protested during the national anthem in Week 3 |publisher=[[ESPN]] |date=September 25, 2017 |accessdate=October 20, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018233550/http://www.espn.com/blog/nflnation/post/_/id/249755/nfl-players-who-protested-during-the-national-anthem-in-week-3 |archive-date=October 18, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>  Indiana is the home state of Vice President [[Mike Pence]], who weeks later intentionally walked out of a Colts game against the 49ers.<ref>{{cite news|last=Crawford|first=Dakota|title=What is cost for Mike Pence to leave the Colts-49ers game|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/sports/nfl/colts/2017/10/08/vice-president-mike-pences-quick-and-costly-exit-colts-49-ers-game/744668001/|newspaper=[[The Indianapolis Star]]|date=October 8, 2017|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181009073220/https://www.indystar.com/story/sports/nfl/colts/2017/10/08/vice-president-mike-pences-quick-and-costly-exit-colts-49-ers-game/744668001/|archive-date=October 9, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 16, 2017 Colin Kaepernick filed a grievance for collusion against NFL owners. Instead of using the NFLPA, Kaepernick hired Mark Geragos to be his attorney.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21035352/colin-kaepernick-files-grievance-nfl-owners-collusion|title=Kaepernick files grievance claiming collusion|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929000504/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21035352/colin-kaepernick-files-grievance-nfl-owners-collusion|archive-date=September 29, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> As of August 31, 2018, an arbitrator ruled that there is sufficient evidence that the case can continue.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/08/31/643582437/colin-kaepernicks-grievance-against-nfl-moves-forward|title=Colin Kaepernick's Grievance Against NFL Moves Forward|work=NPR.org|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929000443/https://www.npr.org/2018/08/31/643582437/colin-kaepernicks-grievance-against-nfl-moves-forward|archive-date=September 29, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn Week 8 at Seattle, the majority of the Texans players knelt during the anthem after Houston owner [[Bob McNair]] had commented about having the \"inmates running the prison\" during a league owner meeting regarding the ongoing protest. McNair had apologized, stating that he was not referring to the players, but rather to the \"relationship between the league office and team owners\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Barshop|first=Sarah|title=Texans' Duane Brown on kneeling for anthem: Team felt sense of unity playing for each other|date=October 29, 2017|website=ESPN.com|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21215907/majority-houston-texans-players-kneeled-linked-arms-national-anthem|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030025608/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21215907/majority-houston-texans-players-kneeled-linked-arms-national-anthem|archivedate=October 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first1=Seth|last1=Wickersham|first2=Don|last2=Van Natta Jr.|title=Gaffes, TV ratings concerns dominated as NFL, players forged anthem peace|date=October 27, 2017|website=ESPN.com|url=http://www.espn.com/espn/otl/story/_/id/21170410/gaffes-tv-ratings-concerns-dominated-nfl-players-forged-anthem-peace-league-meetings|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171029050500/http://www.espn.com/espn/otl/story/_/id/21170410/gaffes-tv-ratings-concerns-dominated-nfl-players-forged-anthem-peace-league-meetings|archivedate=October 29, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> It was the first time a Texans player had knelt during the anthem.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wilson|first=Aaron|title=Texans' Duane Brown says Bob McNair meeting 'didn't go too well'|date=October 29, 2017|newspaper=Houston Chronicle|url=http://www.chron.com/sports/texans/article/Majority-of-Texans-kneel-for-national-anthem-12315599.php|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030132035/http://www.chron.com/sports/texans/article/Majority-of-Texans-kneel-for-national-anthem-12315599.php|archivedate=October 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===2018 preseason===\nOn May 23, 2018, NFL Commissioner [[Roger Goodell]] and all NFL team owners, except for two that abstained from voting in a show of hand voting process, approved a new policy that would require all players to stand during the national anthem or be given the option to stay in the locker room during the national anthem. The vote took place without consulting the NFLPA.<ref>{{cite news|last=Healy|first=John|title=NFL admits there was no official vote on national anthem policy, instead informal show of hands|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/football/nfl-admits-no-official-vote-national-anthem-policy-article-1.4009450|newspaper=[[New York Daily News]]|date=May 25, 2018|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526043054/http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/football/nfl-admits-no-official-vote-national-anthem-policy-article-1.4009450|archive-date=May 26, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The policy also stated that any players from all NFL teams who protested the anthem while on the field would become subject to discipline from the league. In addition, the teams as a whole would be subject to punishment and other forms of discipline from the NFL as a result.<ref>{{cite news|last=Knoblauch|first=Austin|title=NFL expected to enact national anthem policy for '18|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000933952/article/nfl-expected-to-enact-national-anthem-policy-for-18|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=NFL.com|date=May 23, 2018|accessdate=May 23, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524003621/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000933952/article/nfl-expected-to-enact-national-anthem-policy-for-18|archive-date=May 24, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Roger Goodell's statement on national anthem policy|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000933962/article/roger-goodells-statement-on-national-anthem-policy|publisher=NFL Enterprises, LLC|website=NFL.com|date=May 23, 2018|accessdate=May 23, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180523184943/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000933962/article/roger-goodells-statement-on-national-anthem-policy|archive-date=May 23, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn disagreement with the policy, several players on the Super Bowl champions [[Philadelphia Eagles]] indicated that they would decline an invitation from Trump to visit the [[White House]] on June 5, leading the President to rescind the offer the day before the event.<ref>{{cite news|title=Donald Trump calls off Eagles' White House visit over national anthem dispute|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/donald-trump-calls-off-eagles-white-house-visit-players-decline-invitation-232323202.html|publisher=Oath Inc. (Verizon)|website=Yahoo Sports|date=June 4, 2018|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180604235948/https://sports.yahoo.com/donald-trump-calls-off-eagles-white-house-visit-players-decline-invitation-232323202.html|archive-date=June 4, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The Eagles were the second sports franchise that Trump had uninvited, joining the 2017 [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA) champion [[Golden State Warriors]], whose visit was cancelled after several players publicly declined to attend.<ref>{{cite news|title='Fragile egomaniac': Philly Mayor responds to Trump's White House snub|date=June 5, 2018|work=Fox Sports|url=https://www.foxsports.com.au/nfl/donald-trump-cancels-the-philadelphia-eagles-visit-to-the-white-house/news-story/e6a2b3c5b5ee2a9f7f0a8b42633e0706|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718112114/https://www.foxsports.com.au/nfl/donald-trump-cancels-the-philadelphia-eagles-visit-to-the-white-house/news-story/e6a2b3c5b5ee2a9f7f0a8b42633e0706|archivedate=July 18, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn July 19, the NFL and the players association issued a joint statement that \"no rules relating to the anthem will be issued for the next several weeks.\" This came after the [[Associated Press]] had reported earlier in the day that Miami team rules stated that improper anthem conduct could result in a player suspension of up to four games, more than some players receive for violating the [[NFL domestic violence policy|league's domestic violence policy]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Orr|first=Connor|title=The Five Hours That Forced the NFL to Reconsider Its Anthem Policy|date=July 20, 2018|website=SI.com|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/07/19/miami-dolphins-national-anthem-policy-rule-nfl-training-camp|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721123241/https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/07/19/miami-dolphins-national-anthem-policy-rule-nfl-training-camp|archivedate=July 21, 2018}}</ref> The following day, Trump tweeted that players should be suspended for one game the first time kneeling, and for the entire season without pay after a second offense.<ref>{{cite news|last=West|first=Jenna|title=Donald Trump Suggests Players Kneeling for Anthem Should Be Suspended for Entire Season|date=July 20, 2018|website=SI.com|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/07/20/donald-trump-national-anthem-policy-players-kneel-no-pay-suspended|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721105831/https://www.si.com/nfl/2018/07/20/donald-trump-national-anthem-policy-players-kneel-no-pay-suspended|archivedate=July 21, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===2019 Season===\nAs of 2019, only three players in the NFL continue to protest.\n\n[[Eric Reid]] of the [[Carolina Panthers]] continues to kneel and says he will continue to do so in the future. Reid is the first player on the Carolina Panthers to kneel during the playing of the national anthem. <ref>https://www.si.com/nfl/2019/07/29/carolina-panthers-eric-reid-anthem-kneeling</ref>\n\n[[Kenny Stills]] who was traded to the [[Houston Texans]] continues to kneel during the playing of the anthem.<ref>https://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2019/09/09/kenny-stills-took-a-knee-for-the-national-anthem/</ref> Stills says that he will continue to do so even if his job is threatened as a result.<ref>https://sports.yahoo.com/kenny-stills-continue-kneel-during-153502355.html</ref>\n\n[[Albert Wilson (American football)|Albert Wilson]] of the [[Miami Dolphins]] continues to kneel during the playing of the national anthem.<ref>https://thegrio.com/2019/09/11/miami-dolphins-albert-wilson-still-kneels-on-the-field/</ref>\n\n==Other athletes join==\n\n===Soccer===\n[[File:Megan_Rapinoe_USA_vs_Can_Sep17.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Megan Rapinoe]] in 2011]]\n[[Seattle Reign FC]] and [[United States women's national soccer team|U.S. women's national soccer team]] player [[Megan Rapinoe]] knelt during the national anthem in a game on September 5, 2016, explaining that her decision was a \"nod to Kaepernick and everything that he's standing for right now\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/09/05/sport/megan-rapinoe-colin-kaepernick-anthem-kneel/index.html|title=Megan Rapinoe takes knee in solidarity with Kaepernick|last=McKirdy|first=Euan|date=September 5, 2016|publisher=CNN|access-date=September 7, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160906214457/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/09/05/sport/megan-rapinoe-colin-kaepernick-anthem-kneel/index.html|archive-date=September 6, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In a subsequent match at the [[Washington Spirit]], Spirit owner Bill Lynch \u2013 anticipating Rapinoe's protest \u2013 moved the national anthem's performance without warning or notice to occur before the players' appearances on the pitch. [[Jeff Plush]], the league's commissioner, was present at the game and told reporters that he was unaware of Lynch's plans and disagreed with the act of moving the anthem's performance.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/09/07/megan-rapinoe-doesnt-get-chance-to-kneel-for-national-anthem-it-was-played-with-teams-in-locker-room/?tid=a_inl|title=Megan Rapinoe doesn't get chance to kneel for national anthem. It was played with teams in locker room.|date=September 7, 2016|access-date=November 1, 2016|work=The Washington Post|author=Steven Goff|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104003223/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/09/07/megan-rapinoe-doesnt-get-chance-to-kneel-for-national-anthem-it-was-played-with-teams-in-locker-room/?tid=a_inl|archive-date=November 4, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The Spirit's players issued a joint statement also disagreeing with Lynch's decision to move the anthem without first consulting the team's players or coaches.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/09/09/washington-spirit-players-unhappy-with-owners-anthem-move/|title=Washington Spirit players unhappy with owner's anthem move|author=Steven Goff|work=The Washington Post|date=September 9, 2016|access-date=November 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103235815/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/soccer-insider/wp/2016/09/09/washington-spirit-players-unhappy-with-owners-anthem-move/|archive-date=November 3, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAs a member of the U.S. women's national soccer team, Rapinoe also knelt before an international [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Thailand women's national football team|Thailand]] on September 16, despite public statements of disagreement with her protest methods issued before the match by the [[U.S. Soccer Federation]] and her coach [[Jill Ellis]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2016/09/15/megan-rapinoe-uswnt-thailand-national-anthem-kneels|title=USWNT's Megan Rapinoe kneels for national anthem before Thailand match|work=[[Sports Illustrated]]|date=September 19, 2016|access-date=November 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026221809/http://www.si.com/planet-futbol/2016/09/15/megan-rapinoe-uswnt-thailand-national-anthem-kneels|archive-date=October 26, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> U.S. Soccer proceeded to pass a policy that now requires all of its players to stand \"respectfully\" during the national anthem, making it the first American sports league or governing body to do so.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sbnation.com/soccer/2017/3/6/14825652/united-states-soccer-national-anthem-policy-megan-rapinoe-protest-ban|title=U.S. Soccer banned Megan Rapinoe's national anthem protest without caring to understand it|work=SBNation.com|access-date=2017-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011073441/https://www.sbnation.com/soccer/2017/3/6/14825652/united-states-soccer-national-anthem-policy-megan-rapinoe-protest-ban|archive-date=October 11, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[Major League Soccer]] (MLS) have released a statement in September 2017 regarding any potential protests \"The march of players, officials and children into our stadiums and singing of the anthem has been a pre-match tradition since our first game in 1996. The National Anthem provides our clubs and fans an important and time-honored opportunity to salute our country and stand up for its principles -- whether in the United States or in Canada.\"<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20848575|title=How national anthem rules differ across sports leagues|date=May 24, 2018|website=ESPN.com|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128082914/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20848575|archive-date=January 28, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> MLS to date, has yet to encounter national anthem protests.\n\nThe protest had supporters outside the U.S. as well; in an October 2017 match against [[Schalke 04]], players and staff of German soccer club [[Hertha Berlin]] took the knee in solidarity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2017/10/14/hertha-berlin-kneel-german-national-anthem-protest|title=Hertha Berlin players take knee during German anthem|last=Rapaport|first=Daniel|date=October 14, 2017|work=Sports Illustrated|access-date=May 27, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180527202642/https://www.si.com/soccer/2017/10/14/hertha-berlin-kneel-german-national-anthem-protest|archive-date=May 27, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Hertha Berlin has several American players on their roster.\n\n===College===\nOn September 7, 2016, three volleyball players from [[West Virginia University Institute of Technology|West Virginia Tech]] knelt during the national anthem.<ref name=\"kalea\">{{cite web|last1=Gunderson|first1=Kalea|title=West Virginia Tech volleyball players kneel during national anthem|url=http://wchstv.com/news/local/west-virginia-tech-volleyball-players-kneel-during-national-anthem|date=September 7, 2016|publisher=ABC|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921150727/http://wchstv.com/news/local/west-virginia-tech-volleyball-players-kneel-during-national-anthem|archive-date=September 21, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"gibbs\"/>\n\nOn October 1, at [[East Carolina University]], about 19 members of the band knelt, while about another two held the American flag during the national anthem at the beginning of the football game against the [[University of Central Florida]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.witn.com/content/news/395523401.html |title=ECU chancellor, Gov. McCrory speak out about band members kneeling |publisher=WITN-TV |accessdate=November 8, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031084445/http://www.witn.com/content/news/395523401.html |archive-date=October 31, 2016 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> There have been almost no such incidents involving college football players, for the simple reason that college players and coaches are typically in the locker room when the anthem is played. There has been at least one exception to the rule, however. During a September 2016 away game at [[Northwestern Wildcats football|Northwestern]], where players are traditionally on the field during the anthem, three [[Nebraska Cornhuskers football|Nebraska]] players knelt on the sideline.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbnation.com/college-football/2017/9/26/16354940/protests-college-football-nfl-national-anthem|title=Why protests aren't as common in college football|last=Kirshner|first=Alex|date=September 28, 2017|publisher=SB Nation|access-date=October 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008231719/https://www.sbnation.com/college-football/2017/9/26/16354940/protests-college-football-nfl-national-anthem|archive-date=October 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://journalstar.com/sports/huskers/football/prior-to-game-rose-ivey-told-team-of-his-decision/article_781e987e-82b0-11e6-93cc-53559523f8fe.html|title=Prior to game, Rose-Ivey told team of his decision to kneel for anthem|last=Christopherson|first=Brian|work=Lincoln Journal Star|access-date=October 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008231552/http://journalstar.com/sports/huskers/football/prior-to-game-rose-ivey-told-team-of-his-decision/article_781e987e-82b0-11e6-93cc-53559523f8fe.html|archive-date=October 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The NCAA football rulebook does not address the issue of pregame ceremonies (patriotic or otherwise) at all, except to say that team captains must be present for a [[coin toss]] three minutes before the first-half kickoff.\n\n[[College of the Ozarks]] president Jerry Davis announced in September 2017 that his college's teams would [[Forfeit (sport)|refuse to play]] any team whose players knelt during the anthem.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news-leader.com/story/news/education/2017/09/29/no-pledge-no-play-policy-college-ozarks-student-athletes/717937001/|title=If you kneel, the game is over, C of O tells opposing teams|last=Riley|first=Claudette|date=September 29, 2017|work=Springfield News-Leader|access-date=January 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180106010320/http://www.news-leader.com/story/news/education/2017/09/29/no-pledge-no-play-policy-college-ozarks-student-athletes/717937001/|archive-date=January 6, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In response, the [[National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics|NAIA]] chose to move its [[NAIA Men's Basketball Championships#Division II|Division II men's basketball champion game]] away from College of the Ozarks' [[Keeter Gymnasium]] (where the championship game had been held since 2000) to [[Sanford Pentagon]] in [[Sioux Falls, South Dakota|Sioux Falls]], [[South Dakota]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news-leader.com/story/sports/college/2017/10/27/anthem-protest-policy-moves-naia-basketball-tournament-away-college-ozarks/807857001/|title=Anthem protest policy moves NAIA basketball tournament away from College of the Ozarks|date=October 27, 2017|work=Springfield News-Leader}}</ref>\n\nOn February 23, 2019, eight players of the [[Ole Miss Rebels men's basketball|Ole Miss men's basketball]] team took a knee during the national anthem at their home-game against [[University of Georgia|Georgia]]. The players took a knee to protest the pro-confederate rally that was happening on campus at the time.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/02/23/sports/ole-miss-anthem-protest-kneel.html|title=Ole Miss Players Kneel in Response to Pro-Confederate Rally|last=Press|first=The Associated|date=2019-02-23|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-03-07|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The players previously stood during the national anthem, with this being the first time they took the knee. The athletes were upset by a video posted online by the rally organizers a few days prior.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Paul|first=Maman|date=2019|title=Emotional Intelligence: A Analytical Study of Basketball Players|journal=International Journal of Current Research and Review|volume=11|issue=3|pages=01\u201305|doi=10.31782/ijcrr.2019.11301|issn=2231-2196}}</ref> The protest reached national attention and received negative backlash. However, the athletes received public support from University officials.<ref>{{Cite news|title=27733, 1864-03-07, KERR (Miss) \u2020|doi = 10.1163/2210-7886_asc-27733}}</ref>\n\nOn December 24, 2016 Michigan players Jordan Lewis and Khalid Hill raised their right arms in the air in support of the Anthem Protests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/17626402/college-football-players-protest-anthem|title=UM, MSU players raise fists during anthem|date=2016-09-24|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref>\n\n===High school===\nOn September 2, 2016, a football player at [[Brunswick High School (Ohio)|Brunswick High School]] in [[Ohio]] knelt during the national anthem after he heard his teammates saying \"[[nigger]]\".<ref name=\"gibbs\">{{cite web|last1=Gibbs|first1=Lindsay|title=Tracking the Kaepernick Effect: The anthem protests are spreading|url=https://thinkprogress.org/national-anthem-sports-protest-tracker-kaepernick-284ff1d1ab3e#.c5u4c1quw|publisher=think progress|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103035700/https://thinkprogress.org/national-anthem-sports-protest-tracker-kaepernick-284ff1d1ab3e#.c5u4c1quw|archive-date=January 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> After his protest, the player received racial threats.<ref name=\"fox\">{{cite web|last1=Freeman|first1=Kevin|title=First home game for Brunswick High School since player said he received racial threats|url=http://fox8.com/2016/09/16/first-home-game-for-brunswick-high-school-since-player-said-he-received-racial-threats/|publisher=Fox|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919062749/http://fox8.com/2016/09/16/first-home-game-for-brunswick-high-school-since-player-said-he-received-racial-threats/|archive-date=September 19, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On September 9, high school players across the country knelt during the national anthem. On September 23, four players from [[Withrow High School]], three black and one white, in [[Cincinnati]] knelt during the national anthem before their football game.<ref name=\"gibbs\"/>\n\nIn September 2017, Principal Waylon Bates of [[Parkway High School (Louisiana)|Parkway High School]] in [[Louisiana]] referred to the national anthem protests as a \"disruption\" and threatened to kick any player out of the football team if he knelt during the national anthem.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/28/louisiana-high-school-will-kick-students-off-team-if-they-dont-stand-for-national-anthem/|title=Louisiana high school will kick students off team if they don't stand for national anthem|first=Jacob|last=Bogage|date=September 28, 2017|accessdate=October 4, 2017|via=www.washingtonpost.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171003180303/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/28/louisiana-high-school-will-kick-students-off-team-if-they-dont-stand-for-national-anthem/|archive-date=October 3, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Two black students on the Victory & Praise Christian Academy football team protested during the anthem. Immediately after the anthem concluded, their coach removed them from the team, having them take off their uniforms on the [[sidelines]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfgate.com/sports/highschool/article/High-school-football-kicked-off-team-anthem-kneel-12242713.php|title=Local high school football players kicked off team after protest during anthem|website=sfgate.com|accessdate=October 4, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171004112646/http://www.sfgate.com/sports/highschool/article/High-school-football-kicked-off-team-anthem-kneel-12242713.php|archive-date=October 4, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 2018, the 32 players of the Christian Capital Academy football team as well as the coaching staff decided to take a knee during the national anthem. When asked about their reasons, the team collectively responded that they took a knee as a way to protest for the excessive use of police brutality against minorities, especially against African Americans.<ref>{{Cite news|title=High School Football team|doi=10.31096/wua033-pls90b070}}</ref> The two players did not receive any punishment for their protest.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=January 2017|title=Student-athlete wasn't defamed by being kicked off team|journal=College Athletics and the Law|volume=13|issue=10|pages=10\u201311|doi=10.1002/catl.30300|issn=1552-8774}}</ref>\n\nOn December 2017, Ninth Circuit Court for the Southern District of California ruled in favor of high school players, and stated that no high school football player can be forced to stand during the national anthem or cannot be forced out of the team by refusing to do so.<ref name=\"Stratmoen 204\u2013213\">{{Cite journal|last=Stratmoen|first=Evelyn|last2=Lawless|first2=Tiffany J.|last3=Saucier|first3=Donald A.|date=January 2019|title=Taking a knee: Perceptions of NFL player protests during the National Anthem|journal=Personality and Individual Differences|volume=137|pages=204\u2013213|doi=10.1016/j.paid.2018.09.009|issn=0191-8869}}</ref> The basis for such ruling is that \u201closs of First Amendment freedoms unquestionably constitutes irreparable harm and that the mandate issued by the district superintendent is a violation of the athlete\u2019s First Amendment rights.\u201d<ref name=\"Stratmoen 204\u2013213\"/>\n\n===Baseball===\nOn September 23, 2017, [[Bruce Maxwell]] of the [[Oakland Athletics]] knelt during the national anthem, becoming the first MLB player to join the protest. His team backed him up by saying, \"The Oakland A's pride ourselves on being inclusive. We respect and support all of our players' constitutional rights and freedom of expression.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfgate.com/athletics/article/A-s-Bruce-Maxwell-first-MLB-player-to-kneel-for-12223798.php|title=A's Bruce Maxwell first MLB player to kneel for anthem|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924023030/http://www.sfgate.com/athletics/article/A-s-Bruce-Maxwell-first-MLB-player-to-kneel-for-12223798.php|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/trump-baseball-first-take-national-anthem_us_59c7051ae4b01cc57ff2a61e|title=MLB's First Player Just Took A Knee During The National Anthem|last=Madani|first=Doha|date=September 24, 2017|work=HuffPost|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926184529/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/trump-baseball-first-take-national-anthem_us_59c7051ae4b01cc57ff2a61e|archive-date=September 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Maxwell received a standing ovation from A's fans before his first at-bat following his protest.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sbnation.com/mlb/2017/9/25/16364924/bruce-maxwell-standing-ovation-protest-fans-oakland|title=In his first at-bat after taking a knee, Bruce Maxwell got a standing ovation from fans|work=SBNation.com|access-date=September 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927052806/https://www.sbnation.com/mlb/2017/9/25/16364924/bruce-maxwell-standing-ovation-protest-fans-oakland|archive-date=September 27, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe MLB has no policy regarding the national anthem other than it has to be played before games.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\n===Basketball===\nOn September 24, 2017, prior to Game 1 of the [[2017 WNBA Finals]], players from the [[Los Angeles Sparks]] chose to stay in the locker room during the national anthem, while members of the [[Minnesota Lynx]] locked arms on the court.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadspin.com/los-angeles-sparks-leave-court-before-national-anthem-i-1818709276|title=Los Angeles Sparks Leave Court Before National Anthem in Game 1 of WNBA Finals|last=Theisen|first=Lauren|date=September 24, 2017|work=Deadspin|access-date=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925012416/http://deadspin.com/los-angeles-sparks-leave-court-before-national-anthem-i-1818709276|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe [[NBA]] has a policy that requires players to stand up during the national anthem in their CBA, however many prominent players have expressed support for the NFL protests on social media or in interviews.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/celtics/2018/06/04/why-don-players-have-problem-with-nba-national-anthem-policy/RDqhgKaScJL2DPLLSuWiVM/story.html|title=Why don't players have a problem with the NBA's national anthem policy?|newspaper=[[The Boston Globe]]|first=Gary|last=Washburn|accessdate=February 2, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828071305/https://www.bostonglobe.com/sports/celtics/2018/06/04/why-don-players-have-problem-with-nba-national-anthem-policy/RDqhgKaScJL2DPLLSuWiVM/story.html|archive-date=August 28, 2018|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Ice hockey===\nOn October 7, 2017, [[J. T. Brown (ice hockey)|J. T. Brown]] of the [[Tampa Bay Lightning]] raised his fist while standing on the bench during the national anthem. He had also done the same in a preseason game, in an attempt to \"bring awareness to police brutality against minorities and racial inequality\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tampabay.com/sports/hockey/lightning/lightnings-jt-brown-raises-fist-in-protest-during-anthem-before-panthers/2340305|title=Lightning's J.T. Brown raises fist in protest during anthem before Panthers game|last=Smith|first=Joe|date=October 7, 2017|work=tampabay.com|publisher=Tampa Bay Times|accessdate=October 7, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008080405/http://www.tampabay.com/sports/hockey/lightning/lightnings-jt-brown-raises-fist-in-protest-during-anthem-before-panthers/2340305|archive-date=October 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He stated that he had \"received death threats\" after the protest.<ref name=thescore>{{cite web|url=https://www.thescore.com/nhl/news/1393535-lightning-s-brown-i-have-received-death-threats-after-protest|title=Lightning's Brown: 'I have received death threats' after protest|last=Livingstone|first=Flip|date=October 8, 2017|work=[[TheScore Inc.|TheScore.com]]|publisher=Score Media Ventures Inc.|accessdate=October 8, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Pan American Games===\nAt the [[2019 Pan American Games]] in [[Lima]], Peru, team fencing gold medalist [[Race Imboden]] kneeled and women's hammer throw champion [[Gwen Berry]] raised a fist on the awards stand during the American national anthem.<ref>{{cite news|last=Taylor|first=Derrick Bryson|title=U.S. Fencer, Race Imboden, Takes a Knee at Pan-American Games|date=August 11, 2019|newspaper=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/11/sports/race-imboden-fencer-kneels.html|accessdate=August 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>https://www.chicagotribune.com/sports/breaking/ct-race-imboden-gwen-berry-athlete-protest-20190811-gceardedn5fyjclxim5b7qexta-story.html</ref>\n{{quote|\"Racism, gun control, mistreatment of immigrants, and a president who spreads hate are at the top of a long list.  I chose to sacrifice my moment today at the top of the podium to call attention to issues that I believe need to be addressed.  I encourage others to please use your platforms for empowerment and change.\"|Race Imboden}}\n{{quote|\"It's too important to not say something. Something has to be said. If nothing is said, nothing will be done, and nothing will be fixed, and nothing will be changed.\"|Gwen Berry}}\n\n==Role of Russian bots in amplifying controversy==\nA [[Clemson University]] research paper found that Russian bots played a role in amplifying the controversy over kneeling during the national anthem. Some 12,000 tweets linked to 491 accounts linked to Russia's [[Internet Research Agency]] were sent from the end of 2014 to mid-2018; those tweets peaked on September 22, 2017, after President Donald Trump's speech in Huntsville, Alabama.<ref>Gardner, Steve (October 22, 2018). [https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2018/10/22/russian-bots-twitter-trolls-nfl-national-anthem-controversy/1732873002/ \"Report: Russian Twitter trolls helped fan flames of NFL's national anthem controversy\"]. ''USAToday NFL''. Retrieved November 17, 2019.</ref><ref>Andrew Beaton, [https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-russian-trolls-inflamed-nfls-anthem-controversy-1540233979 How Russian Trolls Inflamed the NFL's Anthem Controversy], ''Wall Street Journal'' (October 22, 2018).</ref>\n\nU.S. Senator [[James Lankford]] of [[Oklahoma]] said [[Trolls from Olgino|Russian internet trolls]], seeking to polarize Americans, helped fuel online discord.<ref>{{cite web|author=Devlin Barrett|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/lawmaker-russian-trolls-trying-to-sow-discord-in-nfl-kneeling-debate/2017/09/27/5f46dce0-a3b0-11e7-ade1-76d061d56efa_story.html|title=Lawmaker: Russian trolls trying to sow discord in NFL kneeling debate|publisher=washingtonpost.com|date=September 27, 2017|accessdate=December 1, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171128103832/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/lawmaker-russian-trolls-trying-to-sow-discord-in-nfl-kneeling-debate/2017/09/27/5f46dce0-a3b0-11e7-ade1-76d061d56efa_story.html|archive-date=November 28, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/russian-trolls-using-nfl-protests-sow-discord-online-republican-senator-n805296|title=Russian trolls using NFL protests to sow discord online, GOP senator says|access-date=December 10, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171205035419/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/russian-trolls-using-nfl-protests-sow-discord-online-republican-senator-n805296|archive-date=December 5, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/russian-internet-trolls-calling-takeaknee-boycottnf-sow-discord/story?id=50132807|title=Russian internet trolls pushed national anthem controversy, #TakeAKnee: Senator|date=September 27, 2017|publisher=ABC News|access-date=May 25, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180526041155/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/russian-internet-trolls-calling-takeaknee-boycottnf-sow-discord/story?id=50132807|archive-date=May 26, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> During a Senate hearing, Lankford said: \"We watched, even this weekend, the Russians and their troll farms, their internet folks, start hashtagging out #TakeAKnee and also hashtagging out #BoycottNFL. They were taking both sides of the argument this weekend ... to try to raise the noise level of America and make a big issue seem like an even bigger issue as they are trying to push divisiveness in this country.\"<ref>Phillip Ewing, [https://www.npr.org/2017/09/28/554024047/as-scrutiny-of-social-networks-grows-influence-attacks-continue-in-real-time As Scrutiny Of Social Networks Grows, Influence Attacks Continue In Real Time], NPR (September 28, 2017).</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\n\n===Political figures===\n[[File:Mike Pence NFL Protests 2017.jpg|thumb|Vice President Pence stands for anthem prior to leaving after players knelt]]\nIn September 2016, President [[Barack Obama]] stated that Kaepernick was \"exercising his constitutional right\" to protest. He went on: \"I don't doubt his sincerity. I think he cares about some real, legitimate issues that have to be talked about. If nothing else, he's generated more conversation about issues that have to be talked about.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hjelmgaard|first1=Kim|title=24095 924 494 Obama defends Kaepernick's national anthem protest|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2016/09/05/obama-defends-kaepernicks-national-anthem-protest/89879478/|work=USA Today|accessdate=September 20, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923102513/http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2016/09/05/obama-defends-kaepernicks-national-anthem-protest/89879478/|archive-date=September 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[U.S. Supreme Court|Supreme Court]] Justice [[Ruth Bader Ginsburg]] criticized the protest as \"dumb and disrespectful\", stating that athletes have the right to protest \"if they want to be stupid\". The Supreme Court later issued a statement from Ginsburg stating that her comments were \"inappropriately dismissive and harsh. I should have declined to respond.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Ruth Bader Ginsburg apologizes for criticizing anthem protests|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/17795159/ruth-bader-ginsburg-apologizes-criticizing-colin-kaepernick-anthem-protest|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=October 14, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015193145/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/17795159/ruth-bader-ginsburg-apologizes-criticizing-colin-kaepernick-anthem-protest|archive-date=October 15, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn September 25, 2017, [[U.S. Representative]] [[Sheila Jackson Lee]] knelt on the floor of the House of Representatives.<ref>{{cite news |last=Chason |first=Rachel |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/09/26/that-is-racism-black-lawmaker-condemns-trump-kneels-in-congress-to-honor-nfl-players/ |title='That is racism': Black lawmaker condemns Trump, kneels in Congress to honor NFL players |newspaper=The Washington Post |accessdate=September 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927001132/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/09/26/that-is-racism-black-lawmaker-condemns-trump-kneels-in-congress-to-honor-nfl-players/ |archive-date=September 27, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Fellow congressman [[Mark Pocan]] knelt on the floor of the House the next day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thehill.com/blogs/floor-action/house/352448-another-democrat-takes-a-knee-on-house-floor-to-support-nfl-protests |title=Another Democrat takes a knee on House floor to support NFL protests |publisher=TheHill |accessdate=September 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928014606/http://thehill.com/blogs/floor-action/house/352448-another-democrat-takes-a-knee-on-house-floor-to-support-nfl-protests |archive-date=September 28, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn September 26, 2017, Louisiana Lt. Gov. [[Billy Nungesser]] told ''[[The Times-Picayune]]'' that he would not be attending the [[New Orleans Saints]] game against the [[Miami Dolphins]], which was going to be taking place in London. Although he was going to be in London during the time of the game, he told the newspaper that he would not attend because he was \"disappointed in the NFL.\" He added that \"it is disgraceful that anybody would use that as a time to protest.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Seraaj |first1=Intisar |last2=Zdanowicz |first2=Christina |title=From Jersey burnings to players being uninvited, backlash to the #TakeAKnee protest grows |url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/25/us/anthem-protests-burning-nfl-jerseys-trnd/index.html |website=CNN |accessdate=28 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928201044/https://www.cnn.com/2017/09/25/us/anthem-protests-burning-nfl-jerseys-trnd/index.html |archive-date=September 28, 2018 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn October 8, 2017, [[United States Vice President|Vice President]] [[Mike Pence]] left a game between the NFL's [[Indianapolis Colts]] and the San Francisco 49ers, members of which had knelt during the anthem, \"because President Trump and I will not dignify any event that disrespects our soldiers, our Flag, or our National Anthem.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/10/08/556531518/vp-pence-takes-a-stand-and-walks-away-after-nfl-players-kneel|title=Trump Defends Pence's NFL Protest Amid Claims It Was A Publicity Stunt|last=Romo|first=Vanessa|publisher=NPR|date=October 8, 2017|accessdate=October 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171008230746/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/10/08/556531518/vp-pence-takes-a-stand-and-walks-away-after-nfl-players-kneel|archive-date=October 8, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Corporations===\nMajor sports sponsors [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]], [[Under Armour]], and [[Ford]] all issued statements in support of athletes' freedom of expression after Trump's comments regarding the NFL.  Nike's statement read, \"Nike supports athletes and their right to freedom of expression on issues that are of great importance to our society.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nike-becomes-first-nfl-sponsor-take-side-trump-vs-nfl-193639102.html|title=Nike, an NFL sponsor, takes clear side in Trump vs NFL|access-date=2017-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170929000415/https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nike-becomes-first-nfl-sponsor-take-side-trump-vs-nfl-193639102.html|archive-date=September 29, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Nike's ad featuring Kaepernick read \"Believe in something. Even if it means sacrificing everything.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/09/07/sport/colin-kaepernick-protest-taking-the-knee-nate-boyer-spt-intl/index.html|title=Colin Kaepernick: A cultural star fast turning into a global icon|first=Aimee |last=Lewis|website=CNN|access-date=2019-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190117040007/https://edition.cnn.com/2018/09/07/sport/colin-kaepernick-protest-taking-the-knee-nate-boyer-spt-intl/index.html|archive-date=January 17, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In September 2016, after [[Brandon Marshall (linebacker)|Brandon Marshall]] knelt during the national anthem, [[Century Link]] and [[Air Academy Federal Credit Union]] dropped him as a paid sponsor.<ref name=\"crab\">{{cite web|last1=Crabtree|first1=Curtis|title=Brandon Marshall picks up new endorsement after losing two following anthem kneel|url=http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2016/09/15/brandon-marshall-picks-up-new-endorsement-after-losing-two-following-anthem-kneel/|publisher=NBC Sports|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919144007/http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2016/09/15/brandon-marshall-picks-up-new-endorsement-after-losing-two-following-anthem-kneel/|archive-date=September 19, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Radio station [[WFAY]] dropped a broadcast of an [[East Carolina University]] football game on the station after the marching band took part in the protest, calling it an insult to the U.S. Armed Forces.<ref>Martin, Nick (October 6, 2016). [http://deadspin.com/local-espn-radio-station-to-drop-ecu-game-after-band-pr-1787404764 Local ESPN Radio Station To Drop ECU Game After Band Protest] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161007121144/http://deadspin.com/local-espn-radio-station-to-drop-ecu-game-after-band-pr-1787404764 |date=October 7, 2016 }}. ''Deadspin''. Retrieved October 6, 2016.</ref> [[John Schnatter]] of sponsor [[Papa John's Pizza]] blamed the protests for a drop in sales and a 24% fall in stock during 2017, saying that the \"controversy is polarizing the customer, polarizing the country\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/11/01/media/nfl-papa-johns-protests/index.html|title=Papa John's says NFL protests are hurting sales|last=Meyersohn|first=Nathaniel|date=November 1, 2017|access-date=November 2, 2017|work=CNN Money|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171101230132/http://money.cnn.com/2017/11/01/media/nfl-papa-johns-protests/index.html|archive-date=November 1, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Later that day, the company announced that the NFL shield or \"official sponsor\" designation on Papa John's commercials and advertising would be removed.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21250448/nfl-sponsor-papa-john-not-happy-anthem-protests|title=Papa John's says anthem protests are hurting deal with NFL|first=Darren|last=Rovell|work=ESPN.com|date=November 1, 2017|accessdate=November 2, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171102011930/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21250448/nfl-sponsor-papa-john-not-happy-anthem-protests|archive-date=November 2, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In December 2017 [[Sanderson Farms]] CEO questioned whether the NFL protests were to blame for falling [[Buffalo wing|chicken wing]] prices.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-12-14/nfl-player-protests-hurting-chicken-wing-sales-producer-says|title=Chicken Wing Company Says NFL Player Protests Are Hurting Sales|first=Megan|last=Durisin|work=Bloomberg.com|date=December 15, 2017|accessdate=January 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180111132819/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-12-14/nfl-player-protests-hurting-chicken-wing-sales-producer-says|archive-date=January 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAfter his first kneel in 2016, Nike was well on its way to severing its four year long partnership with Kaepernick.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/26/sports/nike-colin-kaepernick.html|title=Nike Nearly Dropped Colin Kaepernick Before Embracing Him|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928032659/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/26/sports/nike-colin-kaepernick.html|archive-date=September 28, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Nigel Powell, chief communications executive of Nike, convinced the company to maintain their partnership with Kaepernick which eventually led to the launch of the politically and socially controversial advertisement released in 2018, \"Nike - Dream Crazy\", with Kaepernick as their face of their 30th anniversary campaign.<ref>{{Citation|last=Nike|title=Nike - Dream Crazy|date=2018-09-05|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fq2CvmgoO7I|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928094000/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fq2CvmgoO7I|archive-date=September 28, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Despite the prevalent backlash on social media of people who criticized Kaepernick's actions by burning and cutting up their Nike brand clothing, and even attracting the attention of President Trump, who then tweeted against the company's campaign,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/30/business/nike-colin-kaepernick-nfl-just-do-it/index.html|title=Why Nike is betting its slogan on Colin Kaepernick|last=Business|first=Nathaniel Meyersohn, CNN|website=CNN|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref> Nike sales increased by 31% within five days after the advertisement was released. However, the campaign did result in a temporary drop of 2.2% in the company's stock price.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/5390884/nike-sales-go-up-kaepernick-ad/|title=Nike Sales Increase 31% After Kaepernick Ad Despite Backlash|website=Time|access-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180930162220/http://time.com/5390884/nike-sales-go-up-kaepernick-ad/|archive-date=September 30, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/09/19/nike-colin-kaepernick-ads-national-anthem-protest-controversy.html|title=Some people may hate Nike's marketing campaigns\u2014but the brand keeps adding billions to its bottom line|last=Turner|first=Dymond Green, Ashley|date=2018-09-19|work=CNBC|access-date=2018-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180927204349/https://www.cnbc.com/2018/09/19/nike-colin-kaepernick-ads-national-anthem-protest-controversy.html|archive-date=September 27, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> By September 13, 2018, Nike's stock price closed at $83.47, which at the time was the highest in the company's history.<ref name=\"https://www.facebook.com/CindyBoren\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2018/09/13/colin-kaepernicks-nike-ad-campaign-gets-more-yeahs-than-nays-from-young-people/|title=Nike's Colin Kaepernick ad campaign gets more yeas than nays from young people|last=Boren|first=Cindy|website=Washington Post|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref> Nike took this backlash and converted it into a meme by releasing an ad that provided instructions to their customer on how to burn their products \"properly\".<ref name=\"https://www.facebook.com/CindyBoren\"/>\n\n===Athletes and sports media===\nThroughout the remainder of the 2016 season, Kaepernick received public backlash for his protest, with an anonymous [[NFL]] executive calling Kaepernick \"a traitor\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2651681-mike-freemans-10-point-stance-kaepernick-anger-intense-in-nfl-front-offices|title=Kaepernick Anger Intense in NFL Front Offices|first=Mike|last=Freeman|accessdate=September 8, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160908034911/http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2651681-mike-freemans-10-point-stance-kaepernick-anger-intense-in-nfl-front-offices|archive-date=September 8, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On September 20, 2016, Kaepernick also stated that he received death threats primarily through social media.<ref name=\"deaththreats\">[http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/09/nfl-kaepernick-received-death-threats-160921152934415.html US: Colin Kaepernick says he has received death threats] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160922124538/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/09/nfl-kaepernick-received-death-threats-160921152934415.html |date=September 22, 2016 }}. [[Al Jazeera]]. September 22, 2016.</ref>\n\nSportscaster [[Bob Costas]] offered support for Kaepernick stating, \"Patriotism comes in many forms and what has happened is it's been conflated with a bumper-style kind of flag-waving and with the military only so that people cannot see that in his own way Colin Kaepernick, however imperfectly, is doing a [[patriotic]] thing.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/09/bob-costas-trump-nfl|title=Bob Costas puts the entire national anthem debate in perspective with one powerful segment|date=September 25, 2017|work=For The Win|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925161813/http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/09/bob-costas-trump-nfl|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[Trent Dilfer]] criticized Kaepernick. \"The big thing that hit me through all this was this is a backup quarterback whose job is to be quiet, and sit in the shadows and get the starter ready to play Week 1,\" Dilfer said on ''[[Sunday NFL Countdown]]''. \"Yet he chose a time where all of a sudden he became the center of attention. And it has disrupted that organization. It has caused friction. And it's torn at the fabric of the team.\"<ref name=\"mercury\">{{cite news|last1=Inman|first1=Cam|title=Colin Kaepernick told by ESPN's Trent Dilfer to 'be quiet, sit in the shadows'|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/2016/09/11/colin-kaepernick-told-by-espns-trent-dilfer-to-be-quiet-sit-in-the-shadows/|website=The Mercury News|accessdate=September 21, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924014013/http://www.mercurynews.com/2016/09/11/colin-kaepernick-told-by-espns-trent-dilfer-to-be-quiet-sit-in-the-shadows/|archive-date=September 24, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nStemming from the Kaepernick controversy, before the beginning of the [[2016 World Cup of Hockey]] tournament in [[Toronto|Toronto, Canada]], Team USA coach [[John Tortorella]] told in an interview that if any one of his players were to sit out during the anthem, they would sit on the bench for the entire duration of the game.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/world-cup-of-hockey/tortorella-will-sit-anthem-protests-team-usa/|title=Tortorella 'will sit' any Team USA player who protests anthem - Sportsnet.ca|newspaper=Sportsnet.ca|access-date=2017-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180806024405/https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/world-cup-of-hockey/tortorella-will-sit-anthem-protests-team-usa/|archive-date=August 6, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe September 2016 police shootings of [[Shooting of Terence Crutcher|Terence Crutcher]] and [[Shooting of Keith Lamont Scott|Keith Lamont Scott]] bolstered support for his protest.<ref>{{cite news|last=Maxwell|first=Francis|title=Silence From Kaepernick Critics Speaks Volumes|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/57e2f47fe4b05d3737be53de?timestamp=1474507429354|website=[[HuffPost]]|date=September 21, 2016|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923064107/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/57e2f47fe4b05d3737be53de?timestamp=1474507429354|archive-date=September 23, 2016|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Kaepernick said of the Terence Crutcher shooting, \"this is a perfect example of what this is about.\"<ref name=\"deaththreats\"/> Boxer [[Floyd Mayweather]] criticized Kaepernick, stating, \"You know, a lot of times, we get stuck, and we are followers. When you hear one person say 'black lives matter' or 'blue lives matter,' all lives matter.\" Adding moments later, \"With me being a fighter, and my hands being registered, if I hit a guy for breaking in my house, or breaking in my car, it's gonna cost me more money, so I gotta work smarter, not harder. I'm gonna call the cops.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Payne|first=Marissa|title=Floyd Mayweather advises people to 'follow order' because 'all lives matter'|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2016/10/11/floyd-mayweather-advises-people-to-follow-order-because-all-lives-matter/|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=October 11, 2016|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180824134922/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2016/10/11/floyd-mayweather-advises-people-to-follow-order-because-all-lives-matter/|archive-date=August 24, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nDiscussion continued throughout August 2017. [[National Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum|Baseball Hall of Famer]] [[Hank Aaron]] said, \"I think he's getting a raw deal\" from the NFL.<ref>{{cite news|last=Axisa|first=Mike|title=MLB Hall of Famer Hank Aaron says Colin Kaepernick is 'getting a raw deal' from NFL|url=https://www.cbssports.com/mlb/news/mlb-hall-of-famer-hank-aaron-says-colin-kaepernick-is-getting-a-raw-deal-from-nfl/|publisher=CBS Sports|website=CBSSports.com|date=August 26, 2017|accessdate=June 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180821160522/https://www.cbssports.com/mlb/news/mlb-hall-of-famer-hank-aaron-says-colin-kaepernick-is-getting-a-raw-deal-from-nfl/|archive-date=August 21, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> That same month, [[Pro Football Hall of Fame]]r and longtime [[Civil and political rights|civil rights activist]] [[Jim Brown]], who a year earlier supported Kaepernick \"100 percent\",<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000692374/article/jim-brown-im-with-colin-kaepernick-100-percent|title=Jim Brown: I'm with Colin Kaepernick '100 percent'|publisher=National Football League|date=August 29, 2016|access-date=August 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826174257/http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000692374/article/jim-brown-im-with-colin-kaepernick-100-percent|archive-date=August 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> now criticized him, suggesting Kaepernick ought to decide whether to be an athlete or an activist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/08/25/jim-brown-says-i-dont-desecrate-my-flag-thinks-colin-kaepernick-should-pick-football-or-activism/|title=Jim Brown says 'I don't desecrate my flag,' thinks Colin Kaepernick should pick football or activism|website=The Washington Post|access-date=August 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826030425/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/08/25/jim-brown-says-i-dont-desecrate-my-flag-thinks-colin-kaepernick-should-pick-football-or-activism/|archive-date=August 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> \"I'm an American,\" said Brown. \"I don't desecrate my flag and my national anthem. ... This is my country, and I'll work out the problems, but I'll do it in an intelligent manner.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/08/25/jim-brown-colin-kaepernick-i-dont-desecrate-my-flag-and-my-national-anthem/602349001/|title=Jim Brown on Colin Kaepernick: 'I don't desecrate my flag and my national anthem'|date=August 25, 2017|website=USA Today|accessdate=August 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826022704/https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/2017/08/25/jim-brown-colin-kaepernick-i-dont-desecrate-my-flag-and-my-national-anthem/602349001/|archive-date=August 26, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[Jim Harbaugh]], Kaepernick's former coach, penned a strong statement of support for him as part of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]''{{'}}s \"[[Time 100|100 Most Influential People]]\" series. Harbaugh wrote, \"His willingness to take a position at personal cost is now part of our American story. How lucky for us all and for our country to have among our citizens someone as remarkable as Colin Kaepernick.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/collection/2017-time-100/4736257/colin-kaepernick/|title=Colin Kaepernick: The World's 100 Most Influential People|website=Time|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170924062914/http://time.com/collection/2017-time-100/4736257/colin-kaepernick/|archive-date=September 24, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[NASCAR]] team owners [[Richard Petty]] and [[Richard Childress]] have supported Trump and said that they would fire drivers and employees who would not stand for the national anthem.<ref>{{cite news|last=Parco|first=Nicholas|title=NASCAR owners threaten to fire any drivers who kneel during national anthem|work=Daily News|location=New York|date=September 24, 2017|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/more-sports/nascar-owners-threaten-fire-drivers-protest-anthem-article-1.3518424|accessdate=September 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925081415/http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/more-sports/nascar-owners-threaten-fire-drivers-protest-anthem-article-1.3518424|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Petty said, \"Anybody that don't stand up for the anthem ought to be out of the country. Period.\" Childress said, \"It'll get you a ride on a Greyhound bus\" if anyone on his team protested the anthem.<ref>{{cite news | last2=Hamilton | last1=Bieler | first2=Tracee | first1=Des | title=Richard Petty, other NASCAR owners decry protests, but Dale Earnhardt Jr. offers support | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/24/richard-petty-among-nascar-owners-saying-anthem-protests-will-get-employees-fired/ | work=Washington Post | date=September 25, 2017 | accessdate=September 26, 2017 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926000633/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2017/09/24/richard-petty-among-nascar-owners-saying-anthem-protests-will-get-employees-fired/ | archive-date=September 26, 2017 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Driver [[Dale Earnhardt Jr.]], however, expressed support for the peaceful protests, quoting President [[John F. Kennedy]], \"Those who make peaceful revolution impossible will make violent revolution inevitable.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbssports.com/general/news/nascars-dale-earnhardt-jr-voices-support-for-peaceful-protests-in-america/|title=NASCAR's Dale Earnhardt Jr. voices support for peaceful protests in America|publisher=CBSSports.com|access-date=September 25, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925230434/https://www.cbssports.com/general/news/nascars-dale-earnhardt-jr-voices-support-for-peaceful-protests-in-america/|archive-date=September 25, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> NASCAR released a statement on September 25 in response to the protests that said, \"Sports are a unifying influence in our society, bringing people of differing backgrounds and beliefs together. Our respect for the national anthem has always been a hallmark of our pre-race events. Thanks to the sacrifices of many, we live in a country of unparalleled freedoms and countless liberties, including the right to peacefully express one's opinion.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=NASCAR statement|publisher=NASCAR.com|date=September 25, 2017|url=https://www.nascar.com/news-media/2017/09/25/nascar-statement-september-25/|accessdate=September 26, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927112541/https://www.nascar.com/news-media/2017/09/25/nascar-statement-september-25/|archive-date=September 27, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[Jemele Hill]] tweeted, \"Just so we're clear: the president's comments will only incite more player protests, not quell them.\" following Trump's initial response to the protests.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/09/13/media/jemele-hill-espn-white-house/index.html|title=ESPN says it accepts Jemele Hill's apology after anti-Trump tweets|publisher=CNN|date=September 14, 2017|access-date=October 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009214059/http://money.cnn.com/2017/09/13/media/jemele-hill-espn-white-house/index.html|archive-date=October 9, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://thehill.com/homenews/media/352026-espns-jemele-hill-trumps-nfl-remarks-will-only-make-more-players-protest|title=ESPN's Jemele Hill: Trump's NFL remarks will only make more players protest|newspaper=The Hill|date=September 9, 2017|access-date=October 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171010004627/http://thehill.com/homenews/media/352026-espns-jemele-hill-trumps-nfl-remarks-will-only-make-more-players-protest|archive-date=October 10, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Hill was later put on a two-week suspension for \"a second violation of our social media guidelines\", after Hill suggested people direct their disagreements towards advertisers of Dallas Cowboys owner [[Jerry Jones]], after Jones stated he would bench any player who protested the national anthem on October 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20961541/dallas-cowboys-owner-jerry-jones-says-player-disrespects-flag-play|title=Jerry Jones: Cowboys will bench any player who 'disrespects' flag|publisher=ESPN|date=October 9, 2017|access-date=October 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009233903/http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/20961541/dallas-cowboys-owner-jerry-jones-says-player-disrespects-flag-play|archive-date=October 9, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://money.cnn.com/2017/10/09/media/jemele-hill-espn-suspended/index.html|title=ESPN suspends Jemele Hill over tweets|publisher=CNNMoney|date=October 9, 2017|access-date=October 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171009202340/http://money.cnn.com/2017/10/09/media/jemele-hill-espn-suspended/index.html|archive-date=October 9, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn September 25, 2017, [[Bill Russell]] posted a photo to Twitter while kneeling and wearing his [[Presidential Medal of Freedom]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://whdh.com/news/celtics-legend-bill-russell-takes-knee-in-photo-with-presidential-medal-of-freedom/ |title=Celtics legend Bill Russell takes knee in photo with Presidential Medal of Freedom |publisher=WHDH 7News |date=February 13, 2011 |accessdate=September 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927000037/http://whdh.com/news/celtics-legend-bill-russell-takes-knee-in-photo-with-presidential-medal-of-freedom/ |archive-date=September 27, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> On September 26, 2017, Joey Odoms, the national anthem singer for the home games of the Ravens, resigned citing the \"tone/actions of a large number of NFL fans in the midst of our country's cultural crisis\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Zrebiec |first1=Jeff |title=Ravens national anthem singer Joey Odoms, a combat veteran, informs team he is resigning |url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/ravens/ravens-insider/bs-sp-odoms-resigning-20170926-story.html |accessdate=September 27, 2017 |work=The Baltimore Sun |date=September 26, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927112842/http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/ravens/ravens-insider/bs-sp-odoms-resigning-20170926-story.html |archive-date=September 27, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nFormer [[Chicago Bears]] coach [[Mike Ditka]] commented, \"If you don't respect our country, then you shouldn't be in this country playing football ... So I would say, adios.\" He added that he was \"not condemning anybody or criticizing anybody\" in his remarks. According to Ditka, \"there has been no oppression in the last 100 years that I know of.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/sports/mike-ditka-nfl-protests-there-s-been-no-oppression-u-n809566|title=Mike Ditka on NFL Protests: There's Been No Oppression in U.S. in Last 100 Years|publisher=NBC News|date=October 10, 2017|access-date=October 11, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011012733/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/sports/mike-ditka-nfl-protests-there-s-been-no-oppression-u-n809566|archive-date=October 11, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Entertainment===\nNFL ratings have been in decline for the past couple years, except for the 2018 season, which saw an increase of 4%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/what-drove-the-nfls-tv-ratings-increase-in-2018/|title=What Drove the NFL's TV Ratings Increase in 2018?|date=2019-01-05|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> However, during the 2016 and 2017 seasons ratings were down by 8% and 9.7% respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2685400-nfl-tv-ratings-reportedly-down-8-percent-for-2016-17-season|title=NFL TV Ratings Reportedly Down 8 Percent for 2016 Season|last=Chiari|first=Mike|website=Bleacher Report|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/21960086|title=TV ratings for NFL down 9.7 percent during '17|date=2018-01-04|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> A UBS securities analysis show that the primary cause of the drop in the ratings from the NFL is mainly due to players protesting the national anthem. According to the same survey, 50% of the decline in rating in 2017 is because of players taking a knee before the game, whereas this action only accounts for 18% of the decline of rating in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2018/feb/6/nfl-ratings-down-due-anthem-protests-survey/|title=NFL ratings down due to anthem protests: survey|last=http://www.washingtontimes.com|first=The Washington Times|website=The Washington Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> The decline in ratings have had a huge impact on the ad revenue from major television companies, especially CBS and Fox.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/mikeozanian/2017/11/03/nfl-anthem-protests-smack-leagues-broadcasters-and-sponsors/|title=NFL Anthem Protests Continue To Smack League's Broadcasters And Sponsors|last=Ozanian|first=Mike|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>\n\n[[Stevie Wonder]] knelt during the 2017 [[Global Citizen Festival]] on September 23, saying \"Tonight, I'm taking a knee for America\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Phillips |first=Kristine |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2017/09/24/im-taking-a-knee-for-america-stevie-wonder-joins-a-movement-trump-deplores/ |title='I'm taking a knee for America': Stevie Wonder joins a movement Trump deplores |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=September 24, 2017 |accessdate=September 25, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102101044/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2017/09/24/im-taking-a-knee-for-america-stevie-wonder-joins-a-movement-trump-deplores/ |archive-date=January 2, 2019 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n[[Eddie Vedder]], [[Pharrell Williams]], [[Dave Matthews]], [[John Legend]] and [[Roger Waters]] knelt to support the protests during concerts on September 24.<ref>{{cite web |last=Kreps |first=Daniel |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/eddie-vedder-roger-waters-take-knee-onstage-in-protest-w505227 |title=Eddie Vedder, Roger Waters Take Knee Onstage in Protest |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=September 25, 2017 |accessdate=September 25, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170925173143/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/eddie-vedder-roger-waters-take-knee-onstage-in-protest-w505227 |archive-date=September 25, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> The same day [[Sonequa Martin-Green]] posted in her [[Instagram]] account a picture of several members from ''[[Star Trek: Discovery]]''{{'}}s cast alongside producer [[Akiva Goldsman]] and herself kneeling.<ref>{{cite web |last=Hibberd |first=James |url=http://ew.com/tv/2017/09/25/star-trek-discovery-sonequa-takes-knee/ |title=Star Trek: Discovery cast takes a knee in premiere night protest |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=September 25, 2017 |accessdate=September 29, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928072419/http://ew.com/tv/2017/09/25/star-trek-discovery-sonequa-takes-knee/ |archive-date=September 28, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> [[Shonda Rhimes]] posted a photo kneeling with the cast of ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/greys-anatomy-take-a-knee-1202574019/|title='Grey's Anatomy' Cast, Creator Take a Knee in Instagram Post|first=Daniel|last=Holloway|date=September 27, 2017|website=variety.com|accessdate=October 4, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002145613/http://variety.com/2017/tv/news/greys-anatomy-take-a-knee-1202574019/|archive-date=October 2, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n''[[The X-Files]]'' actors [[Gillian Anderson]] and [[David Duchovny]] posted a photo on Twitter of themselves kneeling with arms locked on September 26.<ref>{{cite web |author=Gael Fashingbauer Cooper |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/x-files-gillian-anderson-david-duchovny-take-a-knee-nfl-colin-kaepernick-donald-trump/ |title='X-Files' stars Gillian Anderson, David Duchovny take a knee |website=CNET |date=September 19, 2017 |accessdate=September 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928204923/https://www.cnet.com/news/x-files-gillian-anderson-david-duchovny-take-a-knee-nfl-colin-kaepernick-donald-trump/ |archive-date=September 28, 2017 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nActor [[Damien Leake]] had been making a similar protest for almost 50 years, since the assassination of [[Martin Luther King Jr.]].  When asked to comment:\n\n{{quote|Does it ever occur to you that the playing of the national anthem has no place at a sporting event, period?  Those of you who know me from high school may remember that I decided to start sitting during the playing of the Star Spangled Banner on April 4th 1968, and have been sitting ever since.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mynewsla.com/hollywood/2017/10/03/trump-bashes-nfl-but-serpico-actor-sits-for-national-anthem-since-1968/|title='Serpico' actor: Why I've sat for national anthem since 1968|date=October 4, 2017|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190211174230/https://mynewsla.com/hollywood/2017/10/03/trump-bashes-nfl-but-serpico-actor-sits-for-national-anthem-since-1968/|archive-date=February 11, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>|}}\n\n===Colleges===\nOn October 11, 2018, Colin Kaepernick was awarded the [[W. E. B. Du Bois|W.E.B. Du Bois]] Medal at [[Harvard University]] during the Hutchins Center Honors sponsored by the Hutchins Center for African & African American Research. The award is going to be given for his \"significant contributions and African-American history and culture\", and for his support \"for intercultural understanding and human rights in an increasingly global and interconnected world\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2018/09/kaepernick-and-chappelle-among-eight-du-bois-medalists-at-harvard/|title=Kaepernick and Chappelle among eight Du Bois medalists at Harvard|date=September 20, 2018|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181212065845/https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2018/09/kaepernick-and-chappelle-among-eight-du-bois-medalists-at-harvard/|archive-date=December 12, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Some might think that the award is significant because it shows what he has sacrificed for starting and upholding the national anthem protest, and gives credibility to him as an activist based on the criteria for the award and past honorees such as [[Muhammad Ali]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/21/us/harvard-honors-kaepernick-trnd/index.html|title=Harvard will honor Colin Kaepernick for contributions to African-American history and culture|author1=Christina Maxouris |author2=Saeed Ahmed|website=CNN|accessdate=January 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180929084511/https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/21/us/harvard-honors-kaepernick-trnd/index.html|archive-date=September 29, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Law enforcement===\n\nDue to Kaepernick's 2018 advertisement with Nike, both plaudits and denunciations have been voiced. On September 5, 2018 in response to the new Kaepernick-Nike campaign, the National Black Police Association provided a letter stating, \"The NBPA believes that Mr. Kaepernick's stance is in direct alignment with what law enforcement stands for \u2014 the protection of a people, their human rights, their dignity, their safety and their rights as American citizens.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/identities/2018/9/6/17827348/colin-kaepernick-nfl-protest-police-unions-boycott |title=A black police organization issued a powerful defense of Colin Kaepernick|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181216031205/https://www.vox.com/identities/2018/9/6/17827348/colin-kaepernick-nfl-protest-police-unions-boycott|archive-date=December 16, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Despite being police officers, the NBPA defends Kaepernick's actions because they feel that the issue of race must be addressed in order to tackle the ongoing issue.<ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2018/09/06/black-officers-group-issues-stirring-defense-kaepernick-says-values-directly-align-with-police/?noredirect=on|title=Why a black police group issued a stirring defense of Colin Kaepernick|first=Eli Rosenberg|last=Washington Post|website=Washington POst|accessdate=February 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190220181523/https://www.washingtonpost.com/nation/2018/09/06/black-officers-group-issues-stirring-defense-kaepernick-says-values-directly-align-with-police/?noredirect=on&utm_term=.fe7823e14721|archive-date=February 20, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}\n</ref>\n\nThere is a wide divide of agreement on this subject between law enforcement groups; especially between the NBPA and [http://www.napo.org/ The National Police Association] (who felt that Kaepernick's gestures regarding the national anthem were disrespectful).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/1380985/nikes-colin-kaepernick-ad-is-dividing-us-police/ |title=Nike's Colin Kaepernick ad is dividing US police|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181216031712/https://qz.com/1380985/nikes-colin-kaepernick-ad-is-dividing-us-police/|archive-date=December 16, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> NAPO has even called for a boycott of Nike products due to their recent partnership with Kaepernick.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.napo.org/washington-report/latest-news-updates/napo-calls-boycott-nike/ |title=NAPO Calls for Boycott of Nike|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181207150721/http://www.napo.org/washington-report/latest-news-updates/napo-calls-boycott-nike/|archive-date=December 7, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Social media ===\nKneeling during the national anthem became a symbol of resistance, similar to the [[Raised fist|black power fist]]. The act was discussed heavily on social media, with users on [[Twitter]] and [[Facebook]] using #TakeAKnee or #TakeTheKnee to discuss the act. The use of this [[hashtag]] exploded with 4 million tweets.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adweek.com/brand-marketing/this-social-analytics-firm-says-the-4-million-takeaknee-tweets-are-just-the-beginning/|title=This Social Analytics Firm Says the 4 Million #TakeAKnee Tweets Are Just the Beginning|last=Monllos{{!}}September 25|first=Kristina|last2=2017|website=www.adweek.com|access-date=2019-03-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adweek.com/digital/takeaknee-taketheknee-athletes-twitter-trump/|title=Twitter Saw 3.8 Million #TakeAKnee Tweets Amid Trump's Weekend Dust-Up With Pro Sports|website=www.adweek.com|access-date=2019-03-07}}</ref> The hashtag was often used with other hashtags such as #BoycottNFL and #BlackLivesMatter. #BoycottNFL is used in different states than #TakeAKnee, with those using #BoycottNFL wanting to boycott the NFL and those using #TakeAKnee supporting the players who choose to protest.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.phillyvoice.com/twitter-numbers-boycott-nfl-vs-take-knee/|title=By the social-media numbers: Boycott NFL vs. Take a Knee|last=Hickey|first=Brian|website=www.phillyvoice.com|access-date=2019-03-07}}</ref>\n\n=== NFL national anthem policy ===\nThe previous national anthem policy by the NFL written about a decade before the new policy in May 2018 contained vocabulary that allotted more leeway in the players' behavior during the national anthem before games. It required players to be on the sideline but only stated that players should, not must, stand during the national anthem.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mannersmentor.com/12-months-of-holidays/u-s-flag-pledge-of-allegiance-and-national-anthem-etiquette/|title=U.S. Flag, Pledge of Allegiance, and National Anthem Etiquette}}</ref> Colin Kaepernick used this fact to an advantage and conducted his act of a peaceful protest which remained inconspicuous until President Trump posted his tweets on Twitter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/23/sports/national-anthem-nfl.html|title=N.F.L. Anthem Policy Bound to Please Only the N.F.L.|last=Belson|first=Ken|date=2018-05-23|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-04-26|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The tweets brought enormous amounts of media attention to the participating players and found people on two sides of the issue; one group that supported Kaepernick and many other players that were protesting to bring awareness to police brutality black people faced and the other group that believed kneeling was disrespectful to the country, flag, or the military.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/the-two-sides-of-the-us-national-anthem-protests-in-the-nfl/a-40673869|title=The two sides of the US national anthem protests in the NFL {{!}} DW {{!}} 25.09.2017|last=VanOpdorp|first=Davis|website=DW.COM|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>\n\nTo address the backlash, the NFL released a national anthem policy in May 2018, stating that players and team personnel were required to stand during the national anthem. Those who chose not to stand were required to remain in the locker room.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000941064/article/nfl-anthem-policy-on-hold-under-standstill-agreement|title=NFL anthem policy on hold under standstill agreement|website=NFL.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-10}}</ref> Though NFL commissioner [[Roger Goodell]] said the vote was unanimous among all NFL owners, [[Jed York]], the owner of the [[San Francisco 49ers]] and Kaepernick's previous team said he abstained.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/23582533|title=NFL owners pass new national anthem policy|last=Seifert|first=Kevin|last2=Graziano|first2=Dan|date=2018-05-23|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref> During an interview, President Trump said that the NFL did \"the right thing\" of releasing the new policy. He added, \"You have to stand proudly for the national anthem or you shouldn\u2019t be playing. You shouldn\u2019t be there. Maybe you shouldn\u2019t be in the country.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ajc.com/news/nfl-new-national-anthem-policy-has-people-talking/JqNUUdBClTX9DNAn2UrgZL/|title=NFL's policy on flag, national anthem has people talking|last=Brett|first=Jennifer|website=AJC|language=English|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>\n\nSince passing the new national anthem policy in May 2018, the policy was put on hold in July 2018. This occurred when the [[National Football League Players Association|NFLPA]] filed a grievance against the NFL's national anthem policy, stating that the policy violated the players' rights because there were no prior discussions between the NFL and NFLPA. The policy remained suspended until [[Super Bowl LIII]] and will remain suspended until further notice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/the-super-bowl-2019-kneeling-policy-leaves-that-decision-up-to-players-15867537|title=What To Know About The NFL's Kneeling Policy Ahead Of The 2019 Super Bowl|last=Friedmann|first=Sarah|website=Bustle|language=en|access-date=2019-04-26}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[1968 Olympics Black Power salute]]\n* [[United States Flag Code]]\n* [[Quarterback kneel]]\n* [[Tim Tebow]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Black Lives Matter}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:U.S. national anthem protests (2016-present)}}\n[[Category:U.S. national anthem protests (2016\u2013present)| ]]\n[[Category:2016 beginnings]]\n[[Category:2016 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:2016 in American sports]]\n[[Category:2016 protests]]\n[[Category:2017 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:2017 in American sports]]\n[[Category:2017 protests]]\n[[Category:2018 protests]]\n[[Category:2018 controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:African-American sports history]]\n[[Category:Anti-racism in the United States]]\n[[Category:Civil rights protests in the United States]]\n[[Category:Criticism of police brutality]]\n[[Category:Flag controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Kneeling]]\n[[Category:African-American-related controversies]]\n[[Category:Race-related controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Media-related controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Music and politics]]\n[[Category:National Football League controversies]]\n[[Category:Ongoing protests]]\n[[Category:Police brutality in the United States]]\n[[Category:Politics and race in the United States]]\n[[Category:Politics and sports]]\n[[Category:Protests against Donald Trump]]\n[[Category:Sports controversies]]\n[[Category:The Star-Spangled Banner]]\n[[Category:Trump administration controversies]]\n", "name_user": "108.208.75.203", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._national_anthem_protests_(2016%E2%80%93present)"}
{"title_page": "Mary Forster (Quaker)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n'''Mary Forster''' (c. 1620\u20131687) was an English [[Quaker]] campaigner. She wrote a preface to the 1671 edition of ''Guide to the Blind'', which had been written by her husband, Thomas Forster (died 1660). She also composed an address \"To the Reader\" which accompanied a Petition to the [[Parliament of England]] presented on 20 May 1659, expressing the opposition of over 7000 women to \"the oppression of [[Tithe]]s\" levied by the established church.<ref name=\"Feminist\" >Virginia Blain, Patricia Clements and Isobel Grundy, eds, ''The Feminist Companion to Literature in English. Women Writers from the Middle Ages to the Present'' (London: Batsford, 1990), p. 388.</ref>\n\n==A female approach==\nTo justify the then unusual political intervention by women in the form of a parliamentary petition, Forster states that it is God's way to employ \"weak means to bring to pass his mighty work.\" She gives testimony in ''Piety Promoted'' (1686) on behalf of [[Anne Whitehead]], who is considered to have been the first woman preacher among the Quakers in 1655. As one of five signatories to ''A Living Testimony from... Our Faithful Women's Meeting'' (1685) she argues that \"we are not to put our Candles under a Bushel, nor to hide our Talents in a Napkin,\" having gained wisdom of God about \"what will do in Families\" as \"Mothers of Children, and Antient Women in Our Families\".<ref name=\"Feminist\" />\n\nHer main issue in ''Some Seasonable Considerations'' (1684) is the continuing persecution of the Quakers (Society of Friends).<ref>Christopher Densmore and Barbara Addison, ''Quaker History'', Vol. 101, No. 1 (Spring 2012), pp. 39\u201346.</ref>\n\nHowever, Mary Forster still sees the [[Protofeminism|Protofeminist]] protests of women as a secondary reinforcement to the work of men. She justifies their parliamentary protest against tithes as auxiliary, while noting that it is compatible with the actions of the Quaker \"Brethren\".<ref>Catie Gill: ''Women in the Seventeenth-Century Quaker Community: A Literary Study of Political Identities, 1650\u20131700'' (Routledge, 2017).</ref>\n\nVery little else is known of her private life. Mary Forster died in 1687.<ref name=\"Feminist\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1687 deaths]]\n[[Category:17th-century Quakers]]\n[[Category:English Quakers]]\n[[Category:Quaker writers]]\n[[Category:17th-century English women writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n'''Mary Forster''' (c. 1620\u20131687) was an English [[Quaker]] campaigner. She wrote a preface to the 1671 edition of ''Guide to the Blind'', which had been written by her husband, Thomas Forster (died 1660). She also composed an address \"To the Reader\" which accompanied a Petition to the [[Parliament of England]] presented on 20 May 1659, expressing the opposition of over 7000 women to \"the oppression of [[Tithe]]s\" levied by the established church.<ref name=\"Feminist\" >Virginia Blain, Patricia Clements and Isobel Grundy, eds, ''The Feminist Companion to Literature in English. Women Writers from the Middle Ages to the Present'' (London: Batsford, 1990), p. 388.</ref>\n\n==A female approach==\nTo justify the then unusual political intervention by women in the form of a parliamentary petition, Forster states that it is God's way to employ \"weak means to bring to pass his mighty work.\" She gives testimony in ''Piety Promoted'' (1686) on behalf of [[Anne Whitehead]], who is considered to have been the first woman preacher among the Quakers in 1655. As one of five signatories to ''A Living Testimony from... Our Faithful Women's Meeting'' (1685) she argues that \"we are not to put our Candles under a Bushel, nor to hide our Talents in a Napkin,\" having gained wisdom of God about \"what will do in Families\" as \"Mothers of Children, and Antient Women in Our Families\".<ref name=\"Feminist\" />\n\nHer main issue in ''Some Seasonable Considerations'' (1684) is the continuing persecution of the Quakers (Society of Friends).<ref>Christopher Densmore and Barbara Addison, ''Quaker History'', Vol. 101, No. 1 (Spring 2012), pp. 39\u201346.</ref>\n\nHowever, Mary Forster still sees the [[Protofeminism|Protofeminist]] protests of women as a secondary reinforcement to the work of men. She justifies their parliamentary protest against tithes as auxiliary, while noting that it is compatible with the actions of the Quaker \"Brethren\".<ref>Catie Gill: ''Women in the Seventeenth-Century Quaker Community: A Literary Study of Political Identities, 1650\u20131700'' (Routledge, 2017).</ref>\n\nVery little else is known of her private life. Mary Forster died in 1687.<ref name=\"Feminist\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1687 deaths]]\n[[Category:17th-century Quakers]]\n[[Category:English Quakers]]\n[[Category:Quaker writers]]\n[[Category:17th-century English women writers]]\n", "name_user": "Bmcln1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mary_Forster_(Quaker)"}
{"title_page": "S/O Satyamurthy", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=March 2016}}\n{{Good article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}}\n{{Infobox film\n| italic title   = \n| name           = S/O Satyamurthy\n| image          = Son of Satyamurthy poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| alt            = Allu Arjun and Samantha Ruth Prabhu in dance poses.\n| writer         = Trivikram Srinivas\n| starring       = Sojol Khan/Stylish king[[Allu Arjun]]<br />[[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]]<br />[[Samantha Akkineni|Samantha Ruth Prabhu]]<br />[[Nithya Menen]]<br />[[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]]<br />[[Adah Sharma]]<br />[[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]]<br />[[Prakash Raj]]<br />[[Sampath Raj]]<br />[[Vennela Kishore]]<br />[[Brahmanandam]]\n| narrator      = Allu Arjun\n| director       = [[Trivikram Srinivas]]\n| cinematography = [[Prasad Murella]]\n| producer       = [[S. Radha Krishna]]\n| editing        = [[Prawin Pudi]]\n| studio         = Haarika & Hassine Creations\n| distributor    = Classic Entertainments<br /><small>(Overseas)</small><ref name=\"Classic\" /><br />[[Sri Venkateswara Creations]]<br /><small>(Nizam)</small><ref name=\"Nizam\" />\n| country        = India\n| released       = {{Film date|2015|04|09|df=y|ref1=<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjuns-son-satyamurthy-gets-u-certificate-censor-board-set-grand-release-627641 | title=Allu Arjun's 'Son of Satyamurthy' Gets 'U/A' Certificate from Censor Board; Set For Grand Release | work=[[International Business Times]] India | date=30 March 2015 | accessdate=30 March 2015 | last=H. Hooli | first=Shekhar | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330145624/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjuns-son-satyamurthy-gets-u-certificate-censor-board-set-grand-release-627641 | archivedate=30 March 2015}}</ref>}}\n| runtime        =\n| language       = Telugu\n| music          = [[Devi Sri Prasad]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Devi-Sri-Prasad-to-compose-tunes-for-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/27650233.cms | title=Devi Sri Prasad to compose tunes for Allu Arjun's next | work=[[The Times of India]] | date=19 December 2013 | accessdate=8 April 2014 | author=Times News Network | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031152802/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Devi-Sri-Prasad-to-compose-tunes-for-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/27650233.cms | archivedate=31 October 2014}}</ref>\n| budget         = {{INR}}400{{mdash}}500&nbsp;million{{efn|''[[International Business Times]] India'' claims the film's budget as {{INR}}400&nbsp;million,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjun-join-twitter-ahead-s-o-sathyamurthy-release-628140 | title=Allu Arjun to Join Twitter Ahead of 'S/O Sathyamurthy' Release | work=International Business Times India | date=4 April 2015 | accessdate=4 April 2015 | last=V. P. | first=Nicy | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150404145231/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjun-join-twitter-ahead-s-o-sathyamurthy-release-628140 | archivedate=4 April 2015}}</ref> whereas [[Oneindia.com|Oneindia Entertainment]] claims it as {{INR}}500&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/allu-arjun-s-son-of-satyamurthy-enters-profit-zone-before-its-release-178557.html | title=Son of Satyamurthy Enters Profit Zone Before Its Release | publisher=[[Oneindia]] Entertainment | date=31 March 2015 | accessdate=31 March 2015 | last=Anjuri | first=Pravallika | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150331131445/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/allu-arjun-s-son-of-satyamurthy-enters-profit-zone-before-its-release-178557.html | archivedate=31 March 2015}}</ref>}}\n| gross          = {{INR}}900&nbsp;million<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/regional/content-over-star-power-story-of-south-cinema-in-first-half-of-2015/article1-1364817.aspx | title=Content over star power: Story of south cinema in first half of 2015 | work=[[Hindustan Times]] | date=1 July 2015 | accessdate=11 July 2015 | last=Pudipeddi | first=Harichandran | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150711120039/http://www.hindustantimes.com/regional/content-over-star-power-story-of-south-cinema-in-first-half-of-2015/article1-1364817.aspx | archivedate=11 July 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''S/O Satyamurthy''''' (read as ''Son of Satyamurthy'') is a 2015 Indian [[Telugu language|Telugu-language]] [[action drama film]] directed by [[Trivikram Srinivas]] and produced by S. Radha Krishna for Haarika & Haasine Creations. It features an ensemble cast of [[Allu Arjun]], [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]], [[Samantha Akkineni|Samantha Ruth Prabhu]], [[Nithya Menen]], [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]], [[Adah Sharma]], [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]], [[Sampath Raj]], [[Vennela Kishore]], [[Brahmanandam]] and [[Ali (actor)|Ali]]. [[Prakash Raj]] makes a [[cameo appearance]] as Satyamurthy.\n\nThe film revolves around three characters; the first follows his heart, the second uses his brain and the third uses his brawn. The first is Viraj Anand, the son of a billionaire named Satyamurthy, who gives his money to creditors after his father's death. A creditor still owed money is Paida Sambasiva Rao (the second of the three), whose daughter Sameera falls in love with Anand. Sambasiva Rao informs Anand that he has to produce documentation of land sold by Satyamurthy to a landlord, Devaraj Naidu (the third of the three) to marry Sameera. The rest of the film focuses on the consequences faced by Anand and Sambasiva Rao's change in viewpoint toward Satyamurthy.\n\nIn addition to directing the film, Srinivas wrote its screenplay. Initially planned as a multilingual film shot in Tamil, Malayalam and Telugu, the producers filmed in Telugu and dubbed it into Malayalam with the same title. [[Devi Sri Prasad]] composed the score and [[Prasad Murella]] was its cinematographer. Production began on 10 April 2014 at [[Ramanaidu Studios]] in [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]]. [[Principal photography]] began on 22 September 2014 in Hyderabad, lasting until mid-March 2015. Except for three songs filmed in [[Europe]], the rest of the film was shot in and around Hyderabad.\n\nThe Telugu version was released worldwide on 1375 screens on 9 April 2015 to a lukewarm response, and the Malayalam version was released on 24 April 2015. On a {{INR}}400{{ndash}}500-million budget, ''S/O Satyamurthy'' earned a distributor share of {{INR}}519 million and grossed {{INR}}1 billion. The film was an above average grosser based on the return on the distributors' investment of {{INR}}540 million. It is in seventh place on the all-time list of highest-grossing Telugu films at the global box office. With this film, Allu Arjun became the first Telugu actor with two consecutive films earning more than {{INR}}500&nbsp;million worldwide.\n\n== Plot ==\nNarrator Viraj Anand is the younger son of Satyamurthy, a billionaire businessman who dies in an accident. Although Anand has {{INR}}3&nbsp;billion worth of property and stock which is worthless, he owes an equal amount. Paida Sambasiva Rao, one of Satyamurthy's creditors, suggests that Anand file for bankruptcy to protect his wealth but Anand wants to preserve his father's image. Anand's older brother becomes mentally unstable and, at Sambasiva Rao's advice, the father of Anand's fianc\u00e9e Pallavi cancels their upcoming wedding. Anand and his family move to a simpler home in Hyderabad, and he becomes the family's sole breadwinner. He joins his friend's event-management company as a wedding planner, and his assistant Param goes with him.\n\nAnand is assigned to plan a destination wedding at [[Ooty]], which turns out to be Pallavi's. There he meets Sameera (also known as Subbalakshmi), a diabetic, with whom he eventually falls in love. While planning Pallavi's marriage Anand faces many difficulties, including an attempt by Pallavi's uncle and his son to stop the marriage because of her father's mistreatment. Pallavi's father and uncle reconcile, and Anand is paid more than the agreed amount in gratitude. Sameera turns out to be Sambasiva Rao's daughter; the latter objects to their marriage, saying that Satyamurthy cheated him when he sold a {{convert|8000|sqft|m2|adj=on}} property illegally acquired by landlord Devaraj Naidu. The current market value of the land is half&nbsp;billion rupees. Sambasiva Rao tells Anand that he will agree to the marriage if Anand can deliver the land documents from Devaraj in four weeks.\n\nAnand and Param set out for house number 6 in Reddiarpatti to exchange the original documents for fake ones. Instead, they end up in house number 9 and reveal their intentions to Devaraj, who traps them without harm; Devaraj cannot hurt anyone in front of his wife, Lakshmi, from whom he has hidden his true self for twenty years. Sambasiva Rao's family is kidnapped and brought to Devaraj's house; the next day Anand saves Devaraj from the brother (Kumarasamy Naidu, Devaraj's henchman since five years) of his rival, Veerasamy Naidu. Impressed, Devaraj agrees to return the land documents if Anand becomes engaged to his sister Valli. However, Valli wants to marry Lakshmi's brother and threatens to kill Anand if he does not break their engagement.\n\nValli teases Sameera, acting as if she is in love with Anand (which makes Devaraj happy). Devaraj's brother-in-law Koda Rambabu goes to Reddiarpatti, mistakenly believing that Parandhamaiah is Sameera's lover and Valli's potential lover. He wants to stop the marriage, and at Anand's suggestion Rambabu and Sambasiva Rao ask Veerasamy to have his henchmen kill the bridegroom; this would stop the marriage on the last day of the four-week deadline imposed by Sambasiva Rao. Although Anand plans to help Valli elope with her cousin, Veerasamy's henchmen mistake him for Anand and try to kill him. Devaraj and Anand save her cousin; when Devaraj tries to kill Rambabu, Anand says that he was the mastermind behind the plan and wants the real land documents.\n\nNine minutes are left before Sambasiva Rao's deadline; as Anand and Devaraj duel, Anand's mother enters. Devaraj and his family are shocked, remembering that Satyamurthy was fatally injured when he saved Valli from an accident planned by Veerasamy. Before he died, Satyamurthy told Valli that he made a mistake selling illegally acquired land to his friend and wants to rectify it with the landlord. Devaraj and Sambasiva Rao are full of remorse, and Devaraj returns the land documents to Anand in accordance with Satyamurthy's last wish. Anand gives the papers to Sambasiva Rao, who apologises for his behaviour and Sameera reunites with him. Veerasamy dies in an accident, and Koda Rambabu is spared.\n\nAnand and Sambasiva Rao are on their way home with their families when Pallavi's father meets them with news that the market value of Anand's stock is now worth five&nbsp; billion rupees. An emotional Anand thanks his father at the spot where Satyamurthy saved Valli's life.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Allu Arjun]] as Viraj Anand\n*[[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]] as Devaraj Naidu\n*[[Prakash Raj]] as Satyamurthy ([[Guest appearance]])\n*[[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]] as Paida Sambasiva Rao\n*[[Samantha Akkineni|Samantha Ruth Prabhu]] as Sameera / Subbalakshmi\n*[[Nithya Menen]] as Valli\n*[[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] as Lakshmi\n*[[Adah Sharma]] as Pallavi Kolasani\n*[[Ali (actor)|Ali]] as Parandhamayya\n*[[Sindhu Tolani]] as Viraj Anand's sister-in-law\n*[[Pavitra Lokesh]] as Viraj Anand's mother\n*[[Brahmanandam]] as Koda Rambabu\n*[[M. S. Narayana]] as Pallavi's paternal uncle\n*[[Kota Srinivasa Rao]] as Devaraj's Father\n*[[Rao Ramesh]] as Pallavi's Father\n*[[Sampath Raj]] as Veerasamy Naidu\n*[[Vennela Kishore]] as Viraj Anand's elder brother\n*Baby Vernika as Sweety\n*[[Mamilla Shailaja Priya]] as Sameera's mother\n*[[Vamsi Krishna]] as Yogeshwar\n*[[Chaitanya Krishna]] as Vinay, Lakshmi's brother\n*[[Ravi Prakash (Telugu actor)|Ravi Prakash]] as Kumaraswamy Naidu\n*[[Sree Vishnu]] as Viraj Anand's friend\n*[[Amit Tiwari]] as Pallavi's cousin\n*Prabhu as Devaraj's brother-in-law\n<!--*[[Madhunandan]]-->\n*[[Surekha Vani]] as the principal of the school Sweety studies in\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\n[[Trivikram Srinivas]] planned to direct [[Allu Arjun]] in a film produced by S. Radha Krishna for Haarika & Haasine Creations (who produced their 2012 collaboration ''[[Julai]]''), since Srinivas had committed to another film with them.<ref name=\"Arjun Trivikram film\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Trivikrams-next-is-with-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/25176762.cms|title=Trivikram's next is with Allu Arjun?|work=The Times of India|date=3 November 2013|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031164716/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Trivikrams-next-is-with-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/25176762.cms|archivedate=31 October 2014}}</ref> [[Allu Aravind]] was later rumoured to co-produce of the film as [[Geetha Arts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/geetha-arts-joins-bunnytrivikram-project-telugu-news-100209|title=Geetha Arts Joins Bunny-Trivikram Project|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=22 November 2013|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141009011631/http://www.indiaglitz.com/geetha-arts-joins-bunnytrivikram-project-telugu-news-100209|archivedate=9 October 2014}}</ref> The film's ''[[Puja (Hinduism)|pooja]]'' ceremony was held at Radha Krishna's office in early December 2013, and filming was expected to begin in February 2014.<ref name=\"AA TR shoot Feb\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Allu-Arjun-Trivikram-film-to-start-soon/articleshow/26960910.cms|title=Allu Arjun, Trivikram film to start soon|work=The Times of India|date=6 December 2013|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031164828/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Allu-Arjun-Trivikram-film-to-start-soon/articleshow/26960910.cms|archivedate=31 October 2014}}</ref> Rumors that the film was shelved were denied by a film-unit source, who said that Srinivas' screenplay was nearly complete.<ref name=\"Trivikram ready\">{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140328/entertainment-tollywood/article/trivikram-ready-his-next-film|title=Trivikram is ready for his next film|work=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|date=28 March 2014|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031164914/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140328/entertainment-tollywood/article/trivikram-ready-his-next-film|archivedate=31 October 2014}}</ref> [[Devi Sri Prasad]] was chosen to compose the score and [[Prawin Pudi]] was signed as the film editor, marking Pudi's fifth collaboration with Srinivas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/Devi-Sri-Prasad-music-for-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/33141251.cms|title=Devi Sri Prasad music for Allu Arjun's next|last=Pasupulate|first=Karthik|work=The Times of India|date=2 April 2014|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031163909/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/Devi-Sri-Prasad-music-for-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/33141251.cms|archivedate=31 October 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"prawin\">{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150303/entertainment-tollywood/article/rise-prawin-pudi|title=The rise of Prawin Pudi|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=3 March 2015|accessdate=3 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150303015733/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150303/entertainment-tollywood/article/rise-prawin-pudi|archivedate=3 March 2015}}</ref>{{efn|Prawin Pudi and Trivikram Srinivas collaborated for four films in the past : ''[[Jalsa]]'' (2008), ''[[Khaleja]]'' (2010), ''[[Julai]]'' (2012) and ''[[Attarintiki Daredi]]'' (2013).<ref name=\"prawin\" />}}\n\nThe film was officially launched at [[Ramanaidu Studios]] in Hyderabad on 10 April 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Allu-Arjun-Trivikrams-film-to-be-launched-on-April-10/articleshow/33406705.cms |title=Allu Arjun, Trivikram's film to be launched on April 10 |work=The Times of India |date=7 April 2014 |access-date=8 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408061308/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Allu-Arjun-Trivikrams-film-to-be-launched-on-April-10/articleshow/33406705.cms |archive-date= 8 April 2014 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref name=\"film launch hyd\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/news/today/samanthawithalluarjun-trivikramfilm.html|title=Samantha in Allu Arjun&nbsp;\u2013 Trivikram film, movie launch at 11:06&nbsp;am on 10 April|publisher=[[Idlebrain.com]]|date=7 April 2014|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408064106/http://idlebrain.com/news/today/samanthawithalluarjun-trivikramfilm.html|archivedate=8 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjun-Trivikram-Srinivas-movie-launched-telugu-news-106006|title=Allu Arjun&nbsp;\u2013 Trivikram Srinivas movie launched|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=10 April 2014|accessdate=10 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006162242/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjun-Trivikram-Srinivas-movie-launched-telugu-news-106006|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> In June, the film's title was rumoured to be ''Kavacham''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News-Interviews/Allu-Arjuns-new-movie-is-Kavacham/articleshow/36935243.cms|title=Allu Arjun's new movie is Kavacham?|work=The Times of India|date=21 June 2014|accessdate=21 June 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101021251/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News-Interviews/Allu-Arjuns-new-movie-is-Kavacham/articleshow/36935243.cms|archivedate=1 November 2014}}</ref> After considerable discussion, the producers reportedly tentatively planned to name the film ''Trishulam'' (also the title of a [[Trishulam|1982 Telugu film]] starring [[Krishnam Raju]] and [[Sridevi]]). Agreements between the principals of both films were reportedly signed in early November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141102/entertainment-tollywood/article/it-another-trisulam|title=Is it another Trisulam|last=King|first=Vincent|publisher=Deecan Chronicle|date=2 November 2014|accessdate=2 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141102170341/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141102/entertainment-tollywood/article/it-another-trisulam|archivedate=2 November 2014}}</ref> Radhakrishna denied the reports, saying that the film's title would be announced in early December 2014 with its preview.<ref name=\"Sify\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/allu-arjun-s-big-plan-for-valentine-s-day-news-telugu-ol0plLedcgdea.html|title=Allu Arjun's big plan for Valentine's Day|publisher=[[Sify]]|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=27 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141127075350/http://www.sify.com/movies/allu-arjun-s-big-plan-for-valentine-s-day-news-telugu-ol0plLedcgdea.html|archivedate=27 November 2014}}</ref> Trivikram reportedly considered the title ''Hushaaru'' in mid-January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150122/entertainment-tollywood/article/husharu-title|title=Husharu, the title?|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=22 January 2015|accessdate=22 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150122172328/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150122/entertainment-tollywood/article/husharu-title|archivedate=22 January 2015}}</ref> Another title under consideration was ''Jaadugar'', earlier used for a [[Jaadugar|1989 Hindi film]] starring [[Amitabh Bachchan]] and [[Jaya Prada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Amitabh-Bachchans-Title-For-Allu-Arjun-telugu-news-123463|title=Amitabh Bachchan's title for Allu Arjun|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=19 January 2015|accessdate=19 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150119143639/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Amitabh-Bachchans-Title-For-Allu-Arjun-telugu-news-123463|archivedate=19 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe producers reportedly dropped the first two titles after poor feedback, and ''Jaadugar'' was expected to be chosen;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjun-says-no-lip-locks-upcoming-film-likely-be-titled-jaadugar-620985|title=Allu Arjun Says No to Lip-Locks; Upcoming Film Likely to be Titled 'Jaadugar'|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=20 January 2015|accessdate=21 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150121072349/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjun-says-no-lip-locks-upcoming-film-likely-be-titled-jaadugar-620985|archivedate=21 January 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Krishnamurthy'' was also considered.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-is-S/O-Krishnamurthy/articleshow/45987118.cms|title=Allu Arjun's film is S/O Krishnamurthy?|work=The Times of India|date=23 January 2015|accessdate=23 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150123084707/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-is-S/O-Krishnamurthy/articleshow/45987118.cms|archivedate=23 January 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy'' (read as ''Son of Satyamurthy'') was confirmed as the film's title on 6 March 2015 in a press release from the producers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Sathyamurthy-Pre-first-Look-On-The-Eve-Of-Holi-telugu-news-127146|title='Son of Sathyamurthy' Pre-First Look on the Eve of Holi|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=5 March 2015|accessdate=6 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306015439/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Sathyamurthy-Pre-first-Look-On-The-Eve-Of-Holi-telugu-news-127146|archivedate=6 March 2015}}</ref> The film was initially planned for simultaneous release in Telugu, Tamil and Malayalam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/allu-arjuntrivikrams-movie-in-three-languages-telugu-news-112511|title=Allu Arjun-Trivikram's movie in three languages|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=22 August 2014|accessdate=26 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006233202/http://www.indiaglitz.com/allu-arjuntrivikrams-movie-in-three-languages-telugu-news-112511|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140825/entertainment-tollywood/article/trilingual-film-allu-arjun|title=Trilingual film for Allu Arjun|author=King, Vincent|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=25 August 2014|accessdate=26 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006072223/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140825/entertainment-tollywood/article/trilingual-film-allu-arjun|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> A dubbed Kannada version, along with Tamil and Malayalam, later was planned because of Upendra and Allu Arjun's popularity in Karnataka.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/allu-arjun-wants-to-increase-his-market-there-telugu-news-117646|title=Allu Arjun wants to increase his market there|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=1 November 2014|accessdate=2 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141102150008/http://www.indiaglitz.com/allu-arjun-wants-to-increase-his-market-there-telugu-news-117646|archivedate=2 November 2014}}</ref>\n\nAlthough the dubbed Malayalam version was also entitled ''S/O Satyamurthy'', the dubbed Tamil and Kannada versions were scrapped for fiscal reasons and it was released in Tamil Nadu and Karnataka with English subtitles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/S/O-Satyamurthy-set-for-grand-release/articleshow/46828272.cms |title=S/O Satyamurthy set for grand release |last=Kamal |first=S. S. |work=[[Bangalore Mirror]] |date=6 April 2015 |access-date=7 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407050917/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/S/O-Satyamurthy-set-for-grand-release/articleshow/46828272.cms |archive-date= 7 April 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Arjun began [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbing]] his role in early January,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-dubs-for-Trivikrams-film/articleshow/45741778.cms|title=Allu Arjun dubs for Trivikram's film|work=The Times of India|date=3 January 2015|accessdate=3 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103130406/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-dubs-for-Trivikrams-film/articleshow/45741778.cms|archivedate=3 January 2015}}</ref> and [[post-production]] was scheduled to resume in late February.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Prince-wants-the-crown-back/articleshow/46014299.cms |title=Prince wants the crown back |last=Kamal |first=S. S. |work=Bangalore Mirror |date=25 January 2015 |access-date=26 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150126092008/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Prince-wants-the-crown-back/articleshow/46014299.cms |archive-date=26 January 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> The actor resumed dubbing on 7 March, after returning from [[Spain]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjun-Busy-With-son-Of-Satyamurthy-Dubbing-telugu-news-127265|title=Allu Arjun busy with 'Son of Satyamurthy' dubbing|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=7 March 2015|accessdate=7 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150307092148/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjun-Busy-With-son-Of-Satyamurthy-Dubbing-telugu-news-127265|archivedate=7 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\n{{multiple image\n<!-- Essential parameters -->\n| align     = right\n| direction = horizontal\n| footer    =[[Samantha Akkineni]] (''left''), [[Adah Sharma]] (''middle'') and [[Nithya Menen]] (''right'') were signed for the female lead roles.\n| width     = \n<!-- Image 1 -->\n| image1    = Samantha Ruth Prabhu at 60th South Filmfare Awards 2013.jpg\n| width1    = 118\n| alt1      = Smiling young woman at the Filmfare Awards\n| caption1  =\n\n<!-- Image 2 -->\n| image2    = Adah Sharma at Riyaz & Reshma Gangji's bridal show.jpg\n| width2    = 148\n| alt2      = Smiling young woman in a pink-and-yellow sash\n| caption2  =\n\n<!-- Image 3 -->\n| image3    = Nithya Menen Thalsamayam 2011.jpg\n| width3    = 150\n| alt3      = Pensive-looking young woman with plain earrings\n| caption3  =\n}}\n[[Allu Arjun]] was part of the project since its initial stages in early November 2013.<ref name=\"Arjun Trivikram film\" /> [[Samantha Akkineni|Samantha Ruth Prabhu]] was cast as one of the film's heroines, her first collaboration with Arjun.<ref name=\"Samantha\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Allu-Arjun-to-romance-Samantha/articleshow/28851074.cms|title=Allu Arjun to romance Samantha?|work=The Times of India|date=15 January 2014|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116045936/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Allu-Arjun-to-romance-Samantha/articleshow/28851074.cms|archivedate=16 January 2014}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy'' has three female leads; although Arjun initially denied this,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News-Interviews/Three-heroines-for-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/33138774.cms|title=Three heroines for Allu Arjun?|work=The Times of India|date=2 April 2014|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140403061221/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Three-heroines-for-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/33138774.cms|archivedate=3 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/105902.html|title=Allu Arjun&nbsp;\u2013 Trivikram movie launch on 10th|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=8 April 2014|accessdate=8 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141009004540/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/article/105902.html|archivedate=9 October 2014}}</ref> Srinivas confirmed that the film has three heroines.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Kriti-Sanon-in-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/35517991.cms|title=Kriti Sanon in Allu Arjun's next?|work=The Times of India|date=23 May 2014|accessdate=24 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101021837/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Kriti-Sanon-in-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/35517991.cms|archivedate=1 November 2014}}</ref> [[Kriti Sanon]] was rumoured to be one of the three female leads, although she later denied it.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Kriti-Sanon-clueless-about-Allu-Arjuns-film/articleshow/34536994.cms|title=Kriti Sanon clueless about Allu Arjun's film|last=Kumar|first=Hemanth|work=The Times of India|date=2 May 2014|accessdate=3 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504051357/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Kriti-Sanon-clueless-about-Allu-Arjuns-film/articleshow/34536994.cms|archivedate=4 May 2014}}</ref> [[Adah Sharma]] and [[Pranitha Subhash]] were cast as the other two female leads,<ref name=\"Adah Sharma\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/adah-sharma-to-romance-allu-arjun-in-trivikrams-film/articleshow/41882931.cms|title=Adah Sharma to romance Allu Arjun in Trivikram's film|author=Kumar, Hemanth|work=The Times of India|date=6 September 2014|accessdate=7 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140906225136/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Adah-Sharma-to-romance-Allu-Arjun-in-Trivikrams-film/articleshow/41882931.cms|archivedate=6 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Pranitha\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Telugu/Movies/News/Pranitha-to-now-romance-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/43628626.cms|title=Pranitha to now romance Allu Arjun|last=Pasupulate|first=Karthik|work=The Times of India|date=27 September 2014|accessdate=28 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140928093838/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Pranitha-to-now-romance-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/43628626.cms|archivedate=28 September 2014}}</ref> after [[Regina Cassandra]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140818/entertainment-tollywood/article/regina-may-romance-allu-arjun|title=Regina may romance Allu Arjun|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|publisher=Deecan Chronicle|date=19 August 2014|accessdate=19 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819233811/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140818/entertainment-tollywood/article/regina-may-romance-allu-arjun|archivedate=19 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140825/entertainment-tollywood/article/samantha-ruth-and-pranitha-subhash-together-third-time|title=Samantha Ruth and Pranitha Subhash together for third time?|publisher=Deecan Chronicle|date=25 August 2014|accessdate=26 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140826160757/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140825/entertainment-tollywood/article/samantha-ruth-and-pranitha-subhash-together-third-time|archivedate=26 August 2014}}</ref> [[Nayantara]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-to-release-in-three-languages/articleshow/40777168.cms|title=Allu Arjun's film to release in three languages?|work=The Times of India|date=23 August 2014|accessdate=23 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101022924/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-to-release-in-three-languages/articleshow/40777168.cms|archivedate=1 November 2014}}</ref> and [[Rashi Khanna (actress)|Rashi Khanna]] were considered for Subhash's role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Who-is-Allu-Arjuns-third-heroine/articleshow/42081647.cms|title=Who is Allu Arjun's third heroine?|work=The Times of India|date=8 September 2014|accessdate=17 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140910034851/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Who-is-Allu-Arjuns-third-heroine/articleshow/42081647.cms|archivedate=10 September 2014}}</ref> Subhash was later replaced by [[Nithya Menen]] because of conceptual differences with Srinivas,<ref name=\"Nithya\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Nithya-Menon-keen-to-work-with-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/44934472.cms|title=Nithya Menon keen to work with Allu Arjun|work=The Times of India|date=25 October 2014|accessdate=26 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141026094038/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Nithya-Menon-keen-to-work-with-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/44934472.cms|archivedate=26 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Trivikram-loses-cool-Pranitha-walks-out/articleshow/44978890.cms|title=Trivikram loses cool; Pranitha walks out|last=A.S.|first=Sasidhar|work=The Times of India|date=29 October 2014|accessdate=30 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101023417/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Trivikram-loses-cool-Pranitha-walks-out/articleshow/44978890.cms|archivedate=1 November 2014}}</ref> although she later said that she never signed for the film and reports that she had walked out were rumours.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/I-have-never-shot-for-Trivikrams-film-says-Pranitha/articleshow/45049668.cms |title=I have never shot for Trivikram's film, says Pranitha |work=The Times of India |date=5 November 2014 |access-date=6 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141106023637/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/I-have-never-shot-for-Trivikrams-film-says-Pranitha/articleshow/45049668.cms |archive-date= 6 November 2014 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\nRao Ramesh was cast in a crucial role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140519/entertainment-tollywood/article/busy-time-rao-ramesh|title=A busy time for Rao Ramesh|publisher=Deecan Chronicle|date=19 May 2014|accessdate=19 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140519034434/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140519/entertainment-tollywood/article/busy-time-rao-ramesh|archivedate=19 May 2014}}</ref> Although [[Arjun Sarja]] was reported to be the film's antagonist in mid-August 2014,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Arjun-to-play-villain-opposite-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/40200588.cms |title=Arjun to play villain opposite Allu Arjun? |work=The Times of India |date=13 August 2014 |access-date=13 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140814235922/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Arjun-to-play-villain-opposite-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/40200588.cms |archive-date=14 August 2014 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140813/entertainment-tollywood/article/it%E2%80%99s-arjun-vs-arjun|title=It's Arjun vs Arjun|publisher=Deecan Chronicle|date=13 August 2014|accessdate=14 August 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140815002222/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140813/entertainment-tollywood/article/it%E2%80%99s-arjun-vs-arjun|archivedate=15 August 2014}}</ref> Sarja later confirmed that he was not part of the project due to other commitments.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Arjun-isnt-playing-villain-in-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/43071500.cms|title=Arjun isn't playing villain in Allu Arjun's next|agency=Indo-Asian News Service|work=The Times of India|date=21 September 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101024010/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Arjun-isnt-playing-villain-in-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/43071500.cms|archivedate=1 November 2014}}</ref> [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] confirmed in mid-September 2014 that she had an important role in the film.<ref name=\"Sneha\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Sneha-Confirms-Signing-Allu-Arjun---Trivikrams-Film-telugu-news-114371|title=Sneha confirms signing Allu Arjun&nbsp;\u2013 Trivikram's film|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=17 September 2014|accessdate=17 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006205558/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Sneha-Confirms-Signing-Allu-Arjun---Trivikrams-Film-telugu-news-114371|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]] and [[Rajendra Prasad (actor)|Rajendra Prasad]] were said to play important roles in the film,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2014/sneha-roped-in-for-allu-arjun-next-film-159765.html|title=Sneha Turns Allu Arjun's Sister-In-Law|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=19 September 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924111458/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2014/sneha-roped-in-for-allu-arjun-next-film-159765.html|archivedate=24 September 2014}}</ref> and Upendra later confirmed his inclusion.<ref name=\"Upendra\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/Upendra-Graces-Trivikrams-Telugu-Project/2014/09/22/article2442723.ece|title=Upendra Graces Trivikram's Telugu Project|last=A.|first=Sharadhaa|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=22 September 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006212525/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/Upendra-Graces-Trivikrams-Telugu-Project/2014/09/22/article2442723.ece|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> [[Vennela Kishore]] and [[Surekha Vani]] were selected to play supporting roles.<ref name=\"shooting start\" /> [[Kota Srinivasa Rao]] was cast at the end of November 2014,<ref name=\"Kota Srinivasa Rao\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-next-is-a-family-drama/articleshow/45270040.cms|title=Allu Arjun's next is a family drama|work=The Times of India|date=25 November 2014|accessdate=26 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141126091156/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-next-is-a-family-drama/articleshow/45270040.cms|archivedate=26 November 2014}}</ref> and [[Mamilla Shailaja Priya]] was cast in a supporting role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/Vanisri-is-my-inspiration-Priya/articleshow/45513316.cms|title=Vanisri is my inspiration: Priya|work=The Times of India|date=14 December 2014|accessdate=17 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141217050306/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/telugu/Vanisri-is-my-inspiration-Priya/articleshow/45513316.cms|archivedate=17 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nSupporting character actor [[M. S. Narayana]] died after most of his portions in the film was completed. Although Srinivas decided not to delete any of his scenes, he faced a dilemma: whether to use a double or make do with what they had.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150201/entertainment-tollywood/article/dub-or-not-dub|title=To dub or not to dub|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=1 February 2015|accessdate=2 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202022716/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150201/entertainment-tollywood/article/dub-or-not-dub|archivedate=2 February 2015}}</ref> After evaluating many mimics, Srinivas and Arjun reportedly decided to use [[Siva Reddy]] to flesh out Narayana's role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/alluarjun-trivikrams-film-in-trouble-172745.html|title=Dubbing Problems For Allu Arjun-Trivikram's Film|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=4 February 2015|accessdate=4 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150204061232/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/alluarjun-trivikrams-film-in-trouble-172745.html|archivedate=4 February 2015}}</ref> [[Sampath Raj]] was cast in early February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Sampath-Raj-is-on-a-roll/articleshow/46087725.cms |title=Sampath Raj is on a roll |last=Kumar |first=Hemanth |work=The Times of India |date=3 February 2015 |access-date=3 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203024702/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Sampath-Raj-is-on-a-roll/articleshow/46087725.cms |archive-date= 3 February 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\n=== Characters ===\n{{multiple image\n<!-- Essential parameters -->\n| align     = right\n| direction = horizontal\n| footer    = The way actor [[Kamal Haasan]] (''left'') and cricketer [[Wasim Akram]] (''middle'') handled [[diabetes mellitus|diabetes]] in real life inspired Srinivas to make Samantha's character diabetic in the film.\n| width     = \n<!-- Image 1 -->\n| image1    = Kamal Haasan at Promotions of 'Vishwaroop' with Videocon (03).jpg\n| width1    = 137\n| alt1      = Man in a brown jacket, speaking into a microphone\n| caption1  =\n\n<!-- Image 2 -->\n| image2    = Wasim Akram.jpg\n| width2    = 150\n| alt2      = Smiling man with rectangular glasses\n| caption2  =\n}}\n''S/O Satyamurthy'' was considered an image makeover for Arjun.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Allu-Arjun-set-for-image-makeover/articleshow/35017688.cms|title=Allu Arjun set for image makeover|work=The Times of India|date=12 May 2014|accessdate=24 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512234907/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Allu-Arjun-set-for-image-makeover/articleshow/35017688.cms|archivedate=12 May 2014}}</ref> Although his character's name (Viraj Anand) was intended for another role in the film, he requested Srinivas to use the name for the titular character's son.<ref name=\"BM Sam\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/When-Samantha-puked-listening-to-S/O-Sathyamurthy-storyline/articleshow/46867324.cms |title=When Samantha puked listening to S/O Sathyamurthy storyline |last=Vivan |first=Sridhar |work=Bangalore Mirror |date=9 April 2015 |access-date=13 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413040901/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/When-Samantha-puked-listening-to-S/O-Sathyamurthy-storyline/articleshow/46867324.cms |archive-date=13 April 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Arjun learned flips, somersaults and other gymnastic skills to perform his stunts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Bunnylearns-flips-and-somersaults/articleshow/34819544.cms|title=Bunny learns flips and somersaults|work=The Times of India|date=8 May 2014|accessdate=24 May 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140509093952/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news-interviews/Bunnylearns-flips-and-somersaults/articleshow/34819544.cms|archivedate=9 May 2014}}</ref> He, his brother [[Allu Sirish]] and stylist Ashwin bought his costumes in [[Dubai]], and he lost {{convert|10|kg|lb}} with a special diet and gym workouts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140909/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun%E2%80%99s-shopping-spree|title=Allu Arjun's on a shopping spree|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=9 September 2014|accessdate=17 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140930162440/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140909/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun%E2%80%99s-shopping-spree|archivedate=30 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-sheds-10-kgs-for-Trivikrams-film/articleshow/42464148.cms|title=Allu Arjun sheds 10 kgs [sic] for Trivikram's film|work=The Times of India|date=14 September 2014|accessdate=17 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101050925/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-sheds-10-kgs-for-Trivikrams-film/articleshow/42464148.cms|archivedate=1 November 2014}}</ref> Sneha was rumoured to play Arjun's sister-in-law.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Sneha-to-play-Allu-Arjuns-Vadina/articleshow/42807985.cms|title=Sneha to play Allu Arjun's Vadina?|last=Pasupulate|first=Karthik|work=The Times of India|date=18 September 2014|accessdate=22 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140918145545/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Sneha-to-play-Allu-Arjuns-Vadina/articleshow/42807985.cms|archivedate=18 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nUpendra was confirmed in a role paralleling Arjun's in the film,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Upendra-Not-Playing-Villain-In-Allu-Arjuns-Film-telugu-news-115480|title=Upendra not playing villain in Allu Arjun's film|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=1 October 2014|accessdate=2 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006215839/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Upendra-Not-Playing-Villain-In-Allu-Arjuns-Film-telugu-news-115480|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> and Sharma reportedly wore a traditional attire to suit her role.<ref name=\"Adah Sharma\" /> Sharma's character was revealed to be unstable, while Arjun's character was nuanced;<ref name=\"Pranitha\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/adah-sharma-excited-about-her-role-in-allu-arjuns-film-telugu-news-115977|title=Adah Sharma excited about her role in Allu Arjun's film|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=9 October 2014|accessdate=12 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018221116/http://www.indiaglitz.com/adah-sharma-excited-about-her-role-in-allu-arjuns-film-telugu-news-115977|archivedate=18 October 2014}}</ref> he was confirmed as an event manager in late October 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141026/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun-sheds-weight|title=Allu Arjun sheds weight|last=King|first=Vincent|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=27 October 2014|accessdate=27 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141027080332/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141026/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun-sheds-weight|archivedate=27 October 2014}}</ref> Nithya Menen would reportedly play a negative role as Upendra's sister in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Nitya-Menons-Negative-Role-In-Allu-Arjuns-Film--telugu-news-117731|title=Nitya Menon's negative role in Allu Arjun's film ?|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=2 November 2014|accessdate=2 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141102063536/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Nitya-Menons-Negative-Role-In-Allu-Arjuns-Film--telugu-news-117731|archivedate=2 November 2014}}</ref> About Arjun's look, stylist Ashwin said it would reflect the current fashion trends in [[Milan]], [[Paris]] and [[London]] (incorporating pieces from the autumn-winter 2014 and spring-summer 2015 collections).<ref name=\"Ashwin\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-to-sport-a-Brit-Look/articleshow/45071291.cms |title=Allu Arjun to sport a Brit Look |last=A.S. |first=Sasidhar |work=The Times of India |date=7 November 2014 |access-date=8 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108152003/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-to-sport-a-Brit-Look/articleshow/45071291.cms |archive-date= 8 November 2014 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\nAshwin said that they shopped in Dubai because Arjun wanted to select his costumes, and the European capitals at that time had only winter collections. Arjun would have several hairstyles in the film.<ref name=\"Ashwin\" /> Upendra's role was reported to be a Tamil living in [[Madurai]],<ref name=\"Madurai\">{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141129/entertainment-tollywood/article/bunny%E2%80%99s-set-gets-special-house|title=Bunny's set gets a special house|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=29 November 2014|accessdate=30 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141130012231/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141129/entertainment-tollywood/article/bunny%E2%80%99s-set-gets-special-house|archivedate=30 November 2014}}</ref> and he was confirmed as the landlord at the end of January 2015.<ref name=\"Madurai set\">{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150130/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun-action|title=Allu Arjun in action|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=30 January 2015|accessdate=30 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150130180523/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150130/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun-action|archivedate=30 January 2015}}</ref> He was not included in the film's promotional activities since Srinivas did not want to reveal what he considered a crucial character.<ref name=\"BM Sam\" /> The way [[Kamal Haasan]] and [[Wasim Akram]] handled [[diabetes mellitus|diabetes]] in real life inspired Srinivas to make Samantha's character diabetic in the film.<ref name=\"films TV\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/i-am-not-doing-films-for-tv-trivikram-interview-telugu-news-130156|title=I am not doing films for TV : Trivikram [Interview]|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=11 April 2015|accessdate=13 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413042711/http://www.indiaglitz.com/i-am-not-doing-films-for-tv-trivikram-interview-telugu-news-130156|archivedate=13 April 2015}}</ref> Samantha was comfortable in the role, since she too had been diagnosed with the disease two years earlier.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/even-i-suffered-with-diabetes-samantha-telugu-news-130277.html|title=Even I suffered with diabetes : Samantha|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=13 April 2015|accessdate=13 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413152114/http://www.indiaglitz.com/even-i-suffered-with-diabetes-samantha-telugu-news-130277.html|archivedate=13 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nPrakash Raj had a limited role, since Srinivas wanted to tell the story of a father by not showing him but instead showing his son's love and his influence on his life.<ref name=\"films TV\" /> The death of Sampath Raj was an accident because Srinivas did not believe in killing his antagonists directly, but to have them die as a result of their mistakes. Srinivas added that his death was planned so the film would have a good ending.<ref name=\"films TV\" />\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[File:Ramoji Film City.jpg|thumb|right|200px|alt=Ornate outdoor sign on pillars, reading \"Ramoji Film City\"|[[Ramoji Film City]] where Arjun's fight scenes were filmed under the supervision of Peter Hein]]\nIn early December 2013 it was announced that filming would begin the following February, after Arjun finished ''[[Race Gurram]]''.<ref name=\"AA TR shoot Feb\" /> At the end of March 2014, shooting was postponed to the following month and it was later announced that filming would start during the third week of April.<ref name=\"Trivikram ready\" /><ref name=\"film launch hyd\" /> In June, filming was again postponed to the following month, when Arjun was scheduled to finish ''[[Rudramadevi (film)|Rudramadevi]]'';<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/allu-arjun-trivikram-srinivas-movie-from-july-telugu-news-109231|title=Allu Arjun&nbsp;\u2013 Trivikram Srinivas movie from July|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=20 June 2014|accessdate=20 June 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006135025/http://www.indiaglitz.com/allu-arjun-trivikram-srinivas-movie-from-july-telugu-news-109231|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> he completed the film on 30 July.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140730/entertainment-tollywood/article/bunny-completes-his-part-rudhramadevi|title=Allu Arjun completes his part in Rudhramadevi|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=30 July 2014|accessdate=30 July 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140731020646/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140730/entertainment-tollywood/article/bunny-completes-his-part-rudhramadevi|archivedate=31 July 2014}}</ref>\n\nPrincipal photography began on 22 September at a Hyderabad-based shopping mall.<ref name=\"shooting start\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-new-film-rolls-out/articleshow/43241498.cms|title=Allu Arjun's new film rolls out|work=The Times of India|date=23 September 2014|accessdate=23 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031164522/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-new-film-rolls-out/articleshow/43241498.cms|archivedate=31 October 2014}}</ref> Samantha arrived at the set on 1 October 2014, after completing ''[[Kaththi]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140923/entertainment-tollywood/article/samantha%E2%80%99s-busy-schedule|title=Samantha's busy schedule|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=23 September 2014|accessdate=23 September 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006140228/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140923/entertainment-tollywood/article/samantha%E2%80%99s-busy-schedule|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> and Sharma joined the production unit five days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Adah-Sharma-joins-the-sets-of-Trivikram-Allu-Arjuns-film/articleshow/44606282.cms|title=Adah Sharma joins the sets of Trivikram-Allu Arjun's film|last=Kumar|first=Hemanth|work=The Times of India|date=7 October 2014|accessdate=8 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141009194447/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Adah-Sharma-joins-the-sets-of-Trivikram-Allu-Arjuns-film/articleshow/44606282.cms|archivedate=9 October 2014}}</ref> A week-long shooting schedule planned at [[Ooty]] for scenes with Arjun, Upendra, Samantha and Sneha was disrupted because of unrest in Tamil Nadu due to [[Disproportionate Asset case against Jayalalithaa|Jayalalithaa's conviction]], and the scenes were filmed near [[Shamshabad]] in Hyderabad.<ref name=\"Ooty\">{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140930/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun%E2%80%99s-film-shoot-now-shifts-ooty|title=Allu Arjun's film shoot now shifts to Ooty|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=30 September 2014|accessdate=2 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141002164509/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/140930/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun%E2%80%99s-film-shoot-now-shifts-ooty|archivedate=2 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/telugu/Upendra-Not-Playing-Villain-in-Allu-Arjuns-Film/2014/10/03/article2460225.ece|title=Upendra Not Playing Villain in Allu Arjun's Film|work=The New Indian Express|date=3 October 2014|accessdate=5 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006151900/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/telugu/Upendra-Not-Playing-Villain-in-Allu-Arjuns-Film/2014/10/03/article2460225.ece|archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref> Art director Ravinder built a large outdoor set for the destination-wedding scene, with flowers flown in from [[Bangkok]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141009/entertainment-tollywood/article/ooty-%E2%80%98made%E2%80%99-city|title=Ooty, 'made' in city!|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=10 October 2014|accessdate=10 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141011120517/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141009/entertainment-tollywood/article/ooty-%E2%80%98made%E2%80%99-city|archivedate=11 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nA fight scene with Arjun was shot at [[Ramoji Film City]] under the supervision of [[Peter Hein]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-gets-into-an-action-mode-for-Trivikrams-film/articleshow/44970214.cms|title=Allu Arjun gets into an action mode for Trivikram's film|work=The Times of India|date=29 October 2014|accessdate=29 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030173847/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-gets-into-an-action-mode-for-Trivikrams-film/articleshow/44970214.cms|archivedate=30 October 2014}}</ref> A residential set was built at a cost of {{INR}}30&nbsp;million by Ravinder in [[Kokapet]], where scenes with Brahmanandam and Srinivasa Rao were filmed in late November 2014.<ref name=\"Kota Srinivasa Rao\" /><ref name=\"climax\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/special-set-erected-for-bunny-trivikram-film.html|title=Special set erected for Bunny, Trivikram film|publisher=123telugu.com|date=22 November 2014|accessdate=22 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141122044749/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/special-set-erected-for-bunny-trivikram-film.html|archivedate=22 November 2014}}</ref> The Kokapet set, of a Tamil house in Madurai, required three truckloads of trees from a farmhouse in [[Kadiam]] (near [[Rajahmundry]]) and materials from [[Delhi]] and [[Chennai]].<ref name=\"Madurai\" /> For the set, Srinivas and Ravinder travelled to a small city near Madurai and researched houses. By then, filming was nearly complete and the producers confirmed that the dialogue would be finished by the end of November and the songs shot the following month.<ref name=\"Sify\" />\n\nFilming was suspended because of a strike by Film Federation employees and the Memu Saitham [[Cyclone Hudhud]] relief fundraiser at Visakhapatnam.<ref name=\"Madurai\" /> The strike was called off, and shooting resumed on 6 December.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Shootings-To-Resume-From-Tomorrow-telugu-news-120281|title=Shootings to resume from tomorrow|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=5 December 2014|accessdate=6 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141206030730/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Shootings-To-Resume-From-Tomorrow-telugu-news-120281|archivedate=6 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/AP-Film-workers-calls-off-strike/articleshow/45396153.cms |title=AP Film workers calls off strike |work=The Times of India |date=6 December 2014 |access-date=7 December 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141207053843/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/AP-Film-workers-calls-off-strike/articleshow/45396153.cms |archive-date= 7 December 2014 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> When Upendra finished his first shooting schedule for the film, he returned to the set of ''[[Upendra 2|Uppi 2]]'' on 10 December.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2014/upendra-shoots-for-all-arjun-starrer-trishoolam-167194.html|title=Upendra Shoots For Allu Arjun Starrer Trishoolam|last=Bhat|first=Bharath|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=10 December 2014|accessdate=10 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141210071213/http://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/news/2014/upendra-shoots-for-all-arjun-starrer-trishoolam-167194.html|archivedate=10 December 2014}}</ref> In addition to Arjun's action sequences,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-progressing-in-RFC/articleshow/45478490.cms |title=Allu Arjun's film progressing in RFC |work=The Times of India |date=11 December 2014 |access-date=11 December 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141211150355/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-progressing-in-RFC/articleshow/45478490.cms |archive-date=11 December 2014 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Some more scenes were filmed at Ramoji Film City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/allu-arjun-trivikram-film-heads-to-rfc.html|title=Allu Arjun, Trivikram film heads to RFC|publisher=123telugu.com|date=17 December 2014|accessdate=17 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141217022319/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/allu-arjun-trivikram-film-heads-to-rfc.html|archivedate=17 December 2014}}</ref> Comedy sequences featuring Arjun and Samantha were shot at Hyderabad in late December.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/bunny-samantha-shooting-for-comic-scenes.html|title=Bunny-Samantha shooting for comic scenes|publisher=123telugu.com|date=28 December 2014|accessdate=29 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141229030319/http://www.123telugu.com/mnews/bunny-samantha-shooting-for-comic-scenes.html|archivedate=29 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nArjun spent the New Year with his wife and son in [[South Africa]], and was scheduled to return to the set during the second week of January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141227/entertainment-tollywood/article/new-year-safari-allu-arjun|title=Allu Arjun to ring in New Year at South Africa|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=28 December 2014|accessdate=29 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141229030631/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/141227/entertainment-tollywood/article/new-year-safari-allu-arjun|archivedate=29 December 2014}}</ref> The final shooting schedule began on 6 January in Hyderabad.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150106/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun-back-holiday|title=Allu Arjun back from holiday|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=6 January 2015|accessdate=7 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150107053310/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150106/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun-back-holiday|archivedate=7 January 2015}}</ref> Additional filming of action and romantic scenes began on 20 January.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150118/entertainment-tollywood/article/almost-complete-no-name|title=Almost complete, but no name|last=King|first=Vincent|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=18 January 2015|accessdate=19 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150119034325/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150118/entertainment-tollywood/article/almost-complete-no-name|archivedate=19 January 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy''{{'s}} climactic scenes were filmed on the Kokapet house set in late January.<ref name=\"Madurai set\" /><ref name=\"climax\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjuns-son-Of--Satya-Murthy-Movie-Details-telugu-news-124440|title=Allu Arjun's 'Son of Satya Murthy' movie details|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=31 January 2015|accessdate=31 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150131115142/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjuns-son-Of--Satya-Murthy-Movie-Details-telugu-news-124440|archivedate=31 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nShooting was scheduled to continue there until the first week of February, when the dialogue would be completed.<ref name=\"climax\" /> A fight scene with Arjun and hundreds of other fighters was filmed in early February,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-fighting-for-Son-of-Satyamurthy/articleshow/46183063.cms |title=Allu Arjun fighting for Son of Satyamurthy |work=The Times of India |date=11 February 2015 |access-date=11 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150211025532/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjun-fighting-for-Son-of-Satyamurthy/articleshow/46183063.cms |archive-date=11 February 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> and Upendra returned to the Hyderabad set for his scenes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Sampoornesh-Babu-is-a-big-fan-of-Upendra/articleshow/46200465.cms |title=Sampoornesh Babu is a big fan of Upendra! |last=Kumar |first=Hemanth |work=The Times of India |date=12 February 2015 |access-date=12 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150212092626/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Sampoornesh-Babu-is-a-big-fan-of-Upendra/articleshow/46200465.cms |archive-date=12 February 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> A song, choreographed by [[Sekhar (choreographer)|Shekhar]] and featuring Arjun, Samantha and Menen, was filmed on the Kokapet house set in late February.<ref name=\"DSP song\">{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150220/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun%E2%80%99s-dancing-days|title=Allu Arjun's dancing days|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=20 February 2015|accessdate=21 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150221092844/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150220/entertainment-tollywood/article/allu-arjun%E2%80%99s-dancing-days|archivedate=21 February 2015}}</ref> The film unit then went to Spain to film three songs<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-progressing-in-Spain/articleshow/46391539.cms |title=Allu Arjun's film progressing in Spain |work=The Times of India |date=27 February 2015 |access-date=27 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150227054851/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-progressing-in-Spain/articleshow/46391539.cms |archive-date=27 February 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> also featuring Arjun, Samantha and Menen, returning on 6 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Satya-Murthy-Audio-Release-Date-Confirmed-Officially-telugu-news-127157|title='Son of Satya Murthy' audio release date confirmed officially|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=6 March 2015|accessdate=6 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306061247/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Satya-Murthy-Audio-Release-Date-Confirmed-Officially-telugu-news-127157|archivedate=6 March 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy''{{'s}} principal photography completed when the last song (choreographed by Jani and featuring Arjun, Samantha and Sharma) was filmed on 11 March 2015 in a specially erected set at [[Annapurna Studios]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Son-Of-Satya-Murthy-Song-Being-Shot-telugu-news-127547|title='Son of Satya Murthy' Song Being Shot|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=11 March 2015|accessdate=12 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150312034400/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Son-Of-Satya-Murthy-Song-Being-Shot-telugu-news-127547|archivedate=12 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Themes and influences ==\nAlthough ''S/O Satyamurthy'' was reportedly about a conflict between two families,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/Top-Sandalwood-stars-do-the-Perfect-balancing-act-with-non-Kannada-films/articleshow/45297901.cms|title=Top Sandalwood stars do the perfect balancing act with non-Kannada films|last=Christopher|first=Kavya|work=The Times of India|date=28 November 2014|accessdate=28 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141128022053/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/Top-Sandalwood-stars-do-the-Perfect-balancing-act-with-non-Kannada-films/articleshow/45297901.cms|archivedate=28 November 2014}}</ref> according to Upendra it revolves around three characters: one who follows his heart, a second who uses his brain and a third who uses his brawn.<ref name=\"Upendra\" /> The characters are a wedding planner (Arjun), a wealthy businessman (Prasad) and a [[Boss (crime)|boss]] (Upendra).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/revealed-s-o-satyamurthy-story-allu-arjuns-role-628277|title=Revealed: 'S/O Satyamurthy' Story and Allu Arjun's Role|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=6 April 2015|accessdate=7 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407053312/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/revealed-s-o-satyamurthy-story-allu-arjuns-role-628277|archivedate=7 April 2015}}</ref> Srinivas told the [[Indo-Asian News Service]] that his film would highlight a father's role in a person's life, because more films dramatise relationships with mothers.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ianslive.in/index.php?param=news/S/O_Satyamurthy_an_ode_to_fathers_Trivikram-472242/ENTERTAINMENT/15 |title='S/O Satyamurthy' an ode to fathers: Trivikram |agency=Indo-Asian News Service |date=8 April 2015 |access-date=8 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150408082212/http://ianslive.in/index.php?param=news%2FS%2FO_Satyamurthy_an_ode_to_fathers_Trivikram-472242%2FENTERTAINMENT%2F15 |archive-date= 8 April 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy'' has urban and rural settings similar to the director's previous film, ''[[Attarintiki Daredi]]'' (2013).<ref name=\"IG Review\" />\n\nThe film refers to situations in the ''[[Ramayana]]'' and the ''[[Mahabharata]]'' in the lives of [[Rama]], [[Sita]], [[Ravana]], [[Yudhishthira]] and [[Karna]] and to the [[dowry system in India|dowry system]].<ref name=\"IANS Review\" /><ref name=\"TOI Review\" /><ref name=\"IBN Review\" /> Sangeetha Devi Dundoo of ''[[The Hindu]]'' wrote in her review that the film \"attempts to break away from staid portrayal of women and notions of machismo in Telugu cinema\". Upendra's character wants his wife to be happy, and hides his dark side from her; Samantha's character is diabetic, and the wall full of [[post-it note]]s in Rajendra Prasad's house illustrate marriages where communication has broken down. Dundoo notes lines of dialogue which \"scoff\" at people who call a girl unlucky if her engagement is broken.<ref name=\"TH Review\" />\n\nFor the scenes between M. S. Narayana and Rao Ramesh, Srinivas was inspired by his mother's maternal uncles in the village of [[Tallapudi|Vegeswarapuram]] in [[West Godavari district]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sakshi.com/news/movies/trivikram-srinivas-exclusive-interview-229525|title=Trivikram Srinivas exclusive interview|work=[[Sakshi (newspaper)|Sakshi]]|date=12 April 2015|accessdate=13 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413025601/http://www.sakshi.com/news/movies/trivikram-srinivas-exclusive-interview-229525|archivedate=13 April 2015}}</ref> In an interview, the director said that the screenplay was based on situations faced by people close to him and how they handled them.<ref name=\"films TV\" />\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = S/O Satyamurthy\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| longtype   = To S/O Satyamurthy\n| artist     = [[Devi Sri Prasad]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 15 March 2015\n| recorded   = 2014\u20132015\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 26:43\n| language   = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| label      = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer   = [[Devi Sri Prasad]]\n| prev_title = [[Alludu Seenu]]\n| prev_year  = 2014\n| next_title = [[Srimanthudu]]\n| next_year  = 2015\n}}\n\n[[Devi Sri Prasad]] composed the soundtrack album and background score for ''S/O Satyamurthy''. Folk singer [[Raghu Dixit]] made his Telugu cinema debut as a playback singer, saying on 4 February 2015 that he had recorded a song for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/Raghu-Dixit-croons-for-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/46120149.cms |title=Raghu Dixit croons for Allu Arjun's next |work=The Times of India |date=4 February 2015 |access-date=4 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150204115641/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/music/Raghu-Dixit-croons-for-Allu-Arjuns-next/articleshow/46120149.cms |archive-date= 4 February 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Dsp-Introduces-Another-Pop-Singer-With-Allu-Arjuns-Film-telugu-news-124738|title=DSP introduces another pop singer with Allu Arjun's film|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=4 February 2015|accessdate=4 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150204121919/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Dsp-Introduces-Another-Pop-Singer-With-Allu-Arjuns-Film-telugu-news-124738|archivedate=4 February 2015}}</ref> The soundtrack was scheduled to be released on 14 March,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Mahesh-Babu-And-Pawan-Kalyan-For-son-Of--Satya-Murthy-Audio--telugu-news-125474|title=Mahesh Babu and Pawan Kalyan for 'Son of Satya Murthy' audio ?|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=13 February 2015|accessdate=13 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150213123400/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Mahesh-Babu-And-Pawan-Kalyan-For-son-Of--Satya-Murthy-Audio--telugu-news-125474|archivedate=13 February 2015}}</ref> with [[Pawan Kalyan]] and [[Mahesh Babu]] the expected guests of honour at the release party.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Pawan-Mahesh-to-promote-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/46229332.cms|title=Pawan, Mahesh to promote Allu Arjun?|work=The Times of India|date=14 February 2015|accessdate=14 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150214030146/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Pawan-Mahesh-to-promote-Allu-Arjun/articleshow/46229332.cms|archivedate=14 February 2015}}</ref> In late February 2015, Prasad wrote and recorded a song.<ref name=\"DSP song\" /> [[Aditya Music]] acquired the soundtrack's marketing rights, and the seven-track list was released on 14 March 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/track-list-allu-arjuns-movie-s-o-sathyamurthy-released-626251|title=Track List of Allu Arjun's Movie 'S/O Sathyamurthy' Released|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=International Business Times India|date=14 March 2015|accessdate=14 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150314132455/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/track-list-allu-arjuns-movie-s-o-sathyamurthy-released-626251|archivedate=14 March 2015}}</ref> The soundtrack was released the following day, on 15 March 2015, at the Hotel Novotel in Hyderabad.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Satya-Murthy-Audio-Launched-telugu-news-127913|title='Son of Satya Murthy' audio launched|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=16 March 2015|accessdate=16 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316070756/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Satya-Murthy-Audio-Launched-telugu-news-127913|archivedate=16 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nIndiaGlitz gave the soundtrack 3.25 out of five stars, calling it \"electrifying\" and \"different offering in part, not totally\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/musicreview/19562.html|title=Son of SatyaMurthy&nbsp;\u2013 Being electrifying, DSP style|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=16 March 2015|accessdate=17 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317162810/http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/musicreview/19562.html|archivedate=17 March 2015}} {{rating|3.5|5|score=3.25/5 stars}}</ref> [[Oneindia]] gave it three out of five stars, selecting \"Seethakalam\", \"Come to the Party\" and \"Super Machi\" as the film's best songs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-music-review-super-machi-176919.html|title=MUSIC REVIEW: Son Of Satyamurthy&nbsp;\u2014 Super Machi|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=16 March 2015|accessdate=17 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317162912/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-music-review-super-machi-176919.html|archivedate=17 March 2015}} {{rating|3|5}}</ref> Behindwoods gave the soundtrack 2.75 out of five stars, calling it typical of the commercially-successful Arjun-Srinivas-Prasad team and low in experimentation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/telugu-movies/so-satyamurthy/s-o-satyamurthy-songs-review.html|title=S/O SATYAMURTHY SONGS REVIEW|publisher=Behindwoods|date=16 March 2015|accessdate=17 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317163026/http://behindwoods.com/telugu-movies/so-satyamurthy/s-o-satyamurthy-songs-review.html|archivedate=17 March 2015}} {{rating|3|5|score=2.75/5 stars}}</ref> The soundtrack's success was celebrated on 6 April 2015 at Haailand, [[Vijayawada]].<ref name=\"V. P\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/watch-live-streaming-allu-arjuns-s-o-satyamurthy-audio-success-meet-video-628282|title=Watch Live Streaming of Allu Arjun's 'S/O Satyamurthy' Audio Success Meet [VIDEO]|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|date=6 April 2015|publisher=International Business Times India|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407051622/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/watch-live-streaming-allu-arjuns-s-o-satyamurthy-audio-success-meet-video-628282|archivedate=7 April 2015|accessdate=7 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{Tracklist\n| collapsed       =\n| headline        = Tracklist\n| extra_column    = Artist(s)\n| total_length    = 26:43\n| title1          = One & Two & Three\n| lyrics1         = [[Devi Sri Prasad]]\n| extra1          = [[Sooraj Santhosh]]\n| length1         = 02:08\n| title2          = Seethakalam\n| lyrics2         = [[Sri Mani]], 1080&nbsp;g (Rap)\n| extra2          = [[Yazin Nizar]], 1080&nbsp;g (Rap)\n| length2         = 04:24\n| title3          = Super Machi\n| lyrics3         = Devi Sri Prasad\n| extra3          = Devi Sri Prasad, [[Sravana Bhargavi]], [[Magizhini Manimaaran]]\n| length3         = 04:40\n| title4          = Come to the Party\n| lyrics4         = [[Sirivennela Sitaramasastri]]\n| extra4          = [[Vijay Prakash]]\n| length4         = 04:02\n| title5          = Jaaruko\n| lyrics5         = Sri Mani\n| extra5          = Sagar, [[M. M. Manasi]]\n| length5         = 04:23\n| title6          = Chal Chalo Chalo\n| lyrics6         = [[Ramajogayya Sastry]]\n| extra6          = [[Raghu Dixit]], Sooraj Santhosh, [[Rita (Indian singer)|Rita]]\n| length6         = 05:10\n| title7          = Vachchaadu\n| lyrics7         = Devi Sri Prasad\n| extra7          = [[Javed Ali]]\n| length7         = 02:36\n}}\n\n== Release ==\n''S/O Satyamurthy''{{'s}} release date was originally scheduled for 5 February 2015 in late November 2014,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjun-trivikram-film-release-5-february-will-it-clash-rudhramadevi-615025|title=Allu Arjun-Trivikram Film to Release on 5 February; Will it Clash with 'Rudhramadevi'?|last=Seshagiri|first=Sangeetha|publisher=International Business Times India|date=25 November 2014|accessdate=25 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141125072820/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjun-trivikram-film-release-5-february-will-it-clash-rudhramadevi-615025|archivedate=25 November 2014}}</ref> and was later postponed to 2 April (after the [[2015 Cricket World Cup]]) due to post-production delays.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Allu-will-come-after-World-Cup/articleshow/45981721.cms |title=Allu will come after World Cup |last=Kamal |first=S. S. |work=Bangalore Mirror |date=22 January 2015 |access-date=26 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150126070030/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Allu-will-come-after-World-Cup/articleshow/45981721.cms |archive-date=26 January 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/allu-arjun-trivikram-film-son-of-satyamurthy-to-release-on-april-2/|title=Allu Arjun-Trivikram film Son of Satyamurthy to release on April 2!|last=Srinivasan|first=Latha|publisher=Bollywood Life|date=6 March 2015|accessdate=7 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150307012252/http://www.bollywoodlife.com/south-gossip/allu-arjun-trivikram-film-son-of-satyamurthy-to-release-on-april-2/|archivedate=7 March 2015}}</ref> After the film's review by the censors on 30 March 2015, its release date was rescheduled for 9 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-gets-u-a-releases-on-9-april-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-178408.html|title=Son of Satyamurthy Clears Censor And Gets A Release Date|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=30 March 2015|accessdate=30 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330103406/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-gets-u-a-releases-on-9-april-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-178408.html|archivedate=30 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n''S/O Satyamurthy'' was one of the rare Telugu films to be released in [[Tamil Nadu]] with English subtitles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-15/allu-arjun-will-make-an-entry-in-twitter-space-on-apr-8th.html|title=Allu Arjun to make a grand entry ...|publisher=Behindwoods|date=5 April 2015|accessdate=5 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150405151332/http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-15/allu-arjun-will-make-an-entry-in-twitter-space-on-apr-8th.html|archivedate=5 April 2015}}</ref> The film was confirmed for release on 100 screens across Karnataka, at the same time as ''[[Rana Vikrama]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjuns-s-o-satyamurthy-clash-puneet-rajkumars-ranavikrama-628358|title=Allu Arjun's 'S/o Satyamurthy' to Clash with Puneet Rajkumar's 'Ranavikrama'|last=Upadhyaya|first=Prakash|publisher=International Business Times India|date=7 April 2015|accessdate=7 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150407145555/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjuns-s-o-satyamurthy-clash-puneet-rajkumars-ranavikrama-628358|archivedate=7 April 2015}}</ref> Its global screen count was 1375, the largest Telugu film release of the year; however, it did not break the record 1450 screens set by 2014's ''[[Aagadu]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-set-grand-release-allu-arjun-starrer-fails-beat-aagadu-record-628491|title=S/O Satyamurthy Set for Grand Release: Allu Arjun Starrer Fails to Beat Aagadu Record|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=9 April 2015|accessdate=9 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150409042502/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-set-grand-release-allu-arjun-starrer-fails-beat-aagadu-record-628491|archivedate=9 April 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy''{{'s}} dubbed [[Malayalam]] version was released on 24 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/allu-arjun-is-back-with-a-bang-in-kerala-news-malayalam-peykSyeegdjai.html|title=Allu Arjun is back with a bang in Kerala!|publisher=Sify|date=24 April 2015|accessdate=24 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150424143819/http://www.sify.com/movies/allu-arjun-is-back-with-a-bang-in-kerala-news-malayalam-peykSyeegdjai.html|archivedate=24 April 2015}}</ref> At first, it was titled as ''Bunny \u2013 The Perfect Gentleman'', later the title was changed to ''Son of Satyamurthy'' and had a theatrical release in 2016. [[Allu Arjun]]'s voice was dubbed by Sanket Mhatre.<ref>{{cite AV media | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LU9ALgdM3GI | title=Son of Satyamurthy | publisher=Goldmine Telefilms | date=2016 | people=[[Trivikram Srinivas|Srinivas, Trivikram]] (director) | medium=motion picture | location=India | language=Hindi}}</ref>\n\n=== Distribution ===\n''S/O Satyamurthy''{{'s}} overseas theatrical rights were sold to Classics Entertainment for an undisclosed sum in late October 2014,<ref name=\"Classic\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-overseas-rights-sold-out/articleshow/44900655.cms|title=Allu Arjun's film overseas rights sold out|work=The Times of India|date=21 October 2014|accessdate=22 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022020357/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-film-overseas-rights-sold-out/articleshow/44900655.cms|archivedate=22 October 2014}}</ref> and days later its Karnataka rights were also sold for an undisclosed price.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Bunnys-film-Karnataka-rights-sold-for-a-whopping/articleshow/44982634.cms|title=Bunny's film Karnataka rights sold for a whopping|work=The Times of India|date=30 October 2014|accessdate=31 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101090133/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Bunnys-film-Karnataka-rights-sold-for-a-whopping/articleshow/44982634.cms|archivedate=1 November 2014}}</ref> [[Dil Raju]] acquired the Nizam regional rights for {{INR}}140&nbsp;million, one of the highest prices paid for Nizam rights to a film.<ref name=\"Nizam\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjun---Trivikram-Movie-Nizam-Rights-Sold-For-A-Bomb-telugu-news-119227|title=Allu Arjun&nbsp;\u2013 Trivikram movie Nizam rights sold for a bomb|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=21 November 2014|accessdate=21 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141121142755/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjun---Trivikram-Movie-Nizam-Rights-Sold-For-A-Bomb-telugu-news-119227|archivedate=21 November 2014}}</ref> Bhopal Reddy acquired the Karnataka regional distribution rights for {{INR}}60&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2014/allu-arjun-upcoming-movie-break-record-before-its-release-165245.html|title=Allu Arjun Upcoming Movie Breaks Record Before Its Release|author=Veena|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=22 November 2014|accessdate=22 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141122011706/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2014/allu-arjun-upcoming-movie-break-record-before-its-release-165245.html|archivedate=22 November 2014}}</ref> The film's theatrical rights were sold for a total of {{INR}}540&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"45 mark\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-4-day-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-crosses-45-cr-mark-monday-629120|title='S/O Satyamurthy' 5-Day Collection at Box Office: Allu Arjun Starrer Crosses \u20b945 Cr Mark on Monday|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=14 April 2015|accessdate=14 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414091142/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-4-day-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-crosses-45-cr-mark-monday-629120|archivedate=14 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Promotion ===\nSai Gopal, who had assisted Srinivas since ''[[Swayamvaram (1999 film)|Swayamvaram]]'' (1999), orchestrated ''S/O Satyamurthy''{{'s}} promotion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/trivikram-always-believes-in-him-telugu-news-130851.html|title=Trivikram always believes in him|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=21 April 2015|accessdate=22 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150422050107/http://www.indiaglitz.com/trivikram-always-believes-in-him-telugu-news-130851.html|archivedate=22 April 2015}}</ref> Although the film was expected to preview in December 2014,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/first-look-posters-allu-arjuns-untitled-film-jr-ntrs-temper-release-soon-615229|title=First Look Posters of Allu Arjun's Untitled Film, Jr NTR's 'Temper' to Release Soon|last=Seshagiri|first=Sangeetha|publisher=International Business Times India|date=26 November 2014|accessdate=27 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141127075805/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/first-look-posters-allu-arjuns-untitled-film-jr-ntrs-temper-release-soon-615229|archivedate=27 November 2014}}</ref> its preliminary preview was released on 6 March 2015 (the night before [[Holi]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-first-look-allu-arjun-release-holi-audio-launch-15-march-625399|title='S/o Satyamurthy': First Look of Allu Arjun to Release on Holi; Audio Launch on 15 March|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=6 March 2015|accessdate=6 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306080715/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-first-look-allu-arjun-release-holi-audio-launch-15-march-625399|archivedate=6 March 2015}}</ref> The preview featured sixteen actors, including the leads (whose faces were blurred), and the film's logo was muted. In a press release, the producers announced that the film's promotion would be in full swing at the soundtrack release party, with party passes awarded to those predicting the sixteen actors on the preview poster.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Sathyamurthy-Pre-first-Look-Poster-telugu-news-127180|title='Son of Sathyamurthy' Pre-First Look Poster|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=6 March 2015|accessdate=6 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306093218/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Sathyamurthy-Pre-first-Look-Poster-telugu-news-127180|archivedate=6 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nIts 45-second advance-preview video was released on 7 March,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-teaser-gets-amazing-response-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-176019.html|title=Son of Satyamurthy Teaser Gets Amazing Response|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=7 March 2015|accessdate=7 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150307170340/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-teaser-gets-amazing-response-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-176019.html|archivedate=7 March 2015}}</ref> receiving a good response on [[YouTube]] (where it was viewed by more than 300,000 people within 12 hours of its release).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjuns-s-o-satyyamurthys-extended-pre-look-teaser-gets-good-response-video-625607|title=Allu Arjun's 'S/o Satyyamurthy's' Extended Pre-Look Teaser Gets Good Response [VIDEO]|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=8 March 2015|accessdate=10 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150310084037/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/allu-arjuns-s-o-satyyamurthys-extended-pre-look-teaser-gets-good-response-video-625607|archivedate=10 March 2015}}</ref> The film's logo was disclosed the following day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjuns-Son-Of--Satyamurthy-Official-Logo-telugu-news-127339|title=Allu Arjun's Son of Satyamurthy Official Logo|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=8 March 2015|accessdate=8 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150308121519/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjuns-Son-Of--Satyamurthy-Official-Logo-telugu-news-127339|archivedate=8 March 2015}}</ref> Thirty-one-second 2D and 3D motion posters featuring Arjun, created by Prawin Pudi and designed by Siva Kiran of Working Title, were released on 9 March and two preview posters of Arjun were distributed the following day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kFEMAMMk7oQ|title=S/o Satyamurthy&nbsp;\u2013 Motion Poster&nbsp;\u2013 Allu Arjun, Upendra, Samantha, Trivikram|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=9 March 2015|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sm_6up72qgQ|title=S/o Satyamurthy \u2013 3D Motion Poster&nbsp;\u2013 Allu Arjun, Upendra, Samantha, Trivikram|publisher=YouTube|date=9 March 2015|accessdate=10 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjuns-son-Of-Satyamurthy-Posters-telugu-news-127502|title=Allu Arjun's 'Son of SatyaMurthy' posters|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=10 March 2015|accessdate=10 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150310141143/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjuns-son-Of-Satyamurthy-Posters-telugu-news-127502|archivedate=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n''S/O Satyamurthy''{{'s}} 27-second trailer was released on 11 March;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-teaser-gets-amazing-response-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-176019.html|title=Stylish Star Allu Arjun Enthralls With Son of Satyamurthy Teaser|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=12 March 2015|accessdate=12 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150312060707/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/stylish-star-allu-arjun-enthralls-with-son-of-satya-murthy-teaser-176480.html|archivedate=12 March 2015}}</ref> two posters featuring Arjun, Samantha and Menen in Spain were distributed the following day,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjuns-son-Of-Satyamurthy-Latest-Posters-telugu-news-127678|title=Allu Arjun's 'Son of SatyaMurthy' latest posters|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=12 March 2015|accessdate=12 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150312161342/http://www.indiaglitz.com/Allu-Arjuns-son-Of-Satyamurthy-Latest-Posters-telugu-news-127678|archivedate=12 March 2015}}</ref> and a poster of Arjun was released on 14 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Satya-Murthy-New-Poster-telugu-news-127848|title='Son of Satya Murthy' new poster|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=14 March 2015|accessdate=14 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150314133227/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-Of-Satya-Murthy-New-Poster-telugu-news-127848|archivedate=14 March 2015}}</ref> The theatrical trailer had more than one million views on one YouTube channel in three and a half days, a record.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-team-thanks-the-audience/articleshow/46629723.cms |title=Allu Arjun's team thanks the audience |work=The Times of India |date=20 March 2015 |access-date=30 March 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330103711/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Allu-Arjuns-team-thanks-the-audience/articleshow/46629723.cms |archive-date=30 March 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> The trailer for a promotional song with Arjun and Prasad was released on 28 March,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/watch-s-o-satyamurthy-promotional-song-teaser-features-allu-arjun-devi-sri-prasad-video-627531|title=Watch: 'S/O Satyamurthy' Promotional Song Teaser Features Allu Arjun, Devi Sri Prasad [VIDEO]|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=International Business Times India|date=28 March 2015|accessdate=30 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330104627/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/watch-s-o-satyamurthy-promotional-song-teaser-features-allu-arjun-devi-sri-prasad-video-627531|archivedate=30 March 2015}}</ref> and the song itself was released on 1 April at 11:00&nbsp;pm [[Indian Standard Time|IST]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-promotional-song-release-time-telugu-news-129299|title=\"Son of Satyamurthy\" promotional song release time|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=1 April 2015|accessdate=2 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402015921/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-promotional-song-release-time-telugu-news-129299|archivedate=2 April 2015}}</ref> Arjun promoted the film's dubbed Malayalam version at the Lulu Mall in [[Kochi|Cochin]] on 21 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/allu-arjun-promotes-son-of-satyamurthy-in-kerala-telugu-news-130861.html|title=Allu Arjun promotes Son of Satyamurthy in Kerala|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=21 April 2015|accessdate=22 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150422050345/http://www.indiaglitz.com/allu-arjun-promotes-son-of-satyamurthy-in-kerala-telugu-news-130861.html|archivedate=22 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== {{anchor|Home Media}}Home media ===\n[[MAA TV]] acquired the film's broadcast-television rights for {{INR}}95&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/trade-news/telugu/MAA-TV-buys-Allu-Arjuns-S/O-Krishnamurthy/articleshow/46467410.cms|title=MAA TV buys Allu Arjun's S/O Krishnamurthy|work=The Times of India|date=3 March 2015|accessdate=6 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306095953/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/trade-news/telugu/MAA-TV-buys-Allu-Arjuns-S/O-Krishnamurthy/articleshow/46467410.cms|archivedate=6 March 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy'' had its global television premiere on 15 July 2015 at 6 p.m. [[Indian Standard Time|IST]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/programmes/s/o-satyamurthy/params/tvprogramme/programmeid-30000000550054640/channelid-10000000001220000/starttime-201507191800|title=S/O Satyamurthy Movie on MAA TV|work=The Times of India|date=19 July 2015|accessdate=19 July 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150719140803/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/programmes/s/o-satyamurthy/params/tvprogramme/programmeid-30000000550054640/channelid-10000000001220000/starttime-201507191800|archivedate=19 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Critical reception ===\n''S/O Satyamurthy'' had a lukewarm reception from critics, with the ''[[International Business Times]]'' calling the film a \"mass entertainer\" and criticising its predictability and length.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-movie-review-round-allu-arjun-samantha-ruth-prabhu-starrer-mass-entertainer-628638|title='S/O Satyamurthy' Movie Review Round-Up: Allu Arjun-Samantha Ruth Prabhu Starrer is a Mass Entertainer|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=9 April 2015|accessdate=9 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150409095012/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-movie-review-round-allu-arjun-samantha-ruth-prabhu-starrer-mass-entertainer-628638|archivedate=9 April 2015}}</ref> According to Sangeetha Devi Dundoo of ''[[The Hindu]]'', \"We've seen enough films with characters placed in the villain's den. Thankfully, the drama is lively and fun moments come through Ali and Brahmanandam. Allu Arjun shoulders the film with his remarkable performance and seems to be getting better with each film. The film's biggest undoing is its length. A trimmer version would be far more engaging\".<ref name=\"TH Review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/so-satyamurthy-review/article7089242.ece|title=S/O Satyamurthy: To keep up a father\u2019s honour|last=Devi Dundoo|first=Sangeetha|work=The Hindu|date=10 April 2015|accessdate=10 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150410162703/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/so-satyamurthy-review/article7089242.ece|archivedate=10 April 2015}}</ref> Pranitha Jonnalagedda of ''[[The Hans India]]'' wrote, \"No denying that there are moments of crazy laughter, witty remarks and some thought-provoking words, but Trivikram's benchmark is set so high that the writing of this film doesn't excite us enough. All said and done, if you are a lover of a Telugu cinema who enjoys watching the hero being the Good Samaritan and fancy a few tear-jerking moments, this film is definitely for you!\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2015-04-10/Not-very-Alluring-143182|title=Not very Alluring|last=Jonnalagedda|first=Pranitha|newspaper=The Hans India|date=10 April 2015|accessdate=10 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150410023617/http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/2015-04-10/Not-very-Alluring-143182|archivedate=10 April 2015}}</ref> IndiaGlitz gave ''S/O Satyamurthy'' 3.25 out of five stars, calling the film a \"family entertainer sans memorable heroism\" and adding that its second half \"will work with a good many number of audience\".<ref name=\"IG Review\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-telugu-movie-review-19562|title=Son of Satyamurthy Movie Review&nbsp;\u2013 Family entertainer for summer|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=9 April 2015|accessdate=9 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150409095648/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-telugu-movie-review-19562|archivedate=9 April 2015}} {{rating|3.5|5|score=3.25/5 stars}}</ref> Madhavi Tata of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook India]]'' gave the film three out of five stars, writing that Trivikram's screenplay \"has too many sub-plots, but the dialogues sparkle, especially when mouthed by veteran actors\". Tata called the film's humour a \"big draw\", with the best saved for Brahmanandam.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.outlookindia.com/article/SO-Satyamurthy/294050|title=S/O Satyamurthy Movie Review|last=Tata|first=Madhavi|work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook india]]|date=17 April 2015|accessdate=17 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417115436/http://www.outlookindia.com/article/SO-Satyamurthy/294050|archivedate=17 April 2015}} {{rating|3|5}}</ref> Hemanth Kumar of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave ''S/O Satyamurthy'' three out of five stars, writing that the film \"works well as an idea, and leaves you with enough questions and thoughts to reflect upon your own life, but as a cinematic experience, it leaves a lot to be desired\".<ref name=\"TOI Review\">{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/S/O-Satyamurthy/movie-review/46867320.cms |title=S/O Satyamurthy Movie Review |last=Kumar |first=Hemanth |work=The Times of India |date=9 April 2015 |access-date=10 April 2015 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6XfreuPOu?url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/S/O-Satyamurthy/movie-review/46867320.cms |archive-date=10 April 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }} {{rating|3|5}}</ref> Pravallika Anjuri of [[Oneindia]] also gave the film three out of five stars, calling it a \"perfect entertainer\" despite being the \"weakest work of Trivikram till date\": \"Nevertheless it is shall be a great fun to watch Son of Satyamurthy along with your family. Cut down the expectations and you will definitely love the movie\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/reviews/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-movie-review-story-plot-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-nithya-menen-179457.html|title=Son of Satyamurthy Movie Review&nbsp;\u2013 Allu Arjun-Trivikram-Samantha|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=9 April 2015|accessdate=9 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150409100039/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/reviews/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-movie-review-story-plot-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-nithya-menen-179457.html|archivedate=9 April 2015}} {{rating|3|5}}</ref> Behindwoods gave it 2.75 out of five stars: \"Without a concrete villain, [the film] still manages to tell us the painful journey of the hero. Thanks to the powerful and meaningful dialogues in the voice-over, [the film] becomes a charming drama\", calling it a \"family drama that also entertains\" and \"another winner for the Trivikram-Allu Arjun combo\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/telugu-movies/s-o-satyamurthy/s-o-satyamurthy-review.html|title=S/O SATYAMURTHY MOVIE REVIEW|publisher=Behindwoods|date=9 April 2015|accessdate=9 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150409111227/http://behindwoods.com/telugu-movies/s-o-satyamurthy/s-o-satyamurthy-review.html|archivedate=9 April 2015}} {{rating|3|5|score=2.75/5 stars}}</ref>\n\nSuresh Kavirayani of ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]'' gave ''S/O Satyamurthy'' 2.5 out of five stars: \"Trivikram has continued the ''[[Attarintiki Daredi]]'' trend of rich-kid-giving-up-luxuries in this film too. But, the hallmark of the director is missing from this movie. The punch dialogues associated with his films are missing and the screenplay is so-so\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150409/entertainment-movie-review/article/movie-review-so-satyamurthy-missing-trivikram-touch|title=Movie review 'S/o Satyamurthy': Missing the Trivikram touch|last=Kavirayani|first=Suresh|work=Deccan Chronicle|date=9 April 2015|accessdate=10 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150410021520/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150409/entertainment-movie-review/article/movie-review-so-satyamurthy-missing-trivikram-touch|archivedate=10 April 2015}} {{rating|2.5|5}}</ref> Karthik Keramalu of [[CNN-IBN]] also gave the film 2.5 out of five stars, calling it an \"inconsistent drama with over-the-top action and a grand message\" and adding: \"If only the screenplay had matched the quality of Allu Arjun's style, which is impeccably taken care of, Trivikram would have won the ''S/O Satyamurthy'' lottery\".<ref name=\"IBN Review\">{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/so-satyamurthy-review-an-inconsistent-drama-with-overthetop-action-and-a-grand-message/538989-71-216.html|title='S/O Satyamurthy' review: An inconsistent drama with over-the-top action and a grand message|last=Keramalu|first=Karthik|publisher=IBN Live|date=10 April 2015|accessdate=10 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150410060516/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/so-satyamurthy-review-an-inconsistent-drama-with-overthetop-action-and-a-grand-message/538989-71-216.html|archivedate=10 April 2015}} {{rating|2.5|5}}</ref> [[Indo-Asian News Service|IANS]] gave ''S/O Satyamurthy'' two out of five stars: \"While all the quintessential Trivikram trademark moments can be found in ''S/O Satyamurthy'', what you miss is the magic he created in his career's best film ''[[Athadu]]''\", adding that the film is a \"predictable and sloppy family drama with a few high and mostly low moments\".<ref name=\"IANS Review\">{{cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/s-o-satyamurthy-predictable-and-sloppy-telugu-movie-review-115041000743_1.html|title=S/O Satyamurthy: Predictable and sloppy (Telugu Movie Review)|agency=Indo-Asian News Service|date=10 April 2015|accessdate=10 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150410163034/http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/s-o-satyamurthy-predictable-and-sloppy-telugu-movie-review-115041000743_1.html|archivedate=10 April 2015}} {{rating|2|5}}</ref>\n\n=== Box office ===\n''S/O Satyamurthy'' grossed {{INR}}205&nbsp;million on its first day at the global box office, the third-highest opening-day gross in the history of Telugu cinema.<ref name=\"gross 1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-is-third-highest-opening-day-grosser-telugu-news-130096|title='Son of Satyamurthy' is third highest opening day grosser|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=10 April 2015|accessdate=11 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411024819/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-is-third-highest-opening-day-grosser-telugu-news-130096|archivedate=11 April 2015}}</ref> The film also had the best opening-day gross of Arjun's film career, breaking records set by 2014's ''[[Race Gurram]]'' (his previous film), ''[[Temper (film)|Temper]]'' and ''[[Gopala Gopala (2015 film)|Gopala Gopala]]''.<ref name=\"trends\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-son-satyamurthy-first-day-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-beat-race-gurram-628706|title='S/O (Son of) Satyamurthy' First Day Collection at Box Office: Allu Arjun Starrer Beats 'Race Gurram' Record|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=9 April 2015|accessdate=11 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411025028/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-son-satyamurthy-first-day-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-beat-race-gurram-628706|archivedate=11 April 2015}}</ref> Trade analyst Trinath told IANS that the film grossed {{INR}}335&nbsp;million in two days at the global box office, the biggest opening of the year to date.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/so-satyamurthy-strikes-gold-at-the-box-office/|title='S/O Satyamurthy' strikes gold at the box office|agency=Indo-Asian News Service|work=The Indian Express|date=11 April 2015|accessdate=12 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150412141637/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/regional/so-satyamurthy-strikes-gold-at-the-box-office/|archivedate=12 April 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy'' earned {{INR}}269.2&nbsp;million in three days at the global box office.<ref name=\"Day 3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-3-days-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-crosses-25-crore-mark-saturday-628972|title='S/O Satyamurthy' 3 Days Collection at Box Office: Allu Arjun Starrer Crosses 25-Crore Mark on Saturday|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=12 April 2015|accessdate=12 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150412141158/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-3-days-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-crosses-25-crore-mark-saturday-628972|archivedate=12 April 2015}}</ref> By the end of its first weekend, the film earned {{INR}}303.1&nbsp;million and was the highest-grossing Telugu film of the year to date.<ref name=\"weekend 1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-first-weekend-collections-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-179864.html|title=BOX OFFICE: Son Of Satyamurthy First weekend Collections|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=13 April 2015|accessdate=13 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413140630/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-first-weekend-collections-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-179864.html|archivedate=13 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nGross earnings for the film's first weekend were {{INR}}483&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"weekend gross\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-4-days-worldwide-gross-telugu-news-130262.html|title=Son of Satyamurthy 4 days worldwide gross|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=13 April 2015|accessdate=13 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413141850/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-4-days-worldwide-gross-telugu-news-130262.html|archivedate=13 April 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy'' netted about {{INR}}35&nbsp;million and grossed {{INR}}50&nbsp;million on its fifth day at the global box office, bringing its five-day global gross and net to  {{INR}}492.4&nbsp;million and {{INR}}357.4&nbsp;million. By then, the film had recovered 60 percent of its cost and was third on the list of Telugu films with all-time top first-week worldwide openings, behind ''[[Attarintiki Daredi]]'' (2013) and ''[[Yevadu]]'' (2014).<ref name=\"45 mark\" /><ref name=\"weeklist\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/box-office-collection-s-o-satyamurthy-beats-govindudu-andarivadele-temper-all-time-top-629302|title=Box Office Collection: 'S/O Satyamurthy' Beats 'Govindudu Andarivadele', 'Temper' in All Time Top First Week Worldwide Openings|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=International Business Times India|date=15 April 2015|accessdate=15 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150415113522/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/box-office-collection-s-o-satyamurthy-beats-govindudu-andarivadele-temper-all-time-top-629302|archivedate=15 April 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy''{{'s}} earnings dropped sharply on its seventh day, and its seven-day global earnings stood at {{INR}}579 million gross and {{INR}}369.4&nbsp;million net.<ref name=\"Day 7 gross\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-first-week-gross-telugu-news-130518.html|title=Son of Satyamurthy first week gross|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=16 April 2015|accessdate=17 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417013823/http://www.indiaglitz.com/son-of-satyamurthy-first-week-gross-telugu-news-130518.html|archivedate=17 April 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Day 7\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-first-week-collections-box-office-report-allu-arjun-180264.html|title=BOX OFFICE: Son Of Satyamurthy First Week Collections|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=16 April 2015|accessdate=16 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150416094852/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-first-week-collections-box-office-report-allu-arjun-180264.html|archivedate=16 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe film crossed the {{INR}}40-[[crore]] (400-million) mark on its eighth day, netting {{INR}}432.4&nbsp;million and grossing more than {{INR}}600&nbsp;million in eight days (recouping over 80 percent of its cost).<ref name=\"Day 8\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-son-satyamurthy-first-week-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-grosses-60-crore-629571|title=S/o (Son of) Satyamurthy First Week Collection at Box Office: Allu Arjun Starrer Grosses \u20b960+ Crore in 8 Days|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=17 April 2015|accessdate=17 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417133924/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-son-satyamurthy-first-week-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-grosses-60-crore-629571|archivedate=17 April 2015}}</ref> In eleven days, it netted a total of {{INR}}425.5&nbsp;million and grossed {{INR}}668.5&nbsp;million at the global box office.<ref name=\"Day 11\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-allu-arjun-promotes-malayalam-version-kerala-630107|title=S/O Satyamurthy: Allu Arjun Promotes Malayalam Version in Kerala|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=22 April 2015|accessdate=22 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150422145343/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-allu-arjun-promotes-malayalam-version-kerala-630107|archivedate=22 April 2015}}</ref> With consistent weekday performance, the film's fifteen-day global total gross and net figures were {{INR}}713.5&nbsp;million and {{INR}}450.5&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"Day 15\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-two-week-collections-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-grosses-70-cr-mark-15-630265|title='S/O Satyamurthy' Two-Week Collections at Box Office: Allu Arjun Starrer Grosses \u20b970 cr Mark in 15 Days|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=24 April 2015|accessdate=24 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150424082617/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-two-week-collections-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-grosses-70-cr-mark-15-630265|archivedate=24 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nDuring its third week, ''S/O Satyamurthy'' lost a large number of screens to new releases ''[[Dohchay]]'', ''Kai Raja Kai'', ''Aloukika'' and ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]''. The film still performed decently, grossing {{INR}}50.5&nbsp;million and netting {{INR}}21.7&nbsp;million in three days for an eighteen-day global total gross and net of {{INR}}775&nbsp;million and {{INR}}469.2&nbsp;million (surpassing the lifetime records of ''[[Naayak]]'' (2013), ''[[Racha (film)|Racha]]'' (2012), ''Temper'', ''[[Eega]]'' (2012), ''Govindudu Andarivadele'' and ''Gopala Gopala''). It was the tenth-highest-grossing Telugu film of all time at the global box office.<ref name=\"Day 18\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-18-days-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-grosses-77-crore-630561|title=S/o Satyamurthy 18 Days Collection at Box Office: Allu Arjun Starrer Grosses \u20b977 Crore|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=27 April 2015|accessdate=27 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150427133730/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-18-days-collection-box-office-allu-arjun-starrer-grosses-77-crore-630561|archivedate=27 April 2015}}</ref> At the end of three weeks, ''S/O Satyamurthy'' grossed over {{INR}}800&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ianslive.in/index.php?param=news/Allu_Arjun_on_a_three_week_holiday-475480/ENTERTAINMENT/15 |title=Allu Arjun on a three-week holiday |agency=Indo-Asian News Service |date=6 May 2015 |access-date=7 May 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150507020743/http://ianslive.in/index.php?param=news%2FAllu_Arjun_on_a_three_week_holiday-475480%2FENTERTAINMENT%2F15 |archive-date= 7 May 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref> Trade analyst Trinath told IANS that the film's three-week global net was over {{INR}}500&nbsp;million, the seventh-highest-grossing Telugu film of all time at the global box office.<ref name=\"3 week\">{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/allu-arjuns-so-satyamurthy-enters-list-of-alltime-top-ten-moneyspinners/544466-71-177.html|title=Allu Arjun's 'S/O Satyamurthy' enters list of all-time top ten moneyspinners|author=[[Indo-Asian News Service|IANS]]|publisher=[[IBN Live]]|date=8 May 2015|accessdate=8 May 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150508135826/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/allu-arjuns-so-satyamurthy-enters-list-of-alltime-top-ten-moneyspinners/544466-71-177.html|archivedate=8 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n''S/O Satyamurthy'' grossed {{INR}}905&nbsp;million and netted a total of {{INR}}519&nbsp;million at the global box office during its full run; of this, {{INR}}507.5&nbsp;million was earned by the Telugu version.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-lion-ganga-life-time-collection-worldwide-box-office-635235|title='S/O Satyamurthy', 'Lion', 'Ganga' Life-Time Collection at Worldwide Box Office|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=9 June 2015|accessdate=9 June 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150609103334/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-lion-ganga-life-time-collection-worldwide-box-office-635235|archivedate=9 June 2015}}</ref> Arjun was the first Telugu actor with two consecutive films crossing the {{INR}}500-million mark at the global box office.<ref name=\"closing OI\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-final-collections-box-office-allu-arjun-toal-185466.html|title=BOX OFFICE: Son Of Satyamurthy Final Collections|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=3 June 2015|accessdate=3 June 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150603080526/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-final-collections-box-office-allu-arjun-toal-185466.html|archivedate=3 June 2015}}</ref> ''[[Bangalore Mirror]]'' called ''S/O Satyamurthy'' a [[Blockbuster (entertainment)|blockbuster]], grossing {{INR}}920&nbsp;million and netting over {{INR}}600&nbsp;million at the global box office during its run.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Allu-Arjun-turns-down-Rs-12-cr-dance-deal/articleshow/47709006.cms |title=Allu Arjun turns down Rs. 12 cr dance deal |last=Pudipeddi |first=Haricharan |work=Bangalore Mirror |date=17 June 2015 |access-date=18 June 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150618061959/http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Allu-Arjun-turns-down-Rs-12-cr-dance-deal/articleshow/47709006.cms |archive-date=18 June 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>\n\n==== India ====\nThe film grossed {{INR}}118.9&nbsp;million at the [[Andhra Pradesh]] and [[Telangana]] box office, {{INR}}43.5&nbsp;million in Karnataka and {{INR}}6&nbsp;million in the rest of India on its first day.<ref name=\"gross 1\" /> Early trends suggested that ''S/O Satyamurthy'' would net {{INR}}85&nbsp;million in Andhra Pradesh,<ref name=\"trends\" /> and the official tally was {{INR}}93.7&nbsp;million; it was the fourth-highest opening-day grossing Telugu film in the state, behind ''Attarintiki Daredi'', ''[[Aagadu]]'' and ''Temper''.{{efn|Though the source claims that ''S/O Satyamurthy'' stands in the fifth place in the list of all time top five opening day grossers of Telugu cinema at AP/Nizam box office preceded by ''[[Attarintiki Daredi]]'' (2013), ''[[Aagadu]]'' (2014), ''[[Temper (film)|Temper]]'' (2015) and ''[[Naayak]]'' (2013),<ref name=\"day 1 share\" /> the official figures reveal that ''Naayak'' collected {{INR}}85.5&nbsp;million on its first day AP/Nizam box office which is lower than that of this film.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2013/ram-charan-naayak-first-day-collection-box-office-102486.html|title=Ram Charan's Naayak first day collection at Box Office|author=Shekhar|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=10 January 2013|accessdate=11 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411032354/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2013/ram-charan-naayak-first-day-collection-box-office-102486.html|archivedate=11 April 2015}}</ref>}}<ref name=\"day 1 share\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-day-1-collections-box-office-allu-arjun-179651.html|title=BOX OFFICE: Son Of Satyamurthy Day 1 Collections|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=10 April 2015|accessdate=11 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411030059/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/son-of-satyamurthy-day-1-collections-box-office-allu-arjun-179651.html|archivedate=11 April 2015}}</ref> The film earned more than {{INR}}29&nbsp;million at the Bangalore box office, with an 80-percent occupancy for two days (the highest of Arjun's films to date). ''S/O Satyamurthy'' earned {{INR}}72&nbsp;million in two days at the Karnataka box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-son-satyamurthys-second-day-friday-box-office-collection-allu-arjun-starrer-performs-628868|title='S/o (Son of) Satyamurthy's Second Day (Friday) Box Office Collection: Allu Arjun Starrer Performs Well in Bengaluru, Tamil Nadu|last=Upadhyaya|first=Prakash|publisher=International Business Times India|date=11 April 2015|accessdate=12 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150412140143/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-son-satyamurthys-second-day-friday-box-office-collection-allu-arjun-starrer-performs-628868|archivedate=12 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nIt earned {{INR}}51.5&nbsp;million and {{INR}}40&nbsp;million on its second and third days in Andhra Pradesh/Telangana, bringing its three-day total to {{INR}}184.2&nbsp;million. It earned approximately {{INR}}25&nbsp;million in Karnataka, Tamil Nadu, Maharashtra and elsewhere in North India in three days.<ref name=\"Day 3\" /> By the end of its first weekend, ''S/O Satyamurthy'' netted {{INR}}207.1&nbsp;million, {{INR}}35&nbsp;million and {{INR}}10&nbsp;million in Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka and the rest of India respectively.<ref name=\"weekend 1\" /> Its first-weekend gross in Andhra Pradesh and Telangana was {{INR}}315&nbsp;million and {{INR}}66&nbsp;million, {{INR}}12&nbsp;million and {{INR}}6&nbsp;million in Karnataka, Tamil Nadu and the rest of India respectively.<ref name=\"weekend gross\" />\n\n''S/O Satyamurthy'' performed well on its fifth day, earning {{INR}}21.6&nbsp;million in Andhra Pradesh for a five-day total of {{INR}}228.7&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/box-office-son-of-satyamurthy-day-5-collections-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-179986.html|title=BOX OFFICE: Son Of Satyamurthy Day 5 Collections|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=14 April 2015|accessdate=14 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414093044/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/box-office-son-of-satyamurthy-day-5-collections-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-179986.html|archivedate=14 April 2015}}</ref> The film's sixth-day Andhra Pradesh earnings were {{INR}}23.8&nbsp;million, bringing its six-day total in the state to {{INR}}252.5&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/box-office-report-son-of-satyamurthy-day-6-collections-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-180151.html|title=BOX OFFICE: Son Of Satyamurthy Day 6 Collections|last=Anjuri|first=Pravallika|publisher=Oneindia Entertainment|date=15 April 2015|accessdate=15 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150415115359/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/box-office-report-son-of-satyamurthy-day-6-collections-allu-arjun-trivikram-samantha-180151.html|archivedate=15 April 2015}}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy'' was the sixth-highest first-week earning Telugu film in Andhra Pradesh,<ref name=\"weeklist\" /> at {{INR}}262.4&nbsp;million. The film earned {{INR}}39&nbsp;million and {{INR}}12&nbsp;million in Karnataka and the rest of India in its first week.<ref name=\"Day 7\" /> Its Karnataka gross was {{INR}}47.5&nbsp;million, the highest ever for a Telugu film in the state.<ref name=\"Day 7 gross\" />\n\nIt was the fourth Arjun film to net {{INR}}10&nbsp;million in the Nizam region,{{efn|For film trade purpose, the Nizam region includes the three districts of [[Gulbarga district|Gulbarga]], [[Bidar district|Bidar]], and [[Raichur district|Raichur]] in [[Karnataka]] and seven districts in the [[Marathwada]] region including [[Aurangabad district, Maharashtra|Aurangabad]], [[Latur district|Latur]], [[Nanded district|Nanded]], [[Parbhani district|Parbhani]], [[Beed district|Beed]], [[Jalna district|Jalna]] and [[Osmanabad district|Osmanabad]] apart from the state of [[Telangana]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/hyderabad/Nizam-territory-will-remain-indispensable-for-Tollywood/articleshow/21499426.cms |title=Nizam territory will remain indispensable for Tollywood |work=The Times of India |date=31 July 2013 |access-date=17 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417014555/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/hyderabad/Nizam-territory-will-remain-indispensable-for-Tollywood/articleshow/21499426.cms |archive-date=17 April 2015 |url-status=dead |df= }}</ref>}} after ''Julai'', ''[[Iddarammayilatho]]'' (2013) and ''Race Gurram''.<ref name=\"Day 7 gross\" /> In eighteen days, the film netted {{INR}}337.2&nbsp;million, {{INR}}54.5&nbsp;million, {{INR}}6.3&nbsp;million and {{INR}}7.2&nbsp;million in AP/Nizam, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu and the rest of India respectively.<ref name=\"Day 18\" /> During its run ''S/O Satyamurthy'' netted {{INR}}376.5&nbsp;million, {{INR}}58&nbsp;million, {{INR}}6.3&nbsp;million and {{INR}}7.2&nbsp;million in AP/Nizam, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu and the rest of India respectively, {{INR}}140.5&nbsp;million in the Nizam region alone.<ref name=\"closing OI\" />\n\n==== Overseas ====\n''S/O Satyamurthy'' grossed {{INR}}37.5&nbsp;million on its first day at the overseas box office.<ref name=\"gross 1\" /> According to [[Taran Adarsh]], the film earned $347,267 on its Wednesday premiere in the United States and was the second-highest US premiere grosser (behind ''Aagadu''). It earned $136,168 on Thursday, bringing its two-day US box-office total to $483,435 (about {{INR}}30.1&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-son-satyamurthy-box-office-collection-allu-arjun-starrer-beats-attarintiki-daaredi-628879|title='S/O (Son of) Satyamurthy' Box Office Collection: Allu Arjun Starrer Beats 'Attarintiki Daaredi', 'Gopala Gopala', 'Temper'|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=International Business Times India|date=11 April 2015|accessdate=12 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411033055/http://www.filmibeat.com/telugu/news/2015/allu-arjun-next-to-pawan-kalyan-and-mahesh-babu-179620.html|archivedate=11 April 2015 }}</ref> ''S/O Satyamurthy'' earned $233,870 on Friday, bringing its three-day US box-office total to $720,984 (about {{INR}}44.9&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-cross-1m-mark-us-box-office-allu-arjun-beat-ntrs-temper-record-628941|title=S/o Satyamurthy to Cross $1M Mark at US Box Office; Allu Arjun to Beat NTR's 'Temper' Record|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=12 April 2015|accessdate=12 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150412140854/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-cross-1m-mark-us-box-office-allu-arjun-beat-ntrs-temper-record-628941|archivedate=12 April 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe film passed the million-dollar mark on Sunday, the second Telugu film of 2015 to do so (after ''Temper'').<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-son-sathymurthy-box-office-collection-allu-arjun-starrer-cross-1-million-mark-us-629061|title='S/O (Son of) Sathymurthy' Box Office Collection : Allu Arjun Starrer Cross $1 Million Mark in US|last=V. P.|first=Nicy|publisher=International Business Times India|date=13 April 2015|accessdate=13 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413130237/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-son-sathymurthy-box-office-collection-allu-arjun-starrer-cross-1-million-mark-us-629061|archivedate=13 April 2015}}</ref> Gross overseas receipts for the first weekend were {{INR}}84.6&nbsp;million,<ref name=\"weekend gross\" /> with net earnings of {{INR}}51&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"weekend 1\" /> The film continued a good run on the international market despite a drop in collections in India, earning {{INR}}56&nbsp;million in eight days.<ref name=\"Day 7\" />\n\n''S/O Satyamurthy'' lost 60 percent of its screens after the release of ''[[O Kadhal Kanmani|OK Bangaram]]'', but (according to Taran Adarsh) earned $1,235,073 by 19 April 2015. It broke the lifetime records of ''Temper'', ''Gopala Gopala'' and ''Govindudu Andarivadele'' in 11 days, and was the ninth-highest-grossing Telugu film of all time at the US box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-11-day-collection-us-box-office-allu-arjun-beats-temper-gopala-gopala-629934|title='S/O Satyamurthy' 11-Day Collection at US Box Office: Allu Arjun Beats 'Temper', 'Gopala Gopala' Lifetime Records|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|publisher=International Business Times India|date=21 April 2015|accessdate=21 April 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150421120405/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/s-o-satyamurthy-11-day-collection-us-box-office-allu-arjun-beats-temper-gopala-gopala-629934|archivedate=21 April 2015}}</ref> The film earned {{INR}}52&nbsp;million in the US and {{INR}}7&nbsp;million at the remaining overseas box offices during its run.<ref name=\"closing OI\" />\n\n=== Accolades ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Ceremony\n! Category\n! Nominee\n! Result\n! {{tooltip|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[International Indian Film Academy Awards|IIFA Utsavam 2015]]\n| Best Performance in a Leading Role&nbsp;\u2013 Male\n| [[Allu Arjun]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/rajamoulis-baahubali-maheshs-srimanthudu-top-iifa-utsavam-2015-nomination-list-656032|title=Rajamouli's 'Baahubali', Mahesh's 'Srimanthudu' top IIFA Utsavam 2015 nomination list|last=H. Hooli|first=Shekhar|work=International Business Times India|date=22 November 2015|accessdate=29 November 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151129085518/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/rajamoulis-baahubali-maheshs-srimanthudu-top-iifa-utsavam-2015-nomination-list-656032|archivedate=29 November 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Lyrics\n| [[Devi Sri Prasad]] <small>(for the song \"Super Machi\")</small>\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Gulf Andhra Music Awards\n| Best Commercial Song\n| Devi Sri Prasad and [[Sravana Bhargavi]] <small>(for the song \"Super Machi\")</small>\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref>