{"title_page": "Torvild Aakvaag", "text_new": "{{short description|Norwegian businessperson}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Torvild Aakvaag\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|1927|01|27|df=y}}\n| death_date = {{Death date and age|2020|04|09|1927|01|27|df=y}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://e24.no/naeringsliv/i/0nyz12/tidligere-hydro-sjef-torvild-aakvaag-er-doed |title= Tidligere Hydro-sjef Torvild Aakvaag er d\u00f8d |date=2020-04-14 |website=E24.no |language=no |access-date=2020-04-14 }}</ref>\n| nationality = Norwegian\n| home_town = B\u00e6rum, Norway\n}}{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n\n'''Torvild Aakvaag''' (27 January 1927 \u2013 9 April 2020) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[businessperson]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://snl.no/Torvild_Aakvaag |title=Torvild Aakvaag |date=2017-11-03 |website=[[Store norske leksikon]] |language=no |access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref>\n\nHe was born in [[B\u00e6rum]], and was a [[cand.jur.]] by education. He was employed in the [[Norwegian Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] from 1951 to 1956, but left for a career in [[Norsk Hydro]]. He was promoted to head of the judicial department in 1967, and head of the petroleum department in 1970. He advanced to become assisting director-general in 1977, and director-general (CEO) in 1984.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Torvild Aakvaag|encyclopedia=Store norske leksikon|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|editor=Henriksen, Petter|url=http://www.snl.no/Torvild_Aakvaag|language=Norwegian|accessdate=22 August 2009}}</ref> He succeeded [[Odd Narud]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://e24.no/kommentar/e24-kommentar/article2861978.ece|title=Kong Reiten ansetter tronf\u00f8lger|last=\u00d8rjas\u00e6ter|first=Elin|authorlink=Elin \u00d8rjas\u00e6ter |date=12 January 2009|work=[[E24 N\u00e6ringsliv]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=24 August 2009}}</ref> He stayed in this position until 1991; after this he was chairman of the board from 1992 to 1997.<ref name=snl/> He has also been a board member of [[Orkla Borregaard]], [[Storebrand]] and [[Nobel Industrier]], and chaired [[Hydro Aluminium]] and [[Korn- og Foderstof Kompagniet]].<ref>{{cite news|title=T\u00f8ffere tider for styrene|last=De Lange|first=Grete|date=30 January 1988|work=Aftenposten|page=5|language=Norwegian|display-authors=etal}}</ref>\n\nHe was decorated as a Commander of the [[Royal Norwegian Order of St. Olav]] in 1989.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Torvild Aakvaag|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Gunnar|last=Stavrum|authorlink=Gunnar Stavrum|volume=|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Torvild_Aakvaag/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=22 August 2009}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bus}}\n{{succession box | before=[[Odd Narud]]| title=[[Norsk Hydro|Director General of Norsk Hydro]] |years=1984\u20131991 |after=[[Egil Myklebust]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aakvaag, Torvild}}\n[[Category:1927 births]]\n[[Category:People from B\u00e6rum]]\n[[Category:Norwegian jurists]]\n[[Category:Norwegian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Norsk Hydro people]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n\n{{Norway-business-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Norwegian businessperson}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Torvild Aakvaag\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|1927|01|27|df=y}}\n| death_date = {{Death date and age|2020|04|09|1927|01|27|df=y}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://e24.no/naeringsliv/i/0nyz12/tidligere-hydro-sjef-torvild-aakvaag-er-doed |title= Tidligere Hydro-sjef Torvild Aakvaag er d\u00f8d |date=2020-04-14 |website=E24.no |language=no |access-date=2020-04-14 }}</ref>\n| nationality = Norwegian\n| home_town = B\u00e6rum, Norway\n}}{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}\n\n'''Torvild Aakvaag''' (27 January 1927 - 9 April 2020) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[businessperson]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://snl.no/Torvild_Aakvaag |title=Torvild Aakvaag |date=2017-11-03 |website=[[Store norske leksikon]] |language=no |access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref>\n\nHe was born in [[B\u00e6rum]], and was a [[cand.jur.]] by education. He was employed in the [[Norwegian Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] from 1951 to 1956, but left for a career in [[Norsk Hydro]]. He was promoted to head of the judicial department in 1967, and head of the petroleum department in 1970. He advanced to become assisting director-general in 1977, and director-general (CEO) in 1984.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Torvild Aakvaag|encyclopedia=Store norske leksikon|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|editor=Henriksen, Petter|url=http://www.snl.no/Torvild_Aakvaag|language=Norwegian|accessdate=22 August 2009}}</ref> He succeeded [[Odd Narud]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://e24.no/kommentar/e24-kommentar/article2861978.ece|title=Kong Reiten ansetter tronf\u00f8lger|last=\u00d8rjas\u00e6ter|first=Elin|authorlink=Elin \u00d8rjas\u00e6ter |date=12 January 2009|work=[[E24 N\u00e6ringsliv]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=24 August 2009}}</ref> He stayed in this position until 1991; after this he was chairman of the board from 1992 to 1997.<ref name=snl/> He has also been a board member of [[Orkla Borregaard]], [[Storebrand]] and [[Nobel Industrier]], and chaired [[Hydro Aluminium]] and [[Korn- og Foderstof Kompagniet]].<ref>{{cite news|title=T\u00f8ffere tider for styrene|last=De Lange|first=Grete|date=30 January 1988|work=Aftenposten|page=5|language=Norwegian|display-authors=etal}}</ref>\n\nHe was decorated as a Commander of the [[Royal Norwegian Order of St. Olav]] in 1989.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Torvild Aakvaag|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Gunnar|last=Stavrum|authorlink=Gunnar Stavrum|volume=|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Torvild_Aakvaag/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=22 August 2009}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bus}}\n{{succession box | before=[[Odd Narud]]| title=[[Norsk Hydro|Director General of Norsk Hydro]] |years=1984-1991 |after=[[Egil Myklebust]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aakvaag, Torvild}}\n[[Category:1927 births]]\n[[Category:People from B\u00e6rum]]\n[[Category:Norwegian jurists]]\n[[Category:Norwegian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Norsk Hydro people]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n\n{{Norway-business-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Snickers2686", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Torvild_Aakvaag"}
{"title_page": "List of theatre personnel", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=June 2009}}\nstage director-you are in charge , makeup artist-add characters to people\u2019s faces, set designer- design the props and background , choreographer-designer the dance (you need a lot of imagination), lighting designer-put spotlights \n\n{{Expand list|date=August 2008}}\n\n==Pre-production==\nThese positions are responsible for the development of a production from conception to performance. Typically, although there will be \nsignificant involvement in the fabrication and initial development, these positions will not be involved in the performances.\n \n*[[Theatrical producer|Producer]]\n*[[Theatre director|Director]]\n*[[Playwright]]\n*[[Dramaturge]]\n*[[Scenic design]]er\n*[[Scenographer]]\n*[[Lighting designer]]\n*[[Costume designer]]\n*[[Set designer]]\n*[[Sound design]]er\n*[[Composer]]\n*[[Music director]]\n*[[Choreographer]]\n*[[Movement director]]\n\n==Production==\nThese positions are responsible for the fabrication of a production \nprior to the initial performance. Although there will be significant \ninvolvement in initial development of a production, some of these \npositions may not be involved once performances before an audience \nbegin.\n\n*[[Actor]]\n*[[Audio engineer]]\n*[[Parts of a theater#Backstage or offstage|Backstage]]\n*[[Carpenter (theatre)|Carpenter]] and master carpenter\n*[[Charge artist]]\n*[[Dancer]]\n*[[Electrician (theater)|Electrician]]\n*[[Front of house]] manager\n*[[Lighting technician]]\n*[[Master electrician]]\n*[[Musician]]\n*[[Paint crew]]\n*[[Playbill writer]]\n*[[Production manager (theatre)|Production manager]]\n*[[Property master]]\n*[[Publicist]]\n*[[Scenic artist]]\n*[[Stagehand]]s\n*[[Stage manager]]\n*[[ASM(Assistant Stage Manager)]]\n*[[Technical director]]\n*[[Theatrical technician]]\n*[[Wardrobe supervisor]]\n\n==Theatre staff==\nThese staff members are responsible for running a theatre group from year to year.  Their objective is to facilitate the success of individual productions.  Staff positions help ensure good attendance in safe facilities. They help ensure the theatre remains financially solvent, that it is well run, and that it is perceived as an asset to the community it serves.\n\n*[[Artistic director]]\n*[[Theater manager]], the administrator of the theater, also called general manager, managing director, or intendant (UK English); often also has the responsibilities of an artistic director \n*[[Director of production]]\n*[[Technical director]]\n*[[Costume director]]\n*[[Marketing director]]\n*[[Director of public relations]]\n*[[Director of audience services]]\n*[[Director of development]]\n*[[Director of special events]]\n*[[Dramaturge]]\n*[[Literary manager]]\n*[[Company manager]]\n*[[House management|House manager]]\n*[[Usher (occupation)|Usher]]\n*[[Ticketing agent]]\n*Crew chief\n*[[Janitor]]\n*[[Dresser (theatre)|Dresser]]\n*[[Stage crew]]\n*[[Fly crew]]\n*[[Light board operator]]\n*[[Spotlight operator]]\n*[[Grip (job)|Grip]]s\n*[[Call boy (theatre)|Call boy]], a stagehand who alerts actors and actresses of their entrances during a performance\n\n==See also==\n*[[Character actor]]\n*[[Pantomime dame]]\n*[[Stagehand]]\n*[[Running crew]]\n\n{{Running crew}}\n{{Theatre}}\n\n[[Category:Stage crew| ]]\n[[Category:Stagecraft]]\n[[Category:Theatrical occupations| ]]\n[[Category:Theatre-related lists|Personnel]]\n[[Category:Lists of occupations]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=June 2009}}\ncinimas are not real... \n\n{{Expand list|date=August 2008}}\n\n==Pre-production==\nThese positions are responsible for the development of a production from conception to performance. Typically, although there will be \nsignificant involvement in the fabrication and initial development, these positions will not be involved in the performances.\n \n*[[Theatrical producer|Producer]]\n*[[Theatre director|Director]]\n*[[Playwright]]\n*[[Dramaturge]]\n*[[Scenic design]]er\n*[[Scenographer]]\n*[[Lighting designer]]\n*[[Costume designer]]\n*[[Set designer]]\n*[[Sound design]]er\n*[[Composer]]\n*[[Music director]]\n*[[Choreographer]]\n*[[Movement director]]\n\n==Production==\nThese positions are responsible for the fabrication of a production \nprior to the initial performance. Although there will be significant \ninvolvement in initial development of a production, some of these \npositions may not be involved once performances before an audience \nbegin.\n\n*[[Actor]]\n*[[Audio engineer]]\n*[[Parts of a theater#Backstage or offstage|Backstage]]\n*[[Carpenter (theatre)|Carpenter]] and master carpenter\n*[[Charge artist]]\n*[[Dancer]]\n*[[Electrician (theater)|Electrician]]\n*[[Front of house]] manager\n*[[Lighting technician]]\n*[[Master electrician]]\n*[[Musician]]\n*[[Paint crew]]\n*[[Playbill writer]]\n*[[Production manager (theatre)|Production manager]]\n*[[Property master]]\n*[[Publicist]]\n*[[Scenic artist]]\n*[[Stagehand]]s\n*[[Stage manager]]\n*[[ASM(Assistant Stage Manager)]]\n*[[Technical director]]\n*[[Theatrical technician]]\n*[[Wardrobe supervisor]]\n\n==Theatre staff==\nThese staff members are responsible for running a theatre group from year to year.  Their objective is to facilitate the success of individual productions.  Staff positions help ensure good attendance in safe facilities. They help ensure the theatre remains financially solvent, that it is well run, and that it is perceived as an asset to the community it serves.\n\n*[[Artistic director]]\n*[[Theater manager]], the administrator of the theater, also called general manager, managing director, or intendant (UK English); often also has the responsibilities of an artistic director \n*[[Director of production]]\n*[[Technical director]]\n*[[Costume director]]\n*[[Marketing director]]\n*[[Director of public relations]]\n*[[Director of audience services]]\n*[[Director of development]]\n*[[Director of special events]]\n*[[Dramaturge]]\n*[[Literary manager]]\n*[[Company manager]]\n*[[House management|House manager]]\n*[[Usher (occupation)|Usher]]\n*[[Ticketing agent]]\n*Crew chief\n*[[Janitor]]\n*[[Dresser (theatre)|Dresser]]\n*[[Stage crew]]\n*[[Fly crew]]\n*[[Light board operator]]\n*[[Spotlight operator]]\n*[[Grip (job)|Grip]]s\n*[[Call boy (theatre)|Call boy]], a stagehand who alerts actors and actresses of their entrances during a performance\n\n==See also==\n*[[Character actor]]\n*[[Pantomime dame]]\n*[[Stagehand]]\n*[[Running crew]]\n\n{{Running crew}}\n{{Theatre}}\n\n[[Category:Stage crew| ]]\n[[Category:Stagecraft]]\n[[Category:Theatrical occupations| ]]\n[[Category:Theatre-related lists|Personnel]]\n[[Category:Lists of occupations]]\n", "name_user": "92.14.92.76", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_theatre_personnel"}
